a primitive root; to seize (often with the accessory idea of holding in possession):--+ be affrighted, bar, (catch, lay, take) hold (back), come upon, fasten, handle, portion, (get, have or take) possess(-ion).
from 270; possessor; Achaz, the name of a Jewish king and of an Israelite:--Ahaz.
feminine passive participle from 270; something seized, i.e. a possession (especially of land):--possession.
from 270; seizer; Achzai, an Israelite:--Ahasai.
or (prolonged) rAchazyahuw {akh-az-yaw'-hoo}; from 270 and 3050; Jah has seized; Achazjah, the name of a Jewish and an Israelite king:--Ahaziah.
from 270; seizure; Achuzzam, an Israelite:--Ahuzam.
a variation of 272; possession; Achuzzath, a Philistine:--Ahuzzath.
from 251; brotherly; Achi, the name of two Israelites:--Ahi.

from 251 and 517; brother of the mother (i.e. uncle); Achiam, an Israelite:--Ahiam.

or (prolonged) pAchiyahuw {akh-ee-yaw'-hoo}; from 251 and 3050; brother (i.e. worshipper) of Jah; Achijah, the name of nine Israelites:--Ahiah, Ahijah.
from 251 and 1935; brother (i.e. possessor) of renown; Achihud, an Israelite:--Ahihud.
prolonged from 251; brotherly; Achio, the name of three Israelites:--Ahio.
from 251 and 2330; brother of a riddle (i.e. mysterious); Achichud, an Israelite:--Ahihud.
from 251 and 2898; brother of goodness; Achitub, the name of several priests:--Ahitub.
from 251 and 3205; brother of one born; Achilud, an Israelite:--Ahilud.
from 251 and 4191; brother of death; Achimoth, an Israelite:--Ahimoth.
from 251 and 4428; brother of (the) king; Achimelek, the name of an Israelite and of a Hittite:--Ahimelech.
or mAchiyman {akh-ee-mawn'}; from 251 and 4480; brother of a portion (i.e. gift); Achiman, the name of an Anakite and of an Israelite:--Ahiman.
from 251 and the equivalent of 4619; brother of anger; Achimaats, the name of three Israelites:--Ahimaaz.
from 251; brotherly; Achjan, an Israelite:--Ahian.
from 251 and 5068; brother of liberality; Achinadab, an Israelite:--Ahinadab.
from 251 and 5278; brother of pleasantness; Achinoam, the name of two Israelitesses:--Ahinoam.
from 251 and 5564; brother of support; Achisamak, an Israelite:--Ahisamach.
from 251 and 5828; brother of help; Achiezer, the name of two Israelites:--Ahiezer.
from 251 and 6965; brother of rising (i.e. high); Achikam, an Israelite:--Ahikam.

from 251 and 7451; brother of wrong; Achira, an Israelite:--Ahira.
from 251 and 7837; brother of (the) dawn; Achishachar, an Israelite:--Ahishar.
from 251 and 7891; brother of (the) singer; Achishar, an Israelite:--Ahishar.
from 251 and 8602; brother of folly; Achithophel, an Israelite:--Ahithophel.
from the same root as 2459; fatness (i.e. fertile); Achlab, a place in Palestine:--Ahlab.

or achaley {akh-al-ay'}; prob from 253 and a variation of 3863; would that!:--O that, would God.

of Persian derivation; Achmetha (i.e. Ecbatana), the summer capital of Persia:--Achmetha.
of uncertain derivation; Achasbai, an Israelite:--Ahasbai.
a primitive root; to loiter (i.e. be behind); by implication to procrastinate:--continue, defer, delay, hinder, be late (slack), stay (there), tarry (longer).

from 309; properly, the hind part; generally used as an adverb or conjunction, after (in various senses):--after (that, -ward), again, at, away from, back (from, -side), behind, beside, by, follow (after, -ing), forasmuch, from, hereafter, hinder end, + out (over) live, + persecute, posterity, pursuing, remnant, seeing, since, thence(-forth), when, with.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 310; after:--(here-)after.
from 309; properly, hinder; generally, next, other, etc.:--(an-)other man, following, next, strange.
the same as 312; Acher, an Israelite:--Aher.

or (shortened) ;acharon {akh-ar-one'}; from 309; hinder; generally, late or last; specifically (as facing the east) western:--after (-ward), to come, following, hind(-er, -ermost, -most), last, latter, rereward, ut(ter)most.
from 310 and 251; after (his) brother: Achrach, an Israelite:--Aharah.
from 310 and 2426; behind (the) intrenchment (i.e. safe); Acharchel, an Israelite:--Aharhel,
(Aramaic) from 311; other:--(an-)other.
(Aramaic) or (shortened) :ochoren (Aramaic) {okh-or-ane'}; from 317; last:--at last.
from 310; the last or end, hence, the future; also posterity:--(last, latter) end (time), hinder (utter) -most, length, posterity, remnant, residue, reward.
(Aramaic) from 311; the same as 319; later:--latter.
(Aramaic) from 311; the same as 317; other:--(an-)other.
prolonged from 268; backwards:--back (-ward, again).
of Persian derivation; a satrap or governor of a main province (of Persia):--lieutenant.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 323:--prince.

or (shortened) pAchashrosh {akh- ash-rosh'} (Esth. 10:1); of Persian origin; Achashverosh (i.e. Ahasuerus or Artaxerxes, but in this case Xerxes), the title (rather than name) of a Persian king:--Ahasuerus.
probably of Persian derivation; an achastarite (i.e. courier); the designation (rather than name) of an Israelite:--Haakashtari (includ. the article).
of Persian origin; a mule:--camel.
from an unused root perhaps meaning to move softly; (as a noun) a necromancer (from their soft incantations), (as an adverb) gently:--charmer, gently, secret, softly.
from an unused root probably meaning to pierce or make fast; a thorn-tree (especially the buckthorn):--Atad, bramble, thorn.
from an unused root (probably meaning to bind); properly, twisted (yarn), i.e. tapestry:--fine linen.
a primitive root; to close (the lips or ears); by analology to contract (a window by bevelled jambs):--narrow, shut, stop.
a primitive root; to close up:--shut.
from 332; maimed; Ater, the name of three Israelites:--Ater.
from 332; shut up, i.e. impeded (as to the use of the right hand):--+ left-handed.
perhaps from 370; where? hence how?:--how, what, whence, where, whether, which (way).
probably identical with 335 (through the idea of a query); not:--island (Job 22:30).
short from 188; alas!:--woe.
probably identical with 337 (through the idea of a doleful sound); a howler (used only in the plural), i.e. any solitary wild creature; --wild beast of the islands.
from 183; properly, a habitable spot (as desirable); dry land, a coast, an island:--country, isle, island.
a primitive root; to hate (as one of an opposite tribe or party); hence to be hostile:--be an enemy.
or (fully) owyeb {o-yabe'}; active participle of 340; hating; an adversary:--enemy, foe.
from 340; hostility:--emnity, hatred.
from the same as 181 (in the sense of bending down); oppression; by implication misfortune, ruin:--calamity, destruction.
perhaps from 337; the screamer, i.e. a hawk:--kite, vulture.
the same as 344; Ajah, the name of two Israelites:--Aiah, Ajah.
prolonged from 335; where?:--where.
from 340; hated (i.e. persecuted); Ijob, the patriarch famous for his patience:--Job.
from 336 and 2083; Izebel, the wife of king Ahab:--Jezebel.
also eykah {ay-kaw'}; and teykakah {ay-kaw'-kah}; prolonged from 335; how? or how!; also where:--how, what.
from 336 and 3519; (there is) no glory, i.e. inglorious; Ikabod, a son of Phineas:--I-chabod.
probably a variation for 349, but not as an interogative; where:--where.

from the same as 193; properly, strength; hence, anything strong; specifically a chief (politically); also a ram (from his strength); a pilaster (as a strong support); an oak or other strong tree:--mighty (man), lintel, oak, post, ram, tree.
a variation of 352; strength:--strength.
an intensive form of 352 (in the sense of ram); a stag or male deer:--hart.
feminine of 354; a doe or female deer:--hind.
or (shortened) ;Elown {ay-lone'}; or Eylon {ay- lone'}; from 352; oak-grove; Elon, the name of a place in Palestine, and also of one Hittite, two Israelites:--Elon.
from 354; deer-field; Ajalon, the name of five places in Palestine:--Aijalon, Ajalon.
from 356, 1004, and 2603; oak-grove of (the) house of favor; Elon of Beth-chanan, a place in Palestine:--Elon-beth-hanan.
or mEylath {ay-lath'}; from 352; trees or a grove (i.e. palms); Eloth or Elath, a place on the Red Sea:--Elath, Eloth.
feminine of 353; power; by implication, protection:--strength.
or (shortened) ;elam {ay-lawm'}; or (feminine) ielammah {ay-lam-maw'}; probably from 352; a pillar-space (or colonnade), i.e. a pale (or portico):--arch.
plural of 352; palm-trees; Elim, a place in the Desert:--Elim.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 356; a tree:--tree.
from 352 and 6290; oak of Paran; El- Paran, a portion of the district of Paran:--El-paran.
the same as 355; a doe:--hind, Aijeleth.
from an unused root (meaning to frighten); frightful:--terrible.
or (shortened) remah {ay-maw'}; from the same as 366; fright; concrete, an idol (as a bugbear):--dread, fear, horror, idol, terrible, terror.
plural of 367; terrors; Emim, an early Canaanitish (or Maobitish) tribe:--Emims.

as if from a primitive root meaning to be nothing or not exist; a non-entity; generally used as a negative particle:--else, except, fail, (father-)less, be gone, in(-curable), neither, never, no (where), none, nor, (any, thing), not, nothing, to nought, past, un(-searchable), well-nigh, without. Compare 370.
probably identical with 369 in the sense of query (compare 336); --where? (only in connection with prepositional prefix, whence):--whence, where.
apparently a shortened form of 369; but (like 370) an interrogative: is it not?:--not.
from 336 and 5828; helpless; Iezer, an Israelite:--Jeezer.
patronymic from 372; an Iezrite or descendant of Iezer:--Jezerite.
or (shortened) ephah {ay-faw'}; of Egyptian derivation; an ephah or measure for grain; hence, a measure in general:-- ephah, (divers) measure(-s).
from 335 and 6311; what place?; also (of time) when?; or (of means) how?; --what manner, where.

contracted for 582 (or perhaps rather from an unused root meaning to be extant); a man as an individual or a male person; often used as an adjunct to a more definite term (and in such cases frequently not expressed in translation):--also, another, any (man), a certain, + champion, consent, each, every (one), fellow, (foot-, husband-)man, (good-, great, mighty) man, he, high (degree), him (that is), husband, man(-kind), + none, one, people, person, + steward, what (man) soever, whoso(-ever), worthy. Compare 802.
denominative from 376; to be a man, i.e. act in a manly way:--show (one) self a man.
from 376 and 1322; man of shame; Ish- Bosheth, a son of King Saul:--Ish-bosheth.
from 376 and 1935; man of renown; Ishod, an Israelite:--Ishod.
diminutive from 376; the little man of the eye; the pupil or ball; hence, the middle (of night):--apple (of the eye), black, obscure.
from 376 and 2428; man of might; by defect. transcription (2 Sam. 23:20) Iysh-Chay {eesh-khah'ee}; as if from 376 and 2416; living man; Ish-chail (or Ish-chai), an Israelite:--a valiant man.
from 376 and 2897; man of Tob; Ish-Tob, a place in Palestine:--Ish-tob.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 3426; properly, entity; used only as a particle of affirmation, there is:--art thou, can, do ye, have, it be, there is (are), X we will not.
perhaps from 837 and 410; God has arrived; Ithiel, the name of an Israelite, also of a symbolical person:--Ithiel.
from 339 and 8558; coast of the palm-tree; Ithamar, a son of Aaron:--Ithamar.
or (shortened) ethan {ay-thawn'}; from an unused root (meaning to continue); permanence; hence (concrete) permanent; specifically a chieftain:--hard, mighty, rough, strength, strong.
the same as 386; permanent; Ethan, the name of four Israelites:--Ethan.
plural of 386; always with the article; the permanent brooks; Ethanim, the name of a month:--Ethanim.

akin to 403; a particle of affirmation, surely; hence (by limitation) only:--also, in any wise, at least, but, certainly, even, howbeit, nevertheless, notwithstanding, only, save, surely, of a surety, truly, verily, + wherefore, yet (but).
from an unused root probably meaning to strengthen; a fortress; Accad, a place in Babylon:--Accad.
from 3576; falsehood; by implication treachery:--liar, lie.
from 391; deceitful (in the sense of a winter- torrent which fails in summer); Akzib, the name of two places in Palestine:--Achzib.
from an unused root (apparently meaning to act harshly); violent; by implication deadly; also (in a good sense) brave:--cruel, fierce.
from 393; terrible:--cruel (one).
from 394; fierceness:--cruel.
feminine from 398; something eatable, i.e. food:--meat.
of uncertain derivation; Akish, a Philistine king:--Achish.
a primitive root; to eat (literally or figuratively):--X at all, burn up, consume, devour(-er, up), dine, eat(-er, up), feed (with), food, X freely, X in...wise(-deed, plenty), (lay) meat, X quite.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 398:--+ accuse, devour, eat.
from 398; food:--eating, food, meal(-time), meat, prey, victuals.
or mUkkal {ook-kawl'}; apparently from 398; devoured; Ucal, a fancy name:--Ucal.
feminine of 401; food:--consume, devour, eat, food, meat.
from 3559 (compare 3651); firmly; figuratively, surely; also (advers.) but:--but, certainly, nevertheless, surely, truly, verily.
a primitive root; apparently meaning to curve (as with a burden); to urge:--crave.
from 404; a load; by implication, a stroke (others dignity):--hand.
from an unused root meaning to dig; a farmer:--husbandman, ploughman.
from 3784; fascination; Acshaph, a place in Palestine:--Achshaph.
a negative particle (akin to 3808); not (the qualified negation, used as a deprecative); once (Job 24:25) as a noun, nothing:--nay, neither, + never, no ,nor, not, nothing (worth), rather than.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 408:--not.
shortened from 352; strength; as adjective, mighty; especially the Almighty (but used also of any deity):--God (god), X goodly, X great, idol, might(-y one), power, strong. Compare names in "-el."
a demonstrative particle (but only in a plural sense) these or those:--these, those. Compare 428.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 411:--these.

(but only used in the shortened constructive form sel {el}); a primitive particle; properly, denoting motion towards, but occasionally used of a quiescent position, i.e. near, with or among; often in general, to:--about, according to ,after, against, among, as for, at, because(-fore, -side), both...and, by, concerning, for, from, X hath, in(- to), near, (out) of, over, through, to(-ward), under, unto, upon, whether, with(-in).
a variation of 424; oak; Ela, an Israelite:--Elah.
from 410 and 430 and 3478; the mighty god if Jisrael; El-Elohi-Jisrael, the title given to a consecrated spot by Jacob:--El-elohe-israel.
from 410 and 1008; the God of Bethel; El-Bethel, the title given to a consecrated spot by Jacob:--El-beth-el.
from 410 and 1378; hail (as if a great pearl):--great hail(-stones).
by transposition for 484; sticks of algum wood:--algum (trees).
from 410 and 1730; God has loved; Eldad, an Israelite:--Eldad.
from 410 and 3045; God of knowledge; Eldaah, a son of Midian:--Eldaah.
a primitive root (rather identical with 422 through the idea of invocation); to bewail:--lament.
a primitive root; properly, to adjure, i.e. (usually in a bad sense) imprecate:--adjure, curse, swear.
from 422; an imprecation:--curse, cursing, execration, oath, swearing.
feminine of 352; an oak or other strong tree:--elm, oak, teil-tree.
the same as 424; Elah, the name of an Edomite, of four Israelites, and also of a place in Palestine:--Elah.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 433; God:--God, god.
A variation of 424:--oak.
prolonged from 411; these or those:--an- (the) other; one sort, so, some, such, them, these (same), they, this, those, thus, which, who(-m).
(Aramaic) corresponding to 428:--these.

plural of 433; gods in the ordinary sense; but specifically used (in the plural thus, especially with the article) of the supreme God; occasionally applied by way of deference to magistrates; and sometimes as a superlative:--angels, X exceeding, God (gods)(-dess, -ly), X (very) great, judges, X mighty.
(Aramaic) probably prolonged from 412; lo!:--behold.
probably from 408; nay, i.e. (softened) if:--but if, yea though.
probably prolonged (emphat.) from 410; a deity or the Deity:--God, god. See 430.
for 457; good for nothing:--thing of nought.
probably of foreign derivation; Elul, the sixth Jewish month:--Elul.
prolonged from 352; an oak or other strong tree:--plain. See also 356.
a variation of 436:--oak.
the same as 437; Allon, an Israelite, also a place in Palestine:--Allon.
from 437 and a variation of 1068; oak of weeping; Allon-Bakuth, a monumental tree:--Allon-bachuth.
or rather (shortened) oEloniy {ay-lo-nee'}; patron from 438; an Elonite or descendant (collectively) of Elon:--Elonites.

or (shortened) talluph {al-loof'}; from 502; familiar; a friend, also gentle; hence, a bullock (as being tame; applied, although masculine, to a cow); and so, a chieftain (as notable, like neat cattle):--captain, duke, (chief) friend, governor, guide, ox.
of uncertain derivation; Alush, a place in the Desert:--Alush.
from 410 and 2064; God has bestowed; Elzabad, the name of two Israelites:--Elzabad.
a primitive root; to muddle, i.e. (figuratively and intransitive) to turn (morally) corrupt:--become filthy.
from 410 and 2603; God (is) gracious; Elchanan, an Israelite:--Elkanan.
from 410 and 1; God of (his) father; Eliab, the name of six Israelites:--Eliab.
from 410 repeated; God of (his) God; Eliel, the name of nine Israelites:--Eliel.
or (contraction) ;Eliyathah {el-ee-yaw- thaw'}; from 410 and 225; God of (his) consent; Eliathah, an Israelite:-- Eliathah.
from the same as 419; God of (his ) love; Elidad, an Israelite:--Elidad.
from 410 and 3045; God (is) knowing; Eljada, the name of two Israelites and of an Aramaean leader:--Eliada.
from 422 (in the original sense of strength); the stout part, i.e. the fat tail of the Oriental sheep:--rump.
or prolonged tEliyahuw {ay-lee-yaw'-hoo}; from 410 and 3050; God of Jehovah; Elijah, the name of the famous prophet and of two other Israelites:--Elijah, Eliah.
or (fully) dEliyhuwh {el-ee-hoo'}; from 410 and 1931; God of him; Elihu, the name of one of Job's friends, and of three Israelites:--Elihu.
or (shortened) yElyow{eynay {el- yo-ay-nah'ee}; from 413 and 3068 and 5869; towards Jehovah (are) my eyes; Eljehoenai or Eljoenai, the name of seven Israelites:--Elihoenai, Elionai.
from 410 and 2244; God will hide; Eljachba, an Israelite:--Eliahbah.
from 410 and 2779; God of autumn; Elichoreph, an Israelite:--Elihoreph.
apparently from 408; good for nothing, by anal. vain or vanity; specifically an idol:--idol, no value, thing of nought.
from 410 and 4428; God of (the) king; Elimelek, an Israelite:--Elimelech.
(Aramaic) or shorter oillen {il-lane'}; prolonged from 412; these:--the, these.
from 410 and 3254; God (is) gatherer; Eljasaph, the name of two Israelites:--Eliasaph.
from 410 and 5828; God of help; Eliezer, the name of a Damascene and of ten Israelites:--Eliezer.
probably contracted for 454; Elienai, an Israelite:--Elienai.
from 410 and 5971; God of (the) people; Eliam, an Israelite:--Eliam.
from 410 and 6337; God of gold; Eliphaz, the name of one of Job's friends, and of a son of Esau:--Eliphaz.
from 410 and 6419; God of judgment; Eliphal, an Israelite:--Eliphal.
from 410 and 6395; God of his distinction; Eliphelehu, an Israelite:--Elipheleh.
or (shortened) Elpelet {el-peh'-let}; from 410 and 6405; God of deliverance; Eliphelet or Elpelet, the name of six Israelites:--Eliphalet, Eliphelet, Elpalet.
from 410 and 6697; God of (the) rock; Elitsur, an Israelite:--Elizur.
or (shortened) Eltsaphan {el-tsaw- fawn'}; from 410 and 6845; God of treasure; Elitsaphan or Eltsaphan, an Israelite:--Elizaphan, Elzaphan.
from 410 and 6958; God of rejection; Elika, an Israelite:--Elika.
from 410 and 6965; God of raising; Eljakim, the name of four Israelites:--Eliakim.
from 410 and 7651 (in the sense of 7650); God of (the) oath; Elisheba, the wife of Aaron:--Elisheba.
probably of foreign derivation; Elishah, a son of Javan:--Elishah.
from 410 and 7769; God of supplication (or of riches); Elishua, the son of King David:--Elishua.
from 410 and 7725; God will restore; Eljashib, the name of six Israelites:--Eliashib.
from 410 and 8085; God of hearing; Elishama, the name of seven Israelites:--Elishama.
contracted for 474.; Elisha, the famous prophet:--Elisha.
from 410 and 8199; God of judgment; Elishaphat, an Israelite:--Elishaphat.
(Aramaic) prolonged from 412; these:--these, those.
by reduplication from 421; alas!:--woe.
a primitive root; to tie fast; hence (of the mouth) to be tongue-tied:--bind, be dumb, put to silence.
from 481; silence (i.e. mute justice):--congregation. Compare 3128.
from 481; speechless:--dumb (man).
probably of foreign derivation (used thus only in the plural); almug (i.e. probably sandle-wood) sticks:--almug trees. Compare 418.
or (masculine) ealum {aw-loom'}; passive participle of 481; something bound; a sheaf:--sheaf.
probably of foreign derivation:--Almodad, a son of Joktan:--Almodad.
from 427 and 4428; oak of (the) king; Allammelek, a place in Palestine:--Alammelech.
prolonged from 481 in the sense of bereavement; discarded (as a divorced person):--forsaken.
from 481 as in 488; bereavement:--widowhood.
fem of 488; a widow; also a desolate place:--desolate house (palace), widow.
feminine of 488; concrete, a widow; abstract, widowhood:--widow, widowhood.
from 489 in the sense of concealment; some one (i.e. so and so, without giving the name of the person or place):--one, and such.
from 410 and 5276; God (is his) delight; Elnaam, an Israelite:--Elnaam.
from 410 and 5414; God (is the) giver; Elnathan, the name of four Israelites:--Elnathan.
probably of foreign derivation; Ellasar, an early country of Asia:--Ellasar.
from 410 and 5749; God has testified; Elad, an Israelite:--Elead.
from 410 and 5710; God has decked; Eladah, an Israelite:--Eladah.
from 410 and 5756 (in the sense of 5797); God (is) defensive; Eluzai, an Israelite:--Eluzai.
from 410 and 5826; God (is) helper; Elazar, the name of seven Israelites:--Eleazar.
or (more properly) GEl aleh {el-aw-lay'}; from 410 and 5927; God (is) going up; Elale or Elaleh, a place east of the Jordan:--Elealeh.
from 410 and 6213; God has made; Elasah, the name of four Israelites:--Elasah, Eleasah.
a primitive root, to associate with; hence, to learn (and causatively to teach):--learn, teach, utter.
denominative from 505; causative, to make a thousandfold:--bring forth thousands.
from 502; a family; also (from the sense of yoking or taming) an ox or cow:--family, kine, oxen.
prop, the same as 504; hence (the ox's head being the first letter of the alphabet, and this eventually used as a numeral) a thousand:--thousand.
(Aramaic) or meleph (Aramaic) {eh'-lef}; corresponding to 505:--thousand.
the same as 505; Eleph, a place in Palestine:--Eleph.
from 410 and 6466; God (is) act; Elpaal, an Israelite:--Elpaal.
a primitive root; to press:--urge.
probably from 408 and 6965; a non-rising (i.e. resistlessness):--no rising up.
from 410 and 7069; God has obtained; Elkanah, the name of several Israelites:--Elkanah.
patrial from a name of uncertain derivation; an Elkoshite or native of Elkosh:--Elkoshite.
probably from 410 and a masculine form of 8435 (compare 8434); God (is) generator; Eltolad, a place in Palestine:-- Eltolad.
or (more properly) nEltqeh {el-te-kay'}; of uncertain derivation; Eltekeh or Elteke, a place in Palestine:-- Eltekeh.
from 410 and 8626; God (is) straight; Eltekon, a place in Palestine:--Eltekon.
from 408 and 7843; Thou must not destroy; probably the opening words to a popular song:--Al-taschith.
a primitive word; a mother (as the bond of the family); in a wide sense (both literally and figuratively (like 1):--dam, mother, X parting.

a primitive particle; used very widely as demonstrative, lo!; interrog., whether?; or conditional, if, although; also Oh that!, when; hence, as a negative, not:--(and, can-, doubtless, if, that) (not), + but, either, + except, + more(-over if, than), neither, nevertheless, nor, oh that, or, + save (only, -ing), seeing, since, sith, + surely (no more, none, not), though, + of a truth, + unless, + verily, when, whereas, whether, while, + yet.
apparently a primitive word; a maid-servant or female slave:--(hand-)bondmaid(-woman), maid(-servant).
