from an unused root (meaning to flit); a fly (especially one of a stinging nature):--fly.
from 2064; given, Zabud, an Israelite:--Zabud.
a form of 2071; given; Zabbud, an Israelite:--Zabbud.
or zbul {zeb-ool'}; from 2082; a residence:--dwell in, dwelling, habitation.
or Zbuluwn {zeb-oo-loon'}; or Zbuwlun {zeb-oo-loon'}; from 2082; habitation; Zebulon, a son of Jacob; also his territory and tribe:--Zebulun.
patronymically from 2074; a Zebulonite or descendant of Zebulun:--Zebulonite.
a primitive root; to slaughter an animal (usually in sacrifice):--kill, offer, (do) sacrifice, slay.

a primitive root (compare 6695); to press together, &� tighten:--close, rush, thrust together.

probably from the root of 2123; prominent; Zaza, an Israelite:--Zaza.

feminine active participle of 2119; crawling (i.e. serpent); Zocheleth, a boundary stone in. Palestine:--Zoheleth.
from 2102; boiling of water, i.e. wave:--proud.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 2099; (figuratively) cheerfulness:--brightness, countenance.
from an unused root apparently meaning to be conspicuous; fulness of the breast; also a moving creature:--abundance, wild beast.
apparently from the same as 2123; prominence; Ziza, the name of two Israelites:--Ziza.
another form for 2124; Zizah, an Israelite:--Zizah.
from 2109; well-fed; or perhaps an orthographical error for 2124; Zina, an Israelite:--Zina.
from 2111; agitation; Zia, an Israelite:--Zia.
from the same as 2203; flowing; Ziph, the name of a place in Palestine; also of an Israelite:--Ziph.

patrial from 2128; a Ziphite or inhabitant of Ziph:--Ziphim, Ziphite.

(Isa. 50: (feminine); and ziq {zeek}; or zeq {zake}; from 2187; properly, what leaps forth, i.e. flash of fire, or a burning arrow; also (from the original sense of the root) a bond:--chain, fetter, firebrand, spark.
probably from an unused root (akin to 2099); an olive (as yielding illuminating oil), the tree, the branch or the berry:--olive (tree, -yard), Olivet.
from 2132; olive grove; Zethan, an Israelite:--Zethan.
from 2141; clear:--clean, pure.
a primitive root (compare 2141); to be translucent; figuratively, to be innocent:--be (make) clean, cleanse, be clear, count pure.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to 2135; purity:--innocency.
from 2135; properly, transparency, i.e. glass:--crystal.
properly, passive participle of 2142, but used for 2145; a male (of man or animals):--males, men-children.
from 2142; mindful; Zakkur, the name of seven Israelites:--Zaccur, Zacchur.
from 2141; pure; Zakkai, an Israelite:--Zaccai.
a primitive root (compare 2135); to be transparent or clean (phys. or morally):--be (make) clean, be pure(-r).

a primitive root; properly, to mark (so as to be recognized), i.e. to remember; by implication, to mention; also (as denominative from 2145) to be male:--X burn (incense), X earnestly, be male, (make) mention (of), be mindful, recount, record(-er), remember, make to be remembered, bring (call, come, keep, put) to (in) remembrance, X still, think on, X well.
or zeker {zeh'-ker}; from 2142; a memento, abstr. recollection (rarely if ever); by implication, commemoration:--memorial, memory, remembrance, scent.
the same as 2143; Zeker, an Israelite:--Zeker.
from 2142; properly, remembered, i.e. a male (of man or animals, as being the most noteworthy sex):--X him, male, man(child, -kind).
from 2142; a memento (or memorable thing, day or writing):--memorial, record.
from 2142; memorable; Zicri, the name of twelve Israelites:--Zichri.
or Zkaryahuw {zek-ar-yaw'-hoo}; from 2142 and 3050; Jah has remembered; Zecarjah, the name of twenty-nine Israelites:--Zachariah, Zechariah.
from 2151; properly, a shaking, i.e. perhaps a tempest:--vilest.
by reduplication from 2151; tremulous, i.e. a twig:--sprig.
a primitive root (compare 2107); to shake (as in the wind), i.e. to quake; figuratively, to be loose morally, worthless or prodigal:--blow down, glutton, riotous (eater), vile.
or ziliaphaph {zil-aw-faw'}; from 2196; a glow (of wind or anger); also a famine (as consuming):--horrible, horror, terrible.
: from an unused root apparently meaning to trickle, as myrrh; fragrant dropping; Zilpah, Leah's maid:--Zilpah.
or zammah {zam-maw'}; from 2161; a plan, especially a bad one:--heinous crime, lewd(-ly, -ness), mischief, purpose, thought, wicked (device, mind, -ness).
the same as 2154; Zimmah, the name of two Israelites:--Zimmah.
or zmorah {zem-o-raw'} (feminine); and zmor {zem-ore'} (masculine); from 2168; a twig (as pruned):--vine, branch, slip.
from 2161; intriguing; a Zamzumite, or native tribe of Palestine:--Zamzummim.
or zamir {zaw-meer'}; and (feminine) zmirah {zem-ee-raw'}; from 2167; a song to be accompanied with instrumental music:--psalm(-ist), singing, song.
from 2168; a twig (as pruned):--branch.
feminine of 2158; song; Zemirah, an Israelite:--Zemira.
a primitive root; to plan, usually in a bad sense:--consider, devise, imagine, plot, purpose, think (evil).
from 2161; a plot:--wicked device.
a primitive root; to fix (a time):--appoint.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 2163; to agree (on a time and place):--prepare.
from 2163; an appointed occasion:--season, time.
(Aramaic) from 2165; the same as 2165:--season, time.

a primitive root (perhaps ident. with 2168 through the idea of striking with the fingers); properly, to touch the strings or parts of a musical instrument, i.e. play upon it; to make music, accompanied by the voice; hence to celebrate in song and music:--give praise, sing forth praises, psalms.
a primitive root (compare 2167, 5568, 6785); to trim (a vine):--prune.
apparently from 2167 or 2168; a gazelle (from its lightly touching the ground):--chamois.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to 2167; instrumental music:--musick.
(Aramaic) from the same as 2170; an instrumental musician:--singer.
from 2167; a musical piece or song to be accompanied by an instrument:--melody, psalm.
from 2168; pruned (i.e. choice) fruit:--best fruit.
from 2167; musical; Zimri, the name of five Israelites, and of an Arabian tribe:--Zimri.
from 2167; musical; Zimran, a son of Abraham by Keturah:--Zimran.
from 2167; instrumental music; by implication, praise:--song.
from 2109; properly, nourished (or fully developed), i.e. a form or sort:--divers kinds, X all manner of store.

a primitive root meaning to wag; used only as a denominative from 2180; to curtail, i.e. cut off the rear:--smite the hindmost.
from 2179 (in the original sense of flapping); the tail (literally or figuratively):--tail.

a primitive root (highly-fed and therefore wanton); to commit adultery (usually of the female, and less often of simple fornication, rarely of involuntary ravishment); figuratively, to commit idolatry (the Jewish people being regarded as the spouse of Jehovah):--(cause to) commit fornication, X continually, X great, (be an, play the) harlot, (cause to be, play the) whore, (commit, fall to) whoredom, (cause to) go a-whoring, whorish.
from 2186; rejected; Zanoach, the name of two places in Palestine:--Zanoah.
from 2181; adultery; figuratively, idolatry:--whoredom.
from 2181; adultery, i.e. (figuratively) infidelity, idolatry:--whoredom.
regarded by some as if from 2109 or an unused root, and applied to military equipments; but evidently the feminine plural active participle of 2181; harlots:--armour.
a primitive root meaning to push aside, i.e. reject, forsake, fail:--cast away (off), remove far away (off).
a primitive root; properly, to draw together the feet (as an animal about to dart upon its prey), i.e. to spring forward:-- leap.
from 2111 (in the sense of 3154); perspiration:--sweat.
by transposition for 2113; agitation, maltreatment:--X removed, trouble.
from 2111; disquiet; Zaavan, an Idumaean:--Zaavan.
from an unused root (akin (by permutation) to 6819), meaning to dwindle; small:--little.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 2191:--little.
a primitive root; to extinguish:--be extinct.
a primitive root; properly, to foam at the mouth, i.e. to be enraged:--abhor, abominable, (be) angry, defy, (have) indignation.
from 2194; strictly froth at the mouth, i.e. (figuratively) fury (especially of God's displeasure with sin):--angry, indignation, rage.
a primitive root; properly, to boil up, i.e. (figuratively) to be peevish or angry:--fret, sad, worse liking, be wroth.
from 2196; anger:--indignation, rage(-ing), wrath.
from 2196; angry:--displeased.

a primitive root; to shriek (from anguish or danger); by analogy, (as a herald) to announce or convene publicly:-- assemble, call (together), (make a) cry (out), come with such a company, gather (together), cause to be proclaimed.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 2199; to make an outcry:--cry.
and (feminine) zoaqah {zeh-aw-kaw'}; from 2199; a shriek or outcry:--cry(-ing).
from an unused root (meaning to be fragrant); Ziphron, a place in Palestine:--Ziphron.
from an unused root (meaning to liquify); asphalt (from its tendency to soften in the sun):--pitch.
a primitive root; to be old:--aged man, be (wax) old (man).
from 2204; old:--aged, ancient (man), elder(-est), old (man, men and...women), senator.
from 2204; the beard (as indicating age):--beard.
from 2204; old age:--age.
properly, passive participle of 2204 (used only in the plural as a noun); old age:-old age.
feminine of 2205; old age:--old (age).
a primitive root; to life, i.e. (figuratively) comfort:--raise (up).
(Aramaic) corresponding to 2210; to hang, i.e. impale:--set up.
a primitive root; to strain, (figuratively) extract, clarify:--fine, pour down, purge, purify, refine.
from 2237 (in the sense of scattering); a chaplet (as spread around the top), i.e. (specifically) a border moulding:--crown.
from 2114 (in the sense of estrangement) (compare 2219); disgust:--loathsome.
a primitive root; to flow away:--wax warm.
from 2215 and 894; descended of (i.e. from) Babylon, i.e. born there; Zerubbabel, an Israelite:--Zerubbabel.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 2216:--Zerubbabel.
from an unused root meaning to be exuberant in growth; lined with shrubbery; Zered, a brook East of the Dead Sea:--Zared, Zered.
a primitive root (compare 2114); to toss about; by implication, to diffuse, winnow:--cast away, compass, disperse, fan, scatter (away), spread, strew, winnow.

or (shortened) zroao {zer-o'-ah}; and (feminine) zrowpah {zer-o-aw'}; or zrowah {zer-o-aw'}; from 2232; the arm (as stretched out), or (of animals) the foreleg; figuratively, force:--arm, + help, mighty, power, shoulder, strength.
from 2232; something sown, i.e. a plant:--sowing, thing that is sown.
by reduplication from an unused root meaning to flow; a pouring rain:--water.
by reduplication from 2115; properly, tightly girt, i.e. probably a racer, or some fleet animal (as being slender in the waist):--+ greyhound.
a primitive root; properly, to irradiate (or shoot forth beams), i.e. to rise (as the sun); specifically, to appear (as a symptom of leprosy):--arise, rise (up), as soon as it is up.
from 2224; a rising of light:--rising.
the same as 2225; Zerach, the name of three Israelites, also of an Idumaean and an Ethiopian prince:--Zarah, Zerah.
patronymically from 2226; a Zarchite or descendant of Zerach:--Zarchite.
from 2225 and 3050; Jah has risen: Zerachjah, the name of two Israelites:--Zerahiah.
a primitive root; to gush (as water):--carry away as with a flood, pour out.
from 2229; a gush of water:--flood, overflowing, shower, storm, tempest.
feminine of 2230; a gushing of fluid (semen):--issue.
a primitive root; to sow; figuratively, to disseminate, plant, fructify:--bear, conceive seed, set with sow(-er), yield.
from 2232; seed; figuratively, fruit, plant, sowing-time, posterity:--X carnally, child, fruitful, seed(-time), sowing- time.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 2233; posterity:--seed.
or zeraSon {zay-raw-ohn'}; from 2232; something sown (only in the plural), i.e. a vegetable (as food):--pulse.
a primitive root; to sprinkle (fluid or solid particles):--be here and there, scatter, sprinkle, strew.
a primitive root (compare 2114); perhaps to diffuse, i.e. (specifically) to sneeze:--sneeze.
of Persian origin; Zeresh, Haman's wife:--Zeresh.
from 2219; the spread of the fingers, i.e. a span:--span.
of uncertain derivation; Zattu, an Israelite:--Zattu.
apparently a variation for 2133; Zetham, an &� Israelite:--Zetham.
of Persian origin; Zethar, a eunuch of Xerxes:--Zethar.
by contraction from 2245; properly, a cherisher, i.e. the bosom:--bosom.
a primitive root (compare 2245); to secrete:--X held, hide (self), do secretly.
a primitive root (compare 2244, 2247); properly, to hide (as in the bosom), i.e. to cherish (with affection):--love.
from 2245; cherished; Chobab, father-in-law of Moses:--Hobab.
a primitive root (compare 2245); to secrete:--hide (self).
(Aramaic) from 2255; properly, overthrown, i.e. (morally) crime:--hurt.
from 2266; united; Chabor, a river of Assyria:--Habor.
or chabburah {khab-boo-raw'}; or chaburah {khab-oo-raw'}; from 2266; properly, bound (with stripes), i.e. a weal (or black-and-blue mark itself):--blueness, bruise, hurt, stripe, wound.
a primitive root; to knock out or off:--beat (off, out), thresh.
or Chabayah {khab-aw-yaw'}; from 2247 and 3050; Jah has hidden; Chabajah, an Israelite:--Habaiah.
from 2247; a concealment:--hiding.

a primitive root; to wind tightly (as a rope), i.e. to bind; specifically, by a pledge; figuratively, to pervert, destroy; also to writhe in pain (especially of parturition):--X at all, band, bring forth, (deal) corrupt(-ly), destroy, offend, lay &� to (take a) pledge, spoil, travail, X very, withhold.

or chebel {khay'-bel}; from 2254; a rope (as twisted), especially a measuring line; by implication, a district or inheritance (as measured); or a noose (as of cords); figuratively, a company (as if tied together); also a throe (especially of parturition); also ruin:--band, coast, company, cord, country, destruction, line, lot, pain, pang, portion, region, rope, snare, sorrow, tackling.

from 2254 (in the sense of furnished with ropes); a mast:--mast.
of uncertain derivation; probably meadow-saffron:--rose.
of uncertain derivation; Chabatstsanjah, a Rechabite:--Habazaniah.

from 2263; a clasping of the hands (in idleness):--fold.
by reduplication from 2263; embrace; Chabakkuk, the prophet:--Habakkuk.

a primitive root; to join (literally or figuratively); specifically (by means of spells) to fascinate:--charm(- er), be compact, couple (together), have fellowship with, heap up, join (self, together), league.
from 2266; a society; also a spell:--+ charmer(- ing), company, enchantment, X wide.
the same as 2267; community; Cheber, the name of a Kenite and of three Israelites:--Heber.

from 2266; an associate:--companion, fellow, knit together.
from 2266; a partner:--companion.

from 2267; seat of association; Chebron, a place in Palestine, also the name of two Israelites:--Hebron.

feminine of 2270; a consort:--companion.
feminine active participle of 2266; a joint:--which coupleth, coupling.
a primitive root; to wrap firmly (especially a turban, compress, or saddle); figuratively, to stop, to rule:--bind (up), gird about, govern, healer, put, saddle, wrap about.
from an unused root probably meaning to cook (compare 4227); something fried, probably a griddle-cake:--pan.
or chag {khawg}; from 2287; a festival, or a victim therefor:--(solemn) feast (day), sacrifice, solemnity.
from an unused root meaning to revolve (compare 2287); properly, vertigo, i.e. (figuratively) fear:--terror.
of uncertain derivation; a locust:--locust.
the same as 2284; locust; Chagab, one of the Nethinim:--Hagab.
or Chagabah {khag-aw-baw'}; feminine of 2285; locust; Chagaba or Chagabah, one of the Nethinim:--Hagaba, Hagabah.

a primitive root (compare 2283, 2328); properly, to move in a circle, i.e. (specifically) to march in a sacred procession, to observe a festival; by implication, to be giddy:--celebrate, dance, (keep, hold) a (solemn) feast (holiday), reel to and fro.
from an unused root meaning to take refuge; a rift in rocks:--cleft.
from 2296; belted:--girded with.

from 2287; festive, Chaggi, an Israelite; also (patronymically) a Chaggite, or descendant of the same:--Haggi, Haggites.
from 2282; festive; Chaggai, a Heb. prophet:--Haggai.
from 2282 and 3050; festival of Jah; Chaggijah, an Israelite:--Haggiah.
feminine of 2291; festive; Chaggith, a wife of David:--Haggith.
of uncertain derivation; probably a partridge; Choglah, an Israelitess:--Hoglah. See also 1031.
a primitive root; to gird on (as a belt, armor, etc.):--be able to put on, be afraid, appointed, gird, restrain, X on every side.

(Aramaic) corresponding to 2297; as card. one; as article single; as an ordinal, first; adverbially, at once:--a, first, one, together.
from 2300; sharp:--sharp.
a primitive root; to be (causatively, make) sharp or (figuratively) severe:--be fierce, sharpen.
from 2300; fierce; Chadad, an Ishmaelite:--Hadad.
a primitive root; to rejoice:--make glad, be joined, rejoice.
from 2300; a point:--sharp.
from 2302; rejoicing:--gladness, joy.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 2304:--joy.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 2373; a breast:--breast.
from 2300; a peak; Chadid, a place in Palestine:--Hadid.
a primitive root; properly, to be flabby, i.e. (by implication) desist; (figuratively) be lacking or idle:--cease, end, fall, forbear, forsake, leave (off), let alone, rest, be unoccupied, want.
from 2308; rest, i.e. the state of the dead:--world.
from 2308; vacant, i.e. ceasing or destitute:--he that forbeareth, frail, rejected.
from 2309; idle; Chadlai, an Israelite:--Hadlai.
from an unused root meaning to sting; a prickly plant:--brier, thorn.
probably of foreign origin; the Chiddekel (or Tigris) river:--Hiddekel.
a primitive root; properly, to inclose (as a room), i.e. (by analogy,) to beset (as in a siege):--enter a privy chamber.
from 2314; an apartment (usually literal):--((bed) inner)chamber, innermost(-ward) part, parlour, + south, X within.
another form for 2315; chamber; Chadar, an Ishmaelite:--Hadar.
of uncertain derivation; Chadrak, a Syrian deity:--Hadrach.
a primitive root; to be new; causatively, to rebuild:--renew, repair.
from 2318; new:--fresh, new thing.
from 2318; the new moon; by implication, a month:--month(-ly), new moon.
the same as 2320; Chodesh, an Israelitess:--Hodesh.
feminine of 2319; new; Chadashah, a place in Palestine:--Hadashah.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 2319; new:--new.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 2331; to show:--shew.
also chayab {khaw-yab'}; a primitive root; properly, perhaps to tie, i.e. (figuratively and reflexively) to owe, or (by implication) to forfeit:--make endanger.
from 2325; debt:--debtor.
feminine active participle of 2247; hiding place; Chobah, a place in Syria:--Hobah.
a primitive root (compare 2287); to describe a circle:--compass.
from 2328; a circle:--circle, circuit, compass.
a primitive root; properly, to tie a knot, i.e. (figuratively) to propound a riddle:--put forth.
a primitive root; (compare 2324, 2421); properly, to live; by implication (intensively) to declare or show:--show.
causatively from 2331; life-giver; Chavvah (or Eve), the first woman:--Eve.
properly, the same as 2332 (life-giving, i.e. living-place); by implication, an encampment or village:--(small) town.
from the plural of 2333 and a modification of 3265; hamlets of Jair, a region of Palestine:--(Bashan- )Havoth-jair.
from 2374; visionary; Chozai, an Israelite:--the seers.
from an unused root apparently meaning to pierce; a thorn; by analogy, a ring for the nose:--bramble, thistle, thorn.
perhaps the same as 2336; a dell or crevice (as if pierced in the earth):--thicket.
(Aramaic) corresponding to the root of 2339, perhaps as a denominative; to string together, i.e. (figuratively) to repair:--join.
from an unused root probably meaning to sew; a string; by implication, a measuring tape:--cord, fillet, line, thread.
perhaps from 2333; a villager; a Chivvite, one of the aboriginal tribes of Palestine:--Hivite.
probably from 2342; circular; Chavilah, the name of two or three eastern regions; also perhaps of two men:--Havilah.

or chiyl {kheel}; a primitive root; properly, to twist or whirl (in a circular or spiral manner), i.e. (specifically) to dance, to writhe in pain (especially of parturition) or fear; figuratively, to wait, to pervert:--bear, (make to) bring forth, (make to) calve, dance, drive away, fall grievously (with pain), fear, form, great, grieve, (be) grievous, hope, look, make, be in pain, be much (sore) pained, rest, shake, shapen, (be) sorrow(-ful), stay, tarry, travail (with pain), tremble, trust, wait carefully (patiently), be wounded.
from 2342; a circle; Chul, a son of Aram; also the region settled by him:--Hul.
from 2342; sand (as round or whirling particles):--sand.
from an unused root meaning to be warm, i.e. (by implication) sunburnt or swarthy (blackish):--brown.
feminine active participle of an unused root apparently meaning to join; a wall of protection:--wall, walled.
a primitive root; properly, to cover, i.e. (figuratively) to compassionate:--pity, regard, spare.
from an unused root meaning to cover; a cove (as a sheltered bay):--coast (of the sea), haven, shore, (sea-)side.
from the same as 2348; protection: Chupham, an Israelite:--Hupham.
patronymically from 2349; a Chuphamite or descendant of Chupham:--Huphamites.

or (shortened) chuts {khoots}; (both forms feminine in the plural) from an unused root meaning to sever; properly, separate by a wall, i.e. outside, outdoors:--abroad, field, forth, highway, more, out(-side, -ward), street, without.
or (shortened) chur {khoor}; from an unused root probably meaning to bore; the crevice of a serpent; the cell of a prison:--hole.
from 2357; white linen:--white.
the same as 2353 or 2352; Chur, the name of four Israelites and one Midianite:--Hur.
the same as 2353; white linen:--network. Compare 2715.
or (shortened) chor {khore}; the same as 2352; a cavity, socket, den:--cave, hole.
a primitive root; to blanch (as with shame):--wax pale.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to 2357; white:--white.
probably from 2353; linen-worker; Churi, an Israelite:--Huri.
probably an orthographical variation for 2359; Churai, an Israelite:--Hurai.
probably from 2353; whiteness, i.e. noble; Churam, the name of an Israelite and two Syrians:--Huram. Compare 2438.
apparently from 2357 (in the sense of 2352); cavernous; Chavran, a region East of the Jordan:--Hauran.
a primitive root; to hurry; figuratively, to be eager with excitement or enjoyment:--(make) haste(-n), ready.
from 2363; haste; Chushah, an Israelite:--Hushah.
from 2363; hasty; Chushai, an Israelite:--Hushai.
or Chushiym {khoo-shem'}; or Chushim {khoo- sheem'}; plural from 2363; hasters; Chushim, the name of three Israelites:--Hushim.
or Chusham {khoo-shawm'}; from 2363; hastily; Chusham, an Idumaean:--Husham.
or chotham {kho-thawm'}; from 2856; a signature-ring:--seal, signet.
the same as 2368; seal; Chotham, the name of two Israelites:--Hotham, Hothan.
(Aramaic) or chazah (Aramaic) {khaz-aw'}; corresponding to 2372; to gaze upon; mentally to dream, be usual (i.e. seem):--behold, have (a dream), see, be wont.
or Chazahoel {khaz-aw-ale'}; from 2372 and 410; God has seen; Chazael, a king of Syria:--Hazael.
a primitive root; to gaze at; mentally, to perceive, contemplate (with pleasure); specifically, to have a vision of:--behold, look, prophesy, provide, see.
from 2372; the breast (as most seen in front):--breast.
active participle of 2372; a beholder in vision; also a compact (as looked upon with approval):--agreement, prophet, see that, seer, (star-)gazer.
from 2372; seer; Chazo, a nephew of Abraham:--Hazo.
(Aramaic) from 2370; a sight:--look, vision.
from 2372; a sight (mentally), i.e. a dream, revelation, or oracle:--vision.
from 2372; a revelation:--vision.
(Aramaic) from 2370; a view:--sight.
from 2372; a look; hence (figuratively) striking appearance, revelation, or (by implication) compact:--agreement, notable (one), vision.
from 2372 and 410; seen of God; Chaziel, a Levite:--Haziel.
from 2372 and 3050; Jah has seen; Chazajah, an Israelite:--Hazaiah.
from 2372; vision; Chezjon, a Syrian:--Hezion.
from 2372; a revelation, expectation by dream:--vision.
from an unused root meaning to glare; a flash of lightning:--bright cloud, lightning.
from an unused root probably meaning to enclose; a hog (perhaps as penned):--boar, swine.
from the same as 2386; perhaps protected; Chezir, the name of two Israelites:--Hezir.

a primitive root; to fasten upon; hence, to seize, be strong (figuratively, courageous, causatively strengthen, cure, help, repair, fortify), obstinate; to bind, restrain, conquer:--aid, amend, X calker, catch, cleave, confirm, be constant, constrain, continue, be of good (take) courage(-ous, -ly), encourage (self), be established, fasten, force, fortify, make hard, harden, help, (lay) hold (fast), lean, maintain, play the man, mend, become (wax) mighty, prevail, be recovered, repair, retain, seize, be (wax) sore, strengthen (self), be stout, be (make, shew, wax) strong(-er), be sure, take (hold), be urgent, behave self valiantly, withstand.
from 2388; strong (usu. in a bad sense, hard, bold, violent):--harder, hottest, + impudent, loud, mighty, sore, stiff(-hearted), strong(-er).
from 2388; powerful:--X wax louder, stronger.
from 2388; help:--strength.
from 2388; power:--strength.
feminine of 2391; prevailing power:--strength(- en self), (was) strong.
feminine of 2392; vehemence (usually in a bad sense):--force, mightily, repair, sharply.
from 2388; strong; Chizki, an Israelite:--Hezeki.

or Chizqiyahuw {khiz-kee-yaw'-hoo}; also Ychizqiyah {yekh-iz-kee-yaw'}; or Ychizqiyahuw {yekh-iz-kee-yaw'-hoo}; from 2388 and 3050; strengthened of Jah; Chizkijah, a king of Judah, also the name of two other Israelites:--Hezekiah, Hizkiah, Hizkijah. Compare 3169.
once (Ezek. 29:4) chachiy {khakh-ee'}; from the same as 2336; a ring for the nose (or lips):--bracelet, chain, hook.

a primitive root; properly, to miss; hence (figuratively and generally) to sin; by inference, to forfeit, lack, expiate, repent, (causatively) lead astray, condemn:--bear the blame, cleanse, commit (sin), by fault, harm he hath done, loss, miss, (make) offend(-er), offer for sin, purge, purify (self), make reconciliation, (cause, make) sin(-ful, -ness), trespass.
from 2398; a crime or its penalty:--fault, X grievously, offence, (punishment of) sin.
intensively from 2398; a criminal, or one accounted guilty:--offender, sinful, sinner.
feminine of 2399; an offence, or a sacrifice for it:--sin (offering).
(Aramaic) corresponding to 2401; an offence, and the penalty or sacrifice for it:--sin (offering).

or chattacth {khat-tawth'}; from 2398; an offence (sometimes habitual sinfulness), and its penalty, occasion, sacrifice, or expiation; also (concretely) an offender:--punishment (of sin), purifying(-fication for sin), sin(-ner, offering).
a primitive root; to chop or carve wood:--cut down, hew(-er), polish.
feminine passive participle of 2404; properly, a carving; hence, a tapestry (as figured):--carved.
of uncertain derivation; wheat, whether the grain or the plant:--wheat(-en).
from an unused root of uncertain signification; Chattush, the name of four or five Israelites:--Hattush.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to 2398; an offence:--sin.
(Aramaic) from the same as 2408; an expiation:--sin offering.
from an unused root apparently meaning to dig out; explorer; Chatita, a temple porter:--Hatita.
from an unused root apparently meaning to wave; fluctuating; Chattil, one of "Solomon's servants":--Hattil.
from 2414; robber; Chatipha, one of the Nethinim:--Hatipha.
a primitive root; to stop:--refrain.
a primitive root; to clutch; hence, to seize as a prisoner:--catch.
from an unused root of uncertain signification; a twig:--rod.

from 2421; alive; hence, raw (flesh); fresh (plant, water, year), strong; also (as noun, especially in the feminine singular and masculine plural) life (or living thing), whether literally or figuratively:--+ age, alive, appetite, (wild) beast, company, congregation, life(-time), live(-ly), living (creature, thing), maintenance, + merry, multitude, + (be) old, quick, raw, running, springing, troop.
(Aramaic) from 2418; alive; also (as noun in plural) life:--life, that liveth, living.
(Aramaic) or chayah (Aramaic) {khah-yaw'}; corresponding to 2421; to live:--live, keep alive.
from 2416 and 410; living of God; Chiel, an Israelite:--Hiel.
from 2330; a puzzle, hence, a trick, conundrum, sententious maxim:--dark saying (sentence, speech), hard question, proverb, riddle.

a primitive root (compare 2331, 2421); to live, whether literally or figuratively; causatively, to revive:--keep (leave, make) alive, X certainly, give (promise) life, (let, suffer to) live, nourish up, preserve (alive), quicken, recover, repair, restore (to life), revive, (X God) save (alive, life, lives), X surely, be whole.
from 2421; vigorous:--lively.
(Aramaic) from 2418; an animal:--beast.
from 2421; life:--X living.
a primitive root (compare 2421); to live; causatively to revive:--live, save life.
or (shortened) chel {khale}; a collateral form of 2428; an army; also (by analogy,) an intrenchment:--army, bulwark, host, + poor, rampart, trench, wall.
and (feminine) chiylah {khee-law'}; from 2342; a throe (expectant of childbirth):--pain, pang, sorrow.

from 2342; probably a force, whether of men, means or other resources; an army, wealth, virtue, valor, strength:--able, activity, (+) army, band of men (soldiers), company, (great) forces, goods, host, might, power, riches, strength, strong, substance, train, (+)valiant(-ly), valour, virtuous(-ly), war, worthy(-ily).
(Aramaic) corresponding to 2428; an army, or strength:--aloud, army, X most (mighty), power.
feminine of 2428; an intrenchment:--bulwark.
or Cheleam {khay-lawm'}; from 2428; fortress; Chelam, a place East of Palestine:--Helam.
from 2428; fortress; Chilen, a place in Palestine:--Hilen.
another form for 2580; beauty:--comely.
another form for 2351; a wall:--wall.
from 2434; properly, the (outer) wall side; hence, exterior; figuratively, secular (as opposed to sacred):--outer, outward, utter, without.
or cheq {khake}; and chowq {khoke}; from an unused root, apparently meaning to inclose; the bosom (literally or figuratively):--bosom, bottom, lap, midst, within.
from 2357 in the sense of splendor; Chirah, an Adullamite:--Hirah.
or Chiyrowm {khee-rome'}; another form of 2361; Chiram or Chirom, the name of two Tyrians:--Hiram, Huram.
another form of 2363; to hurry:--make haste.
from 2439; properly, a hurry; hence (adverb) quickly:--soon.
probably from 2596 in the sense of tasting; properly, the palate or inside of the mouth; hence, the mouth itself (as the organ of speech, taste and kissing):--(roof of the) mouth, taste.
a primitive root (apparently akin to 2707 through the idea of piercing); properly, to adhere to; hence, to await:--long, tarry, wait.
probably from 2442; a hook (as adhering):--angle, hook.
from the same as 2447; dark; Chakilah, a hill in Palestine:--Hachilah.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to 2449; wise, i.e. a Magian:--wise.
from the base of 2447 and 3050; darkness of Jah; Chakaljah, an Israelite:--Hachaliah.
by reduplication from an unused root apparently meaning to be dark; darkly flashing (only of the eyes); in a good sense, brilliant (as stimulated by wine):--red.
from 2447; flash (of the eyes); in a bad sense, blearedness:--redness.
a primitive root, to be wise (in mind, word or act):--X exceeding, teach wisdom, be (make self, shew self) wise, deal (never so) wisely, make wiser.
from 2449; wise, (i.e. intelligent, skilful or artful):--cunning (man), subtil, ((un-)), wise((hearted), man).
from 2449; wisdom (in a good sense):--skilful, wisdom, wisely, wit.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 2451; wisdom:--wisdom.
from 2449; skilful; Chakmoni, an Israelite:--Hachmoni, Hachmonite.
or chakmowth {khak-moth'}; collateral forms of 2451; wisdom:--wisdom, every wise (woman).
from 2490; properly, exposed; hence, profane:--common, profane (place), unholy.
a primitive root (compare 2470); to be sick:--be diseased.
from 2456; properly, disease; hence, rust:--scum.
the same as 2457; Chelah, an Israelitess:--Helah.
or cheleb {khay'-leb}; from an unused root meaning to be fat; fat, whether literally or figuratively; hence, the richest or choice part:--X best, fat(-ness), X finest, grease, marrow.
the same as 2459; fatness; Cheleb, an Israelite:--Heleb.
from the same as 2459; milk (as the richness of kine):--+ cheese, milk, sucking.
feminine of 2459; fertility: Chelbah, a place in Palestine:--Helbah.
from 2459; fruitful; Chelbon, a place in Syria:--Helbah.
from 2459; galbanam, an odorous gum (as if fatty):--galbanum.
from an unused root apparently meaning to glide swiftly; life (as a fleeting portion of time); hence, the world (as transient):--age, short time, world.
the same as 2465; Cheled, an Israelite:--Heled.
from the same as 2465; a weasel (from its gliding motion):--weasel.
feminine of 2467; Chuldah, an Israelitess:--Huldah.
from 2466; worldliness; Cheldai, the name of two Israelites:--Heldai.

a primitive root (compare 2342, 2470, 2490); properly, to be rubbed or worn; hence (figuratively) to be weak, sick, afflicted; or (causatively) to grieve, make sick; also to stroke (in flattering), entreat:--beseech, (be) diseased, (put to) grief, be grieved, (be) grievous, infirmity, intreat, lay to, put to pain, X pray, make prayer, be (fall, make) sick, sore, be sorry, make suit (X supplication), woman in travail, be (become) weak, be wounded.
from 2490; a cake (as usually punctured):--cake.
or (shortened) chalom {khal-ome'}; from 2492; a dream:--dream(-er).
or (shortened) Cholon {kho-lone'}; probably from 2344; sandy; Cholon, the name of two places in Palestine:--Holon.
a window (as perforated):--window.
from 2498; properly, surviving; by implication (collectively) orphans:--X destruction.
feminine passive participle of 2522; defeat:--being overcome.
probably of foreign origin; Chalach, a region of Assyria:--Halah.
by reduplication from 2342; contorted; Chalchul, a place in Palestine:--Halhul.
feminine from the same as 2478; writhing (in childbirth); by implication, terror:--(great, much) pain.
a primitive root; to snatch at:--catch.
from 2470; a trinket (as polished):--jewel, ornament.
the same as 2481; Chali, a place in Palestine:--Hali.
from 2470; malady, anxiety, calamity:--disease, grief, (is) sick(-ness).
feminine of 2481; a trinket:--jewel.
from 2490; a flute (as perforated):--pipe.
or chalilah {khaw-lee'-law}; a directive from 2490; literal for a profaned thing; used (interj.) far be it!:--be far, (X God) forbid.
from 2498; alternation:--change, course.
from 2503; spoil:--armour.
or chelkah {khay-lek-aw'}; apparently from an unused root probably meaning to be dark or (figuratively) unhappy; a wretch, i.e. unfortunate:--poor.

a primitive root (compare 2470); properly, to bore, i.e. (by implication) to wound, to dissolve; figuratively, to profane (a person, place or thing), to break (one's word), to begin (as if by an "opening wedge"); denom. (from 2485) to play (the flute):--begin (X men began), defile, X break, defile, X eat (as common things), X first, X gather the grape thereof, X take inheritance, pipe, player on instruments, pollute, (cast as) profane (self), prostitute, slay (slain), sorrow, stain, wound.
from 2490; pierced (especially to death); figuratively, polluted:--kill, profane, slain (man), X slew, (deadly) wounded.

a primitive root; properly, to bind firmly, i.e. (by implication) to be (causatively to make) plump; also (through the figurative sense of dumbness) to dream:--(cause to) dream(-er), be in good liking, recover.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to 2492; a dream:--dream.
from 2492; a dream; Chelem, an Israelite:--Helem. Compare 2469.
from 2492 (in the sense of insipidity); probably purslain:--egg.
probably from 2492 (in the sense of hardness); flint:--flint(-y), rock.
from 2428; strong; Chelon, an Israelite:--Helon.

a primitive root; properly, to slide by, i.e. (by implication) to hasten away, pass on, spring up, pierce or change:--abolish, alter, change, cut off, go on forward, grow up, be over, pass (away, on, through), renew, sprout, strike through.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 2498; to pass on (of time):--pass.
from 2498; properly, exchange; hence (as preposition) instead of:--X for.
the same as 2500; change; Cheleph, a place in Palestine:--Heleph.

a primitive root; to pull off; hence (intensively) to strip, (reflex.) to depart; by implication, to deliver, equip (for fight); present, strengthen:--arm (self), (go, ready) armed (X man, soldier), deliver, draw out, make fat, loose, (ready) prepared, put off, take away, withdraw self.
or Chelets {khay'-lets; from 2502; perhaps, strength; Chelets, the name of two Israelites:--Helez.
from 2502 (in the sense of strength); only in the dual; the loins (as the seat of vigor):--loins, reins.

a primitive root; to be smooth (figuratively); by implication (as smooth stones were used for lots) to apportion or separate:--deal, distribute, divide, flatter, give, (have, im-)part(-ner), take away a portion, receive, separate self, (be) smooth(-er).
from 2505; properly, smoothness (of the tongue); also an allotment:--flattery, inheritance, part, X partake, portion.
the same as 2506; portion; Chelek, an Israelite:--Helek.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to 2505; a part:--portion.
from 2505; smooth (especially of tongue):--flattering, smooth.
the same as 2509; bare; Chalak, a mountain of Idumaea:--Halak.
from 2505; smooth:--smooth.
from 2505; smooth:--smooth.

feminine of 2506; properly, smoothness; figuratively, flattery; also an allotment:--field, flattering(-ry), ground, parcel, part, piece of land (ground), plat, portion, slippery place, smooth (thing).
feminine from 2505; flattery:--flattery.
feminine of 2512; a distribution:--division.
patronymically from 2507; a Chelkite or descendant of Chelek:--Helkites.
from 2505; apportioned; Chelkai, an Israelite:--Helkai.
or Chilqiyahuw {khil-kee-yaw'-hoo}'from 2506 and 3050; portion of Jah; {Chilhijah, the name of eight Israelites:-- Hillkiah.
by reduplication from 2505; properly, something very smooth; i.e. a treacherous spot; figuratively, blandishment:--flattery, slippery.
a form of 2513; smoothness; Chelkath, a place in Palestine:--Helkath.
from 2520 and the plural of 6697, with the article inserted; smoothness of the rocks; Chelkath Hats-tsurim, a place in Palestine:--Helkath-hazzurim.
a primitive root; to prostrate; by implication, to overthrow, decay:--discomfit, waste away, weaken.
from 2522; frail:--weak.
from the same as 2346; a father-in-law (as in affinity):--father in law.
from 2552; hot:--hot, warm.
the same as 2525; hot (from the tropical habitat); Cham, a son of Noah; also (as a patronymic) his descendants or their country:--Ham.
from 2552; heat:--heat, to be hot (warm).
(Aramaic) or chamah (Aramaic) {kham-aw'}; corresponding to 2534; anger:--fury.
or (shortened) chemah {khay-maw'}; from the same root as 2346; curdled milk or cheese:--butter.
a primitive root; to delight in:--beauty, greatly beloved, covet, delectable thing, (X great) delight, desire, goodly, lust, (be) pleasant (thing), precious (thing).
om 2530; delight:--desirable, pleasant.
feminine of 2531; delight:--desire, goodly, pleasant, precious.
from 2531; pleasant; Chemdan, an Idumaean:--Hemdan.

or (Dan. 11:44) chemaC {khay-maw'}; from 3179; heat; figuratively, anger, poison (from its fever):--anger, bottles, hot displeasure, furious(-ly, -ry), heat, indignation, poison, rage, wrath(- ful). See 2529.
from 2525; heat; by implication, the sun:--heat, sun.
from 2535 and 410; anger of God; Chammuel, an Israelite:--Hamuel.
or Chamiytal {kham-ee-tal'}; from 2524 and 2919; father-in-law of dew; Chamutal or Chamital, an Israelitess:-- Hamutal.
from 2550; pitied; Chamul, an Israelite:--Hamul.
patronymically from 2538: a Chamulite (collectively) or descendants of Chamul:--Hamulites.
from 2552; warm spring; Chammon, the name of two places in Palestine:--Hammon.
from 2556; properly, violent; by implication, a robber:--oppressed.
from 2559; a wrapping, i.e. drawers:--joints.
or (shortened) chamor {kham-ore}; from 2560; a male ass (from its dun red):--(he)ass.
the same as 2543; donkey; Chamor, a Canaanite:--Hamor.
or (shortened) chamoth {kham-oth'}; feminine of 2524; a mother-in-law:--mother in law.
from an unused root probably meaning, to lie low; a lizard (as creeping):--snail.
feminine of 2546; low; Chumtah, a place in Palestine:--Humtah.
from 2556; seasoned, i.e. salt provender:--clean.
or chamishshiy {kham-ish-shee'}; ord. from 2568; fifth; also a fifth:--fifth (part).
a primitive root; to commiserate; by implication, to spare:--have compassion, (have) pity, spare.
from 2550; commiseration:--merciful, pity.
a primitive root; to be hot (literally or figuratively):--enflame self, get (have) heat, be (wax) hot, (be, wax) warm (self, at).
from 2535; a sun-pillar:--idol, image.
a primitive root; to be violent; by implication, to maltreat:--make bare, shake off, violate, do violence, take away violently, wrong, imagine wrongfully.
from 2554; violence; by implication, wrong; by meton. unjust gain:--cruel(-ty), damage, false, injustice, X oppressor, unrighteous, violence (against, done), violent (dealing), wrong.
a primitive root; to be pungent; i.e. in taste (sour, i.e. literally fermented, or figuratively, harsh), in color (dazzling):--cruel (man), dyed, be grieved, leavened.
from 2556; ferment, (figuratively) extortion:--leaven, leavened (bread).
from 2556; vinegar:--vinegar.
a primitive root; properly, to wrap; hence, to depart (i.e. turn about):--go about, withdraw self.
a primitive root; properly, to boil up; hence, to ferment (with scum); to glow (with redness); as denominative (from 2564) to smear with pitch:--daub, befoul, be red, trouble.
from 2560; wine (as fermenting):--X pure, red wine.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 2561; wine:--wine.
from 2560; properly, a bubbling up, i.e. of water, a wave; of earth, mire or clay (cement); also a heap; hence, a chomer or dry measure:--clay, heap, homer, mire, motion.
from 2560; bitumen (as rising to the surface):--slime(-pit).
from 2560 (compare 2563); a heap:--heap.
from 2560; red; Chamran, an Idumaean:--Amran.
a denominative from 2568; to tax a fifth:--take up the fifth participle
masculine chamishshah {kham-ish-shaw}; a primitive numeral; five:--fif(-teen), fifth, five (X apiece).
from 2567; a fifth tax:--fifth participle
from an unused root probably meaning, to be stout; the abdomen (as obese):--fifth (rib).
passive participle of the same as 2570; staunch, i.e. able-bodied soldiers:--armed (men), harnessed.
multiple of 2568; fifty:--fifty.
from the same as 2346; a skin bottle (as tied up):--bottle.
from the same as 2346; walled; Chamath, a place in Syria:--Hamath, Hemath.
a variation for the first part of 2576; hot springs; Chammath, a place in Palestine:--Hammath.
from the plural of 2535 and 1756; hot springs of Dor; Chammath-Dor, a place in Palestine:--Hamath-Dor.
patrial from 2574; a Chamathite or native of Chamath:--Hamathite.
from 2574 and 6678; Chamath of Tsobah; Chamath-Tsobah; probably the same as 2574:--Hamath-Zobah.
from 2574 and 7237; Chamath of Rabbah; Chamath-Rabbah, probably the same as 2574.
from 2603; graciousness, i.e. subjective (kindness, favor) or objective (beauty):--favour, grace(-ious), pleasant, precious, (well-)favoured.
the same as 2580; grace; Chen, a figurative name for an Israelite:--Hen.
probably from 2580 and l908; favor of Hadad; Chenadad, an Israelite:--Henadad.

a primitive root (compare 2603); properly, to incline; by implication, to decline (of the slanting rays of evening); specifically, to pitch a tent; gen. to encamp (for abode or siege):--abide (in tents), camp, dwell, encamp, grow to an end, lie, pitch (tent), rest in tent.
from 2603; favored; Channah, an Israelitess:--Hannah.
from 2596; initiated; Chanok, an antediluvian patriach:--Enoch.
from 2603; favored; Chanun, the name of an Ammonite and of two Israelites:--Hanun.
from 2603; gracious:--gracious.
from 2583; properly, a vault or cell (with an arch); by implication, a prison:--cabin.
from 2603 (in the sense of prayer); supplication:--be gracious, intreated.
a primitive root; to spice; by implication, to embalm; also to ripen:--embalm, put forth.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 2406; wheat:--wheat.
from 2603 and 410; favor of God; Channiel, the name of two Israelites:--Hanniel.
from 2596; initiated; i.e. practiced:--trained.
from 2603; graciousness:--favour.
from 2583; a lance (for thrusting, like pitching a tent):--javelin, spear.
a primitive root; properly, to narrow (compare 2614); figuratively, to initiate or discipline:--dedicate, train up.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 2598; consecration:--dedication.
from 2596; initiation, i.e. consecration:--dedicating(-tion).
patronymically from 2585; a Chanokite (collectively) or descendants of Chanok:--Hanochites.
from 2580; gratis, i.e. devoid of cost, reason or advantage:--without a cause (cost, wages), causeless, to cost nothing, free(-ly), innocent, for nothing (nought, in vain.
probably by orthographical variation for 2606; Chanamel, an Israelite:--Hanameel.
of uncertain derivation; perhaps the aphis or plantlouse:--frost.

a primitive root (compare 2583); properly, to bend or stoop in kindness to an inferior; to favor, bestow; causatively to implore (i.e. move to favor by petition):--beseech, X fair, (be, find, shew) favour(-able), be (deal, give, grant (gracious(-ly), intreat, (be) merciful, have (shew) mercy (on, upon), have pity upon, pray, make supplication, X very.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 2603; to favor or (causatively) to entreat:--shew mercy, make supplication.
from 2603; favor; Chanan, the name of seven Israelites:--Canan.
from 2603 and 410; God has favored; Chananel, probably an Israelite, from whom a tower of Jerusalem was named:--Hananeel.
from 2603; gracious; Chanani, the name of six Israelites:--Hanani.
or Chananyahuw {khan-an-yaw'-hoo}; from 2603 and 3050; Jah has favored; Chananjah, the name of thirteen Israelites:--Hananiah.
of Egyptian derivation; Chanes, a place in Egypt:--Hanes.
a primitive root; to soil, especially in a moral sense:--corrupt, defile, X greatly, pollute, profane.
from 2610; soiled (i.e. with sin), impious:-- hypocrite(-ical).
from 2610; moral filth, i.e. wickedness:--hypocrisy.
feminine from 2610; impiety:--profaneness.
a primitive root (compare 2596); to be narrow; by implication, to throttle, or (reflex.) to choke oneself to death (by a rope):--hang self, strangle.
probably from 2603; favored; Channathon, a place in Palestine:--Hannathon.

a primitive root; properly, perhaps to bow (the neck only (compare 2603) in courtesy to an equal), i.e. to be kind; also (by euphem. (compare l288), but rarely) to reprove:--shew self merciful, put to shame.

from 2616; kindness; by implication (towards God) piety: rarely (by opposition) reproof, or (subject.) beauty:--favour, good deed(-liness, -ness), kindly, (loving-)kindness, merciful (kindness), mercy, pity, reproach, wicked thing.
the same as 2617: favor; Chesed, an Israelite:--Hesed.
from 2617 and 3050; Jah has favored: Chasadjah, an Israelite:--Hasadiah.
a primitive root; to flee for protection (compare 982); figuratively, to confide in:--have hope, make refuge, (put) trust.
from 2620; hopeful; Chosah, an Israelite; also a place in Palestine:--Hosah.
from 2620; confidence:--trust.
from 2616; properly, kind, i.e. (religiously) pious (a saint):--godly (man), good, holy (one), merciful, saint, (un- )godly.
feminine of 2623; the kind (maternal) bird, i.e. a stork:--X feather, stork.
from 2628; the ravager, i.e. a locust:--caterpillar.
from 2630; properly, firm, i.e. (by implication) mighty:--strong.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to 2637; deficient:--wanting.
a primitive root; to eat off:--consume.
a primitive root; to muzzle; by analogy, to stop the nose:--muzzle, stop.
a primitive root; properly, to (be) compact; by implication, to hoard:--lay up.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 2630; to hold in occupancy:--possess.
(Aramaic) from 2631; strength:--power.
from 2630; wealth:--riches, strength, treasure.
from 2630; powerful:--strong.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to that of 2636; a clod:--clay.
reduplicated from an unused root meaning apparently to peel; a shred or scale:--round thing.
a primitive root; to lack; by implication, to fail, want, lessen:--be abated, bereave, decrease, (cause to) fail, (have) lack, make lower, want.
from 2637; lacking; hence, without:--destitute, fail, lack, have need, void, want.
from 2637; lack; hence, destitution:--poverty, want.
from 2637; poverty:--in want of.
from 2637; want:--Chasrah, an Israelite:--Hasrah.
from 2637; deficiency:--wanting.
from 2653 (in the moral sense of covered from soil); pure:--innocent.
an orthographical variation of 2645; properly, to cover, i.e. (in a sinister sense) to act covertly:--do secretly.
a primitive root (compare 2644, 2653); to cover; by implication, to veil, to encase, protect:--ceil, cover, overlay.
from 2645; a canopy:--chamber, closet, defence.
the same as 2646; Chuppah, an Israelite:--Huppah.
a primitive root; properly, to start up suddenly, i.e. (by implication) to hasten away, to fear:--(make) haste (away), tremble.
from 2468; hasty flight:--haste.
plural of 2646 (compare 2349); Chuppim, an Israelite:--Huppim.
from an unused root of uncertain signification; a fist (only in the dual):--fists, (both) hands, hand(-ful).
from 2651; perhaps pugilist; Chophni, an Israelite:--Hophni.
a primitive root (compare 2645, 3182); to cover (in protection):--cover.

a primitive root; properly, to incline to; by implication (literally but rarely) to bend; figuratively, to be pleased with, desire:--X any at all, (have, take) delight, desire, favour, like, move, be (well) pleased, have pleasure, will, would.
from 2654; pleased with:--delight in, desire, favour, please, have pleasure, whosoever would, willing, wish.

from 2654; pleasure; hence (abstractly) desire; concretely, a valuable thing; hence (by extension) a matter (as something in mind):--acceptable, delight(-some), desire, things desired, matter, pleasant(-ure), purpose, willingly.
from 2656 with suffixes; my delight (is) in her; Cheptsi-bah, a fanciful name for Palestine:--Hephzi-bah.
a primitive root; properly, to pry into; by implication, to delve, to explore:--dig, paw, search out, seek.

a primitive root (perhaps rath. the same as 2658 through the idea of detection): to blush; figuratively, to be ashamed, disappointed; causatively, to shame, reproach:--be ashamed, be confounded, be brought to confusion (unto shame), come (be put to) shame, bring reproach.
from 2658 or 2659; a pit of shame; Chepher, a place in Palestine; also the name of three Israelites:--Hepher.

from 2658; a hole; only in connection with 6512, which ought rather to be joined as one word, thus chapharperah {khaf-ar- pay-raw'}; by reduplication from 2658; a burrower, i.e. probably a rat:--+ mole.
patronymically from 2660; a Chephrite (collectively) or descendants of Chepher:--Hepherites.
dual of 2660; double pit; Chapharajim, a place in Palestine:--Haphraim.
a primitive root; to seek; causatively, to conceal oneself (i.e. let be sought), or mask:--change, (make) diligent (search), disquise self, hide, search (for, out).
from 2664; something covert, i.e. a trick:--search.
a primitive root; to spread loose; figuratively, to manumit:--be free.
from 2666; something spread loosely, i.e. a carpet:--precious.
from 2666; liberty (from slavery):--freedom.
and chophshiyth {khof-sheeth'}; from 2666; prostration by sickness (with 1004, a hospital):--several.
from 2666; exempt (from bondage, tax or care):--free, liberty.

from 2686; properly, a piercer, i.e. an arrow; by implication, a wound; figuratively, (of God) thunder-bolt; (by interchange for 6086) the shaft of a spear:--+ archer, arrow, dart, shaft, staff, wound.

or chatseb {khaw-tsabe'}; a primitive root ; to cut or carve (wood), stone or other material); by implication, to hew, split, square, quarry, engrave:--cut, dig, divide, grave, hew (out, -er), made, mason.
a primitive root (compare 2086)); to cut or split in two; to halve:--divide, X live out half, reach to the midst, participle
a collective form of 2691; village; Chatsor, the name (thus simply) of two places in Palestine and of one in Arabia:-- Hazor.
from 2674 and a Aramaizing form of the feminine of 2319 (compare 2323); new Chatsor, a place in Palestine:--Hazor, Hadattah (as if two places).
from 2673; the middle (of the night):--mid(-night).
from 2673; the half or middle:--half, middle, mid(-night), midst, part, two parts.
or chetsiy {chay-tsee'}; prolongation from 2671; an arrow:--arrow.
from 2677 and the plural of 4496, with the article interposed; midst of the resting- places; Chatsi-ham-Menuchoth, an Israelite:--half of the Manahethites.
patronymically from 2679; a Chatsi-ham-Menachtite or descendant of Chatsi-ham-Menuchoth:--half of the Manahethites.
a collateral form of 2691; a court or abode:--court.
perhaps originally the same as 2681, from the greenness of a courtyard; grass; also a leek (collectively):--grass, hay, herb, leek.
from an unused root meaning to hold firmly; the bosom (as comprised between the arms):--bosom.
a collateral form of 2683, and meaning the same:--arm, lap.
(Aramaic) a primitive root; properly, to shear or cut close; figuratively, to be severe:--hasty, be urgent.

a primitive root (compare 2673); properly, to chop into, pierce or sever; hence, to curtail, to distribute (into ranks); as denom. from 2671, to shoot an arrow:--archer, X bands, cut off in the midst.
from 2687; properly, something cutting; hence, gravel (as grit); also (like 2671) an arrow:--arrow, gravel (stone).
or Chatsatson Tamar {khats-ats-one' taw-mawr'}; from 2686 and 8558; division (i.e. perhaps row) of (the) palm-tree; Chatsetson-tamar, a place in Palestine:--Hazezon- tamar.
by reduplication from 2690; a trumpet (from its sundered or quavering note):--trumpet(-er).

a primitive root; properly, to surround with a stockade, and thus separate from the open country; but used only in the reduplicated form chatsotser {khast-o-tsare'}; or (2 Chronicles 5:12) chatsorer {khats-o-rare'}; as dem. from 2689; to trumpet, i.e. blow on that instrument:--blow, sound, trumpeter.
(masculine and feminine); from 2690 in its original sense; a yard (as inclosed by a fence); also a hamlet (as similarly surrounded with walls):--court, tower, village.
from 2691 and 146; (the) village of Addar; Chatsar-Addar, a place in Palestine:--Hazar-addar.
from 2691 and a feminine of 1408; (the) village of (female) Fortune; Chatsar-Gaddah, a place in Palestine:--Hazar-gaddah.
from 2691 and 8484 with the article interposed; village of the middle; Chatsar-hat-Tikon, a place in Palestine:--Hazar-hatticon.
by an orthographical variation for 2696; enclosure; Chetsro, an Israelite:--Hezro, Hezrai.
from 2691; court-yard; Chetsron, the name of a place in Palestine; also of two Israelites:--Hezron.
patronymically from 2696; a Chetsronite or (collectively) descendants of Chetsron:--Hezronites.
feminine plural of 2691; yards; Chatseroth, a place in Palestine:--Hazeroth.
plural masculine of 2691; yards; Chatserim, a place in Palestine:--Hazerim.
from 2691 and 4194; village of death; Chatsarmaveth, a place in Arabia:--Hazarmaveth.
from 2691 and 5484; village of cavalry; Chatsar-Susah, a place in Palestine:--Hazar-susah.
from 2691 and the plural of 5483; village of horses; Chatsar-Susim, a place in Palestine:--Hazar- susim.
from 2691 and a derivative of 5869; village of springs; Chatsar-Enon, a place in Palestine:--Hazar- enon.
from 2691 and the same as 5881; village of springs; Chatsar-Enan, a place in Palestine:--Hazar-enan.
from 2691 and 7776; village of (the) fox; Chatsar-Shual, a place in Palestine:--Hazar-shual.

from 2710; an enactment; hence, an appointment (of time, space, quantity, labor or usage):--appointed, bound, commandment, convenient, custom, decree(-d), due, law, measure, X necessary, ordinance(- nary), portion, set time, statute, task.
a primitive root; to carve; by implication, to delineate; also to entrench:--carved work, portrayed, set a print.
feminine of 2706, and meaning substantially the same:--appointed, custom, manner, ordinance, site, statute.
from an unused root probably meaning to bend; crooked; Chakupha, one of the Nethinim:--Hakupha.

a primitive root; properly, to hack, i.e. engrave (Judges 5:14, to be a scribe simply); by implication, to enact (laws being cut in stone or metal tablets in primitive times) or (gen.) prescribe:--appoint, decree, governor, grave, lawgiver, note, pourtray, print, set.
from 2710; an enactment, a resolution:--decree, thought.
or (fully) Chuwqoq {khoo-koke'}; from 2710; appointed; Chukkok or Chukok, a place in Palestine:--Hukkok, Hukok.
a primitive root; properly, to penetrate; hence, to examine intimately:--find out, (make) search (out), seek (out), sound, try.
from 2713; examination, enumeration, deliberation:--finding out, number, (un-)search(-able, -ed, out, -ing).
or (fully) chowr {khore}; from 2787; properly, white or pure (from the cleansing or shining power of fire (compare 2751); hence (figuratively) noble (in rank):--noble.
from an unused (and vulgar) root probably meaning to evacuate the bowels: excrement; -dung. Also chariy {khar-ee'}.

or chareb {khaw-rabe'}; a primitive root; to parch (through drought) i.e. (by analogy,) to desolate, destroy, kill:-- decay, (be) desolate, destroy(-er), (be) dry (up), slay, X surely, (lay, lie, make) waste.
(Aramaic) a root corresponding to 2717; to demolish:--destroy.
from 2717; drought; also a cutting instrument (from its destructive effect), as a knife, sword, or other sharp implement:--axe, dagger, knife, mattock, sword, tool.
from 2717; parched or ruined:--desolate, dry, waste.
a collaterally form of 2719; drought or desolation:--desolation, drought, dry, heat, X utterly, waste.
from 2717; desolate; Choreb, a (generic) name for the Sinaitic mountains:--Horeb.
feminine of 2721; properly, drought, i.e. (by implication) a desolation:--decayed place, desolate (place, -tion), destruction, (laid) waste (place).
feminine of 2720; a desert:--dry (ground, land).
from 2717; parching heat:--drought.
or Charbownah {khar-bo-naw'}; of Persian origin; Charbona or Charbonah, a eunuch of Xerxes:--Harbona, Harbonah.
a primitive root; properly, to leap suddenly, i.e. (by implication) to be dismayed:--be afraid.
from 2727; the leaping insect, i.e. a locust:--beetle.
a primitive root; to shudder with terror; hence, to fear; also to hasten (with anxiety):--be (make) afraid, be careful, discomfit, fray (away), quake, tremble.
from 2729; fearful; also reverential:--afraid, trembling.
feminine of 2730; fear, anxiety:--care, X exceedingly, fear, quaking, trembling.
the same as 2731; Charadah, a place in the Desert:--Haradah.
patrial from a derivative of 2729 (compare 5878); a Charodite, or inhabitant of Charod:--Harodite.

a primitive root (compare 2787); to glow or grow warm; figuratively (usually) to blaze up, of anger, zeal, jealousy:--be angry, burn, be displeased, X earnestly, fret self, grieve, be (wax) hot, be incensed, kindle, X very, be wroth. See 8474.
from 2356 and a collateral (masculine) form of 1412, with the article interposed; hole of the cleft: Chor-hag-Gidgad, a place in the Desert:--Hor-hagidgad.
; from 2734 and 3050; fearing Jah; Charhajah, an Israelite:--Harhaiah.
from an unused root meaning to perforate; properly, pierced, i.e. a bead of pearl, gems or jewels (as strung):--chain.
or (shortened) charul {khaw-rool'}; apparently, a passive participle of an unused root probably meaning to be prickly; properly, pointed, i.e. a bramble or other thorny weed: nettle.
from passive participle of 2763 and 639; snub-nosed; Charumaph, an Israelite:--Harumaph.
or (shortened) charon {khaw-rone'}; from 2734; a burning of anger:--sore displeasure, fierce(-ness), fury, (fierce) wrath(-ful).
a patrial from (probably) a collateral form of 2756; a Charuphite or inhabitant of Charuph (or Chariph):--Haruphite.

or charuts {khaw-roots'}; passive participle of 2782; properly, incised or (active) incisive; hence (as noun masculine or feminine) a trench (as dug), gold (as mined), a threshing-sledge (having sharp teeth); (figuratively) determination; also eager:--decision, diligent, (fine) gold, pointed things, sharp, threshing instrument, wall.
the same as 2742; earnest; Charuts, an Israelite:--Haruz.
a fuller form of 2746; inflammation; Charchur, one of the Nethinim:--Harhur.
from the same as 2775; perhaps shining; Charchas, an Israelite:--Harhas.
from 2787; fever (as hot); -extreme burning.
from a primitive root meaning to engrave; a chisel or graver; also a style for writing:--graving tool, pen.
from the same as 2747; a horoscopist (as drawing magical lines or circles):--magician.
(Aramaic) the same as 2748:--magician.
from 2734; a burning (i.e. intense) anger:--fierce, X great, heat.
from the same as 2353; white bread:--white.
from 2356; cave-dweller or troglodyte; a Chorite or aboriginal Idumaean:--Horims, Horites.
or Chowriy {kho-ree'}; the same as 2752; Chori, the name of two men:--Hori.
or charit {khaw-reet'}; from the same as 2747; properly, cut out (or hollow), i.e. (by implication) a pocket:--bag, crisping pin.

from the plural of 2716 and the plural of 3123; excrements of doves {or perhaps rather the plural of a single word charapyown {khar-aw-yone'}; of similar or uncertain derivation, probably a kind of vegetable:--doves' dung.
from 2778; autumnal; Chariph, the name of two Israelites:--Hariph.
or charits {khaw-reets'}; from 2782; properly, incisure or (passively) incised (compare 2742); hence, a threshing-sledge (with sharp teeth): also a slice (as cut):--+ cheese, harrow.
from 2790; ploughing or its season:--earing (time), ground.
from 2790 in the sense of silence; quiet, i.e. sultry (as feminine noun, the sirocco or hot east wind):--vehement.
a primitive root; to braid (i.e. to entangle or snare) or catch (game) in a net:--roast.
(Aramaic) a root probably allied to the equivalent of 2787; to scorch:--singe.
from 2760; properly, a net, i.e. (by analogy) lattice:--lattice.

a primitive root; to seclude; specifically (by a ban) to devote to religious uses (especially destruction); physical and reflexive, to be blunt as to the nose:--make accursed, consecrate, (utterly) destroy, devote, forfeit, have a flat nose, utterly (slay, make away).

or (Zecheriah 14:11) cherem {kheh'-rem}; from 2763; physical (as shutting in) a net (either literally or figuratively); usually a doomed object; abstr. extermination:--(ac-)curse(-d, -d thing), dedicated thing, things which should have been utterly destroyed, (appointed to) utter destruction, devoted (thing), net.
from 2763; devoted; Chorem, a place in Palestine:--Horem.
from 2763; snub-nosed; Charim, an Israelite:--Harim.
from 2763; devoted; Chormah, a place in Palestine:--Hormah.
from 2763; abrupt; Chermon, a mount of Palestine:--Hermon.
plural of 2768; Hermons, i.e. its peaks:--the Hermonites.
from 2763; a sickle (as cutting):--sickle.
from 2787; parched; Charan, the name of a man and also of a place:--Haran.
patrial from 2773; a Choronite or inhabitant of Choronaim:--Horonite.
dual of a derivative from 2356; double cave-town; Choronajim, a place in Moab:--Horonaim.
of uncertain derivation; Charnepher, an Israelite:--Harnepher.
or (with a directive enclitic) charcah (khar'- saw}; from an unused root meaning to scrape; the itch; also (perhaps from the mediating idea of 2777) the sun:--itch, sun.
the same as 2775; shining; Cheres, a mountain in Palestine:--Heres.
from 2775 (apparently in the sense of a red tile used for scraping); a potsherd, i.e. (by implication) a pottery; the name of a gate at Jerusalem:--east.

a primitive root; to pull off, i.e. (by implication) to expose (as by stripping); specifically, to betroth (as if a surrender); figuratively, to carp at, i.e. defame; denominative (from 2779) to spend the winter:--betroth, blaspheme, defy, jeopard, rail, reproach, upbraid.
from 2778; properly, the crop gathered, i.e. (by implication) the autumn (and winter) season; figuratively, ripeness of age:--cold, winter (-house), youth.
from 2778; reproachful; Chareph, an Israelite:--Hareph.
from 2778; contumely, disgrace, the pudenda:--rebuke, reproach(-fully), shame.
a primitive root; properly, to point sharply, i.e. (literally) to wound; figuratively, to be alert, to decide:--bestir self, decide, decree, determine, maim, move.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to 2782 in the sense of vigor; the loin (as the seat of strength):--loin.
of uncertain derivation; a fetter; figuratively, a pain:--band.
from 2782; a sour grape (as sharp in taste):--kernel.
a primitive root; to grate the teeth:--gnash.
a primitive root; to glow, i.e. literally (to melt, burn, dry up) or figuratively (to show or incite passion:--be angry, burn, dry, kindle.
from 2787; arid:--parched place.
a collateral form mediating between 2775 and 2791; a piece of pottery:--earth(-en), (pot-)sherd, + stone.

a primitive root; to scratch, i.e. (by implication) to engrave, plough; hence (from the use of tools) to fabricate (of any material); figuratively, to devise (in a bad sense); hence (from the idea of secrecy) to be silent, to let alone; hence (by implication) to be deaf (as an accompaniment of dumbness):--X altogether, cease, conceal, be deaf, devise, ear, graven, imagine, leave off speaking, hold peace, plow(-er, man), be quiet, rest, practise secretly, keep silence, be silent, speak not a word, be still, hold tongue, worker.
from 2790; magical craft; also silence:--cunning, secretly.
the same as 2791:--Cheresh, a Levite:--Heresh.
from 2790; a forest (perhaps as furnishing the material for fabric):--bough, forest, shroud, wood.
active participle of 2790; a fabricator or mechanic:--artificer.
from 2790; deaf (whether literally or spir.):--deaf.
from 2790; a fabricator or any material:--artificer, (+) carpenter, craftsman, engraver, maker, + mason, skilful, (+) smith, worker, workman, such as wrought.
from 2792; magician; Charsha, one of the Nethinim:--Harsha.
plural of 2796; mechanics, the name of a valley in Jerusalem:--Charashim, craftsmen.
from 2790; mechanical work:--carving, cutting.
the same as 2799; Charosheth, a place in Palestine:--Harosheth.
a primitive root; to engrave:--graven.
from 2801 (but equivalent to 2793); forest; Chereth, a thicket in Palestine:--Hereth.

a primitive root; properly, to plait or interpenetrate, i.e. (literally) to weave or (gen.) to fabricate; figuratively, to plot or contrive (usually in a malicious sense); hence (from the mental effort) to think, regard, value, compute:--(make) account (of), conceive, consider, count, cunning (man, work, workman), devise, esteem, find out, forecast, hold, imagine, impute, invent, be like, mean, purpose, reckon(-ing be made), regard, think.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 2803; to regard:--repute.
from 2803; a belt or strap (as being interlaced):--curious girdle.
from 2803 and 1777; considerate judge; Chasbaddanah, an Israelite:--Hasbadana.
from 2803; estimation; Cashubah, an Israelite:--Hashubah.
from 2803; properly, contrivance; by implication, intelligence:--account, device, reason.
the same as 2808; Cheshbon, a place East of the Jordan:--Heshbon.
from 2803; a contrivance, i.e. actual (a warlike machine) or mental (a machination):--engine, invention.
or Chashabyahuw {khash-ab-yaw'-hoo}; from 2803 and 3050; Jah has regarded; Chashabjah, the name of nine Israelites:--Hashabiah.
feminine of 2808; inventiveness; Chashnah, an Israelite:--Hashabnah.
from 2808 and 3050; thought of Jah; Chashabnejah, the name of two Israelites:--Hashabniah.
a primitive root; to hush or keep quiet:--hold peace, keep silence, be silent, (be) still.
from 2803; intelligent; Chashshub, the name of two or three Israelites:--Hashub, Hasshub.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to 2821; the dark:--darkness.
or Chasuphao {khas-oo-faw'}; from 2834; nakedness; Chasupha, one of the Nethinim:--Hashupha, Hasupha.
(Aramaic) a collateral root to one corresponding to 2363 in the sense of readiness; to be necessary (from the idea of convenience) or (transitively) to need:--careful, have need of.
from a root corresponding to 2818; necessity:--be needful.

a primitive root; to restrain or (reflex.) refrain; by implication, to refuse, spare, preserve; also (by interch. with 2821) to observe:--assuage, X darken, forbear, hinder, hold back, keep (back), punish, refrain, reserve, spare, withhold.
a primitive root; to be dark (as withholding light); transitively, to darken:--be black, be (make) dark, darken, cause darkness, be dim, hide.
from 2821; the dark; hence (literally) darkness; figuratively, misery, destruction, death, ignorance, sorrow, wickedness:--dark(-ness), night, obscurity.
from 2821; dark (figuratively, i.e. obscure):--meaning
from 2821; darkness:--dark.
or chashekah {khash-ay-kaw'}; from 2821; darkness; figuratively, misery:--darkness.
a primitive root; to make (intrans. be) unsteady, i.e. weak:--feeble.
(Aramaic) a root corresponding to 2826; to weaken, i.e. crush:--subdue.
from the same as 2831; enriched; Chashum, the name of two or three Israelites:--Hashum.
the same as 2831; opulent; Cheshmon, a place in Palestine:--Heshmon.
of uncertain derivation; probably bronze or polished spectrum metal:--amber.
from an unused root (probably meaning firm or capacious in resources); apparently wealthy:--princes.
feminine of 2831; fertile; Chasmonah, a place in the Desert:--Hashmonah.
from an unused root probably meaning to contain or sparkle; perhaps a pocket (as holding the Urim and Thummim), or rich (as containing gems), used only of the gorget of the highpriest:--breastplate.
a primitive root; to strip off, i.e. generally to make naked (for exertion or in disgrace), to drain away or bail up (a liquid):--make bare, clean, discover, draw out, take, uncover.
from 2834; properly, drawn off, i.e. separated; hence, a small company (as divided from the rest):--little flock.
a primitive root; to cling, i.e. join, (figuratively) to love, delight in; elliptically (or by interchangeable for 2820) to deliver:--have a delight, (have a ) desire, fillet, long, set (in) love.
from 2836; delight:--desire, pleasure.
or chashuwq {khaw-shook'}; past participle of 2836; attached, i.e. a fence-rail or rod connecting the posts or pillars:--fillet.
from 2836; conjoined, i.e. a wheel-spoke or rod connecting the hub with the rim:--felloe.
from an unused root meaning to bind together; combined, i.e. the nave or hub of a wheel (as holding the spokes together):--spoke.
from the same as 2840; properly, a combination or gathering, i.e. of watery clouds:--dark.
by variation for 7179; dry grass:--chaff.
patronymically from 2364; a Chushathite or descendant of Chushah:--Hushathite.
from 2865; concretely, crushed; also afraid; abstractly, terror:--broken, dismayed, dread, fear.
from 2865; terror; Cheth, an aboriginal Canaanite:--Heth.
a primitive root; to lay hold of; especially to pick up fire:--heap, take (away).
from 2865; fear:--terror.
from 2853; swathed, i.e. a bandage:--roller.
from 2844; terror:--fear.
patronymically from 2845; a Chittite, or descendant of Cheth:--Hittite, Hittities.
from 2865; fear:--terror.
a primitive root; properly, to cut off, i.e. (figuratively) to decree:--determine.
a primitive root; to swathe:--X at all, swaddle.
from 2853; a swathing cloth (figuratively):--swaddling band.
from 2853; enswathed; Chethlon, a place in Palestine:--Hethlon.
a primitive root; to close up; especially to seal:--make an end, mark, seal (up), stop.
(Aramaic) a root corresponding to 2856; to seal:--seal.
feminine active participle of 2856; a seal:--signet.
a primitive root; to give (a daughter) away in marriage; hence (generally) to contract affinity by marriage:--join in affinity, father in law, make marriages, mother in law, son in law.
from 2859; a relative by marriage (especially through the bride); figuratively, a circumcised child (as a species of religious espousal):--bridegroom, husband, son in law.
from 2859; a wedding:--espousal.
a primitive root; to clutch:--take away.
from 2862; properly, rapine; figuratively, robbery:--prey.
a primitive root; to force a passage, as by burglary; figuratively, with oars:--dig (through), row.

a primitive root; properly, to prostrate; hence, to break down, either (literally) by violence, or (figuratively) by confusion and fear:--abolish, affright, be (make) afraid, amaze, beat down, discourage, (cause to) dismay, go down, scare, terrify.
from 2865; dismay:--casting down.
the same as 2866; Chathath, an Israelite:--cathath.
(Aramaic) a primitive root; to rejoice:--be glad.
(Aramaic) from 2868; the same as 2896; good:--fine, good.
from 2895 and 410; pleasing (to) God; Tabeel, the name of a Syrian and of a Persian:--Tabeal, Tabeel.
passive participle of 2881; properly, dyed, i.e. a turban (probably as of colored stuff):--dyed attire.
from an unused root meaning to pile up; properly, accumulated; i.e. (by implication) a summit:--middle, midst.
a primitive root; to slaughter (animals or men):--kill, (make) slaughter, slay.
from 2873; properly, something slaughtered; hence, a beast (or meat, as butchered); abstr. butchery (or concretely, a place of slaughter):--X beast, slaughter, X slay, X sore.
the same as 2874; massacre; Tebach, the name of a Mesopotamian and of an Israelite:--Tebah.
from 2873; properly, a butcher; hence, a lifeguardsman (because he was acting as an executioner); also a cook (usually slaughtering the animal for food):--cook, guard.
(Aramaic) the same as 2876; a lifeguardsman:--guard.
feminine of 2874 and meaning the same:--flesh, slaughter.
feminine of 2876; a female cook:--cook.
from 2878; slaughter; Tibchath, a place in Syria:--Tibhath.
a primitive root; to dip, to immerse:--dip, plunge.
from 2881 and 3050; Jah has dipped; Tebaljah, an Israelite:--Tebaliah.
a primitive root; to sink:--drown, fasten, settle, sink.
plural of 2885; rings; Tabbaoth, one of the Nethinim:--Tabaoth.
from 2883; properly, a seal (as sunk into the wax), i.e. signet (for sealing); hence (generally) a ring of any kind:--ring.
from 2895 and 7417; pleasing (to) Rimmon; Tabrimmon, a Syrian:--Tabrimmon.
probably of foreign derivation; Tebeth, the tenth Heb. month:--Tebeth.
of uncertain derivation; Tabbath, a place East of the Jordan:--Tabbath.
or tahor {taw-hore'}; from 2891; pure (in a physical, chemical, ceremonial or moral sense):--clean, fair, pure(-ness).
from 2891; purity:--pureness.

a primitive root; properly, to be bright; i.e. (by implication) to be pure (physical sound, clear, unadulterated; Levitically, uncontaminated; morally, innocent or holy):--be (make, make self, pronounce) clean, cleanse (self), purge, purify(-ier, self).
from 2891; literally brightness; ceremonially purification:--clearness, glory, purifying.
feminine of 2892; ceremonial purification; moral purity:--X is cleansed, cleansing, purification(-fying).
a primitive root; to sweep away:--sweep.
a primitive root, to be (transitively, do or make) good (or well) in the widest sense:--be (do) better, cheer, be (do, seem) good, (make) goodly, X please, (be, do, go, play) well.

from 2895; good (as an adjective) in the widest sense; used likewise as a noun, both in the masculine and the feminine, the singular and the plural (good, a good or good thing, a good man or woman; the good, goods or good things, good men or women), also as an adverb (well):--beautiful, best, better, bountiful, cheerful, at ease, X fair (word), (be in) favour, fine, glad, good (deed, -lier, -liest, -ly, -ness, -s), graciously, joyful, kindly, kindness, liketh (best), loving, merry, X most, pleasant, + pleaseth, pleasure, precious, prosperity, ready, sweet, wealth, welfare, (be) well ((-favoured)).
the same as 2896; good; Tob, a region apparently East of the Jordan:--Tob.
from 2895; good (as a noun), in the widest sense, especially goodness (superlative concretely, the best), beauty, gladness, welfare:--fair, gladness, good(-ness, thing, -s), joy, go well with.
from 2896 and 138; pleasing (to) Adonijah; Tob-Adonijah, an Israelite:--Tob-adonijah.
or Towbiyahuw {to-bee-yaw'-hoo}; from 2896 and 3050; goodness of Jehovah; Tobijah, the name of three Israelites and of one Samaritan:--Tobiah, Tobijah.
a primitive root; to spin:--spin.
a primitive root; to smear, especially with lime:--daub, overlay, plaister, smut.
from an unusued root meaning to go around or bind; a fillet for the forehead:--frontlet.
a primitive root; to pitch over or reel; hence (transitively) to cast down or out:--carry away, (utterly) cast (down, forth, out), send out.
from an unused root meaning to range in a regular manner; a row; hence, a wall:--row.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6697; a rock or hill:--mountain.
a primitive root; to pounce as a bird of prey:--haste.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to 2901; hunger (as twisting):--fasting.
a primitive root; to stretch a bow, as an archer:--(bow-)shot.
from 2909 (or 2902) in the sense of overlaying; (in the plural only) the kidneys (as being covered); hence (figuratively) the inmost thought:--inward parts.
from 2912; a hand mill; hence, a millstone:--to grind.
a primitive root; to grind meal; hence, to be a concubine (that being their employment):--grind(-er).
from 2912; a hand mill; hence (figuratively) chewing:--grinding.
from an unused root meaning to burn; a boil or ulcer (from the inflammation), especially a tumor in the anus or pudenda (the piles):--emerod.
from (the equiv. of) 2902; mortar or plaster:--daubing.
from an unused root meaning apparently to be sticky (rath. perb. a demon. from 2894, through the idea of dirt to be swept away); mud or clay; figuratively, calamity:--clay, dirt, mire.
(Aramaic) perhaps, by interchange, for a word corresponding to 2916; clay:--miry.
feminine of (an equivalent to) 2905; a wall; hence, a fortress or a hamlet:--(goodly) castle, habitation, palace, row.
from 2926; dew (as covering vegetation):--dew.
(Aramaic) the same as 2919:--dew.
a primitive root; properly, to cover with pieces; i.e. (by implication) to spot or variegate (as tapestry):--clouted, with divers colours, spotted.
apparently from 2921 in the (orig.) sense of covering (for protection); a lamb (compare 2924):--lamb.
from the plural of 2922; lambs; Telaim, a place in Palestine:--Telaim.
by variation for 2922; a lamb:--lamb.
from 2904; overthrow or rejection:--captivity.
a primitive root; properly, to strew over, i.e. (by implication) to cover in or plate (with beams):--cover.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 2926; to cover with shade:--have a shadow.
from an unused root meaning to break up or treat violently; oppression; Telem, the name of a place in Idumaea, also of a temple doorkeeper:--Telem.
from the same as 2728; oppressive; Talmon, a temple doorkeeper:--Talmon.
a primitive root; to be foul, especially in a ceremial or moral sense (contaminated):--defile (self), pollute (self), be (make, make self, pronounce) unclean, X utterly.
from 2930; foul in a relig. sense:--defiled, + infamous, polluted(-tion), unclean.
from 2930; religious impurity:--filthiness, unclean(-ness).
a collateral form of 2930; to be impure in a religious sense:--be defiled, be reputed vile.
a primitive root; to hide (by covering over):--hide, lay privily, in secret.
from an unused root probably meaning to weave; a basket (of interlaced osiers):--basket.
a primitive root; to soil:--defile.
a primitive root; to wander; ,causatively to lead astray:--seduce.
a primitive root; to taste; figuratively, to perceive:--X but, perceive, taste.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 2938; to taste; causatively to feed:--make to eat, feed.
