from 7378 and 1168; Baal will contend; Jerubbaal, a symbol. name of Gideon:--Jerubbaal.
from 7378 and 5971; (the) people will contend; Jarobam, the name of two Israelite kings:--Jeroboam.
from 7378 and 1322; shame (i.e. the idol) will contend; Jerubbesheth, a symbol. name for Gideon: -Jerubbesheth.

a primitive root; to descend (literally, to go downwards; or conventionally to a lower region, as the shore, a boundary, the enemy, etc.; or figuratively, to fall); causatively, to bring down (in all the above applications); -X abundantly, bring down, carry down, cast down, (cause to) come(-ing) down, fall (down), get down, go(-ing) down(-ward), hang down, X indeed, let down, light (down), put down (off), (cause to, let) run down, sink, subdue, take down.
from 3381; a descent; Jered, the name of an antediluvian, and of an Israelite:--Jared.
from 3381; a descender; Jarden, the principal river of Palestine:--Jordan.

or (2 Chr. 26:15) yara; {yaw-raw'}; a primitive root; properly, to flow as water (i.e. to rain); transitively, to lay or throw (especially an arrow, i.e. to shoot); figuratively, to point out (as if by aiming the finger), to teach:--(+) archer, cast, direct, inform, instruct, lay, shew, shoot, teach(-er,-ing), through.
from 3384 and 410; founded of God; Jeruel, a place in Palestine:--Jeruel.
perhaps denominative from 3394; (born at the) new moon; Jaroach, an Israelite:--Jaroah.
from 3417; green, i.e. an herb:--green thing.
or Yaruwshah {yer-oo-shaw'} feminine passive participle of 3423; possessed; Jerusha or Jerushah, as Israelitess:--Jerusha, Jerushah.

rarely Yruwshalayim {yer-oo- shaw-lah'-yim}; a dual (in allusion to its two main hills (the true pointing, at least of the former reading, seems to be that of 3390)); probably from (the passive participle of) 3384 and 7999; founded peaceful; Jerushalaim or Jerushalem, the capital city of Palestine:--Jerusalem.
(Chald)
from a unused root of uncertain signification; a lunation, i.e. month:--month, moon.
the same as 3391; Jerach, an Arabian patriarch:--Jerah.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 3391; a month:--month.
from the same as 3391; the moon:--moon. Yrechow. See 3405.
from 7355; compassionate; Jerocham, the name of seven or eight Israelites:--Jeroham.
from 7355 and 410; God will compassionate; Jerachmeel, the name of three Israelites:--Jerahmeel.
patronymically from 3396; a Jerachmeelite or descendant of Jerachmeel:--Jerahmeelites.
probably of Egyptian origin; Jarcha, an Egyptian:--Jarha.
a primitive root; to precipitate or hurl (rush) headlong; (intransitively) to be rash:--be perverse, turn over.
from 3384 and 410; thrown of God; Jeriel, an Israelite:--Jeriel. Compare 3385.
from 7378; literally, he will contend; properly, adjective, contentious; used as noun, an adversary:--that content(-eth), that strive.
the same as 3401; Jarib, the name of three Israelites:--Jarib.
from 3401; contentious; Jeribai, an Israelite:--Jeribai.
or Yriyahuw {yer-ee-yaw'-hoo}; from 3384 and 3050; Jah will throw; Jerijah, an Israelite:--Jeriah, Jerijah.
or Yrechow {yer-ay-kho'}; or variation (1 Kings 16:34) Yriychoh {yer-ee-kho'}; perhaps from 3394; its month; or else from 7306; fragrant; Jericho or Jerecho, a place in Palestine:--Jericho.

or Yreymowth {yer-ay-mohth'}; or Yremowth {yer-ay-mohth'}; feminine plural from 7311; elevations; Jerimoth or Jeremoth, the name of twelve Israelites:--Jermoth, Jerimoth, and Ramoth (from the margin).
from 3415; a hanging (as tremulous):--curtain.
plural of 3407; curtains; Jerioth, an Israelitess:--Jerioth.
from an unused root meaning to be soft; the thigh (from its fleshy softness); by euphem. the generative parts; figuratively, a shank, flank, side:--X body, loins, shaft, side, thigh.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 3411; a thigh:--thigh.
feminine of 3409; properly, the flank; but used only figuratively, the rear or recess:--border, coast, part, quarter, side.
from 7311; elevation; Jarmuth, the name of two places in Palestine:--Jarmuth.
from 7311; elevated; Jeremai, an Israelite: -Jeremai.
or Yirmyahuw {yir-meh-yaw'-hoo}; from 7311 and 3050; Jah will rise; Jirmejah, the name of eight or nine Israelites:--Jeremiah.
a primitive root; properly, to be broken up (with any violent action) i.e. (figuratively) to fear:--be grevious (only Isa. 15:4; the rest belong to 7489).
from 7495 and 410; God will heal; Jirpeel, a place in Palestine:--Irpeel.
a primitive root; to spit:--X but, spit.
from 3417 (in the sense of vacuity of color); properly, pallor, i.e. hence, the yellowish green of young and sickly vegetation; concretely, verdure, i.e. grass or vegetation:--grass, green (thing).
from the same as 3418; properly, green; concretely, a vegetable:--green, herbs.
from 3418; paleness, whether of persons (from fright), or of plants (from drought):--greenish, yellow.
from 7324 and 5971; people will be poured forth; Jorkeam, a place in Palestine:--Jorkeam.
from the same as 3418; yellowishness: -greenish, yellow.

or yaresh {yaw-raysh'}; a primitive root; to occupy (by driving out previous tenants, and possessing in their place); by implication, to seize, to rob, to inherit; also to expel, to impoverish, to ruin:--cast out, consume, destroy, disinherit, dispossess, drive(-ing) out, enjoy, expel, X without fail, (give to, leave for) inherit(-ance, -or) + magistrate, be (make) poor, come to poverty, (give to, make to) possess, get (have) in (take) possession, seize upon, succeed, X utterly.
from 3423; occupancy:--possession.
from 3423; something occupied; a conquest; also a patrimony:--heritage, inheritance, possession.

perhaps from an unused root meaning to stand out, or exist; entity; used adverbially or as a copula for the substantive verb (1961); there is or are (or any other form of the verb to be, as may suit the connection):--(there) are, (he, it, shall, there, there may, there shall, there should) be, thou do, had, hast, (which) hath, (I, shalt, that) have, (he, it, there) is, substance, it (there) was, (there) were, ye will, thou wilt, wouldest.

a primitive root; properly, to sit down (specifically as judge. in ambush, in quiet); by implication, to dwell, to remain; causatively, to settle, to marry:--(make to) abide(-ing), continue, (cause to, make to) dwell(-ing), ease self, endure, establish, X fail, habitation, haunt, (make to) inhabit(-ant), make to keep (house), lurking, X marry(-ing), (bring again to) place, remain, return, seat, set(- tle), (down-)sit(-down, still, -ting down, -ting (place) -uate), take, tarry.
from 3427 and 1; seat of (his) father; Jeshebab, an Israelite:--Jeshebeab.
from the active participle of 3427 and 7674, with a preposition and the article interposed; sitting in the seat; Josheb-bash-Shebeth, an Israelite:--that sat in the seat.
from 3427 and 5011, with a pronominal suffix and a preposition interposed; his dwelling (is) in Nob; Jishbo-be-Nob, a Philistine:--Ishbi-benob (from the margin).
from 7623; he will praise; Jishbach, an Israelite:--Ishbah.
patronymically from 3437; a Jashubite, or descendant of Jashub:--Jashubites.

from 7725 and 3899; returner of bread; Jashubi-Lechem, an Israelite:--Jashubi-lehem. (Prob. the text should be pointed Yoshbev Lechem {yo-sheh-bay' leh'-khem}, and rendered "(they were) inhabitants of Lechem," i.e. of Bethlehem (by contraction). Compare 3902).
from 7725 and 5971; people will return; Jashobam, the name of two or three Israelites:--Jashobeam.
from an unused root corresponding to 7662; he will leave; Jishbak, a son of Abraham:--Ishbak.
from 3427 and 7186; a hard seat; Joshbekashah, an Israelite:--Joshbekashah.
or Yashiyb {yaw-sheeb'}; from 7725; he will return; Jashub, the name of two Israelites:--Jashub.
from 7737; he will level; Jishvah, an Israelite: -Ishvah, Isvah.
from the same as 3445 and 3050; Jah will empty; Jeshochajah, an Israelite:--Jeshoaiah.
from 7737; level; Jishvi, the name of two Israelites:--Ishuai, Ishvi, Isui, Jesui.
patronymically from 3440; a Jishvite (collectively) or descendants of Jishvi:--Jesuites.
for 3091; he will save; Jeshua, the name of ten Israelites, also of a place in Palestine:--Jeshua.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 3442:--Jeshua.
feminine passive participle of 3467; something saved, i.e. (abstractly) deliverance; hence, aid, victory, prosperity:--deliverance, health, help(-ing), salvation, save, saving (health), welfare.
from an unused root meaning to gape (as the empty stomach); hunger:--casting down.
from 7831; he will laugh; Jischak, the heir of Abraham:--Isaac. Compare 3327.
a primitive root; to extend:--hold out.
by Aramaic Iyshay {ee-shah'-ee}; from the same as 3426; extant; Jishai, David's father:--Jesse.
or Yishshiyahuw {yish-shee-yaw'-hoo}; from 5383 and 3050; Jah will lend; Jishshijah, the name of five Israelites:--Ishiah, Isshiah, Ishijah, Jesiah.
from 7760 and 410; God will place; Jesimael, an Israelite:--Jesimael.
from 3456; desolation:--let death seize (from the margin).
from 3456; a desolation:--desert, Jeshimon, solitary, wilderness.
from 3486; an old man:--(very) aged (man), ancient, very old.
from 3453; aged; Jeshishai, an Israelite:--Jeshishai.
a prim root; to place; intransitively, to be placed:--be put (set).
a primitive root; to lie waste:--be desolate.
from 3456; desolate; Jishma, an Israelite: -Ishma.
from 8085 and 410; God will hear; Jishmael, the name of Abraham's oldest son, and of five Israelites:--Ishmael.
patronymically from 3458; a Jishmaelite or descendant of Jishmael:--Ishmaelite.
or Yishmacyahuw {yish-mah-yaw'-hoo}; from 8085 and 3050; Jah will hear; Jishmajah, the name of two Israelites:--Ishmaiah.
from 8104; preservative; Jishmerai, an Israelite:--Ishmerai.
a primitive root; properly, to be slack or languid, i.e. (by implication) sleep (figuratively, to die); also to grow old, stale or inveterate: -old (store), remain long, (make to) sleep.
from 3462; sleepy:--asleep, (one out of) sleep(-eth, -ing), slept.
the same as 3463; Jashen, an Israelite:--Jashen.
from 3462; old:--old.
feminine of 3465; Jeshanah, a place in Palestine:--Jeshanah.

a primitive root; properly, to be open, wide or free, i.e. (by implication) to be safe; causatively, to free or succor:--X at all, avenging, defend, deliver(-er), help, preserve, rescue, be safe, bring (having) salvation, save(-iour), get victory.
or yeshai {yay'-shah}; from 3467; liberty, deliverance, prosperity:--safety, salvation, saving.
from 3467; saving; Jishi, the name of four Israelites:--Ishi.
or Yshayahuw {yesh-ah-yaw'-hoo}; from 3467 and 3050; Jah has saved; Jeshajah, the name of seven Israelites:--Isaiah, Jesaiah, Jeshaiah.
from an unused root meaning to polish; a gem supposed to be jasper (from the resemblance in name):--jasper.
perhaps from 8192; he will scratch; Jishpah, an Israelite:--Ispah.
probably from the same as 8227; he will hide; Jishpan, an Israelite:--Ishpan.

a primitive root; to be straight or even; figuratively, to be (causatively, to make) right, pleasant, prosperous:--direct, fit, seem good (meet), + please (will), be (esteem, go) right (on), bring (look, make, take the) straight (way), be upright(-ly).
from 3474; the right; Jesher, an Israelite: -Jesher.
from 3474; the right:--equity, meet, right, upright(-ness).
from 3474; straight (literally or figuratively):--convenient, equity, Jasher, just, meet(-est), + pleased well right(-eous), straight, (most) upright(-ly, -ness).
from 8280 and 410; he will rule as God; Jisrael, a symbolical name of Jacob; also (typically) of his posterity: --Israel.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 3478:--Israel.
by variation from 3477 and 410 with directive enclitic; right towards God; Jesarelah, an Israelite:--Jesharelah.
patronymically from 3478; a Jisreelite or descendant of Jisrael:--of Israel, Israelite.
feminine of 3481; a Jisreelitess or female descendant of Jisrael:--Israelitish.
feminine or 3477; rectitude:--uprightness.
from 3474; upright; Jeshurun, a symbol. name for Israel:--Jeshurun.
(strictly yis-saws-kawr'); from 5375 and 7939; he will bring a reward; Jissaskar, a son of Jacob:--Issachar.
from an unused root meaning to blanch; gray-haired, i.e. an aged man:--stoop for age.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 853; a sign of the object of a verb: + whom.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 3427; to sit or dwell: -dwell, (be) set, sit.
from an unused root meaning to pin through or fast; a peg:--nail, paddle, pin, stake.
from an unused root meaning to be lonely; a bereaved person:--fatherless (child), orphan.
passive participle of 3498; properly, what is left, i.e. (by implication) a gleaning:--range.
from 3498; redundant; Jattir, a place in Palestine:--Jattir.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 3492; preeminent; as an adverb, very:--exceeding(-ly), excellent.
probably from 8518; it will hang, i.e. be high; Jithlah, a place in Palestine:--Jethlah.
from the same as 3490; orphanage; Jithmah, an Israelite:--Ithmah.
from an unused root meaning to endure, and 410; continued of God; Jathniel, an Israelite:--Jathniel.
from the same as 8577; extensive; Jithnan, a place in Palestine:--Ithnan.

a primitive root; to jut over or exceed; by implication, to excel; (intransitively) to remain or be left; causatively, to leave, cause to abound, preserve:--excel, leave (a remnant), left behind, too much, make plenteous, preserve, (be, let) remain(-der, -ing, - nant), reserve, residue, rest.

from 3498; properly, an overhanging, i.e. (by implication) an excess, superiority, remainder; also a small rope (as hanging free):--+ abundant, cord, exceeding, excellancy(-ent), what they leave, that hath left, plentifully, remnant, residue, rest, string, with.
the same as 3499; Jether, the name of five or six Israelites and of one Midianite:--Jether, Jethro. Compare 3503.
by variation for 3502; Jithra, an Israelite (or Ishmaelite):--Ithra.
feminine of 3499; properly, excellence, i.e. (by implication) wealth:--abundance, riches.
from 3499 with pron. suffix; his excellence; Jethro, Moses' father-in-law:--Jethro. Compare 3500.
from 3498; preeminence, gain:--better, excellency(-leth), profit(-able).
patronymically from 3500; a Jithrite or descendant of Jether:--Ithrite.
from 3498; excellent; Jithran, the name of an Edomite and of an Israelite:--Ithran.
from 3499 and 5971; excellence of people; Jithream, a son of David:--Ithream.
feminine active participle of 3498; the lobe or flap of the liver (as if redundant or outhanging):--caul.
of uncertain derivation; Jetheth, an Edomite: -Jetheth.
a primitive root; properly, to feel pain; by implication, to grieve; figuratively, to spoil:--grieving, mar, have pain, make sad (sore), (be) sorrowful.
from 3510; suffering (physical or mental), adversity:--grief, pain, sorrow.
a primitive root; to despond: causatively, to deject:--broken, be grieved, make sad.

or kabed {kaw-bade'}; a primitive root; to be heavy, i.e. in a bad sense (burdensome, severe, dull) or in a good sense (numerous, rich, honorable; causatively, to make weighty (in the same two senses):--abounding with, more grievously afflict, boast, be chargeable, X be dim, glorify, be (make) glorious (things), glory, (very) great, be grievous, harden, be (make) heavy, be heavier, lay heavily, (bring to, come to, do, get, be had in) honour (self), (be) honourable (man), lade, X more be laid, make self many, nobles, prevail, promote (to honour), be rich, be (go) sore, stop.
from 3513; weight, multitude, vehemence: -grievousness, heavy, great number.
from 3513; heavy; figuratively in a good sense (numerous) or in a bad sense (severe, difficult, stupid):--(so) great, grievous, hard(-ened), (too) heavy(-ier), laden, much, slow, sore, thick.
the same as 3515; the liver (as the heaviest of the viscera):--liver.
feminine of 3515; difficulty:--X heavily.
a primitive root; to expire or (causatively) to extinguish (fire, light, anger):--go (put) out, quench.
rarely kabod {kaw-bode'}; from 3513; properly, weight, but only figuratively in a good sense, splendor or copiousness:--glorious(-ly), glory, honour(-able).
irreg. feminine passive participle of 3513; weightiness, i.e. magnificence, wealth:--carriage, all glorious, stately.
from the same as 3525 in the sense of limitation; sterile; Cabul, the name of two places in Palestine:--Cabul.
from an unused root meaning to heap up; hilly; Cabon, a place in Palestine:--Cabbon.
from 3527 in the original sense of plaiting; a matrass (of intertwined materials):--pillow.
from 3527; vast, whether in extent (figuratively, of power, mighty; of time, aged), or in number, many:--+ feeble, mighty, most, much, strong, valiant.
from an unused root meaning to twine or braid together; a fetter:--fetter.
a primitive root; to trample; hence, to wash (properly, by stamping with the feet), whether literal (including the fulling process) or figurative:--fuller, wash(-ing).
a primitive root; properly, to plait together, i.e. (figuratively) to augment (especially in number or quantity, to accumulate):--in abundance, multiply.
from 3527; properly, extent of time, i.e. a great while; hence, long ago, formerly, hitherto:--already, (seeing that which), now.
the same as 3528; length; Kebar, a river of Mesopotamia:--Chebar. Compare 2249.
feminine of 3528; properly, length, i.e. a measure (of uncertain dimension):--X little.
from 3527 in its original sense; a sieve (as netted):--sieve.
from an unused root meaning to dominate; a ram (just old enough to butt):--lamb, sheep.
a primitive root; to tread down; hence, negatively, to disregard; positively, to conquer, subjugate, violate:--bring into bondage, force, keep under, subdue, bring into subjection.
from 3533; a footstool (as trodden upon): -footstool.
or kabsah {kab-saw'}; feminine of 3532; a ewe:--(ewe) lamb.
from 3533; a smelting furnace (as reducing metals):--furnace.
from an unused root meaning to deepen; properly, a pail; but generally of earthenware; a jar for domestic purposes:--barrel, pitcher.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to 3576; false: -lying.
from the same as 3537 in the sense of striking fire from a metal forged; a sparkling gem, probably the ruby:--agate.
of foreign origin; Kedorlaomer, an early Persian king:--Chedorlaomer.

from the prefix k and 1931; properly, like this, i.e. by implication, (of manner) thus (or so); also (of place) here (or hither); or (of time) now:--also, here, + hitherto, like, on the other side, so (and much), such, on that manner, (on) this (manner, side, way, way and that way), + mean while, yonder.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 3541:--hitherto.
a primitive root; to be weak, i.e. (figuratively) to despond (causatively, rebuke), or (of light, the eye) to grow dull:-- darken, be dim, fail, faint, restrain, X utterly.
from 3543; feeble, obscure:--somewhat dark, darkish, wax dim, heaviness, smoking.
feminine of 3544; properly, a weakening; figuratively, alleviation, i.e. cure:--healing.
(Aramaic) a root corresponding to 3201 and 3557; to be able:--be able, could.

a primitive root, apparently meaning to mediate in religious services; but used only as denominative from 3548; to officiate as a priest; figuratively, to put on regalia:--deck, be (do the office of a, execute the, minister in the) priest('s office).
active participle of 3547; literally, one officiating, a priest; also (by courtesy) an acting priest (although a layman):--chief ruler, X own, priest, prince, principal officer.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 3548:--priest.
from 3547; priesthood:--priesthood, priest's office.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to 3854 in the sense of piercing; a window (as a perforation):--window.
of foreign derivation; Kub, a country near Egypt:--Chub.
from an unused root meaning to be high or rounded; a helmet (as arched):--helmet. Compare 6959.
a primitive root; properly, to prick or penetrate; hence, to blister (as smarting or eating into):--burn.
from 3554; a branding:--burning.
probably from the same as 3522 (in the sense of rolling) or 3554 (in the sense of blazing); a star (as round or as shining); figuratively, a prince:--star((-gazer)).

a primitive root; properly, to keep in; hence, to measure; figuratively, to maintain (in various senses):--(be able to, can) abide, bear, comprehend, contain, feed, forbearing, guide, hold(-ing in), nourish(-er), be present, make provision, receive, sustain, provide sustenance (victuals).
from an unused root meaning to store away; a jewel (probably gold beads):--tablet.

a primitive root; properly, to be erect (i.e. stand perpendicular); hence (causatively) to set up, in a great variety of applications, whether literal (establish, fix, prepare, apply), or figurative (appoint, render sure, proper or prosperous):--certain(-ty), confirm, direct, faithfulness, fashion, fasten, firm, be fitted, be fixed, frame, be meet, ordain, order, perfect, (make) preparation, prepare (self), provide, make provision, (be, make) ready, right, set (aright, fast, forth), be stable, (e-)stablish, stand, tarry, X very deed.
probably from 3559; established; Kun, a place in Syria:--Chun.
from 3559; something prepared, i.e. a sacrificial wafer:--cake.
from 3559 and 3050; Jah has sustained; Conanjah, the name of two Israelites:--Conaniah, Cononiah. Compare 3663.

from an unused root meaning to hold together; a cup (as a container), often figuratively, a lot (as if a potion); also some unclean bird, probably an owl (perhaps from the cup-like cavity of its eye):--cup, (small) owl. Compare 3599.
from an unused root meaning properly, to dig through; a pot or furnace (as if excavated):--furnace. Compare 3600.
from 3564 and 6227; furnace of smoke; Cor-Ashan, a place in Palestine:--Chor-ashan.
or (Ezra 1:1 (last time),2) Koresh {ko'-resh}; from the Persians; Koresh (or Cyrus), the Persian king:--Cyrus.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 3566:--Cyrus.
probably of foreign origin; Cush (or Ethiopia), the name of a son of Ham, and of his territory; also of an Israelite:--Chush, Cush, Ethiopia.
patronymically from 3568; a Cushite, or descendant of Cush:--Cushi, Cushite, Ethiopian(-s).
the same as 3569; Cushi, the name of two Israelites:--Cushi.
feminine of 3569; a Cushite woman: -Ethiopian.
perhaps from 3568; Cushan, a region of Arabia: -Cushan.
apparently from 3572 and the dual of 7564; Cushan of double wickedness; Cushan-Rishathajim, a Mesopotamian king:--Chushan-rishathayim.
from 3787; prosperity; in plural freedom: -X chain.
or (feminine) Kuwthah {koo-thaw'}; of foreign origin; Cuth or Cuthah, a province of Assyria:--Cuth.
a primitive root; to lie (i.e. deceive), literally or figuratively:--fail, (be found a, make a) liar, lie, lying, be in vain.
from 3576; falsehood; literally (untruth) or figuratively (idol):--deceitful, false, leasing, + liar, lie, lying.
from 3576; fallacious; Cozeba, a place in Palestine:--Choseba.
from 3576; false; Cozbi, a Midianitess:--Cozbi.
from 3576; falsified; Kezib, a place in Palestine:--Chezib.

or (Dan. 11:6) kowach {ko'-akh}; from an unused root meaning to be firm; vigor, literally (force, in a good or a bad sense) or figuratively (capacity, means, produce); also (from its hardiness) a large lizard: -ability, able, chameleon, force, fruits, might, power(-ful), strength, substance, wealth.
a primitive root; to secrete, by act or word; hence (intensively) to destroy:--conceal, cut down (off), desolate, hide.
a primitive root; to paint (with stibium): -paint.
a primitive root; to be untrue, in word (to lie, feign, disown) or deed (to disappoint, fail, cringe):--deceive, deny, dissemble, fail, deal falsely, be found liars, (be-)lie, lying, submit selves.
from 3584; literally, a failure of flesh, i.e. emaciation; figuratively, hypocrisy:--leanness, lies, lying.
from 3584; faithless:--lying.
from 3554; a brand or scar:--burning.

a primitive particle (the full form of the prepositional prefix) indicating causal relations of all kinds, antecedent or consequent; (by implication) very widely used as a relative conjunction or adverb (as below); often largely modified by other particles annexed:--and, + (forasmuch, inasmuch, where-)as, assured(-ly), + but, certainly, doubtless, + else, even, + except, for, how, (because, in, so, than) that, + nevertheless, now, rightly, seeing, since, surely, then, therefore, + (al- )though, + till, truly, + until, when, whether, while, whom, yea, yet.
from a primitive root meaning to strike: a crushing; figuratively, calamity:--destruction.
from the same as 3589 (compare 3539); properly, something struck off, i.e. a spark (as struck):--spark.
from the same as 3589; properly, something to strike with, i.e. a dart (perhaps smaller that 2595):--lance, shield, spear, target.
the same as 3591; Kidon, a place in Palestine: -Chidon.
of uncertain derivation; perhaps tumult:--battle.
from 3559; properly, a statue, i.e. idol; but used (by euphemism) for some heathen deity (perhaps corresponding to Priapus or Baal-peor):--Chiun.

or kiyor {kee-yore'}; from the same as 3564; properly, something round (as excavated or bored), i.e. a chafing-dish for coals or a caldron for cooking; hence (from similarity of form) a washbowl; also (for the same reason) a pulpit or platform:--hearth, laver, pan, scaffold.
or kelay {kay-lah'-ee}; from 3557 in the sense of withholding; niggardly:--churl.
from an unused root meaning to clap or strike with noise; a club or sledge-hammer:--hammer.
from the same as 3558; a cluster of stars, i.e. the Pleiades:--Pleiades, seven stars.
a form for 3563; a cup; also a bag for money or weights:--bag, cup, purse.
a form for 3564 (only in the dual); a cooking range (consisting of two parallel stones, across which the boiler is set): -ranges for pots.
from 3787; literally, a director, i.e. the spindle or shank of a distaff (6418), by which it is twirled:--spindle.
from 3541; just so, referring to the previous or following context:--after that (this) manner, this matter, (even) so, in such a case, thus.

from 3769; a circle, i.e. (by implication) a circumjacent tract or region, expec. the Ghor or valley of the Jordan; also a (round) loaf; also a talent (or large (round) coin):--loaf, morsel, piece, plain, talent.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 3603; a talent:--talent.

or (Jer. 33:8) kowl {kole}; from 3634; properly, the whole; hence, all, any or every (in the singular only, but often in a plural sense):--(in) all (manner, (ye)), altogether, any (manner), enough, every (one, place, thing), howsoever, as many as, (no-)thing, ought, whatsoever, (the) whole, whoso(-ever).
(Aramaic) corresponding to 3605:--all, any, + (forasmuch) as, + be-(for this) cause, every, + no (manner, -ne), + there (where)-fore, + though, what (where, who)-soever, (the) whole.
a primitive root; to restrict, by act (hold back or in) or word (prohibit):--finish, forbid, keep (back), refrain, restrain, retain, shut up, be stayed, withhold.
from 3607; a prison:--prison. Compare 3610, 3628.
apparently from 3607 and 1; restraint of (his) father; Kilab, an Israelite:--Chileab.
dual of 3608 in the original sense of separation; two heterogeneities:--divers seeds (-e kinds), mingled (seed).
from an unused root means. to yelp, or else to attack; a dog; hence (by euphemism) a male prostitute:--dog.
perhaps a form of 3611, or else from the same root in the sense of forcible; Caleb, the name of three Israelites:--Caleb.
from 3612 and 672; Caleb- Ephrathah, a place in Egypt (if the text is correct):--Caleb-ephrathah.
probably by erroneous transcription for Kalebiy {kaw-lay-bee'}; patronymically from 3612; a Calebite or descendant of Caleb:--of the house of Caleb.

a primitive root; to end, whether intransitive (to cease, be finished, perish) or transitived (to complete, prepare, consume):--accomplish, cease, consume (away), determine, destroy (utterly), be (when ... were) done, (be an) end (of), expire, (cause to) fail, faint, finish, fulfil, X fully, X have, leave (off), long, bring to pass, wholly reap, make clean riddance, spend, quite take away, waste.
from 3615; pining:--fail.
from 3615; a completion; adverb, completely; also destruction:--altogether, (be, utterly) consume(-d), consummation(-ption), was determined, (full, utter) end, riddance.
from 3634; a bride (as if perfect); hence, a son's wife:--bride, daughter-in-law, spouse.
from the same as 3611; a bird-trap (as furnished with a clap-stick or treadle to spring it); hence, a basket (as resembling a wicker cage):--basket, cage.
the same as 3619; Kelub, the name of two Israelites:--Chelub.
a form of 3612; Kelubai, an Israelite: -Chelubai.
from 3615; completed; Keluhai, an Israelite:--Chelluh.
denominative passive participle from 3618; bridehood (only in the plural):--espousal.
from an unused root meaning to be complete; maturity:--full (old) age.
the same as 3624; Kelach, a place in Assyria: -Calah.
from 3605 and 2374; every seer; Col- Chozeh, an Israelite:--Col-hozeh.

from 3615; something prepared, i.e. any apparatus (as an implement, utensil, dress, vessel or weapon):--armour ((-bearer)), artillery, bag, carriage, + furnish, furniture, instrument, jewel, that is made of, X one from another, that which pertaineth, pot, + psaltery, sack, stuff, thing, tool, vessel, ware, weapon, + whatsoever.
or kluw1 {kel-oo'}; from 3607 (compare 3608); a prison:--prison.
feminine of 3627 (only in the plural); a kidney (as an essential organ); figuratively, the mind (as the interior self):--kidneys, reins.
a form of 3631; Kiljon, an Israelite:--Chilion.
from 3615; pining, destruction: -consumption, failing.
from 3634; complete; as noun, the whole (specifically, a sacrifice entirely consumed); as adverb, fully:--all, every whit, flame, perfect(-ion), utterly, whole burnt offering (sacrifice), wholly.
from 3557; sustenance; Calcol, an Israelite:--Calcol, Chalcol.
a primitive root; to complete:--(make) perfect.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 3634; to complete:--finish, make (set) up.
from 3634; complete; Kelal, an Israelite:--Chelal.
a primitive root; properly, to wound; but only figuratively, to taunt or insult:--be (make) ashamed, blush, be confounded, be put to confusion, hurt, reproach, (do, put to) shame.
of foreign derivation; Kilmad, a place apparently in the Assyrian empire:--Chilmad.
from 3637; disgrace:--confusion, dishonour, reproach, shame.
from 3639; disgrace:--shame.
or Kalneh {kal-nay'}; also Kalnow {kal-no'}; of foreign derivation; Calneh or Calno, a place in the Assyrian empire:-- Calneh, Calno. Compare 3656.
a primitive root; to pine after:--long.
from 3642; pining; Kimham, an Israelite:--Chimham.
or kamow {kaw-mo'}; a form of the prefix "k-", but used separately (compare 3651); as, thus, so:--according to, (such) as (it were, well as), in comparison of, like (as, to, unto), thus, when, worth.
or (Jer. 48:7) Kmiysh {kem-eesh'}; from an unused root meaning to subdue; the powerful; Kemosh, the god of the Moabites:--Chemosh.
from an unused root meaning to store up or preserve; "cummin" (from its use as a condiment):--cummin.
a primitive root; to store away, i.e. (figuratively) in the memory:--lay up in store.
a primitive root; properly, to intertwine or contract, i.e. (by implication) to shrivel (as with heat); figuratively, to be deeply affected with passion (love or pity):--be black, be kindled, yearn.
from 3648; properly, an ascetic (as if shrunk with self-maceration), i.e. an idolatrous priest (only in plural):--Chemarims (idolatrous) priests.
redupl. from 3648; obscuration (as if from shrinkage of light, i.e. an eclipse (only in plural):--blackness.

from 3559; properly, set upright; hence (figuratively as adjective) just; but usually (as adverb or conjunction) rightly or so (in various applications to manner, time and relation; often with other particles):--+ after that (this, -ward, -wards), as ... as, + (for-)asmuch as yet, + be (for which) cause, + following, howbeit, in (the) like (manner, -wise), X the more, right, (even) so, state, straightway, such (thing), surely, + there (where)-fore, this, thus, true, well, X you.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 3651; so:--thus.
the same as 3651, used as a noun; a stand, i.e. pedestal or station:--base, estate, foot, office, place, well.
from 3661 in the sense of fastening; a gnat (from infixing its sting; used only in plural (and irreg. in Exod. 8:17,18; Heb. 13:14)):--lice, X manner.
a primitive root; to address by an additional name; hence, to eulogize:--give flattering titles, surname (himself).
for 3641; Canneh, a place in Assyria:--Canneh.
from 3661; a plant (as set):--X vineyard.
from a unused root meaning to twang; a harp: -harp.
for 3204; Conjah, an Israelite king:--Coniah.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 3644; so or thus:--so, (in) this manner (sort), thus.
a primitive root; to set out, i.e. plant:--X vineyard.
from 3661; planted; Kenani, an Israelite: -Chenani.
or Knanyahuw {ken-an-yaw'-hoo}; from 3661 and 3050; Jah has planted; Kenanjah, an Israelite:--Chenaniah.
a primitive root; to collect; hence, to enfold: -gather (together), heap up, wrap self.
a primitive root; properly, to bend the knee; hence, to humiliate, vanquish:--bring down (low), into subjection, under, humble (self), subdue.
from 3665 in the sense of folding (compare 3664); a package:--wares.
from 3665; humiliated; Kenaan, a son a Ham; also the country inhabited by him:--Canaan, merchant, traffick.
feminine of 3667; Kenaanah, the name of two Israelites:--Chenaanah.

patrial from 3667; a Kenaanite or inhabitant of Kenaan; by implication, a pedlar (the Canaanites standing for their neighbors the Ishmaelites, who conducted mercantile caravans):--Canaanite, merchant, trafficker.
a primitive root; properly, to project laterally, i.e. probably (reflexive) to withdraw:--be removed.

from 3670; an edge or extremity; specifically (of a bird or army) a wing, (of a garment or bed-clothing) a flap, (of the earth) a quarter, (of a building) a pinnacle:--+ bird, border, corner, end, feather(-ed), X flying, + (one an-)other, overspreading, X quarters, skirt, X sort, uttermost part, wing((-ed)).
or Kinnereth {kin-neh'-reth}; respectively plural and singular feminine from the same as 3658; perhaps harp-shaped; Kinneroth or Kinnereth, a place in Palestine:--Chinnereth, Chinneroth, Cinneroth.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 3664; to assemble:--gather together.
from 3655; a colleague (as having the same title):--companion.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 3674:--companion.
apparently a contraction for 3678, but probably by erroneous transcription for 5251:--sworn.
or keceh {keh'-seh}; apparently from 3680; properly, fulness or the full moon, i.e. its festival:--(time) appointed.
or kicceh {kis-say'}; from 3680; properly, covered, i.e. a throne (as canopied):--seat, stool, throne.
for 3778:--Chaldean.

a primitive root; properly, to plump, i.e. fill up hollows; by implication, to cover (for clothing or secrecy):--clad self, close, clothe, conceal, cover (self), (flee to) hide, overwhelm. Compare 3780.
passive participle of 3680; properly, covered, i.e. (as noun) a covering:--covering.
from 3680; a cover (garment); figuratively, a veiling:--covering, raiment, vesture.
a primitive root; to cut off:--cut down (up).
from 3688; properly, fat, i.e. (figuratively) stupid or silly:--fool(-ish).
the same as 3684; any notable constellation; specifically Orion (as if a burly one):--constellation, Orion.
the same as 3684; Kesil, a place in Palestine: -Chesil.
from 3684; silliness:--foolish.
a primitive root; properly, to be fat, i.e. (figuratively) silly:--be foolish.

from 3688; properly, fatness, i.e. by implication (literally) the loin (as the seat of the leaf fat) or (generally) the viscera; also (figuratively) silliness or (in a good sense) trust:--confidence, flank, folly, hope, loin.
feminine of 3689; in a good sense, trust; in a bad one, silliness:--confidence, folly.
probably of foreign origin; Kisleu, the 9th Heb. month:--Chisleu.
from 3688; hopeful; Kislon, an Israelite:--Chislon.
from 3688; fertile; Kesalon, a place in Palestine:--Chesalon.
feminine plural of passive participle of 3688; fattened; Kesulloth, a place in Palestine:--Chesulloth.
a plural probably of foreign derivation; Casluchim, a people cognate to the Egyptians:--Casluhim.
from the feminine plural of 3689 and 8396; flanks of Tabor; Kisloth-Tabor, a place in Palestine:--Chisloth- tabor.
a primitive root; to shear:--X only, poll. Compare 3765.
from 3697; spelt (from its bristliness as if just shorn):--fitches, rie.
a primitive root; to estimate:--make count.
a primitive root; properly, to become pale, i.e. (by implication) to pine after; also to fear:--(have) desire, be greedy, long, sore.
from 3700; silver (from its pale color); by implication, money:--money, price, silver(-ling).
(Aramaic) corresponding to 3701:--money, silver.
perhaps from 3701; silvery; Casiphja, a place in Bab.:--Casiphia.
from 3680; a cushion or pillow (as covering a seat or bed):--pillow.
(Aramaic) probably from 3652; now:--now.
(Aramaic) or kaeth (Aramaic) {keh-eth'}; feminine of 3705; thus (only in the formula "and so forth"):--at such a time.
a primitive root; to trouble; by implication, to grieve, rage, be indignant:--be angry, be grieved, take indignation, provoke (to anger, unto wrath), have sorrow, vex, be wroth.
or (in Job) kaoas {kah'-as}; from 3707; vexation: -anger, angry, grief, indignation, provocation, provoking, X sore, sorrow, spite, wrath.

from 3721; the hollow hand or palm (so of the paw of an animal, of the sole, and even of the bowl of a dish or sling, the handle of a bolt, the leaves of a palm-tree); figuratively, power:--branch, + foot, hand((-ful), -dle, (-led)), hollow, middle, palm, paw, power, sole, spoon.
from 3721; a hollow rock:--rock.
a primitive root; properly, to bend, i.e. (figuratively) to tame or subdue:--pacify.
feminine of 3709; a leaf of a palm-tree:--branch.
from 3722; properly, a cover, i.e. (by implication) a tankard (or covered goblet); also white frost (as covering the ground):--bason, hoar(-y) frost.
from an unused root meaning to connect; a girder:--beam.
from 3722; a village (as covered in by walls); also a young lion (perhaps as covered with a mane):--(young) lion, village. Compare 3723.
feminine of 3715; the village (always with the art.); Kephirah, a place in Palestine:--Chephirah.
a primitive root; to fold together; figuratively, to repeat:--double.
from 3717; a duplicate:--double.
a primitive root; to bend:--bend.
from 3719; hunger (as making to stoop with emptiness and pain):--famine.
a primitive root; to curve:--bow down (self).

a primitive root; to cover (specifically with bitumen); figuratively, to expiate or condone, to placate or cancel:-- appease, make (an atonement, cleanse, disannul, forgive, be merciful, pacify, pardon, purge (away), put off, (make) reconcile(-liation).
from 3722; a village (as protected by walls): -village. Compare 3715.

from 3722; properly, a cover, i.e. (literally) a village (as covered in); (specifically) bitumen (as used for coating), and the henna plant (as used for dyeing); figuratively, a redemption-price:--bribe, camphire, pitch, ransom, satisfaction, sum of money, village.
from 3722; expiation (only in plural): -atonement.
from 3723 and 5984, with the article interposed; village of the Ammonite; Kefar-ha-Ammoni, a place in Palestine:--Chefar-haamonai.
from 3722; a lid (used only of the cover of the sacred Ark):--mercy seat.
a primitive root; to tread down; figuratively, to humiliate:--cover.
(Aramaic) a root of uncertain correspondence; to fetter:--bind.

or (Am. 9:1) kaphtowr {kaf-tore'}; probably from an unused root meaning to encircle; a chaplet; but used only in an architectonic sense, i.e. the capital of a column, or a wreath-like button or disk on the candelabrum: knop, (upper) lintel.
or (Am. 9:7) Kaphtowr {kaf-tore'}; apparently the same as 3730; Caphtor (i.e. a wreath-shaped island), the original seat of the Philistines:--Caphtor.
patrial from 3731; a Caphtorite (collectively) or native of Caphtor:--Caphthorim, Caphtorim(-s).

from 3769 in the sense of plumpness; a ram (as full-grown and fat), including a battering-ram (as butting); hence, a meadow (as for sheep); also a pad or camel's saddle (as puffed out):--captain, furniture, lamb, (large) pasture, ram. See also 1033, 3746.
from the same as 3564; properly, a deep round vessel, i.e. (specifically) a cor or measure for things dry:--cor, measure. Aramaic the same.
(Aramaic) probably corresponding to 3738 in the sense of piercing (figuratively); to grieve:--be grieved.
from the same as 3525; to gird or clothe: -clothed.
(Aramaic) from a verb corresponding to that of 3736; a mantle:--hat.
a primitive root; properly, to dig; figuratively, to plot; generally, to bore or open:--dig, X make (a banquet), open.
usually assigned as a primitive root, but probably only a special application of 3738 (through the common idea of planning implied in a bargain); to purchase:--buy, prepare.
from 3739; a purchase:--provision.
feminine of 3733; a meadow:--cottage.
of uncertain derivation; a cherub or imaginary figure:--cherub, (plural) cherubims.
the same as 3742; Kerub, a place in Bab.: -Cherub.
(Aramaic) from 3745; a herald:--herald.
(Aramaic) probably of Greek origin; to proclaim:--make a proclamation.
perhaps an abridged plural of 3733 in the sense of leader (of the flock); a life-guardsman:--captains, Cherethites (from the margin).
from 3772; a cut; Kerith, a brook of Palestine: -Cherith.
from 3772; a cutting (of the matrimonial bond), i.e. divorce:--divorce(-ment).
expanded from the same as 3522; a rim or top margin:--compass.
probably of foreign origin; the crocus:--saffron.
of foreign derivation; Karkemish, a place in Syria:--Carchemish.
of Persian origin; Karkas, a eunuch of Xerxes: -Carcas.
from 3769; a dromedary (from its rapid motion as if dancing):--swift beast.
from an unused root of uncertain meaning; a garden or vineyard:--vines, (increase of the) vineyard(-s), vintage. See also 1021.
active participle of an imaginary denominative from 3754; a vinedresser:--vine dresser (as one or two words).
from 3754; gardener; Karmi, the name of three Israelites:--Carmi.
patronymically from 3756; a Karmite or descendant of Karmi:--Carmites.
probably of foreign origin; carmine, a deep red: -crimson.
from 3754; a planted field (garden, orchard, vineyard or park); by implication, garden produce:--full (green) ears (of corn), fruitful field (place), plentiful (field).
the same as 3759; Karmel, the name of a hill and of a town in Palestine:--Carmel, fruitful (plentiful) field, (place).
patron from 3760; a Karmelite or inhabitant of Karmel (the town):--Carmelite.
feminine of 3761; a Karmelitess or female inhabitant of Karmel:--Carmelitess.
of uncertain derivation; Keran, an aboriginal Idumaean:--Cheran.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 3678; a throne:--throne.
from 3697; to lay waste:--waste.
a primitive root; to bend the knee; by implication, to sink, to prostrate:--bow (down, self), bring down (low), cast down, couch, fall, feeble, kneeling, sink, smite (stoop) down, subdue, X very.
from 3766; the leg (from the knee to the ankle) of men or locusts (only in the dual):--leg.
of foreign origin; byssus or fine vegetable wool: -green.
a primitive root; to dance (i.e. whirl): -dance(-ing).
by variation from 7164; the paunch or belly (as swelling out):--belly.
of foreign origin; Karshena, a courtier of Xerxes:--Carshena.

a primitive root; to cut (off, down or asunder); by implication, to destroy or consume; specifically, to covenant (i.e. make an alliance or bargain, originally by cutting flesh and passing between the pieces):--be chewed, be con-(feder-)ate, covenant, cut (down, off), destroy, fail, feller, be freed, hew (down), make a league ((covenant)), X lose, perish, X utterly, X want.
passive participle feminine of 3772; something cut, i.e. a hewn timber:--beam.
probably from 3772 in the sense of executioner; a Kerethite or life-guardsman (compare 2876) (only collectively in the singular as plural):--Cherethims, Cherethites.
apparently by transposition for 3532; a young sheep:--lamb.
feminine of 3775; a young ewe:--lamb.
from an unused root of uncertain meaning; Kesed, a relative of Abraham:--Onesed.

(occasionally with enclitic) Kasdiymah {kas-dee'- maw}; towards the Kasdites:--into Chaldea), patronymically from 3777 (only in the plural); a Kasdite, or descendant of Kesed; by implication, a Chaldaean (as if so descended); also an astrologer (as if proverbial of that people:--Chaldeans, Chaldees, inhabitants of Chaldea.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 3778; a Chaldaean or inhabitant of Chaldaea; by implication, a Magian or professional astrologer:--Chaldean.
a primitive root; to grow fat (i.e. be covered with flesh):--be covered. Compare 3680.
from 3782; properly, a feller, i.e. an axe: -ax.

a primitive root; to totter or waver (through weakness of the legs, especially the ankle); by implication, to falter, stumble, faint or fall:--bereave (from the margin), cast down, be decayed, (cause to) fail, (cause, make to) fall (down, -ing), feeble, be (the) ruin(-ed, of), (be) overthrown, (cause to) stumble, X utterly, be weak.
from 3782; properly, a tottering, i.e. ruin:--fall.
a primitive root; properly, to whisper a spell, i.e. to inchant or practise magic:--sorcerer, (use) witch(-craft).
from 3784; magic:--sorcery, witchcraft.
from 3784; a magician:--sorcerer.
a primitive root properly, to be straight or right; by implication, to be acceptable; also to succeed or prosper:-- direct, be right, prosper.
from 3787; success, advantage:--equity, good, right.
a primitive root; to grave, by implication, to write (describe, inscribe, prescribe, subscribe):--describe, record, prescribe, subscribe, write(-ing, -ten).
(Aramaic) corresponding to 3789:--write(-ten).
from 3789; something written, i.e. a writing, record or book:--register, scripture, writing.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 3791:--prescribing, writing(-ten).
from 3789; a letter or other mark branded on the skin:--X any (mark).

or Kittiyiy {kit-tee-ee'}; patrial from an unused name denoting Cyprus (only in the plural); a Kittite or Cypriote; hence, an islander in general, i.e. the Greeks or Romans on the shores opposite Palestine:--Chittim, Kittim.
from 3807; beaten, i.e. pure (oil): -beaten.
from an unused root meaning to compact; a wall (as gathering inmates):--wall.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 3796:--wall.
from 3796 and 376; wall of a man; Kithlish, a place in Palestine:--Kithlish.
a primitive root; properly, to carve or engrave, i.e. (by implication) to inscribe indelibly:--mark.
from 3799; properly, something carved out, i.e. ore; hence, gold (pure as originally mined):--((most) fine, pure) gold(-en wedge).
or kuttoneth {koot-to'-neth}; from an unused root meaning to cover (compare 3802); a shirt:--coat, garment, robe.

from an unused root meaning to clothe; the shoulder (proper, i.e. upper end of the arm; as being the spot where the garments hang); figuratively, side-piece or lateral projection of anything:--arm, corner, shoulder(-piece), side, undersetter.

a primitive root; to enclose; hence (in a friendly sense) to crown, (in a hostile one) to besiege; also to wait (as restraining oneself):--beset round, compass about, be crowned inclose round, suffer.
from 3803; properly, a circlet, i.e. a diadem: -crown.
feminine active participle of 3803; the capital of a column:--chapiter.
a primitive root; to butt or pound:--bray.
a primitive root; to bruise or violently strike:--beat (down, to pieces), break in pieces, crushed, destroy, discomfit, smite, stamp.

or lowi {lo}; or loh (Deut. 3:11) {lo}; a primitive particle; not (the simple or abs. negation); by implication, no; often used with other particles (as follows):--X before, + or else, ere, + except, ig(-norant), much, less, nay, neither, never, no((-ne), -r, (-thing)), (X as though...,(can-), for) not (out of), of nought, otherwise, out of, + surely, + as truly as, + of a truth, + verily, for want, + whether, without.
(Aramaic) or lah (Aramaic) (Dan. 4:32) {law}; corresponding to 3808:--or even, neither, no(-ne, -r), ((can-))not, as nothing, without.

or Low Dbar (2 Samuel 9:4,5) {lo deb-ar'}; or Lidbir (Joshua 13:26) {lid-beer'}; (probably rather Lodbar {lo-deb-ar'}); from 3808 and 1699; pastureless; Lo-Debar, a place in Palestine:--Debir, Lo-debar.
a primitive root; to tire; (figuratively) to be (or make) disgusted:--faint, grieve, lothe, (be, make) weary (selves).
from 3811; weary; Leah, a wife of Jacob:--Leah.
a primitive root; to muffle:--cover.
from 3813 (or perhaps for active participle of 3874); properly, muffled, i.e. silently:--softly.
from the prepositional prefix and 410; (belonging) to God; Lael an Israelite:--Lael.
or l owm {leh-ome'}; from an unused root meaning to gather; a community:--nation, people.
plural of 3816; communities; Leum mim, an Arabian:--Leummim.
from 3808 and 5971 with pronominal suffix; not my people; Lo-Ammi, the symbolic name of a son of Hosea:--Lo-ammi.
from 3808 and 7355; not pitied; Lo- Ruchamah, the symbol. name of a son of Hosea:--Lo-ruhamah.

a form of 3824; the heart; also used (figuratively) very widely for the feelings, the will and even the intellect; likewise for the centre of anything:--+ care for, comfortably, consent, X considered, courag(-eous), friend(-ly), ((broken-), (hard-), (merry-), (stiff-), (stout-), double) heart((-ed)), X heed, X I, kindly, midst, mind(-ed), X regard((-ed)), X themselves, X unawares, understanding, X well, willingly, wisdom.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 3820:--heart.
plural of 3833; lionesses; Lebaoth, a place in Palestine:--Lebaoth. See also 1034.

a primitive root; properly, to be enclosed (as if with fat); by implication (as denominative from 3824) to unheart, i.e. (in a good sense) transport (with love), or (in a bad sense) stultify; also (as denominative from 3834) to make cakes:--make cakes, ravish, be wise.
from 3823; the heart (as the most interior organ); used also like 3820:--+ bethink themselves, breast, comfortably, courage, ((faint), (tender-)heart((-ed)), midst, mind, X unawares, understanding.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 3824:--heart.
feminine of 3820; the heart:--heart.
for 3852; flame:--flame.
or lbonah {leb-o-naw'}; from 3836; frankincense (from its whiteness or perhaps that of its smoke): -(frank-)incense.
the same as 3828; Lebonah, a place in Palestine:--Lebonah.
or lbush {leb-oosh'}; from 3847; a garment (literally or figuratively); by implication (euphem.) a wife:--apparel, clothed with, clothing, garment, raiment, vestment, vesture.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 3830:--garment.
a primitive root; to overthrow; intransposed, to fall:--fall.

or (Ezek. 19:2) lbiyao {leb-ee-yaw'}; irreg. masculine plural lbaviym {leb-aw-eem'}; irreg. feminine plural lbaeowth {leb-aw-oth'}; from an unused root men. to roar; a lion (properly, a lioness as the fiercer (although not a roarer; compare 738)):--(great, old, stout) lion, lioness, young (lion).
or rather lbibah {leb-ee-baw'}; from 3823 in its original sense of fatness (or perhaps of folding); a cake (either as fried or turned):--cake.
a primitive root; to be (or become) white; also (as denominative from 3843) to make bricks:--make brick, be (made, make) white(-r).
or (Gen. 49:12) laben {law-bane'}; from 3835; white:--white.
the same as 3836; Laban, a Mesopotamian; also a place in the Desert:--Laban.
or Lbanah {leb-aw-naw'}; the same as 3842; Lebana or Lebanah, one of the Nethinim:--Lebana, Lebanah.
from 3835; some sort of whitish tree, perhaps the storax:--poplar.
from 3835; properly, whiteness, i.e. (by implication) transparency:--paved.
the same as 3839; Libnah, a place in the Desert and one in Palestine:--Libnah.
from 3835; properly, (the) white, i.e. the moon:--moon. See also 3838.
from 3835; a brick (from the whiteness of the clay):--(altar of) brick, tile.
from 3825; (the) white mountain (from its snow); Lebanon, a mountain range in Palestine:--Lebanon.
from 3835; white; Libni, an Israelite:--Libni.
patronymically from 3845; a Libnite or descendants of Libni (collectively):--Libnites.

or labesh {law-bashe'}; a primitive root; properly, wrap around, i.e. (by implication) to put on a garment or clothe (oneself, or another), literally or figuratively:--(in) apparel, arm, array (self), clothe (self), come upon, put (on, upon), wear.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 3847:--clothe.
from an unused root apparently meaning to deepen or hollow (like 3537); a log or measure for liquids:--log (of oil).
from an unused root of uncertain signification; Lod, a place in Palestine:--Lod.
from an usused root meaning to gleam; a flash; figuratively, a sharply polished blade or point of a weapon:--blade, bright, flame, glittering.
or lahebeth {lah-eh'-beth}; feminine of 3851, and meaning the same:--flame(-ming), head (of a spear).
plural of 3851; flames; Lehabim, a son of Mizrain, and his descendants:--Lehabim.
from an unused root meaning to be eager; intense mental application:--study.
from an unused root meaning to glow (compare 3851) or else to be earnest (compare 3854); Lahad, an Israelite:--Lahad.
a primitive root meaning properly, to burn, i.e. (by implication) to be rabid (figuratively, insane); also (from the exhaustion of frenzy) to languish:--faint, mad.
a primitive root; properly, to lick, i.e. (by implication) to blaze:--burn (up), set on fire, flaming, kindle.
from 3857; a blaze; also (from the idea of enwrapping) magic (as covert):--flaming, enchantment.
a primitive root; properly, to burn in, i.e. (figuratively) to rankle:--wound.
from the prepositional prefix meaning to or for and 2005; popularly for if; hence, therefore:--for them (by mistake for prepositional suffix).
(Aramaic) corresponding to 3860; therefore; also except:--but, except, save, therefore, wherefore.
probably from an unused root meaning to gather; an assembly:--company.
or lu {loo}; or luw {loo}; a conditional particle; if; by implication (interj. as a wish) would that!:--if (haply), peradventure, I pray thee, though, I would, would God (that).

or Lubbiy (Dan. 11:43) {loob-bee'}; partrial from a name probably derived from an unused root meaning to thirst, i.e. a dry region; apparently a Libyan or inhabitant of interior Africa (only in plural): -Lubim(-s), Libyans.
probably of foreign derivation; Lud, the name of two nations:--Lud, Lydia.
or Luwdiyiy {loo-dee-ee'}; patrial from 3865; a Ludite or inhabitants of Lud (only in plural):--Ludim. Lydians.
a primitive root; properly, to twine, i.e. (by implication) to unite, to remain; also to borrow (as a form of obligation) or (caus.) to lend:--abide with, borrow(-er), cleave, join (self), lend(-er).
a primitive root; to turn aside (compare 3867, 3874 and 3885), i.e. (literally) to depart, (figuratively) be perverse:--depart, froward, perverse(-ness).
probably of foreign origin; some kind of nut-tree, perhaps the almond:--hazel.
probably from 3869 (as growing there); Luz, the name of two places in Palestine:--Luz.
or luach {loo'-akh}; from a primitive root; probably meaning to glisten; a tablet (as polished), of stone, wood or metal:--board, plate, table.
or Luchowth (Jer. 48:5) {loo-khoth'}; from the same as 3871; floored; Luchith, a place East of the Jordan:--Luhith.
active participle of 3907; (the) enchanter; Lochesh, an Israelite:--Hallohesh, Haloshesh (includ. the article).
a primitive root; to wrap up:--cast, wrap.
from 3874; a veil:--covering.
the same as 3875; Lot, Abraham's nephew:--Lot.
from 3875; covering; Lotan, an Idumaean: -Lotan.
from 3867; attached; Levi, a son of Jacob:--Levi. See also 3879, 3881.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 3880:--Levite.
from 3867; something attached, i.e. a wreath: -ornament.
or Leviy {lay-vee'}; patronymically from 3878; a Levite or descendant of Levi:--Leviite.

from 3867; a wreathed animal, i.e. a serpent (especially the crocodile or some other large sea- monster); figuratively, the constellation of the dragon; also as a symbol of Bab.:--leviathan, mourning.
from an unused root meaning to fold back; a spiral step:--winding stair. Compare 3924.
or luwley {loo lay'}; from 3863 and 3808; if not:--except, had not, if (...not), unless, were it not that.

or liyn {leen}; a primitive root; to stop (usually over night); by implication, to stay permanently; hence (in a bad sense) to be obstinate (especially in words, to complain):--abide (all night), continue, dwell, endure, grudge, be left, lie all night, (cause to) lodge (all night, in, -ing, this night), (make to) murmur, remain, tarry (all night, that night).
a primitive root; to gulp; figuratively, to be rash:--swallow down (up).

a primitive root; properly, to make mouths at, i.e. to scoff; hence (from the effort to pronounce a foreign language) to interpret, or (generally) intercede:--ambassador, have in derision, interpreter, make a mock, mocker, scorn(-er, -ful), teacher.
a primitive root; to knead:--knead.
from 3888; kneading; Lush, a place in Palestine:--Laish (from the margin). Compare 3919.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to 3867; properly, adhesion, i.e. (as preposition) with:--X thee.
from 3868; perverseness:--perverse.
from an unused root meaning to be new; fresh, i.e. unused or undried:--green, moist.
from the same as 3892; freshness, i.e. vigor: -natural force.
or lachum {law-khoom'}; passive participle of 3898; properly, eaten, i.e. food; also flesh, i.e. body:--while...is eating, flesh.
from an unused root meaning to be soft; the cheek (from its fleshiness); hence, the jaw-bone:--cheek (bone), jaw (bone).
a form of 3895; Lechi, a place in Palestine:--Lehi. Compare also 7437.
a primitive root; to lick:--lick (up).
a primitive root; to feed on; figuratively, to consume; by implication, to battle (as destruction):--devour, eat, X ever, fight(-ing), overcome, prevail, (make) war(-ring).
from 3898; food (for man or beast), especially bread, or grain (for making it):--((shew-))bread, X eat, food, fruit, loaf, meat, victuals. See also 1036.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 3899:--feast.
from 3898, battle:--war.
from 3899; foodful; Lachmi, an Israelite; or rather probably a brief form (or perhaps erroneous transcription) for 1022:-- Lahmi. See also 3433.
probably by erroneous transcription for Lachmam {lakh-mawm'}; from 3899; food-like; Lachmam or Lachmas, a place in Palestine:--Lahmam.
(Aramaic) from an unused root of uncertain meaning; a concubine:--concubine.
a primitive root; properly, to press, i.e. (figuratively) to distress:--afflict, crush, force, hold fast, oppress(-or), thrust self.
from 3905; distress:--affliction, oppression.
a primitive root; to whisper; by implication, to mumble a spell (as a magician):--charmer, whisper (together).
from 3907; properly, a whisper, i.e. by implication, (in a good sense) a private prayer, (in a bad one) an incantation; concretely, an amulet:--charmed, earring, enchantment, orator, prayer.
a form of 3814 or else participle from 3874; properly, covered, i.e. secret; by implication, incantation; also secrecy or (adverb) covertly: -enchantment, privily, secretly, softly.
probably from 3874; a gum (from its sticky nature), probably ladanum:--myrrh.
from an unused root meaning to hide; a kind of lizard (from its covert habits):--lizard.
masculine plural of passive participle of 3913; hammered (i.e. oppressed) ones; Letushim, an Arabian tribe:--Letushim.
a primitive root; properly, to hammer out (an edge), i.e. to sharpen:--instructer, sharp(-en), whet.
a form of 3880; a wreath:--addition.
or (Isa. 21:11) leyl {lale}; also laylah {lah'- yel-aw}; from the same as 3883; properly, a twist (away of the light), i.e. night; figuratively, adversity:--((mid-))night (season).
(Aramaic) corresponding to 3815:--night.
from 3915; a night spectre:--screech owl.
from 3888 in the sense of crushing; a lion (from his destructive blows):--(old)lion.
the same as 3918; Laish, the name of two places in Palestine:--Laish. Compare 3889.

a primitive root; to catch (in a net, trap or pit); generally, to capture or occupy; also to choose (by lot); figuratively, to cohere:--X at all, catch (self), be frozen, be holden, stick together, take.
from 3920; something to capture with, i.e. a noose:--being taken.
from 3212; a journey; Lekah, a place in Palestine: -Lecah.
from an unused root of uncertain meaning; Lakish, a place in Palestine:--Lachish.
from the same as 3883; a loop:--loop.
a primitive root; properly, to goad, i.e. (by implication) to teach (the rod being an Oriental incentive):(un-) accustomed, X diligently, expert, instruct, learn, skilful, teach(-er, - ing).
a prol. and separable form of the prepositional prefix; to or for:--at, for, to, upon.
or Lmow el {lem-o-ale'}; from 3926 and 410; (belonging) to God; Lemuel or Lemoel, a symbolic name of Solomon: -Lemuel.
or limmud {lim-mood'}; from 3925; instructed: -accustomed, disciple, learned, taught, used.
from an unused root of uncertain meaning; Lemek, the name of two antediluvian patriarchs:--Lamech.
from 3886; the gullet:--throat.
a primitive root; to deride:--mock.
a primitive root; to deride; by implication (as if imitating a foreigner) to speak unintelligibly:--have in derision, laugh (to scorn), mock (on), stammering.
from 3932; derision, scoffing:--derision, scorn (-ing).
from 3932; a buffoon; also a foreigner:--mocker, stammering.
from an unused root of uncertain meaning; Ladah, an Israelite:--Laadah.
from the same as 3935; Ladan, the name of two Israelites:--Laadan.
a primitive root; to speak in a foreign tongue: -strange language.
a primitive root; to swallow greedily; causatively, to feed:--feed.
from an unused root supposed to mean to curse; wormwood (regarded as poisonous, and therefore accursed):--hemlock, wormwood.
or lappid {lap-peed'}; from an unused root probably meaning to shine; a flambeau, lamp or flame:--(fire-)brand, (burning) lamp, lightning, torch.
feminine plural of 3940; Lappidoth, the husband of Deborah:--Lappidoth.
from the prepositional prefix (to or for) and 6440; anterior:--before.
a primitive root; properly, to bend, i.e. (by implication) to clasp; also (reflexively) to turn around or aside:--take hold, turn aside (self).
from 3887; derision:--scornful(-ning).
a primitive root; to deride:--scorn.
from an unused root thought to mean to stop up by a barricade; perhaps fortification; Lakkum, a place in Palestine:--Lakum.

a primitive root; to take (in the widest variety of applications):--accept, bring, buy, carry away, drawn, fetch, get, infold, X many, mingle, place, receive(-ing), reserve, seize, send for, take (away, -ing, up), use, win.

from 3947; properly, something received, i.e. (mentally) instruction (whether on the part of the teacher or hearer); also (in an active and sinister sense) inveiglement:--doctrine, learning, fair speech.
from 3947; learned; Likchi, an Israelite:--Likhi.
a primitive root; properly, to pick up, i.e. (generally) to gather; specifically, to glean:--gather (up), glean.
from 3950; the gleaning:--gleaning.
a primitive root; to lick or lap:--lap, lick.
a primitive root; to gather the after crop:--gather.
from 3953; the after crop:--latter growth.
from an unused root of uncertain meaning; apparently juice, i.e. (figuratively) vigor; also a sweet or fat cake:--fresh, moisture.

or lashon {law-shone'}; also (in plural) feminine lshonah {lesh-o-naw'}; from 3960; the tongue (of man or animals), used literally (as the instrument of licking, eating, or speech), and figuratively (speech, an ingot, a fork of flame, a cove of water):--+ babbler,bay, + evil speaker, language, talker, tongue, wedge.
from an unused root of uncertain meaning; a room in a building (whether for storage, eating, or lodging):--chamber, parlour. Compare 5393.
from an unused root of uncertain meaning; a gem, perhaps the jacinth:--ligure.
the same as 3958; Leshem, a place in Palestine: -Leshem.
a primitive root; properly, to lick; but used only as a denominative from 3956; to wag the tongue, i.e. to calumniate:--accuse, slander.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 3956; speech, i.e. a nation:--language.
from an unused root thought to mean to break through; a boiling spring; Lesha, a place probably East of the Jordan:--Lasha.
from an unused root of uncertain meaning; a measure for things dry:--half homer.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 4100; (as indef.) that:--+ what.
from 75; a granary:--storehouse.

from the same as 181; properly, vehemence, i.e. (with or without preposition) vehemently; by implication, wholly, speedily, etc. (often with other words as an intensive or superlative; especially when repeated):--diligently, especially, exceeding(-ly), far, fast, good, great(-ly), X louder and louder, might(-ily, -y), (so) much, quickly, (so) sore, utterly, very (+ much, sore), well.
or metyah {may-yaw'}; properly, a primitive numeral; a hundred; also as a multiplicative and a fraction:--hundred((-fold), -th), + sixscore.
the same as 3967; Meah, a tower in Jerusalem:--Meah.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 3967:--hundred.
from 183; a desire:--desire.
usually muwm {moom}; as if passive participle from an unused root probably meaning to stain; a blemish (physically or morally):--blemish, blot, spot.
apparently a form of 3971; properly, a speck or point, i.e. (by implication) something; with negative, nothing:--fault, + no(-ught), ought, somewhat, any ((no-))thing.
from 3988; refuse:--refuse.

or maor {maw-ore'}; also (in plural) feminine mpowrah {meh-o-raw'}; or morah {meh-o-raw'}; from 215; properly, a luminous body or luminary, i.e. (abstractly) light (as an element): figuratively, brightness, i.e.cheerfulness; specifically, a chandelier:--bright, light.
feminine passive participle of 215; something lighted, i.e. an aperture; by implication, a crevice or hole (of a serpent):--den.
from 239; (only in the dual) a pair of scales: -balances.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 3976:--balances.
from 398; an eatable (includ. provender, flesh and fruit):--food, fruit, ((bake-)) meat(-s), victual.
from 398; something to eat with,- i.e. a knife:--knife.
from 398; something eaten (by fire), i.e. fuel:--fuel.
from 553; strength, i.e. (plural) resources:--force.
from 559; something (authoritatively) said, i.e. an edict:--commandment, decree.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 3982:--appointment, word.
(Aramaic) probably from a root corresponding to 579 in the sense of an inclosure by sides; a utensil:--vessel.
a primitive root; to refuse:--refuse, X utterly.
from 3985; unwilling:--refuse.
from 3985; refractory:--refuse.

a primitive root; to spurn; also (intransitively) to disappear:--abhor, cast away (off), contemn, despise, disdain, (become) loathe(some), melt away, refuse, reject, reprobate, X utterly, vile person.
from 644; something baked, i.e. a batch: -baken.
from the same as 651; something opaque: -darkness.
prol. feminine of 3990; opaqueness: -darkness.
a primitive root; to be bitter or (causatively) to embitter, i.e. be painful:--fretting, picking.
from 693; an ambuscade:--lie in ambush, ambushment, lurking place, lying in wait.
from 779; an execration:--curse.
from 914; a separation, i.e. (concretely) a separate place:--separate.

from 935; an entrance (the place or the act); specifically (with or without 8121) sunset or the west; also (adverb with preposition) towards:--by which came, as cometh, in coming, as men enter into, entering, entrance into, entry, where goeth, going down, + westward. Compare 4126.
feminine of 3996; a haven:--entry.
from 943; perplexity:--perplexity.
from 2986 in the sense of flowing; a deluge: -flood.
from 995; instructing:--taught.
from 947; a trampling:--treading (trodden) down (under foot).
from 5042; a fountain:--fountain, spring.
from the same as 950; emptiness:--void.
from 977; select, i.e. well fortified:--choice.
from 977; select, i.e. best:--choice(-st), chosen.
the same as 4005; Mibchar, an Israelite:--Mibhar.
or mebbat {meb-bawt'}; from 5027; something expected, i.e. (abstractly) expectation:--expectation.
from 981; a rash utterance (hasty vow):--(that which ...) uttered (out of).
from 982; properly, a refuge, i.e. (objective) security, or (subjective) assurance:--confidence, hope, sure, trust.
from 1082; desistance (or rather desolation):--comfort self.
from 1129; a building:--frame.
from 1129; built up; Mebunnai, an Israelite:--Mebunnai.
also (in plural) feminine (Dan. 11:l5) mibtsarah {mib-tsaw-raw'}; from 1219; a fortification, castle, or fortified city; figuratively, a defender:--(de-, most) fenced, fortress, (most) strong (hold).
the same as 4013; Mibtsar, an Idumaean:--Mibzar.
from 1272; a refugee:--fugitive.
from 954; (plural) the (male) pudenda:--secrets.
from the same as 1314; fragrant; Mibsam, the name of an Ishmaelite and of an Israelite:--Mibsam.
from 1310; a cooking hearth:--boiling-place.
from the same as 1378; stiffening; Magbish, an Israelite, or a place in Palestine:--Magbish.
from 1379; a border:--end.
from the same as 1389; a cap (as hemispherical):--bonnet.
from an unused root probably meaning to be eminent; properly, a distinguished thing; hence something valuable, as a product or fruit:--pleasant, precious fruit (thing).
(Zech. 12 or Mgiddow {meg-id-do'}; from 1413; rendezvous; Megiddon or Megiddo, a place in Palestine:--Megiddo, Megiddon.
or Migdol {mig-dole'}; probably of Egyptian origin; Migdol, a place in Egypt:--Migdol, tower.
from 4022 and 410; preciousness of God; Magdiel, an Idumaean:--Magdiel.

also (in plural) feminine migdalah {mig-daw- law'}; from 1431; a tower (from its size or height); by analogy, a rostrum; figuratively, a (pyramidal) bed of flowers:--castle, flower, tower. Compare the names following.
from 4026 and 410; tower of God; Migdal-El, a place in Palestine:--Migdal-el.
from 4026 and 1408; tower of Fortune; Migdal-Gad, a place in Palestine:--Migdal-gad.
from 4026 and 5739; tower of a flock; Migdal-Eder, a place in Palestine:--Migdal-eder, tower of the flock.
from the same as 4022; preciousness, i.e. a gem:--precious thing, present.
from 1463; Magog, a son of Japheth; also a barbarous northern region:--Magog.
or (Lam. 2:22) maguwr {maw-goor'}; from 1481 in the sense of fearing; a fright (objective or subjective):--fear, terror. Compare 4036.
or magur {maw-goor'}; from 1481 in the sense of lodging; a temporary abode; by extension, a permanent residence:--dwelling, pilgrimage, where sojourn, be a stranger. Compare 4032.
feminine of 4032; affright:--fear.
feminine of 4032 or of 4033; a fright; also a granary:--barn, fear.
from 4032 and 5439 with the preposition inserted; affright from around; Magor-mis-Sabib, a symbolic name of Pashur:--Magor-missabib.
from 1504; a cutting implement, i.e. a blade:--axe.
from an unused root meaning to reap; a sickle:--sickle.
from 1556; a roll:--roll, volume.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 4039:--roll.
from the same as 1571; properly, accumulation, i.e. impulse or direction:--sup up.
a denominative from 4043; properly, to shield; encompass with; figuratively, to rescue, to hand safely over (i.e. surrender):--deliver.

also (in plural) feminine mginnah {meg-in-naw'}; from 1598; a shield (i.e. the small one or buckler); figuratively, a protector; also the scaly hide of the crocodile:--X armed, buckler, defence, ruler, + scale, shield.
from 4042; a covering (in a bad sense), i.e. blindness or obduracy:--sorrow. See also 4043.
from 1605; reproof (i.e. curse):--rebuke.
from 5062; a pestilence; by analogy, defeat:--(X be) plague(-d), slaughter, stroke.
apparently from 1479 or 5062 and 6211; exterminator of (the) moth; Magpiash, an Israelite:--Magpiash.
a primitive root; to yield up; intensively, to precipitate:--cast down, terror.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 4048; to overthrow:--destroy.
from 1641; a saw:--axe, saw.
from 4048; precipice; Migron, a place in Palestine:--Migron.
from 1639; a ledge or offset:--narrowed rest.
from 1640; something thrown off (by the spade), i.e. a clod:--clod.

also (in plural) feminine (Ezek. 27:28) migrashah {mig-raw-shaw'}; from 1644; a suburb (i.e. open country whither flocks are driven from pasture); hence, the area around a building, or the margin of the sea:--cast out, suburb.
or med {made}; from 4058; properly, extent, i.e. height; also a measure; by implication, a vesture (as measured); also a carpet:--armour, clothes, garment, judgment, measure, raiment, stature.
(Aramaic) from 1684; a sacrificial altar:--altar.
from 1696 in the sense of driving; a pasture (i.e. open field, whither cattle are driven); by implication, a desert; also speech (including its organs):--desert, south, speech, wilderness.
a primitive root: properly, to stretch; by implication, to measure (as if by stretching a line); figuratively, to be extended:--measure, mete, stretch self.
from 5074; flight:--be gone.

feminine of 4055; properly, extension, i.e. height or breadth; also a measure (including its standard); hence a portion (as measured) or a vestment; specifically, tribute (as measured):--garment, measure(-ing, meteyard, piece, size, (great) stature, tribute, wide.
(Aramaic) or mindah (Aramaic) {min-daw'}; corresponding to 4060; tribute in money:--toll, tribute.
perhaps from the equivalent of 1722; goldmaking, i.e. exactness:--golden city.
from an unused root meaning to stretch; properly, extent, i.e. measure; by implication, a dress (as measured):--garment.
from 1738; sickness:--disease.
from 5080; seduction:--cause of banishment.
from 1777; a contest or quarrel:--brawling, contention(-ous), discord, strife. Compare 4079, 4090.
from the same as 4063; extensiveness, i.e. height:--stature.
the same as 4067; Madon, a place in Palestine:--Madon.
or madduaa {mad-doo'-ah}; from 4100 and the passive participle of 3045; what (is) known?; i.e. (by implication) (adverbially) why?:--how, wherefore, why.
(Aramaic) or mdor (Aramaic) {med-ore'}; or mdar (Aramaic) {med-awr'}; from 1753; a dwelling:--dwelling.
or mdurah {med-oo-raw'}; from 1752 in the sense of accumulation; a pile of fuel:--pile (for fire).
from 1760; overthrow:--ruin.
from 1765; a push, i.e. ruin:--overthrow.
of foreign derivation; Madai, a country of central Asia:--Madai, Medes, Media.
patrial from 4074; a Madian or native of Madai:--Mede.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 4074:--Mede(-s).
(Aramaic) corresponding to 4075:--Median.
from 4100 and 1767; what (is) enough, i.e. sufficiently:--sufficiently.
a variation for 4066:--brawling, contention(-ous).
the same as 4079; Midjan, a son of Abraham; also his country and (collectively) his descendants:--Midian, Midianite.
a variation for 4080:--Middin.
from 1777; properly, a judgeship, i.e. jurisdiction; by implication, a district (as ruled by a judge); generally, a region:--(X every) province.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 4082:--province.
patronymical or patrial from 4080; a Midjanite or descend. (native) of Midjan:--Midianite. Compare 4092.
from 1743; a mortar:--mortar.
from the same as 1828; dunghill; Madmen, a place in Palestine:--Madmen.
feminine from the same as 1828; a dunghill:--dunghill.
the same as 4087; Madmenah, a place in Palestine:--Madmenah.
a variation for 4087; Madmannah, a place in Palestine:--Madmannah.
a form of 4066:--discord, strife.
the same as 4090; Medan, a son of Abraham:--Medan.
a variation of 4084:--Midianite.
or maddai {mad-dah'}; from 3045; intelligence or consciousness:--knowledge, science, thought.
from 1856; a wound:--piercing.
from an unused root meaning to step; properly, a step; by implication, a steep or inaccessible place:--stair, steep place.
from 1869; a treading, i.e. a place for stepping on:--(foot-)breadth.
from 1875; properly, an investigation, i.e. (by implication) a treatise or elaborate compilation:--story.
from 1758; a threshing, i.e. (concretely and figuratively) down-trodden people:--threshing.
of Persian origin; Medatha, the father of Haman:--Hammedatha (including the article).

or mah {mah}; or ma {maw}; or ma {mah}; also meh {meh}; a primitive particle; properly, interrogative what? (including how? why? when?); but also exclamation, what! (including how!), or indefinitely what (including whatever, and even relatively, that which); often used with prefixes in various adverbial or conjunctive senses:--how (long, oft, (- soever)), (no-)thing, what (end, good, purpose, thing), whereby(-fore, -in, -to, -with), (for) why.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 4100:--how great (mighty), that which, what(-soever), why.
apparently a denominative from 4100; properly, to question or hesitate, i.e. (by implication) to be reluctant:--delay, linger, stay selves, tarry.
from 1949; confusion or uproar:--destruction, discomfiture, trouble, tumult, vexation, vexed.
of Persian origin; Mehuman, a eunuch of Xerxes:--Mehuman.
from 3190 (augmented) and 410; bettered of God; Mehetabel, the name of an Edomitish man and woman:--Mehetabeel, Mehetabel.
or mahir {maw-here'}; from 4116; quick; hence, skilful:--diligent, hasty, ready.
a primitive root; properly, to cut down or reduce, i.e. by implication, to adulterate:--mixed.
from 1980; a walking (plural collectively), i.e. access:--place to walk.
from 1980; a walk, i.e. a passage or a distance:--journey, walk.
from 1984; fame:--praise.
from 4110 and 410; praise of God; Mahalalel, the name of an antediluvian patriarch and of an Israelite:--Mahalaleel.
from 1986; a blow:--stripe, stroke.
from an unused root of uncertain meaning; perhaps an abyss:--deep pit.
from 2015; a destruction: --when...overthrew, overthrow(-n).
from 2015; a wrench, i.e. the stocks:--prison, stocks.

a primitive root; properly, to be liquid or flow easily, i.e. (by implication); to hurry (in a good or a bad sense); often used (with another verb) adverbially, promptly:--be carried headlong, fearful, (cause to make, in, make) haste(-n, -ily), (be) hasty, (fetch, make ready) X quickly, rash, X shortly, (be so) X soon, make speed, X speedily, X straightway, X suddenly, swift.
a primitive root (perhaps rather the same as 4116 through the idea of readiness in assent); to bargain (for a wife), i.e. to wed:--endow, X surely.
from 4116; properly, hurrying; hence (adverbially) in a hurry:--hasteth, hastily, at once, quickly, soon, speedily, suddenly.
from 4117; a price (for a wife):--dowry.
feminine of 4118; properly, a hurry; hence (adverbially) promptly:--hastily, quickly, shortly, soon, make (with) speed(-ily), swiftly.
from 4116; hasty; Maharai, an Israelite:--Maharai.

lexicon.i: from 4118 and 7998 and 2363 and 957; hasting (is he (the enemy) to the) booty, swift (to the) prey; Maher-Shalal-Chash-Baz; the symbolical name of the son of Isaiah:--Maher-sha-lal-bash-baz.
from 2048; a delusion:--deceit.
from a prolonged form of the prepositional prefix m- and 1; from (her (the mother's)) father; Moab, an incestuous son of Lot; also his territory and descendants:--Moab.
feminine Mownabiyah {mo-aw-bee-yaw'}; or Mowabiyth {mo-aw-beeth'}; patronymical from 4124; a Moabite or Moabitess, i.e. a descendant from Moab:--(woman) of Moab, Moabite(-ish, -ss).
by transp. for 3996; an entrance:--coming.
a primitive root; to melt, i.e. literally (to soften, flow down, disappear), or figuratively (to fear, faint):--consume, dissolve, (be) faint(-hearted), melt (away), make soft.
a primitive root; to shake:--measure.
or rather modao {mo-daw'}; from 3045; an acquaintance:--kinswoman.
from 3045; acquaintance:--kindred.

a primitive root; to waver; by implication , to slip, shake, fall:--be carried, cast, be out of course, be fallen in decay, X exceedingly, fall(-ing down), be (re-)moved, be ready, shake, slide, slip.

feminine of 4132; a pole; by implication, an ox-bow; hence, a yoke (either literal or figurative):--bands, heavy, staves, yoke.
