a primitive root; to cut short, i.e. curtail (specifically the prepuce, i.e. to circumcise); by implication, to blunt; figuratively, to destroy:--circumcise(-ing), selves), cut down (in pieces), destroy, X must needs.

or mowl (Deuteronomy 1:1) {mole}; or mowtl (Nehemiah 12:38) {mole}; or mul (Numbers 22:5) {mool}; from 4135; properly, abrupt, i.e. a precipice; by implication, the front; used only adverbially (with prepositional prefix) opposite:--(over) against, before, (fore-)front, from, (God-)ward, toward, with.
from 3205; birth; Moladah, a place in Palestine:--Moladah.
from 3205; nativity (plural birth-place); by implication, lineage, native country; also offspring, family:--begotten, born, issue, kindred, native(-ity).
from 4135; circumcision:--circumcision.
from 3205; genitor; Molid, an Israelite:--Molid.
from 5437; a turn, i.e. circuit (of a building):--winding about.
or mucabbah {moo-sab-baw'}; feminine of 4141; a reversal, i.e. the backside (of a gem), fold (of a double-leaved door), transmutation (of a name):--being changed, inclosed, be set, turning.
from 3245; a foundation:--foundation.
from 3245; a foundation:--foundation.
feminine of 4143; a foundation; figuratively, an appointment:--foundation, grounded. Compare 4328.
or mocadah {mo-saw-daw'}; feminine of 4144; a foundation:--foundation.
also (in plural) feminine mowcerah {mo-say-raw'}; or mocrah {mo-ser-aw'}; from 3256; properly, chastisement, i.e. (by implication) a halter; figuratively, restraint:--band, bond.

from 3256; properly, chastisement; figuratively, reproof, warning or instruction; also restraint:--bond, chastening ((-eth)), chastisement, check, correction, discipline, doctrine, instruction, rebuke.
or (plural) Mocrowth {mo-ser-othe'} feminine of 4147; correction or corrections; Moserah or Moseroth, a place in the Desert:--Mosera, Moseroth.

or moled {mo-ade'}; or (feminine) moweadah (2 Chronicles 8:13) {mo-aw-daw'}; from 3259; properly, an appointment, i.e. a fixed time or season; specifically, a festival; conventionally a year; by implication, an assembly (as convened for a definite purpose); technically the congregation; by extension, the place of meeting; also a signal (as appointed beforehand):--appointed (sign, time), (place of, solemn) assembly, congregation, (set, solemn) feast, (appointed, due) season, solemn(-ity), synogogue, (set) time (appointed).
from 3259; properly, an assembly (as in 4150); figuratively, a troop:--appointed time.
from 3259; an appointed place, i.e. asylum:--appointed.
from 4151 and 3050; assembly of Jah; Moadjah, an Israelite:--Moadiah. Compare 4573.
feminine passive participle of 4571; properly, made to slip, i.e. dislocated:--out of joint.
from 5774; properly, covered, i.e. dark; abstractly, obscurity, i.e. distress:--dimness.
from 3289; a purpose:--counsel, device.
from 5781; pressure, i.e. (figuratively) distress:--affliction.
(Jer. 48:21 or meyphaath {may-fah'-ath}; or mephaath {may-fah'-ath; from 3313; illuminative; Mophaath or Mephaath, a place in Palestine:--Mephaath.
or mopheth {mo-faith'}; from 3302 in the sense of conspicuousness; a miracle; by implication, a token or omen:--miracle, sign, wonder(-ed at).
a primitive root; to press, i.e. (figuratively) to oppress:--extortioner.

or motsai {mo-tsaw'}; from 3318; a going forth, i.e. (the act) an egress, or (the place) an exit; hence, a source or product; specifically, dawn, the rising of the sun (the East), exportation, utterance, a gate, a fountain, a mine, a meadow (as producing grass):--brought out, bud, that which came out, east, going forth, goings out, that which (thing that) is gone out, outgoing, proceeded out, spring, vein, (water-)course (springs).
the same as 4161; Motsa, the name of two Israelites:--Moza.
feminine of 4161; a family descent; also a sewer (marg.; compare 6675):--draught house; going forth.
or muwtsaq {moo-tsawk'}; from 3332; narrowness; figuratively, distress:--anguish, is straitened, straitness.
from 5694; properly, fusion, i.e. literally, a casting (of metal); figuratively, a mass (of clay):--casting, hardness.
or mutsaqah {moo-tsaw-kaw'}; from 3332; properly, something poured out, i.e. a casting (of metal); by implication, a tube (as cast):--when it was cast, pipe.
a primitive root; to jeer, i.e. (intens.) blaspheme:--be corrupt.
from 3344; a fire or fuel; abstractly, a conflagration:--burning, hearth.
feminine of 4168; fuel:--burning.
or moqesh {mo-kashe'}; from 3369; a noose (for catching animals) (literally or figuratively): by implication, a hook (for the nose):--be ensnared, gin, (is) snare(-d), trap.
a primitive root; to alter; by implication, to barter, to dispose of:--X at all, (ex-)change, remove.
or morat {mo-raw'}; or morah (Psa. 9:20) {mo-raw'}; from 3372; fear; by implication, a fearful thing or deed:--dread, (that ought to be) fear(-ed), terribleness, terror.
or morag {mo-rag'}; from an unused root meaning to triturate; a threshing sledge:--threshing instrument.
from 3381; a descent; as architecture, an ornamental appendage, perhaps a festoon:--going down, steep place, thin work.
from 3384; an archer; also teacher or teaching; also the early rain (see 3138):--(early) rain.
or Moreh {mo-reh'}; the same as 4175; Moreh, a Canaanite; also a hill (perhaps named from him):--Moreh.
from 4171 in the sense of shearing; a razor:--razor.
from 3399; obstinate, i.e. independent:--peeled.
or Moriyah {mo-ree-yaw'}; from 7200 and 3050; seen of Jah; Morijah, a hill in Palestine:--Moriah.
from 3423; a possession; figuratively, delight:-- possession, thought.
feminine of 4180; a possession:--heritage, inheritance, possession.
from 3423 and 1661; possession of Gath; Moresheth-Gath, a place in Palestine:--Moresheth-gath.
patrial from 4182; a Morashtite or inhabitant of Moresheth-Gath:--Morashthite.
a primitive root; to touch:--feel, handle.

a primitive root (perhaps rather the same as 4184 through the idea of receding by contact); to withdraw (both literally and figuratively, whether intransitive or transitive):--cease, depart, go back, remove, take away.

or moshab {mo-shawb'}; from 3427; a seat; figuratively, a site; abstractly, a session; by extension an abode (the place or the time); by implication, population:--assembly, dwell in, dwelling(-place), wherein (that) dwelt (in), inhabited place, seat, sitting, situation, sojourning.
or Mushshiy {mush-shee'}; from 4184; sensitive; Mushi, a Levite:--Mushi.
patronymical from 4187; a Mushite (collectively) or descendants of Mushi:--Mushites.
act participle feminine of 4900; something drawing, i.e. (figuratively) a cord:--band.
from 3467; deliverance:--salvation.

a primitive root: to die (literally or figuratively); causatively, to kill:--X at all, X crying, (be) dead (body, man, one), (put to, worthy of) death, destroy(-er), (cause to, be like to, must) die, kill, necro(-mancer), X must needs, slay, X surely, X very suddenly, X in (no) wise.
(Psalm 48 or Muwth lab-ben {mooth lab-bane'}; from 4191 and 1121 with the preposition and article interposed; "To die for the son", probably the title of a popular song:--death, Muthlabben.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 4194; death:--death.
from 4191; death (natural or violent); concretely, the dead, their place or state (hades); figuratively, pestilence, ruin:--(be) dead((-ly)), death, die(-d).
from 3498; literally, gain; figuratively, superiority:--plenteousness, preeminence, profit.
from 2076; an altar:--altar.
from an unused root meaning to mingle (water with wine); tempered wine:--liquor.
from an unused root meaning to suck out; exhausted:--burnt.
probably from an unused root meaning to faint with fear; terror; Mizzah, an Edomite:--Mizzah.
probably from an unused root meaning to gather in; a granary:--garner.
or mzuzah {mez-oo-zaw'}; from the same as 2123; a door-post (as prominent):--(door, side) post.
from 2109; food:--meat, victual.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 4202:--meat.
from 2114 in the sense of turning aside from truth; treachery, i.e. a plot:--wound.
or mazor {maw-zore'}; from 2115 in the sense of binding up; a bandage, i.e. remedy; hence, a sore (as needing a compress):--bound up, wound.
or mezach {may-zakh'}; from 2118; a belt (as movable):--girdle, strength.
or (feminine) mizlagah {miz-law-gaw'}; from an unused root meaning to draw up; a fork:--fleshhook.
apparently from 5140 in the sense of raining; a constellation, i.e. Zodiacal sign (perhaps as affecting the weather):--planet. Compare 4216.
from 2161; a plan, usually evil (machination), sometimes good (sagacity):--(wicked) device, discretion, intent, witty invention, lewdness, mischievous (device), thought, wickedly.
from 2167; properly, instrumental music; by implication, a poem set to notes:--psalm.
from 2168; a pruning-knife:--pruning-hook.
from 2168; a tweezer (only in the plural):--snuffers.
from the same as 2191; fewness; by implication, as superl. diminutiveness:--few, X very.
from 2219; a winnowing shovel (as scattering the chaff):--fan.
apparently from 2219; properly, a scatterer, i.e. the north wind (as dispersing clouds; only in plural):--north.
apparently from 5144 in the sense of distinction; some noted constellation (only in the plural), perhaps collectively, the zodiac:--Mazzoroth. Compare 4208.
from 2224; sunrise, i.e. the east:--east (side, -ward), (sun-)rising (of the sun).
from 2232; a planted field:--thing sown.
from 2236; a bowl (as if for sprinkling):--bason, bowl.
from 4229 in the sense of greasing; fat; figuratively, rich:--fatling (one).
from the same as 4220; fat, i.e. marrow:--marrow.
a primitive root; to rub or strike the hands together (in exultation):--clap.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 4222; to strike in pieces; also to arrest; specifically to impale:--hang, smite, stay.
or machaboo {makh-ab-o'}; from 2244; a refuge:--hiding (lurking) place.
from 2266; a junction, i.e. seam or sewed piece:--coupling.
from 2266; a joiner, i.e. brace or cramp:--coupling, joining.
from the same as 2281; a pan for baking in:--pan.
from 2296; a girdle:--girding.

a primitive root; properly, to stroke or rub; by implication, to erase; also to smooth (as if with oil), i.e. grease or make fat; also to touch, i.e. reach to:--abolish, blot out, destroy, full of marrow, put out, reach unto, X utterly, wipe (away, out).
from 2328; an instrument for marking a circle, i.e. compasses:--compass.
from an unused root meaning to enclose; a harbor (as shut in by the shore):--haven.
or Mchiyyauel {mekh-ee-yaw-ale'}; from 4229 and 410; smitten of God; Mechujael or Mechijael, an anxediluvian patriarch:--Mehujael.
apparently a patrial, but from an unknown place (in the plural only for a singular); a Machavite or inhabitant of some place named Machaveh:--Mahavite.
from 2342; a (round) dance:--dance(-cing).
the same as 4234; dancing; Machol, an Israelite:--Mahol.
from 2372; a vision:--vision.
from 2372; a window:--light.
feminine plural from 2372; visions; Machazioth, an Israelite:--Mahazioth.
from 4229; a stroke, i.e. battering-ram:--engines.
from 2330; junction; Mechida, one of the Nethinim:--Mehida.
from 2421; preservation of life; hence, sustenance; also the live flesh, i.e. the quick:--preserve life, quick, recover selves, reviving, sustenance, victuals.
from an unused root meaning to buy; price, payment, wages:--gain, hire, price, sold, worth.
the same as 4242; price; Mechir, an Israelite:--Mehir.
from 2470; sickness; Machlah, the name apparently of two Israelitesses:--Mahlah.
or (feminine) machalah {makk-al-aw'}; from 2470; sickness:--disease, infirmity, sickness.
feminine of 4284; a dance:--company, dances(-cing).
from 2490; a cavern (as if excavated):--cave.
from 2470; sick; Machlon, an Israelite:--Mahlon.
from 2470; sick; Machli, the name of two Israelites:--Mahli.
patronymical from 4249; a Machlite or (collectively) descendants of Machli:--Mahlites.
from 2470; a disease:--disease.
from 2498; a (sacrificial) knife (as gliding through the flesh):--knife.
from 2498; a ringlet of hair (as gliding over each other):--lock.
from 2502; a mantle (as easily drawn off):--changeable suit of apparel, change of raiment.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 4256; a section (of the Levites):--course.
from 2505; a section (of Levites, people or soldiers):--company, course, division, portion. See also 5555.
from 2470; sickness; Machalath, probably the title (initial word) of a popular song:--Mahalath.
the same as 4257; sickness; Machalath, the name of an Ishmaelitess and of an Israelitess:--Mahalath.
patrial from 65; a Mecholathite or inhabitant of Abel-Mecholah:--Mecholathite.
a denominative from 2529; something buttery (i.e. unctuous and pleasant), as (figuratively) flattery:--X than butter.
from 2530; delightful; hence, a delight, i.e. object of affection or desire:--beloved, desire, goodly, lovely, pleasant (thing).
or machmuwd {makh-mood'}; from 2530; desired; hence, a valuable:--pleasant thing.
from 2550; properly, sympathy; (by paronomasia with 4261) delight:--pitieth.

from 2583; an encampment (of travellers or troops); hence, an army, whether literal (of soldiers) or figurative (of dancers, angels, cattle, locusts, stars; or even the sacred courts):-- army, band, battle, camp, company, drove, host, tents.
from 4264 and 1835; camp of Dan; Machaneh-Dan, a place in Palestine:--Mahaneh-dan.
dual of 4264; double camp; Machanajim, a place in Palestine:--Mahanaim.
from 2614: choking:--strangling.
or machceh {makh-seh'}; from 2620; a shelter (literally or figuratively):--hope, (place of) refuge, shelter, trust.
from 2629; a muzzle:--bridle.
or machcor {makh-sore'}; from 2637; deficiency; hence, impoverishment:--lack, need, penury, poor, poverty, want.
from 4268 and 3050; refuge of (i.e. in) Jah; Machsejah, an Israelite:--Maaseiah.
a primitive root; to dash asunder; by implication, to crush, smash or violently plunge; figuratively, to subdue or destroy:--dip, pierce (through), smite (through), strike through, wound.
from 4272; a contusion:--stroke.
from 2672; properly, a hewing; concretely, a quarry:--hewed(-n).
from 2673; a halving:--half.
from 2673; a halving or the middle:--half (so much), mid(-day).
a primitive root; to crush:--smite off.
from 2713; properly, scrutinized, i.e. (by implication) a recess:--deep place.
probably from 309; properly, deferred, i.e. the morrow; usually (adverbially) tomorrow; indefinitely, hereafter:--time to come, tomorrow.
from the same as 2716; a sink:--draught house.
from 2790; probably a pick-axe:--mattock.
from 2790; probably a hoe:--share.
or mochoratham (1 Sam. 30:17) {mokh-or-aw- thawm'}; feminine from the same as 4279; the morrow or (adverbially) tomorrow:--morrow, next day.

or machashebeth {makh-ash-eh'-beth}; from 2803; a contrivance, i.e. (concretely) a texture, machine, or (abstractly) intention, plan (whether bad, a plot; or good, advice):--cunning (work), curious work, device(-sed), imagination, invented, means, purpose, thought.
from 2821; darkness; concretely, a dark place:--dark(-ness, place).
from 2834; a peeling:--made appear.
probably from 4229; erasure; Machath, the name of two Israelites:--Mahath.
from 2846; properly, a dissolution; concretely, a ruin, or (abstractly) consternation:--destruction, dismaying, ruin, terror.
the same as 4288 in the sense of removal; a pan for live coals:--censer, firepan, snuffdish.
from 2864; a burglary; figuratively, unexpected examination:--breaking up, secret search.
(Aramaic) or mtah (Aramaic) {met-aw'}; apparently corresponding to 4672 in the intransitive sense of being found present; to arrive, extend or happen:--come, reach.
apparently a denominative from 2916; a broom (as removing dirt (compare Engl. "to dust", i.e. remove dust)):--besom.
from 2873; slaughter:--slaughter.

or (feminine) mattah {mat-taw'}; from 5186; a branch (as extending); figuratively, a tribe; also a rod, whether for chastising (figuratively, correction), ruling (a sceptre), throwing (a lance), or walking (a staff; figuratively, a support of life, e.g. bread):--rod, staff, tribe.
from 5786 with directive enclitic appended; downward, below or beneath; often adverbially with or without prefixes:-- beneath, down(-ward), less, very low, under(-neath).
from 5186; a bed (as extended) for sleeping or eating; by analogy, a sofa, litter or bier:--bed((-chamber)), bier.
from 5186; a stretching, i.e. distortion (figuratively, iniquity):--perverseness.
from 5186; expansion:--stretching out.
from 2901; something spun:--spun.
from 2904 in the sense of hammering out; an iron bar (as forged):--bar.
or matmon {mat-mone'}; or matmun {mat-moon'}; from 2934; a secret storehouse; hence, a secreted valuable (buried); generally money:--hidden riches, (hid) treasure(-s).
from 5193; something planted, i.e. the place (a garden or vineyard), or the thing (a plant, figuratively or men); by implication, the act, planting:--plant(-ation, -ing).
or (feminine) matiammah {mat-am-maw'}; from 2938; a delicacy:--dainty (meat), savoury meat.
from 2946; a wide cloak (for a woman):--vail, wimple.
a primitive root; to rain:--(cause to) rain (upon).
from 4305; rain:--rain.
or mattarah {mat-taw-raw'}; from 5201; a jail (as a guard-house); also an aim (as being closely watched):--mark, prison.
from 2956; propulsive; Matred, an Edomitess:--Matred.
from 4305; rainy; Matri, an Israelite:--Matri.

an interrogative pronoun of persons, as 4100 is of things, who? (occasionally, by a peculiar idiom, of things); also (indefinitely) whoever; often used in oblique construction with prefix or suffix:--any (man), X he, X him, + O that! what, which, who(-m, -se, -soever), + would to God.
from 4325 and 1679; water of quiet; Medeba, a place in Palestine:--Medeba.
from 3032 in the sense of loving; affectionate; Medad, an Israelite:--Medad.
from 4325 and 3420 with the art. interposed; water of the yellowness; Me-haj-Jarkon, a place in Palestine:--Me-jarkon.
from 4325 and 2091, water of gold; Me-Zahab, an Edomite:--Mezahab.
from 3190; the best part:--best.
a variation for 4318; Mica, the name of two Israelites:--Micha.
from 4310 and (the prefix derivative from) 3588 and 410; who (is) like God?; Mikael, the name of an archangel and of nine Israelites:--Michael.
an abbrev. of 4320; Micah, the name of seven Israelites:--Micah, Micaiah, Michah.
a contr. for 4321; Mikehu, an Israelite prophet:--Micaiah (2 Chronicles 18:8).
from 4310 and (the prefix derivative from) 3588 and 3050; who (is) like Jah?; Micajah, the name of two Israelites:--Micah, Michaiah. Compare 4318.
or Mikayhuw (Jeremiah 36:11) {me-kaw-yeh-hoo'}; abbrev. for 4322; Mikajah, the name of three Israelites:--Micah, Micaiah, Michaiah.
for 4320; Mikajah, the name of an Israelite and an Israelitess:--Michaiah.
from 3201; properly, a container, i.e. a streamlet:--brook.
apparently the same as 4323; revulet; Mikal, Saul's daughter:--Michal.
dual of a primitive noun (but used in a singular sense); water; figuratively, juice; by euphemism, urine, semen:--+ piss, wasting, water(-ing, (-course, -flood, -spring)).
a form for 4509; Mijamin, the name of three Israelites:--Miamin, Mijamin.
from an unused root meaning to portion out; a sort, i.e. species:--kind. Compare 4480.
properly, feminine passive participle of 3245; something founded, i.e. a foundation:--foundation.
from 5526; a portico (as covered):--covert.
from 4160; pressure:--churning, forcing, wringing.
from 4185; departure; Mesha, a place in Arabia; also an Israelite:--Mesha.
from 4310 and 410 with the abbrev. insep. relatively (see 834) interposed; who (is) what God (is)?; Mishael, the name of three Israelites:--Mishael.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 4332; Mishael, an Israelite:--Mishael.

or miyshor {mee-shore'}; from 3474; a level, i.e. a plain (often used (with the article prefix) as a properly, name of certain districts); figuratively, concord; also straightness, i.e. (figuratively) justice (sometimes adverbially, justly):--equity, even place, plain, right(-eously), (made) straight, uprightness.
borrowed from 4336; Meshak, an Israelite:--Meshak.
(Aramaic) of foreign origin and doubtful significance; Meshak, the Babylonian name of 4333:--Meshak.
from 3467; safety; Mesha, an Israelite:--Mesha.
a variation for 4337; safety; Mesha, a Moabite:--Mesha.

from 3474; evenness, i.e. (figuratively) prosperity or concord; also straightness, i.e. (figuratively) rectitude (only in plural with singular sense; often adverbially):--agreement, aright, that are equal, equity, (things that are) right(-eously, things), sweetly, upright(-ly, -ness).
from 3498; a cord (of a tent) (compare 3499) or the string (of a bow):--cord, string.
sometimes makcowb {mak-obe'}; also (feminine Isaiah 53:3) makfobah {mak-o-baw'}; from 3510; anguish or (figuratively) affliction:--grief, pain, sorrow.
transitive participle of 3527; plenty:--abundance.
from the same as 3522; knoll; Macbena, a place in Palestine settled by him:--Machbenah.
patrial from 4343; a Macbannite or native of Macbena:--Machbanai.
from 3527 in the sense of covering (compare 3531); a grate:--grate.
from 3527 in the sense of covering; a cloth (as netted (compare 4345)):--thick cloth.

or (masculine) makkeh {muk-keh'}; (plural only) from 5221; a blow (in 2 Chronicles 2:10, of the flail); by implication, a wound; figuratively, carnage, also pestilence:--beaten, blow, plague, slaughter, smote, X sore, stripe, stroke, wound((-ed)).
from 3554; a burn:--that burneth, burning.
from 3559; properly, a fixture, i.e. a basis; generally a place, especially as an abode:--foundation, habitation, (dwelling-, settled) place.
or mkonah {mek-o-naw'}; feminine of 4349; a pedestal, also a spot:--base.
or mkorah {mek-o-raw'}; from the same as 3564 in the sense of dipping; origin (as if a mine):--birth, habitation, nativity.
probably from 4134; pining; Maki, an Israelite:--Machi.
from 4376; salesman; Makir, an Israelite:--Machir.
patronymical from 4353; a Makirite or descend. of Makir:--of Machir.
a primitive root; to tumble (in ruins); figuratively, to perish:--be brought low, decay.

from 3615; completion (in plural concrete adverbial, wholly):--perfect. Compare 4356.
from 3634; perfection (i.e. concrete adverbial, splendidly):--most gorgeously, all sorts.
from 3634; perfection (of beauty):--perfection.
from 3634; something perfect, i.e. a splendid garment:--all sorts.

from the same as 3646 in the sense of hiding; treasure (as hidden):--treasure.
(Ezra 2:2 or Mikmash {mik-mawsh'}; or Mikmash (Neh. 11:31) {mik-mash'}; from 3647; hidden; Mikmas or Mikmash, a place in Palestine:--Mikmas, Mikmash.
or mikmor {mik-more'}; from 3648 in the sense of blackening by heat; a (hunter's) net (as dark from concealment):--net.
or mikmoreth {mik-mo'-reth}; feminine of 4364; a (fisher's) net:--drag, net.
apparently from an unused root meaning to hide; concealment; Mikmethath, a place in Palestine:--Michmethath.
from 4100 and 5068 with a particle interposed; what (is) like (a) liberal (man)?; Maknadbai, an Israelite:--Machnadebai.
the same as 4350; a base; Mekonah, a place in Palestine:--Mekonah.
the same as 4350; a spot:--base.
from 3647 in the sense of hiding; (only in dual) drawers (from concealing the private parts):--breeches.
probably from an unused root meaning to enumerate; an assessment (as based upon a census):--tribute.
from 3680; a covering, i.e. weather-boarding:--covering.
feminine of 4371; an enumeration; by implication, a valuation:--number, worth.
from 3680; a covering, i.e. garment; specifically, a coverlet (for a bed), an awning (from the sun); also the omentum (as covering the intestines):--clothing, to cover, that which covereth.
from 3717; a fold; Makpelah, a place in Palestine:--Machpelah.
a primitive root; to sell, literally (as merchandise, a daughter in marriage, into slavery), or figuratively (to surrender):--X at all, sell (away, -er, self).
from 4376; merchandise; also value:--pay, price, ware.
from 5234; an acquaintance:--acquaintance.
from 3738; a pit (for salt):--(salt-)pit.

or mikshol {mik-shole'}; masculine from 3782; a stumbling-block, literally or figuratively (obstacle, enticement (specifically an idol), scruple):--caused to fall, offence, X (no-)thing offered, ruin, stumbling-block.
feminine from 3782; a stumbling-block, but only figuratively (fall, enticement (idol)):--ruin, stumbling-block.

or malae (Esth. 7:5) {maw-law'}; a primitive root, to fill or (intransitively) be full of, in a wide application (literally and figuratively):--accomplish, confirm, + consecrate, be at an end, be expired, be fenced, fill, fulfil, (be, become, X draw, give in, go) full(-ly, -ly set, tale), (over-)flow, fulness, furnish, gather (selves, together), presume, replenish, satisfy, set, space, take a (hand-)full, + have wholly.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 4390; to fill:--fill, be full.
from 4390; full (literally or figuratively) or filling (literally); also (concretely) fulness; adverbially, fully:--X she that was with child, fill(-ed, -ed with), full(-ly), multitude, as is worth.

rarely mlowf {mel-o'}; or mlow (Ezekiel 41:8), {mel-o'}; from 4390; fulness (literally or figuratively):--X all along, X all that is (there-)in, fill, (X that whereof...was) full, fulness, (hand- )full, multitude.
from 4390; a fulfilling (only in plural), i.e. (literally) a setting (of gems), or (technically) consecration (also concretely, a dedicatory sacrifice):--consecration, be set.
feminine of 4392; something fulfilled, i.e. abundance (of produce):--(first of ripe) fruit, fulness.
feminine of 4394; a filling, i.e. setting (of gems):--inclosing, setting.
from an unused root meaning to despatch as a deputy; a messenger; specifically, of God, i.e. an angel (also a prophet, priest or teacher):--ambassador, angel, king, messenger.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 4397; an angel:--angel.

from the same as 4397; properly, deputyship, i.e. ministry; generally, employment (never servile) or work (abstractly or concretely); also property (as the result of labor):--business, + cattle, + industrious, occupation, (+ -pied), + officer, thing (made), use, (manner of) work((-man), -manship).
from the same as 4397; a message:--message.
from the same as 4397; ministrative; Malaki, a prophet:--Malachi.
from 4390; fulness, i.e. (concretely) a plump socket (of the eye):--X fitly.
or malbush {mal-boosh'}; from 3847; a garment, or (collectively) clothing:--apparel, raiment, vestment.
from 3835 (denominative); a brick-kiln:--brickkiln.

from 4448 (plural masculine as if from milleh {mil-leh'}; a word; collectively, a discourse; figuratively, a topic:--+ answer, by-word, matter, any thing (what) to say, to speak(-ing), speak, talking, word.

or mil-loe (2 Kings 12:20) {mil-lo'}; from 4390; a rampart (as filled in), i.e. the citadel:--Millo. See also 1037.
from 4414; sea-purslain (from its saltness):--mallows.
or Malluwkiy (Neh. 12:14) {mal-loo-kee'}; from 4427; remnant; Malluk, the name of five Israelites:--Malluch, Melichu (from the margin).
feminine passive participle of 4427; something ruled, i.e. a realm:--kingsom, king's, X royal.
from 3885; a lodgment, i.e. caravanserai or encampment:--inn, place where...lodge, lodging (place).
feminine from 3885; a hut, a hammock:--cottage, lodge.
apparently from 4448; I have talked (i.e. loquacious):--Mallothi, an Israelite:--Mallothi.

a primitive root; properly, to rub to pieces or pulverize; intransitively, to disappear as dust; also (as denominative from 4417) to salt whether internally (to season with salt) or externally (to rub with salt):--X at all, salt, season, temper together, vanish away.

from 4414 in its original sense; a rag or old garment:--rotten rag.
from 4414 in its second. sense; a sailor (as following "the salt"):--mariner.
from 4414 (in its denominative sense); properly, salted (i.e. land (776 being understood)), i.e. a desert:--barren land(-ness), salt (land).
from 3898 (in the sense of fighting); a battle (i.e. the engagement); generally, war (i.e. warfare):--battle, fight(-ing), war((-rior)).

a primitive root; properly, to be smooth, i.e. (by implication) to escape (as if by slipperiness); causatively, to release or rescue; specifically, to bring forth young, emit sparks:--deliver (self), escape, lay, leap out, let alone, let go, preserve, save, X speedily, X surely.
from 4422, cement (from its plastic smoothness):--clay.
from 4423 and 3050; (whom) Jah has delivered; Melatjah, a Gibeonite:--Melatiah.
from 4449 (in the sense of cropping (compare 4135)); a head of grain (as cut off):--ear.

a primitive root; to reign; inceptively, to ascend the throne; causatively, to induct into royalty; hence (by implication) to take counsel:--consult, X indeed, be (make, set a, set up) king, be (make) queen, (begin to, make to) reign(-ing), rule, X surely.
from 4427; a king:--king, royal.
the same as 4428; king; Melek, the name of two Israelites:--Melech, Hammelech (by including the article).
(Aramaic) corresponding to 4428; a king:--king, royal.

from 4427; Molek (i.e. king), the chief deity of the Ammonites:--Molech. Compare 4445.

from 3920; a snare:--trap.
a form of 4436; queen; Milcah, the name of a Hebrewess and of an Israelite:--Milcah.
feminine of 4428; a queen:--queen.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 4438; dominion (abstractly or concretely):--kingdom, kingly, realm, reign.
or malkuth {mal-kooth'}; or (in plural) malkuyah {mal-koo-yah'}; from 4427; a rule; concretely, a dominion:--empire, kingdom, realm, reign, royal.
from 4428 and 410; king of (i.e. appointed by) God; Malkiel, an Israelite:--Malchiel.
patronymical from 4439; a Malkielite or descendant of Malkiel:--Malchielite.
or Malkiyahuw (Jer. 38:6), {mal-kee-yaw'-hoo}; from 4428 and 3050; king of (i.e. appointed by) Jah; Malkijah, the name of ten Israelites:--Malchiah, Malchijah.
from 4428 and 6664; king of right; Malki-Tsedek, an early king in Palestine:--Melchizedek.

or Milkowm {mil-kome'}; from 4428 for 4432; Malcam or Milcom, the national idol of the Ammonites:--Malcham, Milcom.
from 4427; a queen:--queen.

a primitive root; to speak (mostly poetical) or say:--say, speak, utter.

from 4448; talkative; Milalai, an Israelite:--Milalai.

from 3947; transitively (in dual) the jaws (as taking food); intransitively, spoil (and captives) (as taken):--booty, jaws, prey.

or malqach {mal-kawkh'}; from 3947; (only in dual) tweezers:--snuffers, tongs.

from 4048 (in the sense of depositing); a granary:--barn.
from 4058; a measure:--measure.
or (transp.) Mowmukan (Esth. 1:16) {mo-moo-kawn'}; of Persian derivation; Memucan or Momucan, a Persian satrap:--Memucan.
from 4191; a mortal disease; concretely, a corpse:--death.
from an unused root meaning to alienate; a mongrel, i.e. born of a Jewish father and a heathen mother:--bastard.

a form of 4467 and equiv. to it:--kingdom, reign.
from 4537; mixture, i.e. (specifically) wine mixed (with water or spices):--drink-offering, mixed wine.
from an unused root meaning to grieve; sorrow:--bitterness.
from 4754(in the sense of vigor); lusty; Mamre, an Amorite:--Mamre.
from 4843; a bitterness, i.e. (figuratively) calamity:--bitterness.
from 4886, in the sense of expansion; outspread (i.e. with outstretched wings):--anointed.
from 4910; a ruler or (abstractly) rule:--dominion, that ruled.
feminine of 4474; rule; also (concretely in plural) a realm or a ruler:--dominion, government, power, to rule.
from the same as 4943; a possession:--breeding.
from 4985; something sweet (literally or figuratively):--(most) sweet.
from 4100; literally, a whatness (so to speak), i.e. manna (so called from the question about it):--manna.

or minniy {min-nee'}; or minney (constructive plural) {min-nay'}; (Isaiah 30:11); for 4482; properly, a part of; hence (prepositionally), from or out of in many senses (as follows):--above, after, among, at, because of, by (reason of), from (among), in, X neither, X nor, (out) of, over, since, X then, through, X whether, with.

from an unused root meaning to apportion; a part; hence, a musical chord (as parted into strings):--in (the same) (Psalm 68:23), stringed instrument (Psalm 150:4), whereby (Psalm 45:8 (defective plural)).

from 5059; a satire:--music.

a primitive root; properly, to weigh out; by implication, to allot or constitute officially; also to enumerate or enroll:--appoint, count, number, prepare, set, tell.
from 4487; properly, a fixed weight or measured amount, i.e. (techn.) a maneh or mina:--maneh, pound.
from 4487; properly, something weighed out, i.e. (figuratively) a portion of time, i.e. an instance:--time.
from 4487; properly, something weighed out, i.e. (generally) a division; specifically (of food) a ration; also a lot:--such things as belonged, part, portion.
from 5090; the driving (of a chariot):--driving.

or mnuchah {men-oo-khaw'}; feminine of 4495; repose or (adverbially) peacefully; figuratively, consolation (specifically, matrimony); hence (concretely) an abode:--comfortable, ease, quiet, rest(-ing place), still.

from 5162; comforter; Menachem, an Israelite:--Menahem.
from 5117; rest; Manachath, the name of an Edomite and of a place in Moab:--Manahath.
from 4487; the Apportioner, i.e. Fate (as an idol):--number.
of foreign derivation; Minni, an Armenian province:--Minni.
from 4480 and 3225; from (the) right hand; Minjamin, the name of two Israelites:--Miniamin. Compare 4326.
(Aramaic) from 4483; enumeration:--number.
from the same as 4482; enumeration; Minnith, a place East of the Jordan:--Minnith.
from 5239; completion, i.e. (in produce) wealth:--perfection.
a primitive root; to debar (negatively or positively) from benefit or injury:--deny, keep (back), refrain, restrain, withhold.
or maniul {man-ool'}; from 5274; a bolt:--lock.
from 5274; a bolt:--shoe.
from 5276; a delicacy:--dainty.
from 5128; a sistrum (so called from its rattling sound):--cornet.
from 5352; a sacrificial basin (for holding blood):--bowl.

from 4519; a Menashshite or descendant of Menashsheh:--of Manasseh, Manassites.
from 4487; an allotment (by courtesy, law or providence):--portion.
or mic {mees}; from 4549; properly, a burden (as causing to faint), i.e. a tax in the form of forced labor:--discomfited, levy, task(-master), tribute(-tary).
from 4549; fainting, i.e. (figuratively) disconsolate:--is afflicted.

plural masculine mcibbiym {mes-ib-beem'}; or feminine mcibbowth {mes-ib-bohth'}; from 5437; a divan (as enclosing the room); abstractly (adverbial) around:--that compass about, (place) round about, at table.
from 5462; a fastener, i.e. (of a person) a smith, (of a thing) a prison:--prison, smith.
from 5462; something enclosing, i.e. a margin (of a region, of a panel); concretely, a stronghold:--border, close place, hole.
from 3245; a foundation:--foundation.
from the same as 5468; a colonnade or internal portico (from its rows of pillars):--porch.
a primitive root; to dissolve:--make to consume away, (make to) melt, water.
from 4549 (in the sense of flowing); abundance, i.e. (adverbially) liberally: tribute.
from 5254; a testing, of men (judicial) or of God (querulous):--temptation, trial.
the same as 4531; Massah, a place in the Desert:--Massah.
apparently from an unused root meaning to cover; a veil:--vail.
for 4881; a hedge:--thorn hedge.
from 5255 in the sense of staving off; a cordon, (adverbially) or (as a) military barrier:--broken down.
from 5503; trade:--traffic.
a primitive root; to mix, especially wine (with spices):--mingle.
from 4537; a mixture, i.e. of wine with spices:--mixture.
from 5526; a cover, i.e. veil:--covering, curtain, hanging.
from 5526; a covering, i.e. garniture:--covering.

from 5258; properly, a pouring over, i.e. fusion of metal (especially a cast image); by implication, a libation, i.e. league; concretely a coverlet (as if poured out):--covering, molten (image), vail.
from 5531; indigent:--poor (man).
by transp. from 3664; a magazine: --store(-house), treasure.
from 4542; indigence:--scarceness.
from 5259 in the sense of spreading out; something expanded, i.e. the warp in a loom (as stretched out to receive the woof):--web.
from 5549; a thoroughfare (as turnpiked), literally or figuratively; specifically a viaduct, a staircase:--causeway, course, highway, path, terrace.
from 5549; a thoroughfare (as turnpiked):--highway.
or micmer {mis-mare'}; also (feminine) macmrah {mas-mer-aw'}; or micmrah {mis-mer-aw'}; or even masmrah (Eccles. 12:11) {mas-mer-aw'}; from 5568; a peg (as bristling from the surface):--nail.
a primitive root; to liquefy; figuratively, to waste (with disease), to faint (with fatigue, fear or grief):--discourage, faint, be loosed, melt (away), refuse, X utterly.
from 5265; a departure (from striking the tents), i.e. march (not necessarily a single day's travel); by implication, a station (or point of departure):--journey(-ing).
from 5265 in the sense of projecting; a missile (spear or arrow); also a quarry (whence stones are, as it were, ejected):--before it was brought, dart.
' from 5582; a balustrade (for stairs):--pillar.
from 5594; a lamentation:--lamentation, one mourneth, mourning, wailing.
from an unused root meaning to collect; fodder:--provender.
from 5596; a veil (as spread out):--kerchief.
from 5596; scruf (as spreading over the surface):--scab.

from 5608; a number, definite (arithmetical) or indefinite (large, innumerable; small, a few); also (abstractly) narration:--+ abundance, account, X all, X few, (in-)finite, (certain) number(-ed), tale, telling, + time.
the same as 4457; number; Mispar, an Israelite:--Mizpar. Compare 4559.
feminine of 4437; enumeration; Mispereth, an Israelite:--Mispereth. Compare 4458.
a primitive root; to sunder, i.e. (transitively) set apart, or (reflex.) apostatize:--commit, deliver.
from 3256; admonition:--instruction.
from 631; a band:--bond.
from 5641; a refuge:--covert.
from 5641; properly, a hider, i.e. (abstractly) a hiding, i.e. aversion:--hid.
from 5641; properly, a concealer, i.e. a covert:--secret(-ly, place).
from 5647; an act:--work.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 4566; an act:--work.
from 5666; properly, compact (part of soil), i.e. loam:--clay.

or feminine mapabarah {mah-ab-aw-raw'}; from 5674; a crossing-place (of a river, a ford; of a mountain, a pass); abstractly, a transit, i.e. (figuratively) overwhelming:--ford, place where...pass, passage.
or feminine mapgalah {mah-gaw-law'}; from the same as 5696; a track (literally or figuratively); also a rampart (as circular):--going, path, trench, way((-side)).
a primitive root; to waver:--make to shake, slide, slip.
from 5710; ornamental; Maadai, an Israelite:--Maadai.
from 5710 and 3050; ornament of Jah; Maadjah, an Israelite:--Maadiah. Compare 4153.
or (feminine) maadannah {mah-ad-an-naw'}; from 5727; a delicacy or (abstractly) pleasure (adverbially, cheerfully):--dainty, delicately, delight.
by transitive from 6029; a bond, i.e. group:--influence.
from 5737; a (weeding) hoe:--mattock.
(Aramaic) or m(ae (Aramaic) {meh-aw'}; corresponding to 4578; only in plural the bowels:--belly.

from an unused root probably meaning to be soft; used only in plural the intestines, or (collectively) the abdomen, figuratively, sympathy; by implication, a vest; by extens. the stomach, the uterus (or of men, the seat of generation), the heart (figuratively):--belly, bowels, X heart, womb.
feminine of 4578; the belly, i.e. (figuratively) interior:--gravel.
from 5746; a cake of bread (with 3934 a table- buffoon, i.e. parasite):--cake, feast.
(also mauwz {maw-ooz'}); or mahoz {maw-oze'} (also ma,uz {maw-ooz'}; from 5810; a fortified place; figuratively, a defence:--force, fort(-ress), rock, strength(-en), (X most) strong (hold).
from 4600; oppressed; Maok, a Philistine:--Maoch.

or maiyn (1 Chronicles 4:41) {maw-een'}; from the same as 5772; an abode, of God (the Tabernacle or the Temple), men (their home) or animals (their lair); hence, a retreat (asylum):--den, dwelling((-)place), habitation.
the same as 4583; a residence; Maon, the name of an Israelite and of a place in Palestine:--Maon, Maonites. Compare 1010, 4586.
or msonah {meh-o-naw'}; feminine of 4583, and meaning the same:--den, habitation, (dwelling) place, refuge.
or Msiyniy {meh-ee-nee'}; probably patrial from 4584; a Meunite, or inhabitant of Maon (only in plural):--Mehunim(-s), Meunim.
plural of 4585; habitative; Meonothai, an Israelite:--Meonothai.
from 5774 in the sense of covering with shade (compare 4155); darkness:--dimness.
from 5783; nakedness, i.e. (in plural) the pudenda:--nakedness.
or Ma.azyahuw {mah-az-yaw'-hoo}; probably from 5756 (in the sense of protection) and 3050; rescue of Jah; Maazjah, the name of two Israelites:--Maaziah.

a primitive root; properly, to pare off, i.e. lessen; intransitively, to be (or causatively, to make) small or few (or figuratively, ineffective):--suffer to decrease, diminish, (be, X borrow a, give, make) few (in number, -ness), gather least (little), be (seem) little, (X give the) less, be minished, bring to nothing.
or miat {meh-awt'}; from 4591; a little or few (often adverbial or compar.):--almost (some, very) few(-er, -est), lightly, little (while), (very) small (matter, thing), some, soon, X very.
passive adjective of 4591; thinned (as to the edge), i.e. sharp:--wrapped up.
from 5844; a vestment:--garment.
from 5848; a cloak:--mantle.
from 5753; a pile of rubbish (as contorted), i.e. a ruin (compare 5856):--heap.
probably from 4578; sympathetic; Maai, an Israelite:--Maai.
from 4603 in the sense of covering; a robe (i.e. upper and outer garment):--cloke, coat, mantle, robe.

or ma ynow (Psa. 114:8) {mah-yen-o'}; or (feminine) ma yanah {mah-yaw-naw'}; from 5869 (as a denominative in the sense of a spring); a fountain (also collectively), figuratively, a source (of satisfaction):--fountain, spring, well.
a primitive root; to press, i.e. to pierce, emasculate, handle:--bruised, stuck, be pressed.

or Mamakath (Josh. 13:13) {mah-ak-awth'}; from 4600; depression; Maakah (or Maakath), the name of a place in Syria, also of a Mesopotamian, of three Israelites, and of four Israelitesses and one Syrian woman:--Maachah, Maachathites. See also 1038.
patrial from 4601; a Maakathite, or inhabitant of Maakah:--Maachathite.
a primitive root; properly, to cover up; used only figuratively, to act covertly, i.e. treacherously:--transgress, (commit, do a) trespass(-ing).
from 4603; treachery, i.e. sin:--falsehood, grievously, sore, transgression, trespass, X very.
from 5927; properly, the upper part, used only adverbially with prefix upward, above, overhead, from the top, etc.:-- above, exceeding(-ly), forward, on (X very) high, over, up(-on, -ward), very.
(Aramaic) from 5954; (only in plural as singular) the setting (of the sun):--going down.
from 5927; a raising (of the hands):--lifting up.

from 5927; an elevation, i.e. (concretely) acclivity or platform; abstractly (the relation or state) a rise or (figuratively) priority:--ascent, before, chiefest, cliff, that goeth up, going up, hill, mounting up, stairs.

feminine of 4608; elevation, i.e. the act (literally, a journey to a higher place, figuratively, a thought arising), or (concretely) the condition (literally, a step or grade-mark, figuratively, a superiority of station); specifically a climactic progression (in certain Psalms):--things that come up, (high) degree, deal, go up, stair, step, story.
from 4608 and (the plural of) 6137; Steep of Scorpions, a place in the Desert:--Maaleh- accrabim, the ascent (going up) of Akrabbim.
from 5953; an act (good or bad):--doing, endeavour, invention, work.
from 5975; (figuratively) a position:--attendance, office, place, state.
from 5975; literally, a foothold:--standing.
from 6006; burdensomeness:--burdensome.
from 6009; a deep:--deep, depth.

from 6030; properly, heed, i.e. purpose; used only adverbially, on account of (as a motive or an aim), teleologically, in order that:--because of, to the end (intent) that, for (to,... 's sake), + lest, that, to.
from 6030; a reply (favorable or contradictory):--answer, X himself.
from 6031, in the sense of depression or tilling; a furrow:--+ acre, furrow.
from 6095; closure; Maats, an Israelite:--Maaz.
from 6087; anguish:--sorrow.
from an usused root meaning to hew; an axe:--ax, tongs.
from 6113; objectively, a hindrance:--restraint.
from 6113; subjectively, control:--rule.
from an unused root meaning to repress; a parapet:--battlement.
from 6140; a crook (in a road):--crooked thing.
from 6168; a nude place, i.e. (literally) the pudenda, or (figuratively) a vacant space:--nakedness, proportion.
from 6148, in the sense of trading; traffic; by implication, mercantile goods:--market, merchandise.
or (feminine) maearabah {mah-ar-aw-baw'}; from 6150, in the sense of shading; the west (as a region of the evening sun):--west.
from 6168; a nude place, i.e. a common:--meadows.
feminine of 4629; an open spot:--army (from the margin).
from 5783; a cavern (as dark):--cave, den, hole.
the same as 4631; cave; Mearah, a place in Palestine:-- Mearah.
from 6186; an arrangement, i.e. (figuratively) mental disposition:--preparation.
feminine of 4633; an arrangement; concretely, a pile; specifically a military array:--army, fight, be set in order, ordered place, rank, row.
from 6186; an arrangement, i.e. (concretely) a pile (of loaves):--row, shewbread.
from 6191, in the sense of stripping; bare:--naked.
from 6206; violence:--terror.
a form of 4630; waste; Maarath, a place in Palestine:--Maarath.

from 6213; an action (good or bad); generally, a transaction; abstractly, activity; by implication, a product (specifically, a poem) or (generally) property:--act, art, + bakemeat, business, deed, do(-ing), labor, thing made, ware of making, occupation, thing offered, operation, possession, X well, ((handy-, needle-, net-))work(ing, - manship), wrought.
from 6213; operative; Maasai, an Israelite:--Maasiai.
or Maaseyahuw {mah-as-ay-yaw'-hoo}; from 4639 and 3050; work of Jah; Maasejah, the name of sixteen Israelites:--Maaseiah.
from 6231; oppression:--oppression, X oppressor.
or maasar {mah-as-ar'}; and (in plural) feminine maasrah {mah-as-raw'}; from 6240; a tenth; especially a tithe:-- tenth (part), tithe(-ing).
of Egyptian origin: Moph, the capital of Lower Egypt:-- Memphis. Compare 5297.
from 6293; an object of attack:--mark.
from 5301; a breathing out (of life), i.e. expiring:--giving up.
from 5301; the bellows (i.e. blower) of a forge:--bellows.
or Mphibosheth {mef-ee-bo'-sheth}; probably from 6284 and 1322; dispeller of shame (i.e. of Baal); Mephibosheth, the name of two Israelites:--Mephibosheth.
a plural apparently from 5130; wavings; Muppim, an Israelite:--Muppim. Compare 8206.
from 6327; a breaker, i.e. mallet:--maul.
from 5307; a falling off, i.e. chaff; also something pendulous, i.e. a flap:--flake, refuse.
from 6381; a miracle:--wondrous work.
from 6385; a classification:--division.
or mappelah {map-pay-law'}; from 5307; something fallen, i.e. a ruin:--ruin(-ous).
from 6403; an escape:--escape.
from 6426; a terror, i.e. an idol:--idol.
from an unused root meaning to balance; a poising:--balancing.
from 5307; fall, i.e. decadence; concretely, a ruin; specifically a carcase:--carcase, fall, ruin.
or (feminine) miph.alah {mif-aw-law'}; from 6466; a performance:--work.
from 5310; a smiting to pieces:--slaughter.
from 5310; a smiter, i.e. a war club:--battle ax.
from 6485; an appointment, i.e. mandate; concretely, a designated spot; specifically, a census:--appointed place, commandment, number.
the same as 4662; assignment; Miphkad, the name of a gate in Jerusalem:--Miphkad.
from 6555; a break (in the shore), i.e. a haven:--breach.
from 6561; properly, a fracture, i.e. joint (vertebrae) of the neck:--neck.
from 6566; an expansion:--that which...spreadest forth, spreading.
from 6585; a stride, i.e. (by euphemism) the crotch:--buttocks.
from 6605; an opener, i.e. a key:--key.
from 6605; an aperture, i.e. (figuratively) utterance:--opening.
from the same as 6620; a stretcher, i.e. a sill:--threshold.
or mowts (Zephaniah 2:2) {motes}; from 4160; chaff (as pressed out, i.e. winnowed or (rather) threshed loose):--chaff.

a primitive root; properly, to come forth to, i.e. appear or exist; transitively, to attain, i.e. find or acquire; figuratively, to occur, meet or be present:--+ be able, befall, being, catch, X certainly, (cause to) come (on, to, to hand), deliver, be enough (cause to) find(-ing, occasion, out), get (hold upon), X have (here), be here, hit, be left, light (up-)on, meet (with), X occasion serve, (be) present, ready, speed, suffice, take hold on.
from 5324; a fixed spot; figuratively, an office, a military post:--garrison, station, place where...stood.
from 5324; a station, i.e. military post:--mount.
or mitstsabah {mits-tsaw-baw'}; feminine of 4673; a military guard:--army, garrison.
feminine (causatively) participle of 5324; something stationed, i.e. a column or (memorial stone); by analogy, an idol:--garrison, (standing) image, pillar.
apparently from 4672 and 3050; found of Jah; Metsobajah, a place in Palestine:--Mesobaite.
from 5324; something stationary, i.e. a monumental stone; also the stock of a tree:--pillar, substance.
or mtsad {mets-awd'}; or (feminine) mtsadah {mets-aw-daw'}; from 6679; a fastness (as a covert of ambush):--castle, fort, (strong) hold, munition.
a primitive root; to suck out; by implication, to drain, to squeeze out:--suck, wring (out).
active participle feminine of 4680; drained; Motsah, a place in Palestine:--Mozah.

from 4711 in the sense of greedily devouring for sweetness; properly, sweetness; concretely, sweet (i.e. not soured or bittered with yeast); specifically, an unfermented cake or loaf, or (elliptically) the festival of Passover (because no leaven was then used):--unleaved (bread, cake), without leaven.
from 5327; a quarrel:--contention, debate, strife.
from 6670; a whinnying (through impatience for battle or lust):--neighing.

or (feminine) mtsowdah {mets-o-daw'}; or mtsodah {mets-o-daw'}; from 6679; a net (for capturing animals or fishes):--also (by interchange for 4679) a fastness or (beseiging) tower:--bulwark, hold, munition, net, snare.

or (feminine) mtsuwdah {mets-oo-daw'}; or mtsudah {mets-oo-daw'}; for 4685; a net, or (abstractly) capture; also a fastness; --castle, defense, fort(-ress), (strong) hold, be hunted, net, snare, strong place.
from 6680; a command, whether human or divine (collectively, the Law):--(which was) commanded(-ment), law, ordinance, precept.
or mtsolah {mets-o-law'}; also mtsuwlah {mets-oo-law'}; or mtsulah {mets-oo-law'}; from the same as 6683; a deep place (of water or mud):--bottom, deep, depth.
from 6693; a narrow place, i.e. (abstractly and figuratively) confinement or disability:--anguish, distress, straitness.
or matsuq {maw-tsook'}; from 6693; something narrow, i.e. a column or hilltop:--pillar, situate.
or mtsuqah {mets-oo-kaw'}; feminine of 4690; narrowness, i.e. (figuratively) trouble:--anguish, distress.

or matsuwr {maw-tsoor'}; from 6696; something hemming in, i.e. (objectively) a mound (of besiegers), (abstractly) a siege, (figuratively) distress; or (subjectively) a fastness:--besieged, bulwark, defence, fenced, fortress, siege, strong (hold), tower.
the same as 4692 in the sense of a limit; Egypt (as the border of Palestine):--besieged places, defense, fortified.

or mtsurah {mets-oo-raw'}; feminine of 4692; a hemming in, i.e. (objectively) a mound (of siege), or (subjectively) a rampart (of protection), (abstractly) fortification:--fenced (city, fort, munition, strong hold.
from 5327; a quarrel:--that contended.
from an unused root meaning to be clear, i.e. conspicuous; the forehead (as open and prominent):--brow, forehead, + impudent.
from the same as 4696; a shin-piece of armor (as prominent), only plural:--greaves.
from 6750; a tinkler, i.e. a bell:--bell.
from 6751; shade:--bottom.
from 6750; (only dual) double tinklers, i.e. cymbals:--cymbals.
from 6801; a tiara, i.e. official turban (of a king or high priest):--diadem, mitre.
from 3331; a couch:--bed.
from 6805; a step; figuratively, companionship:--going, step.
feminine of 4705; properly, littleness; concretely, diminutive:--little.
from 6819; petty (in size or number); adverbially, a short (time):--little one (while), small.
the same as 4705; Mitsar, a peak of Lebanon:--Mizar.
from 6822; an observatory, especially for military purposes:--watch tower.
the same as 4707; Mitspeh, the name of five places in Palestine:--Mizpeh, watch tower. Compare 4709.
feminine of 4708; Mitspah, the name of two places in Palestine:--Mitspah. (This seems rather to be only an orthographic variation of 4708 when "in pause".)
from 6845; a secret (place or thing, perhaps, treasure):--hidden thing.
a primitive root; to suck:--milk.
from 6896; something tight, i.e. (figuratively) trouble:--distress, pain, strait.
from 4714; a Mitsrite, or inhabitant of Mitsrajim:--Egyptian, of Egypt.
dual of 4693; Mitsrajim, i.e. Upper and Lower Egypt:--Egypt, Egyptians, Mizraim.
from 6884; a crucible:--fining pot.
from 4743; properly, a melting, i.e. putridity:-- rottenness, stink.
from 5344; properly, a perforatrix, i.e. a hammer (as piercing):--hammer.
from 5344; properly, a perforator, i.e. a hammer (as piercing); also (intransitively) a perforation, i.e. a quarry:--hammer, hole.
from the same as 5348 in the denominative sense of herding (compare 5349); fold; Makkedah, a place in Palestine:-- Makkedah.

or miqqdash (Exod. 15:17) {mik-ked-awsh'}; from 6942; a consecrated thing or place, especially, a palace, sanctuary (whether of Jehovah or of idols) or asylum:--chapel, hallowed part, holy place, sanctuary.
or (feminine) maqhelah {mak-hay-law'}; from 6950; an assembly:--congregation.
plural of 4721 (feminine); assemblies; Makheloth, a place in the Desert:--Makheloth.

or miqveh (1 Kings 10:28) {mik-vay'}; or miqvet (2 Chron. 1:16) {mik-vay'}; from 6960; something waited for, i.e. confidence (objective or subjective); also a collection, i.e. (of water) a pond, or (of men and horses) a caravan or drove:--abiding, gathering together, hope, linen yarn, plenty (of water), pool.
feminine of 4723; a collection, i.e. (of water) a reservoir:--ditch.

or maqom {maw-kome'}; also (feminine) mqowmah {mek-o-mah'}; or mqomah {mek-o-mah'}; from 6965; properly, a standing, i.e. a spot; but used widely of a locality (general or specific); also (figuratively) of a condition (of body or mind):--country, X home, X open, place, room, space, X whither(-soever).

or maqor {maw-kore'}; from 6979; properly, something dug, i.e. a (general) source (of water, even when naturally flowing; also of tears, blood (by euphemism, of the female pudenda); figuratively, of happiness, wisdom, progeny):--fountain, issue, spring, well(-spring).
from 3947; reception:--taking.
from 3947; something received, i.e. merchandise (purchased):--ware.
from 6999; something to fume (incense) on i.e. a hearth place:--to burn...upon.
feminine of 4729; something to fume (incense) in, i.e. a coal-pan:--censer.
or (feminine) maqqlah {mak-kel-aw'}; from an unused root meaning apparently to germinate; a shoot, i.e. stick (with leaves on, or for walking, striking, guiding, divining):--rod, ((hand- ))staff.
(or perhaps mik-kel-ohth') plural of (feminine) 4731; rods; Mikloth, a place in the Desert:--Mikloth.
from 7038 in the sense of taking in; an asylum (as a receptacle):--refuge.
from 7049; a sculpture (probably in bas-relief):--carved (figure), carving, graving.
from 7069; something bought, i.e. property, but only livestock; abstractly, acquisition:--cattle, flock, herd, possession, purchase, substance.
feminine of 4735; properly, a buying, i.e. acquisition; concretely, a piece of property (land or living); also the sum paid:--(he that is) bought, possession, piece, purchase.
from 4735 and 3050; possession of Jah; Miknejah, an Israelite:--Mikneiah.
from 7080; an augury:--divination.
from 7112; end; Makats, a place in Palestine:--Makaz.
or maqtsoa {mak-tso-ah}; or (feminine) maqtso-ah {mak-tso-aw'}; from 7106 in the denominative sense of bending; an angle or recess:--corner, turning.
from 7106; a scraper, i.e. a carving chisel:--plane.
from 7106 in the denominative sense of bending; an angle:--corner.
' a primitive root; to melt; figuratively, to flow, dwindle, vanish:--consume away, be corrupt, dissolve, pine away.
from 7121; something called out, i.e. a public meeting (the act, the persons, or the place); also a rehearsal:--assembly, calling, convocation, reading.
from 7136; something met with, i.e. an accident or fortune:--something befallen, befalleth, chance, event, hap(-peneth).
from 7136; properly, something meeting, i.e. a frame (of timbers):--building.
from the same as 7119; a cooling off:--X summer.
from 7185 in the sense of knotting up round and hard; something turned (rounded), i.e. a curl (of tresses):--X well (set) hair.
feminine of 4748; rounded work, i.e. moulded by hammering (repousse):--beaten (out of one piece, work), upright, whole piece.
denominative from 7180; literally, a cucumbered field, i.e. a cucumber patch:--garden of cucumbers.

or (feminine) marah {maw-raw'}; from 4843; bitter (literally or figuratively); also (as noun) bitterness, or (adverbially) bitterly:--+ angry, bitter(-ly, -ness), chafed, discontented, X great, heavy.
from 4843 in its original sense of distillation; a drop:--drop.
or mowr {more}; from 4843; myrrh (as distilling in drops, and also as bitter):--myrrh.
a primitive root; to rebel; hence (through the idea of maltreating) to whip, i.e. lash (self with wings, as the ostrich in running):--be filthy, lift up self.
for 4751 feminine; bitter; Mara, a symbolic name of Naomi:--Mara.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to 4754 in the sense of domineering; a master:--lord, Lord.
of foreign derivation; Merodak-Baladan, a Babylonian king:--Merodach-baladan. Compare 4781.

from 7200; a view (the act of seeing); also an appearance (the thing seen), whether (real) a shape (especially if handsome, comeliness; often plural the looks), or (mental) a vision:--X apparently, appearance(-reth), X as soon as beautiful(-ly), countenance, fair, favoured, form, goodly, to look (up) on (to), look(-eth), pattern, to see, seem, sight, visage, vision.
feminine of 4758; a vision; also (causatively) a mirror:--looking glass, vision.
apparently feminine passive causative participle of 7200; something conspicuous, i.e. the craw of a bird (from its prominence):--crop.
denominative from 7218; properly, headship, i.e. (plural for collective) dominion:--principality.
or Mareshah {mar-ay-shaw'}; formed like 4761; summit; Mareshah, the name of two Israelites and of a place in Palestine:--Mareshah.
formed like 4761; properly, a headpiece, i.e. (plural for adverbial) at (or as) the head-rest (or pillow):--bolster, head, pillow. Compare 4772.
from 7231; increase; Merab, a daughter of Saul:--Merab.
from 7234; a coverlet:--covering of tapestry.
from 7235; properly, increasing; as noun, greatness, or (adverbially) greatly:--great, increase.
from 7235; abundance, i.e. a great quantity:--much.
from 7235; a multitude; also offspring; specifically interest (on capital):--greatest part, greatness, increase, multitude.
from 7257; a reclining place, i.e. fold (for flocks):--couching place, place to lie down.
from an unused root meaning to tie up; a stall (for cattle):--X fat(-ted), stall.
from 7280; a resting place:--rest.
denominative from 7272; (plural for collective) a footpiece, i.e. (adverbially) at the foot, or (direct.) the foot itself:--feet. Compare 4763.
from 7275; a stone-heap:--sling.
from 7280; rest:--refreshing.
a primitive root; to rebel:--rebel(-lious).
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to 4775; rebellion:--rebellion.
from 4775; rebellion:--rebellion.
the same as 4777; Mered, an Israelite:--Mered.
(Aramaic) from the same as 4776; rebellious:--rebellious.
from 4775; rebelliousness:--X rebellious.
of foreign derivation; Merodak, a Babylonian idol:--Merodach. Compare 4757.
of foreign derivation; Mordecai, an Israelite:--Mordecai.
from 7291; persecuted:--persecuted.

a primitive root; to be (causatively, make) bitter (or unpleasant); (figuratively) to rebel (or resist; causatively, to provoke):--bitter, change, be disobedient, disobey, grievously, provocation, provoke(-ing), (be) rebel (against, -lious).
the same as 4751 feminine; bitter; Marah, a place in the Desert:--Marah.
from 4843; bitterness, i.e. (figuratively) trouble:--grief.
a form of 4786; trouble:--bitterness.
from 7300 in the sense of maltreatment; an outcast; (abstractly) destitution:--cast out, misery.
of uncertain derivation; Meroz, a place in Palestine:--Meroz.
from 4799; bruised, i.e. emasculated:--broken.

from 7311; altitude, i.e. concretely (an elevated place), abstractly (elevation, figuratively (elation), or adverbially (aloft):--(far) above, dignity, haughty, height, (most, on) high (one, place), loftily, upward.
formed like 4791; height; Merom, a lake in Palestine:--Merom.
from 7323; a run (the trial of speed):--race.
or mrutsah {mer-oo-tsaw'}; feminine of 4793; a race (the act), whether the manner or the progress:--course, running. Compare 4835.
from 4838; properly, rubbed; but used abstractly, a rubbing (with perfumery):--purification.
plural of 4751 feminine; bitter springs; Maroth, a place in Palestine:--Maroth.
from an unused root meaning to scream; a cry, i.e. (of job), a revel:--banquet.
formed like 4797; a cry, i.e. (of grief) a lamentation:--mourning.
a primitive root; properly, to soften by rubbing or pressure; hence (medicinally) to apply as an emollient:--lay for a plaister.
from 7337; enlargement, either literally (an open space, usually in a good sense), or figuratively (liberty):--breadth, large place (room).
: from 7368; remoteness, i.e. (concretely) a distant place; often (adverbially) from afar:--(a-, dwell in, very) far (country, off). See also 1023.
from 7370; a stew-pan:--fryingpan.
a primitive root; to polish; by implication, to make bald (the head), to gall (the shoulder); also, to sharpen:--bright, furbish, (have his) hair (be) fallen off, peeled, pluck off (hair).
(Aramaic) corresponding to 4803; to pull off:--be plucked.
from 4784; bitterness, i.e. (figuratively) rebellion; concretely, bitter, or rebellious:--bitter, (most) rebel(-lion, -lious).
from 4754 in the sense of grossness, through the idea of domineering (compare 4756); stall-fed; often (as noun) a beeve:--fat (fed) beast (cattle, -ling).
from 7378 and 1168; quarreller of Baal, Merib-Baal, an epithet of Gideon:--Merib-baal. Compare 4810.
from 7378; quarrel:--provocation, strife.
the same as 4808; Meribah, the name of two places in the Desert:--Meribah.
from 4805 and 1168; rebellion of (i.e. against) Baal; Meri-Baal, an epithet of Gideon:--Meri-baal. Compare 4807.
from 4784; rebellion; Merajah, an Israelite:--Meraiah. Compare 3236.
plural of 4811; rebellious; Merajoth, the name of two Israelites:--Meraioth.
from 4805; rebelliously; Mirjam, the name of two Israelitesses:--Miriam.
from 4843; bitterness, i.e. (figuratively) grief:--bitterness.
from 4843; bitter, i.e. poisonous:--bitter.
perhaps from 7401; softness, i.e. (figuratively) fear:--faintness.
from 7392; a chariot; also a seat (in a vehicle):--chariot, covering, saddle.
feminine of 4817; a chariot:--chariot. See also 1024.
from 7402; a mart:--merchandise.
from 7411 in the sense of deceiving; fraud:--craft, deceit(-ful, -fully), false, feigned, guile, subtilly, treachery.
the same as 4820; Mirmah, an Israelite:--Mirma.
plural from 7311; heights; Meremoth, the name of two Israelites:--Meremoth.
from 7429; abasement (the act or the thing):--tread (down)-ing, (to be) trodden (down) under foot.
patrial from an unused noun; a Meronothite, or inhabitant of some (otherwise unknown) Meronoth.:--Meronothite.
of foreign derivation; Meres, a Persian:--Meres.
of foreign derivation; Marsena, a Persian:--Marsena.
from 7489; used as (abstract) noun, wickedness:--do mischief.
from 7462 in the sense of companionship; a friend:--companion, friend.
from 7462 in the sense of feeding; pasture (the place or the act); also the haunt of wild animals:--feeding place, pasture.
from 7462 in the sense of feeding; pasturage; concretely, a flock:--flock, pasture.
from 7477; perhaps, earthquake; Maralah, a place in Palestine:--Maralah.

from 7495; properly, curative, i.e. literally (concretely) a medicine, or (abstractly) a cure; figuratively (concretely) deliverance, or (abstractly) placidity:--((in-))cure(-able), healing(-lth), remedy, sound, wholesome, yielding.
from 7515; muddled water:--that which...have fouled.
a primitive root; properly, to press, i.e. (figuratively) to be pungent or vehement; to irritate:--embolden, be forcible, grievous, sore.
from 7533; oppression:--violence. See also 4794.
from 7527; an awl:--aul.
from 7528; a pavement:--pavement.
a primitive root; to polish; by implication, to sharpen; also to rinse:--bright, furbish, scour.
from 4838; soup (as if a rinsing):--broth. See also 6564.
from 7543; a spicy herb:--X sweet.
feminine of 4840; abstractly, a seasoning (with spicery); concretely, an unguent-kettle (for preparing spiced oil):--pot of ointment, X well.
from 7543; an aromatic unguent; also an unguent-pot:--prepared by the apothecaries' art, compound, ointment.

a primitive root; properly, to trickle (see 4752); but used only as a denominative from 4751; to be (causatively, make) bitter (literally or figuratively):--(be, be in, deal, have, make) bitter(-ly, - ness), be moved with choler, (be, have sorely, it) grieved(-eth), provoke, vex.
or mrowr {mer-ore'}; from 4843; a bitter herb:-- bitter(-ness).
from 4843; bile (from its bitterness):--gall.
or mrowrah {mer-o-raw'}; from 4843; properly, bitterness; concretely, a bitter thing; specifically bile; also venom (of a serpent):--bitter (thing), gall.
from 4843; bitter; Merari, an Israelite:--Merari. See also 4848.
from 4847; a Merarite (collectively), or decendants of Merari:--Merarites.
from 7561; a female wicked doer:--wicked woman.
dual of 4751 feminine; double bitterness; Merathajim, an epithet of Babylon:--Merathaim.
of foreign derivation; Mash, a son of Aram, and the people descended from him:--Mash.
of foreign derivation; Mesha, a place in Arabia:--Mesha.

from 5375; a burden; specifically, tribute, or (abstractly) porterage; figuratively, an utterance, chiefly a doom, especially singing; mental, desire:--burden, carry away, prophecy, X they set, song, tribute.
the same as 4853; burden; Massa, a son of Ishmael:--Massa.
from 5383; a loan; by implication, interest on a debt:--exaction, usury.
from 5375; partiality (as a lifting up):--respect.
from 7579; a trough for cattle to drink from:--place of drawing water.
from 5375; a conflagration (from the rising of smoke):--burden.
feminine of 4855; a loan:--X any(- thing), debt.
from 5377; dissimulation:--deceit.
from 7592; request; Mishal, a place in Palestine:--Mishal, Misheal. Compare 4913.
from 7592; a request:--desire, petition.
from 7604 in the original sense of swelling; a kneading-trough (in which the dough rises):--kneading trough, store.

from 5375; properly, (abstractly) a raising (as of the hands in prayer), or rising (of flame); figuratively, an utterance; concretely, a beacon (as raised); a present (as taken), mess, or tribute; figuratively, a reproach (as a burden):--burden, collection, sign of fire, (great) flame, gift, lifting up, mess, oblation, reward.
from 7660; a brocade; by analogy, a (reticulated) setting of a gem:--ouch, wrought.
from 7665; the orifice of the womb (from which the fetus breaks forth):--birth, breaking forth.
from 7665; a breaker (of the sea):--billow, wave.
from 7673; cessation, i.e. destruction:--sabbath.
from 7682; properly, a cliff (or other lofty or inaccessible place); abstractly, altitude; figuratively, a refuge:-- defence, high fort (tower), refuge, Misgab, a place in Moab:--Misgab.
from 7686; an error:--oversight.
a primitive root; to pull out (literally or figuratively):--draw(out).
from 4871; drawing out (of the water), i.e. rescued; Mosheh, the Israelite lawgiver:--Moses.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 4872:--Moses.
from 5383; a debt:--+ creditor.
or mshoah {mesh-o-aw'}; from the same as 7722; (a) ruin, abstractly (the act) or concretely (the wreck):--desolation, waste.
or mashshu ah {mash-shoo-aw'}; for 4875; ruin:--desolation, destruction.
from 7725; returned; Meshobab, an Israelite:--Meshobab.
or mshubah {mesh-oo-baw'}; from 7725; apostasy:--backsliding, turning away.
from an unused root meaning to stray; mistake:--error.
or mishshowt {mish-shote'}; from 7751; an oar:--oar.
or msukah {mes-oo-kaw'}; from 7753; a hedge:--hedge.
from an unused root meaning to plunder; spoilation:--spoil.
from an unused root meaning to rasp; a saw:--saw.
from an unused root meaning apparently to divide; a measure (for liquids):--measure.
from 7797; delight, concretely (the cause or object) or abstractly (the feeling):--joy, mirth, rejoice.
a primitive root; to rub with oil, i.e. to anoint; by implication, to consecrate; also to paint:--anoint, paint.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to 4886; oil:--oil.
or moshchah {mosh-khaw'}; from 4886; unction (the act); by implication, a consecratory gift:--(to be) anointed(-ing), ointment.
from 7843; destructive, i.e. (as noun) destruction, literally (specifically a snare) or figuratively (corruption):--corruption, (to) destroy(-ing), destruction, trap, X utterly.
from 7831; a laughing-stock:--scorn.
from 7836 in the sense of day breaking; dawn:--morning.
for 4889; destruction:--destroying.
or moshchath {mosh-khawth'}; from 7843; disfigurement:--corruption, marred.
or mishtach {mish-takh'}; from 7849; a spreading-place:--(to) spread (forth, -ing, upon).
from the same as 7850; enmity:--hatred.
from 7860; jurisdiction:--dominion.
from 4871; silk (as drawn from the cocoon):--silk.
from an equiv. to 7804 and 410; delivered of God; Meshezabel, an Israelite:--Meshezabeel.
from 4886; anointed; usually a consecrated person (as a king, priest, or saint); specifically, the Messiah:--anointed, Messiah.

a primitive root; to draw, used in a great variety of applications (including to sow, to sound, to prolong, to develop, to march, to remove, to delay, to be tall, etc.):--draw (along, out), continue, defer, extend, forbear, X give, handle, make (pro-, sound)long, X sow, scatter, stretch out.
from 4900; a sowing; also a possession:--precious, price.
the same in form as 4901, but probably of foreign derivation; Meshek, a son of Japheth, and the people descended from him:--Mesech, Meshech.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 4904; a bed:--bed.
from 7901; a bed (figuratively, a bier); abstractly, sleep; by euphemism, carnal intercourse:--bed((-chamber)), couch, lieth (lying) with.
from 7919; instructive, i.e. a didactic poem:--Maschil.
from the same as 7906; a figure (carved on stone, the wall, or any object); figuratively, imagination:--conceit, image(-ry), picture, X wish.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 4908; residence:--habitation.

from 7931; a residence (including a shepherd's hut, the lair of animals, figuratively, the grave; also the Temple); specifically, the Tabernacle (properly, its wooden walls):--dwelleth, dwelling (place), habitation, tabernacle, tent.
from 7936; wages or a reward:--reward, wages.
a primitive root; to rule:--(have, make to have) dominion, governor, X indeed, reign, (bear, cause to, have) rule(-ing, -r), have power.

denominative from 4912; to liken, i.e. (transitively) to use figurative language (an allegory, adage, song or the like); intransitively, to resemble:--be(-come) like, compare, use (as a) proverb, speak (in proverbs), utter.

apparently from 4910 in some original sense of superiority in mental action; properly, a pithy maxim, usually of metaphorical nature; hence, a simile (as an adage, poem, discourse):--byword, like, parable, proverb.
for 4861; Mashal, a place in Palestine:--Mashal.
from 4911; a satire:--byword.
(1) from 4910; empire; (2) from 4911; a parallel:--dominion, like.

or mishloach {mish-lo'-akh}; also mishlach {mish-lawkh'}; from 7971; a sending out, i.e. (abstractly) presentation (favorable), or seizure (unfavorable); also (concretely) a place of dismissal, or a business to be discharged:--to lay, to put, sending (forth), to set.
feminine of 4916; a mission, i.e. (abstractly) and favorable) release, or (concretely and unfavorable) an army:--discharge, sending.
from 7999; allied; Meshullam, the name of seventeen Israelites:--Meshullam.
plural from 7999; reconciliations:--Meshillemoth, an Israelite:--Meshillemoth. Compare 4921.
or Mshelemyahuw {mesh-eh-lem-yaw'-hoo}; from 7999 and 3050; ally of Jah; Meshelemjah, an Israelite:--Meshelemiah.
from 7999; reconciliation; Meshillemith, an Israelite:--Meshillemith. Compare 4919.
feminine of 4918; Meshullemeth, an Israelitess:--Meshullemeth.
from 8074; a waste or amazement:--astonishment, desolate.
from 8080; fat, i.e. (literally and abstractly) fatness; but usually (figuratively and concretely) a rich dish, a fertile field, a robust man:--fat (one, -ness, -test, -test place).
from 8080; fatness; Mashmannah, an Israelite:--Mishmannah.
from 8085; a report:--hearing.
the same as 4926; Mishma, the name of a son of Ishmael, and of an Israelite:--Mishma.
feminineal sense of superiority in mental action; properly, a pithy maxim, usually of metaphorical nature; hence, a simile (as a adae, compare, use (as a) proverb, speak (in proverbs), utter.
from 8104; a guard (the man, the post or the prison); a deposit (fig.); also (as observed) a usage (abstr.), or an example (concr.):--diligence, guard, office, prison, ward, watch.
for 4548 fem.; a peg:--nail.

fem. of 4929; watch, i.e. the act (custody), or (concr.) the sentry, the post; obj. preservation, or (concr.) safe; fig. observance, i.e. (abstr.) duty or (obj.) a usage or party:--charge, keep, or to be kept, office, ordinace, safeguard, ward, watch.

from 8138; properly, a repetition, i.e. a duplicate (copy of a document), or a double (in amount); by implication, a second (in order, rank, age, quality or location):--college, copy, double, fatlings, next, second (order), twice as much.
from 8155; plunder:--booty, spoil.
from the same as 8168; a hollow, i.e. a narrow passage:--path.
probably from 8159; inspection:--to supple.
apparently from 8159; inspection; Misham, an Israelite:--Misham.
or mishtan {mish-awn'}; from 8172; a support (concretely), i.e. (figuratively) a protector or sustenance:--stay.
or mishteneth {mish-eh'-neth}; feminine of 4937; support (abstractly), i.e. (figuratively) sustenance or (concretely) a walking-stick:--staff.
from 5596; slaughter:--oppression.
from 8192 (compare 8198); a family, i.e. circle of relatives; figuratively, a class (of persons), a species (of animals) or sort (of things); by extens. a tribe or people:--family, kind(-red).

from 8199; properly, a verdict (favorable or unfavorable) pronounced judicially, especially a sentence or formal decree (human or (participant's) divine law, individual or collective), including the act, the place, the suit, the crime, and the penalty; abstractly, justice, including a participant's right or privilege (statutory or customary), or even a style:--+ adversary, ceremony, charge, X crime, custom, desert, determination, discretion, disposing, due, fashion, form, to be judged, judgment, just(-ice, -ly), (manner of) law(-ful), manner, measure, (due) order, ordinance, right, sentence, usest, X worthy, + wrong.
from 8192; a stall for cattle (only dual):--burden, sheepfold.
from an unused root meaning to hold; possession:--+ steward.
from 8264; a traversing, i.e. rapid motion:--running to and fro.

from 8248; properly, causing to drink, i.e. a butler; by implication (intransitively), drink (itself); figuratively, a well-watered region:--butler(-ship), cupbearer, drink(-ing), fat pasture, watered.
from 8254; weight:--weight.
from 8259 in its original sense of overhanging; a lintel:--lintel.
from 8254; weight (numerically estimated); hence, weighing (the act):--(full) weight.
or mishqoleth {mish-ko'-leth}; feminine of 4948 or 4947; a weight, i.e. a plummet (with line attached):--plummet.
from 8257; a settling place (of water), i.e. a pond:--deep.
from 8280; empire:--government.
from 8281 in the sense of loosening; maceration, i.e. steeped juice:--liquor.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to 8319; a (musical) pipe (from its whistling sound):--flute.
patrial from an unused noun from an unused root; probably meaning to stretch out; extension; a Mishraite, or inhabitant (collectively) of Mishra:--Mishraites.
from 8313; combustion, i.e. cremation (of a corpse), or calcination (of lime):--burning.
from the plural of 4955 and 4325; burnings of water; Misrephoth-Majim, a place in Palestine:--Misrephoth-mayim.
a form for 7796 used denominatively; vineyard; Masrekah, a place in Idumaea:--Masrekah.
apparently from an unused root meaning to perforate, i.e. hollow out; a pan:--pan.
a primitive root; to feel of; by implication, to grope:--feel, grope, search.
from 8354; drink, by implication, drinking (the act); also (by implication) a banquet or (generally) feast:--banquet, drank, drink, feast((-ed), -ing).
(Aramaic) corresponding to 4960; a banquet:--banquet.
from the same as 4970; properly, an adult (as of full length); by implication, a man (only in the plural):--+ few, X friends, men, persons, X small.
denominative from 8401; straw in the heap:--straw.
from an unused root meaning to curb; a bit:--bit, bridle.
from 4964 and 520 with the art. interposed; bit of the metropolis; Metheg-ha-Ammah, an epithet of Gath:--Metheg-ammah.
or mathuwq {maw-thook'}; from 4985; sweet:-- sweet(-er, -ness).
from 4962 and 410, with the relative interposed; man who (is) of God; Methusael, an antediluvian patriarch:--Methusael.
from 4962 and 7973; man of a dart; Methushelach, an antediluvian patriarch:--Methuselah.
a primitive root; to stretch out:--spread out.
from an unused root meaning to extend; properly, extent (of time); but used only adverbially (especially with other particle prefixes), when (either relative or interrogative):--long, when.
or mathkuneth {math-koo'-neth}; from 8505 in the transferred sense of measuring; proportion (in size, number or ingredients):--composition, measure, state, tale.
from 4100 and 8513; what a trouble!:--what a weariness.
contr. from 3216; properly, a biter, i.e. a tooth:--cheek (jaw) tooth, jaw.
from 8552; wholesomeness; also (adverb) completely:--men (by reading 4962), soundness.
from an unused root meaning to be slender; properly, the waist or small of the back; only in plural the loins:--+ greyhound, loins, side.
from 5414; a present:--gift, to give, reward.
the same as 4976; Mattan, the name of a priest of Baal, and of an Israelite:--Mattan.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 4979:--gift.
feminine of 4976; a present; specifically (in a good sense), a sacrificial offering, (in a bad sense) a bribe:--gift.
the same as 4979; Mattanah, a place in the Desert:--Mattanah.
probably patrial from an unused noun meaning slenderness; a Mithnite, or inhabitant of Methen:--Mithnite.
from 4976; liberal; Mattenai, the name of three Israelites:--Mattenai.
or Mattanyahuw {mat-tan-yaw'-hoo}; from 4976 and 3050; gift of Jah; Mattanjah, the name of ten Israelites:--Mattaniah.
from 5375; (used as abstractly) supreme exaltation:--exalted.
a primitive root; to suck, by implication, to relish, or (intransitively) be sweet:--be (made, X take) sweet.
from 4985; figuratively, pleasantness (of discourse):--sweetness.
from 4985; sweetness:--sweetness.
from 4985; a dainty, i.e. (generally) food:--feed sweetly.
feminine of 4987; sweetness; Mithkah, a place in the Desert:--Mithcah.
of Persian origin; Mithredath, the name of two Persians:--Mithredath.
feminine of 4976 abbreviated form; a present:--gift.
for 4993; gift of Jah; Mattattah, an Israelite:--Mattathah.
or Mattithyahuw {mat-tith-yaw'-hoo}; from 4991 and 3050; gift of Jah; Mattithjah, the name of four Israelites:-- Mattithiah.
