a primitive particle of incitement and entreaty, which may usually be rendered: "I pray," "now," or "then"; added mostly to verbs (in the Imperative or Future), or to interjections, occasionally to an adverb or conjunction:--I beseech (pray) thee (you), go to, now, oh.
apparently from 5106 in the sense of harshness from refusal; properly, tough, i.e. uncooked (flesh):--raw.
of Egyptian origin; No (i.e. Thebes), the capital of Upper Egypt:--No. Compare 528.
or noywd {node}; also (feminine) no)dah {no-daw'}; from an unused root of uncertain signification; a (skin or leather) bag (for fluids):--bottle.
a primitive root; properly, to be at home, i.e. (by implication) to be pleasant (or suitable), i.e. beautiful:--be beautiful, become, be comely.
from 4998; a home; figuratively, a pasture:--habitation, house, pasture, pleasant place.
from 4998 or 5116; suitable, or beautiful:--becometh, comely, seemly.
a primitive root; properly, to whisper, i.e. (by implication) to utter as a oracle:--say.
from 5001; an oracle:--(hath) said, saith.
a primitive root; to commit adultery; figuratively, to apostatize:--adulterer(-ess), commit(-ing) adultery, woman that breaketh wedlock.
from 5003; adultery:--adultery.
from 5003; adultery:--adultery.
a primitive root; to scorn; or (Ecclesiastes 12:5) by interchange for 5132, to bloom:--abhor, (give occasion to) blaspheme, contemn, despise, flourish, X great, provoke.
or nematsah {neh-aw-tsaw'}; from 5006; scorn:--blasphemy.
a primitive root; to groan:--groan.
from 5008; a groan:--groaning.
a primitive root; to reject:--abhor, make void.
the same as 5108; fruit; Nob, a place in Palestine:--Nob.
a primitive root; to prophesy, i.e. speak (or sing) by inspiration (in prediction or simple discourse):--prophesy(-ing), make self a prophet.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5012:--prophesy.
a primitive root; to pierce; to be hollow, or (figuratively) foolish:--hollow, vain.
probably of foreign derivation; Nebo, the name of a Babylonian deity, also of a mountain in Moab, and of a place in Palestine:--Nebo.
from 5012; a prediction (spoken or written):--prophecy.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5016; inspired teaching:--prophesying.
of foreign origin; Nebuzaradan, a Babylonian general:--Nebuzaradan.

or Nbukadneotstsar (2 Kings 24:1, 10) {neb-oo-kad-nets-tsar'}; or Nbuwkadnetstsar (Esther 2:6; Daniel 1:18) {neb-oo-kad-nets-tsar'}; or Nbuwkadreotstsar {neb-oo-kad-rets-tsar'}; or Nbuwkadreltstsowr (Ezra 2:1; Jeremiah 49:28) {neb-oo-kad-rets-tsore'}; or foreign derivation; Nebukadnetstsar (or -retstsar, or -retstsor), king of Babylon:--Nebuchadnezzar, Nebuchadrezzar.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5019:--Nebuchadnezzar.
of foreign derivation; Nebushazban, Nebuchadnezzar's chief eunuch:--Nebushazban.
feminine plural from the same as 5011; fruits; Naboth, an Israelite:--Naboth.
(Aramaic) of uncertain derivation; a largess:--reward.
a primitive root; to bark (as a dog):--bark.
from 5024; a bark; Nobach, the name of an Israelite, and of a place East of the Jordan:--Nobah.
of foreign origin; Nibchaz, a deity of the Avites:--Nibhaz.
a primitive root; to scan, i.e. look intently at; by implication, to regard with pleasure, favor or care:--(cause to) behold, consider, look (down), regard, have respect, see.
from 5027; regard; Nebat, the father of Jeroboam I:--Nebat.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5030; a prophet:--prophet.
from 5012; a prophet or (generally) inspired man:--prophecy, that prophesy, prophet.
feminine of 5030; a prophetess or (generally) inspired woman; by implication, a poetess; by association a prophet's wife:--prophetess.
or Nbayoth {neb-aw-yoth'}; feminine plural from 5107; fruitfulnesses; Nebajoth, a son of Ismael, and the country settled by him:--Nebaioth, Nebajoth.
from an unused root meaning to burst forth; a fountain:--spring.

a primitive root; to wilt; generally, to fall away, fail, faint; figuratively, to be foolish or (morally) wicked; causatively, to despise, disgrace:--disgrace, dishounour, lightly esteem, fade (away, - ing), fall (down, -ling, off), do foolishly, come to nought, X surely, make vile, wither.

or nebel {nay'-bel}; from 5034; a skin-bag for liquids (from collapsing when empty); hence, a vase (as similar in shape when full); also a lyre (as having a body of like form):--bottle, pitcher, psaltery, vessel, viol.
from 5034; stupid; wicked (especially impious):-- fool(-ish, -ish man, -ish woman), vile person.
the same as 5036; dolt; Nabal, an Israelite:--Nabal.

from 5034; a flabby thing, i.e. a carcase or carrion (human or bestial, often collectively); figuratively, an idol:-- (dead) body, (dead) carcase, dead of itself, which died, (beast) that (which) dieth of itself.
feminine of 5036; foolishness, i.e. (morally) wickedness; concretely, a crime; by extension, punishment:--folly, vile, villany.
from 5036; properly, disgrace, i.e. the (female) pudenda:--lewdness.
apparently from 5036 and 3909; foolish secrecy; Neballat, a place in Palestine:--Neballat.
a primitive root; to gush forth; figuratively, to utter (good or bad words); specifically, to emit (a foul odor):--belch out, flowing, pour out, send forth, utter (abundantly).
(Aramaic) from an unused root meaning to shine; a light; plural (collectively) a chandelier:--candlestick.
of uncertain derivation; Nibshan, a place in Palestine:--Nibshan.

from an unused root meaning to be parched; the south (from its drought); specifically, the Negeb or southern district of Judah, occasionally, Egypt (as south to Palestine):--south (country, side, -ward).

a primitive root; properly, to front, i.e. stand boldly out opposite; by implication (causatively), to manifest; figuratively, to announce (always by word of mouth to one present); specifically, to expose, predict, explain, praise:--bewray, X certainly, certify, declare(-ing), denounce, expound, X fully, messenger, plainly, profess, rehearse, report, shew (forth), speak, X surely, tell, utter.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5046; to flow (through the idea of clearing the way):--issue.

from 5046; a front, i.e. part opposite; specifically a counterpart, or mate; usually (adverbial, especially with preposition) over against or before:--about, (over) against, X aloof, X far (off), X from, over, presence, X other side, sight, X to view.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5048; opposite:--toward.
a primitive root; to glitter; causatively, to illuminate:--(en-)lighten, (cause to) shine.
from 5050; brilliancy (literally or figuratively):--bright(-ness), light, (clear) shining.
the same as 5051; Nogah, a son of David:--Nogah.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5051; dawn:--morning.
feminine of 5051; splendor:--brightness.
a primitive root; to but with the horns; figuratively, to war against:--gore, push (down, -ing).
from 5055; butting, i.e. vicious:--used (wont) to push.

or nagid {naw-gheed'}; from 5046; a commander (as occupying the front), civil, military or religious; generally (abstractly, plural), honorable themes:--captain, chief, excellent thing, (chief) governor, leader, noble, prince, (chief) ruler.

or ngiynath (Psa. 61:title) {neg-ee-nath'}; from 5059; properly, instrumental music; by implication, a stringed instrument; by extension, a poem set to music; specifically, an epigram:--stringed instrument, musick, Neginoth (plural), song.

a primitive root; properly, to thrum, i.e. beat a tune with the fingers; expec. to play on a stringed instrument; hence (generally), to make music:--player on instruments, sing to the stringed instruments, melody, ministrel, play(-er, -ing).

a primitive root; properly, to touch, i.e. lay the hand upon (for any purpose; euphem., to lie with a woman); by implication, to reach (figuratively, to arrive, acquire); violently, to strike (punish, defeat, destroy, etc.):--beat, (X be able to) bring (down), cast, come (nigh), draw near (nigh), get up, happen, join, near, plague, reach (up), smite, strike, touch.
from 5060; a blow (figuratively, infliction); also (by implication) a spot (concretely, a leprous person or dress):--plague, sore, stricken, stripe, stroke, wound.
a primitive root; to push, gore, defeat, stub (the toe), inflict (a disease):--beat, dash, hurt, plague, slay, smite (down), strike, stumble, X surely, put to the worse.
from 5062; a trip (of the foot); figuratively, an infliction (of disease):--plague, stumbling.
a primitive root; to flow; figuratively, to stretch out; causatively, to pour out or down; figuratively, to deliver over:--fall, flow away, pour down (out), run, shed, spilt, trickle down.
a primitive root; to drive (an animal, a workman, a debtor, an army); by implication, to tax, harass, tyrannize:--distress, driver, exact(-or), oppress(-or), X raiser of taxes, taskmaster.

a primitive root; to be or come (causatively, bring) near (for any purpose); euphemistically, to lie with a woman; as an enemy, to attack; relig. to worship; causatively, to present; figuratively, to adduce an argument; by reversal, to stand back:--(make to) approach (nigh), bring (forth, hither, near), (cause to) come (hither, near, nigh), give place, go hard (up), (be, draw, go) near (nigh), offer, overtake, present, put, stand.
from 5110 in the sense of piling up; a mound, i.e. wave:--heap.
a primitive root; to impel; hence, to volunteer (as a soldier), to present spontaneously:--offer freely, be (give, make, offer self) willing(-ly).
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5068; be (or give) liberal(-ly):--(be minded of...own) freewill (offering), offer freely (willingly).
from 5068; liberal; Nadab, the name of four Israelites:--Nadab.

from 5068; properly (abstractly) spontaneity, or (adjectively) spontaneous; also (concretely) a spontaneous or (by inference, in plural) abundant gift:--free(-will) offering, freely, plentiful, voluntary(-ily, offering), willing(-ly), offering).
from 5068 and 3050; largess of Jah; Nedabjah, an Israelite:--Nedabiah.
(Aramaic) from a root meaning to stick; a layer (of building materials):--row.

a primitive root; properly, to wave to and fro (rarely to flap up and down); figuratively, to rove, flee, or (causatively) to drive away:--chase (away), X could not, depart, flee (X apace, away), (re-)move, thrust away, wander (abroad, -er, -ing).
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5074; to depart:--go from.
passive participle of 5074; properly, tossed; abstractly, a rolling (on the bed):--tossing to and fro.
or nada (2 Kings 17:21) {naw-daw'}; a primitive root; properly, to toss; figuratively, to exclude, i.e. banish, postpone, prohibit:--cast out, drive, put far away.
from 5077 in the sense of freely flinging money; a bounty (for prostitution):--gifts.

from 5074; properly, rejection; by implication, impurity, especially personal (menstruation) or moral (idolatry, incest):--X far, filthiness, X flowers, menstruous (woman), put apart, X removed (woman), separation, set apart, unclean(-ness, thing, with filthiness).

a primitive root; to push off; used in a great variety of applications, literally and figuratively (to expel, mislead, strike, inflict, etc.):--banish, bring, cast down (out), chase, compel, draw away, drive (away, out, quite), fetch a stroke, force, go away, outcast, thrust away (out), withdraw.
from 5068; properly, voluntary, i.e. generous; hence, magnanimous; as noun, a grandee (sometimes a tyrant):--free, liberal (things), noble, prince, willing ((hearted)).
feminine of 5081; properly, nobility, i.e. reputation:--soul.
probably from an unused root meaning to give; a present (for prostitution):--gift.
of uncertain derivation; a sheath (of a sword):--sheath.
(Aramaic) from the same as 5084; a sheath; figuratively, the body (as the receptacle of the soul):--body.
a primitive root; to shove asunder, i.e. disperse:--drive (away, to and fro), thrust down, shaken, tossed to and fro.
a primitive root; to promise (pos., to do or give something to God):--(make a) vow.
or neder {nay'-der}; from 5087; a promise (to God); also (concretely) a thing promised:--vow((-ed)).
from an unused root meaning to lament; lamentation:--wailing.

a primitive root; to drive forth (a person, an animal or chariot), i.e. lead, carry away; reflexively, to proceed (i.e. impel or guide oneself); also (from the panting induced by effort), to sigh:--acquaint, bring (away), carry away, drive (away), lead (away, forth), (be) guide, lead (away, forth).
a primitive root; to groan, i.e. bewail; hence (through the idea of crying aloud), to assemble (as if on proclamation):-- lament, wail.
from 5091; an elegy:--lamentation, wailing.
feminine of 5092; lamentation:--doleful.
(Aramaic) or nehiyruw (Aramaic) {neh-hee-roo'}; from the same as 5105; illumination, i.e. (figuratively) wisdom:--light.
a primitive root; properly, to run with a sparkle, i.e. flow; hence (transitively), to conduct, and (by inference) to protect, sustain:--carry, feed, guide, lead (gently, on).
or Nahalol {nah-hal-ole'}; the same as 5097; Nahalal or Nahalol, a place in Palestine:--Nahalal, Nahallal, Nahalol.
from 5095; pasture:--bush.
a primitive root; to growl:--mourn, roar(-ing).
from 5098; a snarl:--roaring.
feminine of 5099; snarling:--disquietness, roaring.
a primitive root; to bray (as an ass), scream (from hunger:--bray.
a primitive root; to sparkle, i.e. (figuratively) be cheerful; hence (from the sheen of a running stream) to flow, i.e. (figuratively) assemble:--flow (together), be lightened.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to 5102; a river, especially the Euphrates:--river, stream.
from 5102; a stream (including the sea; expec. the Nile, Euphrates, etc.); figuratively, prosperity:--flood, river.
from 5102 in its original sense; daylight:--light.
a primitive root; to refuse, forbid, dissuade, or neutralize:--break, disallow, discourage, make of none effect.
a primitive root; to germinate, i.e. (figuratively) to (causatively, make) flourish; also (of words), to utter:--bring forth (fruit), make cheerful, increase.
or neyb {nabe}; from 5107; produce, literally or figuratively:--fruit.
from 5108; fruitful; Nobai, an Israelite:--Nebai (from the margin).

a primitive root; to nod, i.e. waver; figuratively, to wander, flee, disappear; also (from shaking the head in sympathy), to console, deplore, or (from tossing the head in scorn) taunt:--bemoan, flee, get, mourn, make to move, take pity, remove, shake, skip for joy, be sorry, vagabond, way, wandering.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5116; to flee:--get away.
(only defect. nod {node}); from 5110; exile:--wandering.
the same as 5112; vagrancy; Nod, the land of Cain:--Nod.
from 5068; noble; Nodab, an Arab tribe:--Nodab.
a primitive root; to rest (as at home); causatively (through the implied idea of beauty (compare 5116)), to celebrate (with praises):--keept at home, prepare an habitation.

or (feminine) navah {naw-vaw'}; from 5115; (adjectively) at home; hence (by implication of satisfaction) lovely; also (noun) a home, of God (temple), men (residence), flocks (pasture), or wild animals (den):--comely, dwelling (place), fold, habitation, pleasant place, sheepcote, stable, tarried.

a primitive root; to rest, i.e. settle down; used in a great variety of applications, literal and figurative, intransitive, transitive and causative (to dwell, stay, let fall, place, let alone, withdraw, give comfort, etc.):--cease, be confederate, lay, let down, (be) quiet, remain, (cause to, be at, give, have, make to) rest, set down. Compare 3241.
or nowach {no'-akh}; from 5117; quiet:--rest(-ed, -ing place).
feminine of 5118; quietude; Nochah, an Israelite:--Nohah.
to quake:--be moved.
from 5115; residence; Navith, a place in Palestine:--Naioth (from the margin).
(Aramaic) or nvaliy (Aramaic) {nev-aw-lee'}; from an unused root probably meaning to be foul; a sink:--dunghill.
a primitive root; to slumber (from drowsiness):--sleep, slumber.
from 5123; sleepiness:--drowsiness.
a primitive root; to resprout, i.e. propagate by shoots; figuratively, to be perpetual:--be continued.
or Nown (1 Chron. 7:27) {nohn}; from 5125; perpetuity, Nun or Non, the father of Joshua:--Non, Nun.

a primitive root; to flit, i.e. vanish away (subside, escape; causatively, chase, impel, deliver):--X abate, away, be displayed, (make to) flee (away, -ing), put to flight, X hide, lift up a standard.

a primitive root; to waver, in a great variety of applications, literally and figuratively (as subjoined):--continually, fugitive, X make, to (go) up and down, be gone away, (be) move(-able, -d), be promoted, reel, remove, scatter, set, shake, sift, stagger, to and fro, be vagabond, wag, (make) wander (up and down).
from 3259 and 3050; convened of Jah; Noadjah, the name of an Israelite, and a false prophetess:--Noadiah.

a primitive root; to quiver (i.e. vibrate up and down, or rock to and fro); used in a great variety of applications (including sprinkling, beckoning, rubbing, bastinadoing, sawing, waving, etc.):--lift up, move, offer, perfume, send, shake, sift, strike, wave.
from 5130; elevation:--situation. Compare 5297.
a primitive root; properly, to flash; hence, to blossom (from the brilliancy of color); also, to fly away (from the quickness of motion):--flee away, bud (forth).
or notsah {no-tsaw'}; feminine active participle of 5327 in the sense of flying; a pinion (or wing feather); often (collectively) plumage:--feather(-s), ostrich.
a primitive root; to suckle:--nurse.
(Aramaic) from an unused root (corresponding to that of 5216) meaning to shine; fire:--fiery, fire.
a primitive root; to be sick, i.e. (figuratively) distressed:--be full of heaviness.
a primitive root; to spirt, i.e. besprinkle (especially in expiation):--sprinkle.
from 2102; something boiled, i.e. soup:--pottage.

or nazir {naw-zeer'}; from 5144; separate, i.e. consecrated (as prince, a Nazirite); hence (figuratively from the latter) an unpruned vine (like an unshorn Nazirite):--Nazarite (by a false alliteration with Nazareth), separate(-d), vine undressed.
a primitive root; to drip, or shed by trickling:--distil, drop, flood, (cause to) flow(-ing), gush out, melt, pour (down), running water, stream.
from an unused root of uncertain meaning; a nose-ring:--earring, jewel.
(Aramaic) corresponding to the root of 5143; to suffer (causatively, inflict) loss:--have (en-)damage, hurt(-ful).
from an unused root meaning to injure; loss:--damage.

a primitive root; to hold aloof, i.e. (intransitivey) abstain (from food and drink, from impurity, and even from divine worship (i.e. apostatize)); specifically, to set apart (to sacred purposes), i.e. devote:--consecrate, separate(-ing, self).

or nezer {nay'-zer}; from 5144; properly, something set apart, i.e. (abstractly) dedication (of a priet or Nazirite); hence (concretely) unshorn locks; also (by implication) a chaplet (especially of royalty):--consecration, crown, hair, separation.
the same as 5118; rest; Noach, the patriarch of the flood:--Noah.
from 2247; occult; Nachbi, an Israelite:--Nakbi.
a primitive root; to guide; by implication, to transport (into exile, or as colonists):--bestow, bring, govern, guide, lead (forth), put, straiten.
from 5162; comforted; Nechum, an Israelite:--Nehum.
or nichum {nee-khoom'}; from 5162; properly, consoled; abstractly, solace:--comfort(-able), repenting.
from 5162; comfortable; Nachum, an Israelite prophet:--Nahum.
from the same as 5170; snorer; Nochor, the name of the grandfather and a brother of Abraham:--Nahor.

apparently passive participle of 5172 (perhaps in the sense of ringing, i.e. bell-metal; or from the red color of the throat of a serpent (5175, as denominative) when hissing); coppery, i.e. (figuratively) hard:--of brass.
or nchushah {nekh-oo-shaw'}; feminine of 5153; copper:--brass, steel. Compare 5176.
probably denominative from 2485; a flute:--(plural) Nehiloth.
from the same as 5170; a nostril:--(dual) nostrils.

a primitive root; to inherit (as a (figurative) mode of descent), or (generally) to occupy; causatively, to bequeath, or (generally) distribute, instate:--divide, have ((inheritance)), take as a heritage, (cause to, give to, make to) inherit, (distribute for, divide (for, for an, by), give for, have, leave for, take (for)) inheritance, (have in, cause to, be made to) possess(-ion).

or (feminine) nachlah (Psalm 124:4) {nakh'-law}; or nachalah (Ezekiel 47:19; 48:28) {nakh-al-aw'}; from 5157 in its original sense; a stream, especially a winter torrent; (by implication) a (narrow) valley (in which a brook runs); also a shaft (of a mine):--brook, flood, river, stream, valley.

from 5157 (in its usual sense); properly, something inherited, i.e. (abstractly) occupancy, or (concretely) an heirloom; generally an estate, patrimony or portion:--heritage, to inherit, inheritance, possession. Compare 5158.
from 5158 and 410; valley of God; Nachaliel, a place in the Desert:--Nahaliel.
apparently a patronymic from an unused name (apparently passive participle of 2492); dreamed; a Nechelamite, or descendant of Nechlam:--Nehelamite.

a primitive root; properly, to sigh, i.e. breathe strongly; by implication, to be sorry, i.e. (in a favorable sense) to pity, console or (reflexively) rue; or (unfavorably) to avenge (oneself):--comfort (self), ease (one's self), repent(-er,-ing, self).
from 5162; consolation; Nacham, an Israelite:--Naham.
from 5162; ruefulness, i.e. desistance:--repentance.
from 5162; consolation:--comfort.
from 5162 and 3050; consolation of Jah; Nechemjah, the name of three Israelites:--Nehemiah.
from 5162; consolatory; Nachamani, an Israelite:--Nahamani.
for 587; we:--we.
a primitive root; to be urgent:--require haste.
and (feminine) nacharah {nakh-ar-aw'}; from an unused root meaning to snort or snore; a snorting:--nostrils, snorting.
or Nachray {nakh-rah'-ee}; from the same as 5170; snorer; Nacharai or Nachrai, an Israelite:--Naharai, Nahari.

a primitive root; properly, to hiss, i.e. whisper a (magic) spell; generally, to prognosticate:--X certainly, divine, enchanter, (use) X enchantment, learn by experience, X indeed, diligently observe.
from 5172; an incantation or augury:--enchantment.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5154; copper:--brass.
from 5172; a snake (from its hiss):--serpent.
the same as 5175; Nachash, the name of two persons apparently non-Israelite:--Nahash.
from 5172; enchanter; Nachshon, an Israelite:--Naashon, Nahshon.
for 5154; copper, hence, something made of that metal, i.e. coin, a fetter; figuratively, base (as compared with gold or silver):--brasen, brass, chain, copper, fetter (of brass), filthiness, steel.
from 5178; copper; Nechushta, an Israelitess:--Nehushta.
from 5178; something made of copper, i.e. the copper serpent of the Desert:--Nehushtan.
a primitive root; to sink, i.e. descend; causatively, to press or lead down:--be broken, (cause to) come down, enter, go down, press sore, settle, stick fast.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5181; to descend; causatively, to bring away, deposit, depose:--carry, come down, depose, lay up, place.
from 5182; a descent, i.e. imposition, unfavorable (punishment) or favorable (food); also (intransitively; perhaps from 5117), restfulness:--lighting down, quiet(-ness), to rest, be set on.
the same as 5183; quiet; Nachath, the name of an Edomite and of two Israelites:--Nahath.
from 5181; descending:--come down.

a primitive root; to stretch or spread out; by implication, to bend away (including moral deflection); used in a great variety of application (as follows):--+ afternoon, apply, bow (down, - ing), carry aside, decline, deliver, extend, go down, be gone, incline, intend, lay, let down, offer, outstretched, overthrown, pervert, pitch, prolong, put away, shew, spread (out), stretch (forth, out), take (aside), turn (aside, away), wrest, cause to yield.
from 5190; laden:--that bear.
from 5197; a pendant for the ears (especially of pearls):--chain, collar.
from 5203; a tendril (as an offshoot):--battlement, branch, plant.
a prim root; to lift; by implication, to impose:--bear, offer, take up.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5190; to raise:--take up.
: from 5190; a burden:--weighty.
a primitive root; properly, to strike in, i.e. fix; specifically, to plant (literally or figuratively):--fastened, plant(- er).
from 5193; a plant; collectively, a plantation; abstractly, a planting:--plant.
from 5193; a plant:--plant.
plural of 5194; Netaim, a place in Palestine:--plants.
a primitive root; to ooze, i.e. distil gradually; by implication, to fall in drops; figuratively, to speak by inspiration:--drop(-ping), prophesy(-et).
from 5197; a drop; specifically, an aromatic gum (probably stacte):--drop, stacte.
from 5197; distillation; Netophah, a place in Palestine:--Netophah.
patronymic from 5199; a Netophathite, or inhabitant of Netophah:--Netophathite.
a primitive root; to guard; figuratively, to cherish (anger):--bear grudge, keep(-er), reserve.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5201; to retain:--keep.

a primitive root; properly, to pound, i.e. smite; by implication (as if beating out, and thus expanding) to disperse; also, to thrust off, down, out or upon (inclusively, reject, let alone, permit, remit, etc.):--cast off, drawn, let fall, forsake, join (battle), leave (off), lie still, loose, spread (self) abroad, stretch out, suffer.
a doubtful word; apparently from 5091; lamentation:-- wailing.
from 5110; motion (of the lips in speech):--moving.
feminine of 5205; removal, i.e. exile:--removed.
or niychoach {nee-kho'-akh}; from 5117; properly, restful, i.e. pleasant; abstractly, delight:--sweet (odour).
(Aramaic) or (shorter) niychoach (Aramaic) {nee-kho'-akh}; corresponding to 5207; pleasure:--sweet odour (savour).
from 5125; progeny:--son.
of foreign origin; Nineveh, the capital of Assyria:--Nineveh.
from 5127; fugitive:--that fleeth.
probably of foreign origin; Nisan, the first month of the Jewish sacred year:--Nisan.
from 5340; a spark:--spark.
a root probably identical with that of 5216, through the idea of the gleam of a fresh furrow; to till the soil:--break up.
or nir {neer}; from 5214; properly, plowing, i.e. (concretely) freshly plowed land:--fallow ground, plowing, tillage.

or nir {neer}; also neyr {nare}; or ner {nare}; or (feminine) nerah {nay-raw'}; from a primitive root (see 5214; 5135) properly, meaning to glisten; a lamp (i.e. the burner) or light (literally or figuratively):--candle, lamp, light.
a primitive root; to smite, i.e. drive away:--be viler.
or nakat {naw-kaw'}; from 5217; smitten, i.e. (figuratively) afflicted:--broken, stricken, wounded.
from 5218; properly, a smiting, i.e. (concretely) an aromatic gum (perhaps styrax) (as powdered):--spicery(-ces).
from an unused root meaning to propagate; offspring:--nephew, son's son.

a primitive root; to strike (lightly or severely, literally or figuratively):--beat, cast forth, clap, give (wounds), X go forward, X indeed, kill, make (slaughter), murderer, punish, slaughter, slay(-er, -ing), smite(-r, -ing), strike, be stricken, (give) stripes, X surely, wound.
from 5221; a smiter, i.e. (figuratively) traducer:--abject.
smitten, i.e. (literally) maimed, or (figuratively) dejected:--contrite, lame.
probably of Egyptian origin; Neko, an Egyptian king:--Necho. Compare 6549.
from 3559; prepared; Nakon, probably an Israelite:--Nachon.
from an unused root meaning to be straightforward; properly, the fore part; used adverbially, opposite:--before, over against.
from the same as 5226; properly, the front part; used adverbially (especially with preposition), opposite, in front of, forward, in behalf of:--(over) against, before, direct(-ly), for, right (on).
from the same as 5226; straightforward, i.e. (figuratively), equitable, correct, or (abstractly), integrity:--plain, right, uprightness.
feminine of 5228; properly, straightforwardness, i.e. (figuratively) integrity, or (concretely) a truth:--equity, right (thing), uprightness.
a prim root; to defraud, i.e. act treacherously:--beguile, conspire, deceiver, deal subtilly.
from 5230; deceit:--wile.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5233:--goods.
from an unused root meaning to accumulate; treasure:--riches, wealth.

a primitive root; properly, to scrutinize, i.e. look intently at; hence (with recognition implied), to acknowledge, be acquainted with, care for, respect, revere, or (with suspicion implied), to disregard, ignore, be strange toward, reject, resign, dissimulate (as if ignorant or disowning):--acknowledge, X could, deliver, discern, dissemble, estrange, feign self to be another, know, take knowledge (notice), perceive, regard, (have) respect, behave (make) self strange(-ly).
or noker {no'-ker}; from 5234; something strange, i.e. unexpected calamity:--strange.
' from 5234; foreign, or (concretely) a foreigner, or (abstractly) heathendom:--alien, strange (+ -er).
from 5235 (second form); strange, in a variety of degrees and applications (foreign, non-relative, adulterous, different, wonderful):--alien, foreigner, outlandish, strange(-r, woman).
probably for 5219; spicery, i.e. (generally) valuables:--precious things.
apparently a primitive root; to complete:--make an end.
from 959, despised:--vile.
apparently for 3223; Nemuel, the name of two Israelites:--Nemuel.
from 5241; a Nemuelite, or descendant of Nemuel:--Nemuelite.
a primitive root; to become clipped or (specifically) circumcised:--(branch to) be cut down (off), circumcise.
feminine from 5243; an ant (probably from its almost bisected form):--ant.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5246:--leopard.
from an unused root meaning properly, to filtrate, i.e. be limpid (comp 5247 and 5249); and thus to spot or stain as if by dripping; a leopard (from its stripes):--leopard.
from the same as 5246; clear water; Nimrah, a place East of the Jordan:--Nimrah. See also 1039, 5249.
or Nimrod {nim-rode'}; probably of foreign origin; Nimrod, a son of Cush:--Nimrod.
plural of a masculine corresponding to 5247; clear waters; Nimrim, a place East of the Jordan:--Nimrim. Compare 1039.
probably from 4871; extricated; Nimshi, the (grand-)father of Jehu:--Nimshi.
from 5264; a flag; also a sail; by implication, a flagstaff; generally a signal; figuratively, a token:--banner, pole, sail, (en-)sign, standard.
feminine participle passive of 5437; properly, an environment, i.e. circumstance or turn of affairs:--cause.
a primitive root; to retreat:--departing away, remove, take (hold), turn away.
a primitive root; to test; by implication, to attempt:--adventure, assay, prove, tempt, try.
a primitive root; to tear away:--destroy, pluck, root.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5255:--pull down.
from 5258; properly, something poured out, i.e. a libation; also a molten image; by implication, a prince (as anointed):--drink offering, duke, prince(-ipal).
a primitive root; to pour out, especially a libation, or to cast (metal); by analogy, to anoint a king:--cover, melt, offer, (cause to) pour (out), set (up).
a primitive root (probably identical with 5258 through the idea of fusion); to interweave, i.e. (figuratively) to overspread:--that is spread.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5258; to pour out a libation:--offer.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5262; a libation:--drink offering.
or necek {nay'-sek}; from 5258; a libation; also a cast idol:--cover, drink offering, molten image.
a primitive root; to wane, i.e. be sick:--faint.

a primitive root; to gleam from afar, i.e. to be conspicuous as a signal; or rather perhaps a denominative from 5251 (and identical with 5263, through the idea of a flag as fluttering in the wind); to raise a beacon:--lift up as an ensign.

a primitive root; properly, to pull up, especially the tent-pins, i.e. start on a journey:--cause to blow, bring, get, (make to) go (away, forth, forward, onward, out), (take) journey, march, remove, set aside (forward), X still, be on his (go their) way.
a primitive root; to go up:--ascend.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5266:--take up.
of foreign origin; Nisrok, a Babylonian idol:--Nisroch.
from 5128; motion; Neah, a place in Palestine:--Neah.
from 5128; movement; Noah, an Israelitess:--Noah.

or naur {naw-oor'}; and (feminine) nturah {neh- oo-raw'}; properly, passive participle from 5288 as denominative; (only in plural collectively or emphatic form) youth, the state (juvenility) or the persons (young people):--childhood, youth.
from 5128 and 410; moved of God; Neiel, a place in Palestine:--Neiel.
from 5276; delightful (objective or subjective, literal or figurative):--pleasant(-ure), sweet.
a primitive root; properly, to fasten up, i.e. with a bar or cord; hence (denominative from 5275), to sandal, i.e. furnish with slippers:--bolt, inclose, lock, shoe, shut up.

or (feminine) na;alah {nah-al-aw'}; from 5274; properly, a sandal tongue; by extens. a sandal or slipper (sometimes as a symbol of occupancy, a refusal to marry, or of something valueless):--dryshod, (pair of) shoe((-latchet), -s).
a primitive root; to be agreeable (literally or figuratively):--pass in beauty, be delight, be pleasant, be sweet.
from 5276; pleasure; Naam, an Israelite:--Naam.
from 5276; agreeableness, i.e. delight, suitableness, splendor or grace:--beauty, pleasant(-ness).
feminine of 5277; pleasantness; Naamah, the name of an antediluvian woman, of an Ammonitess, and of a place in Palestine:--Naamah.
patronymic from 5283; a Naamanite, or descendant of Naaman (collectively):--Naamites.
from 5278; pleasant; Noomi, an Israelitess:--Naomi.
from 5276; pleasantness (plural as concrete):--pleasant.
the same as 5282; Naaman, the name of an Israelite and of a Damascene:--Naaman.
patrial from a place corresponding in name (but not identical) with 5279; a Naamathite, or inhabitant of Naamah:--Naamathite.
from an unused root meaning to prick; probably a brier; by implication, a thicket of thorny bushes:--thorn.
a primitive root; to growl:--yell.

a primitive root (probably identical with 5286, through the idea of the rustling of mane, which usually accompanies the lion's roar); to tumble about:--shake (off, out, self), overthrow, toss up and down.

from 5287; (concretely) a boy (as active), from the age of infancy to adolescence; by implication, a servant; also (by interch. of sex), a girl (of similar latitude in age):--babe, boy, child, damsel (from the margin), lad, servant, young (man).
from 5287 in its derivative sense of tossing about; a wanderer:--young one.
from 5287; (abstractly) boyhood (compare 5288):--child, youth.
feminine of 5288; a girl (from infancy to adolescence):--damsel, maid(-en), young (woman).
the same as 5291; Naarah, the name of an Israelitess, and of a place in Palestine:--Naarah, Naarath.
from 5288; youthful; Naarai, an Israelite:--Naarai.
from 5288 and 3050; servant of Jah; Nearjah, the name of two Israelites:--Neariah.
from 5288; juvenile; Naaran, a place in Palestine:--Naaran.
from 5287; something shaken out, i.e. tow (as the refuse of flax):--tow.
a variation of 4644; Noph, the capital of Upper Egypt:--Noph.
from an unused root probably meaning to spring forth; a sprout; Nepheg, the name of two Israelites:--Nepheg.
from 5130 in the sense of lifting; a height; also a sieve:--border, coast, region, sieve.
for 5304; Nephushesim, a Temple- servant:--Nephisesim (from the margin).

a primitive root; to puff, in various applications (literally, to inflate, blow hard, scatter, kindle, expire; figuratively, to disesteem):--blow, breath, give up, cause to lose (life), seething, snuff.
from 5301; a gust; Nophach, a place in Moab:--Nophah.
or nphil {nef-eel'}; from 5307; properly, a feller, i.e. a bully or tyrant:--giant.
plural from an unused root meaning to scatter; expansions; Nephisim, a Temple-servant:--Nephusim (from the margin).
from 5314; refreshed; Naphish, a son of Ishmael, and his posterity:--Naphish.
from an unused root meaning to glisten; shining; a gem, probably the garnet:--emerald.

a primitive root; to fall, in a great variety of applications (intransitive or causative, literal or figurative):--be accepted, cast (down, self, (lots), out), cease, die, divide (by lot), (let) fail, (cause to, let, make, ready to) fall (away, down, -en, -ing), fell(-ing), fugitive, have (inheritance), inferior, be judged (by mistake for 6419), lay (along), (cause to) lie down, light (down), be (X hast) lost, lying, overthrow, overwhelm, perish, present(-ed, -ing), (make to) rot, slay, smite out, X surely, throw down.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5307:--fall (down), have occasion.
or nephel {nay'-fel}; from 5307; something fallen, i.e. an abortion:--untimely birth.
a primitive root; to dash to pieces, or scatter:--be beaten in sunder, break (in pieces), broken, dash (in pieces), cause to be discharged, dispersed, be overspread, scatter.
from 5310; a storm (as dispersing):--scattering.
(Aramaic) a primitive root; to issue; causatively, to bring out:--come (go, take) forth (out).
(Aramaic) from 5312; an outgo, i.e. expense:--expense.
a primitive root; to breathe; passively, to be breathed upon, i.e. (figuratively) refreshed (as if by a current of air):--(be) refresh selves (-ed).

from 5314; properly, a breathing creature, i.e. animal of (abstractly) vitality; used very widely in a literal, accommodated or figurative sense (bodily or mental):--any, appetite, beast, body, breath, creature, X dead(-ly), desire, X (dis-)contented, X fish, ghost, + greedy, he, heart(-y), (hath, X jeopardy of) life (X in jeopardy), lust, man, me, mind, mortally, one, own, person, pleasure, (her-, him-, my-, thy-)self, them (your)-selves, + slay, soul, + tablet, they, thing, (X she) will, X would have it.
for 5299; a height:--country.
from 5130 in the sense of shaking to pieces; a dripping i.e. of honey (from the comb):--honeycomb.
from 6605; opened, i.e. a spring; Nephtoach, a place in Palestine:--Neptoah.
from 6617; properly, wrestled; but ued (in the plural) transitively, a struggle:--wrestling.
plural of foreign origin, Naphtuchim, an Egyptian tribe:--Naptuhim.
from 6617; my wrestling; Naphtali, a son of Jacob, with the tribe descended from him, and its territory:--Naphtali.
from 5340; a flower (from its brilliancy); also a hawk (from it flashing speed); --blossom, hawk.
a primitive root; to go away; --flee.

a prim root; to station, in various applications (literally or figuratively):--appointed, deputy, erect, establish, X Huzzah (by mistake for a proper name), lay, officer, pillar, present, rear up, set (over, up), settle, sharpen, establish, (make to) stand(-ing, still, up, upright), best state.
passive participle of 5324; fixed, i.e. a handle:--haft.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to 5324; fixedness, i.e. firmness:--strength.

a primitive root; properly, to go forth, i.e. (by implication) to be expelled, and (consequently) desolate; causatively, to lay waste; also (specifically), to quarrel:--be laid waste, runinous, strive (together).
feminine of 5322; a blossom; --flower.

a primitive root; properly, to glitter from afar, i.e. to be eminent (as a superintendent, especially of the Temple services and its music); also (as denominative from 5331), to be permanent:--excel, chief musician (singer), oversee(-r), set forward.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5329; to become chief:--be preferred.

or netsach {nay'-tsakh}; from 5329; properly, a goal, i.e. the bright object at a distance travelled towards; hence (figuratively), splendor, or (subjectively) truthfulness, or (objectively) confidence; but usually (adverbially), continually (i.e. to the most distant point of view); --alway(-s), constantly, end, (+ n-)ever(more), perpetual, strength, victory.
probably identical with 5331, through the idea of brilliancy of color; juice of the grape (as blood red):--blood, strength.
or ntsib {nets-eeb'}; from 5324; something stationary, i.e. a prefect, a military post, a statue:--garrison, officer, pillar.
the same as 5333; station; Netsib, a place in Palestine:--Nezib.
from 5329; conspicuous; Netsiach, a Temple- servant:--Neziah.
from 5341; properly, conservative; but used passively, delivered:--preserved.

a primitive root; to snatch away, whether in a good or a bad sense:- X at all, defend, deliver (self), escape, X without fail, part, pluck, preserve, recover, rescue, rid, save, spoil, strip, X surely, take (out).
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5337; to extricate:--deliver, rescue.
from 5322; a blossom:--flower.
a primitive root; to glare, i.e. be bright- colored:--sparkle.

a primitive root; to guard, in a good sense (to protect, maintain, obey, etc.) or a bad one (to conceal, etc.):-- besieged, hidden thing, keep(-er, -ing), monument, observe, preserve(-r), subtil, watcher(-man).
from 5341 in the sense of greenness as a striking color; a shoot; figuratively, a descendant:--branch.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to 5352; clean:--pure.

a primitive root; to puncture, literally (to perforate, with more or less violence) or figuratively (to specify, designate, libel):--appoint, blaspheme, bore, curse, express, with holes, name, pierce, strike through.
a bezel (for a gem):--pipe.
the same as 5345; dell; Nekeb, a place in Palestine:--Nekeb.
from 5344; female (from the sexual form):--female.
from an unused root meaning to mark (by puncturing or branding); spotted:--speckled.
active participle from the same as 5348; a spotter (of sheep or cattle), i.e. the owner or tender (who thus marks them):-- herdman, sheepmaster.
from the same as 5348; a crumb (as broken to spots); also a biscuit (as pricked):--cracknel, mouldy.
feminine of 5348; a boss:--stud.

a primitive root; to be (or make) clean (literally or figuratively); by implication (in an adverse sense) to be bare, i.e. extirpated:--acquit X at all, X altogether, be blameless, cleanse, (be) clear(-ing), cut off, be desolate, be free, be (hold) guiltless, be (hold) innocent, X by no means, be quit, be (leave) unpunished, X utterly, X wholly.
feminine of 5348 (in the figurative sense of marked); distinction; Nekoda, a Temple-servant:--Nekoda.
a primitive root; to loathe:--weary.
or naqiyi (Joel 4 : 19; Jonah 1 : 14), {naw-kee'}; from 5352; innocent:--blameless, clean, clear, exempted, free, guiltless, innocent, quit.
or niqqayon {nik-kaw-yone'}; from 5352; clearness (literally or figuratively):--cleanness, innocency.
from an unused root meaning to bore; a cleft:--hole.
a primitive root; to grudge, i.e. avenge or punish:--avenge(-r, self), punish, revenge (self), X surely, take vengeance.
from 5358; revenge:--+ avenged, quarrel, vengeance.
feminine of 5359; avengement, whether the act of the passion:--+ avenge, revenge(-ing), vengeance.
a primitive root; to feel aversion:--be alienated.

a primitive root; to strike with more or less violence (beat, fell, corrode); by implication (of attack) to knock together, i.e. surround or circulate:--compass (about, -ing), cut down, destroy, go round (about), inclose, round.
from 5362; a threshing (of olives):--shaking.
from 5362; probably a rope (as encircling):--rent.
a primitive root; to bore (penetrate, quarry):--dig, pick out, pierce, put (thrust) out.
from 5365, a fissure:--cleft, clift.
a primitive root; to entrap (with a noose), literally or figuratively:--catch (lay a) snare.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5367; but used in the sense of 5362; to knock:--smote.
the same as 5216; lamp; Ner, an Israelite:--Ner.
of foreign origin; Nergal, a Cuthite deity:--Nergal.
from 5370 and 8272; Nergal-Sharetser, the name of two Babylonians:--Nergal-sharezer.
from an unused root meaning to roll to pieces; a slanderer:--talebearer, whisperer.
of foreign origin; nard, an aromatic:--spikenard.
or Neriyahuw {nay-ree-yaw'-hoo}; from 5216 and 3050; light of Jah; Nerijah, an Israelite:--Neriah.

or nacah (Psalm 4 : 6 (7)) {naw-saw'}; a primitive root; to lift, in a great variety of applications, literal and figurative, absol. and rel. (as follows):--accept, advance, arise, (able to, (armor), suffer to) bear(-er, up), bring (forth), burn, carry (away), cast, contain, desire, ease, exact, exalt (self), extol, fetch, forgive, furnish, further, give, go on, help, high, hold up, honorable (+ man), lade, lay, lift (self) up, lofty, marry, magnify, X needs, obtain, pardon, raise (up), receive, regard, respect, set (up), spare, stir up, + swear, take (away, up), X utterly, wear, yield.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5375:--carry away, make insurrection, take.
a primitive root; to lead astray, i.e. (mentally) to delude, or (morally) to seduce:--beguile, deceive, X greatly, X utterly.
a primitive root (perhaps identical with 5377, through the idea of imposition); to lend on interest; by implication, to dun for debt:--X debt, exact, giver of usury.
passive participle feminine of 5375; something taken, i.e. a present:--gift.
a primitive root; to blow; by implication, to disperse:--(cause to) blow, drive away.
a primitive root; to reach (literally or figuratively):--ability, be able, attain (unto), (be able to, can) get, lay at, put, reach, remove, wax rich, X surely, (over-)take (hold of, on, upon).
a primitive root; to forget; figuratively, to neglect; causatively, to remit, remove:--forget, deprive, exact.
a primitive root (rather identical with 5382, in the sense of 5378); to lend or (by reciprocity) borrow on security or interest:--creditor, exact, extortioner, lend, usurer, lend on (taker on) usury.
from 5382, in the sense of failure; rheumatic or crippled (from the incident to Jacob):--which shrank.
or rather, nsutah {nes-oo-aw'}; feminine. passive participle of 5375; something borne, i.e. a load:--carriage.
from 5383; a debt:--debt.
or nasi8 {naw-see'}; from 5375; properly, an exalted one, i.e. a king or sheik; also a rising mist:--captain, chief, cloud, governor, prince, ruler, vapour.
from 5382; oblivion; --forgetfulness.
(Aramaic) irregular plural feminine of 606:--women.
from 5401; a kiss:--kiss.
a primitive root; to strike with a sting (as a serpent); figuratively, to oppress with interest on a loan:--bite, lend upon usury.
from 5391; interest on a debt:--usury.
for 3957; a cell:--chamber.
a primitive root; to pluck off, i.e. divest, eject or drop:--cast (out), drive, loose, put off (out), slip.
a primitive root; properly, to blow away, i.e. destroy:--destroy.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5397; vital breath:--breath.
from 5395; a puff, i.e. wind, angry or vital breath, divine inspiration, intellect. or (concretely) an animal:--blast, (that) breath(-eth), inspiration, soul, spirit.
a primitive root; to breeze, i.e. blow up fresh (as the wind):--blow.
from 5398; properly, a breeze, i.e. (by implication) dusk (when the evening breeze prevails):--dark, dawning of the day (morning), night, twilight.
a primitive root; to catch fire:--burn, kindle.

a primitive root (identical with 5400, through the idea of fastening up; compare 2388, 2836); to kiss, literally or figuratively (touch); also (as a mode of attachment), to equip with weapons:--armed (men), rule, kiss, that touched.
or nesheq {nay'-shek}; from 5401; military equipment, i.e. (collectively) arms (offensive or defensive), or (concretely) an arsenal:--armed men, armour(-y), battle, harness, weapon.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5404; an eagle:--eagle.
from an unused root meaning to lacerate; the eagle (or other large bird of prey):--eagle.
a primitive root; properly, to eliminate, i.e. (intransitively) to dry up:--fail.
probably of Persian origin; an epistle:--letter.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5406:--letter.
a primitive root; to dismember:--cut (in pieces), divide, hew in pieces.
from 5408; a fragment:--part, piece.
or (feminine) nthiybah {neth-ee-baw'}; or nthibah (Jeremiah 6:16) {neth-ee-baw'}; from an unused root meaning to tramp; a (beaten) track:--path((-way)), X travel(-ler), way.
or Nathuwn (Ezra 8:17) {naw-thoon'} (the proper form as passive participle), from 5414; one given, i.e. (in the plural only) the Nethinim, or Temple-servants (as given to that duty):--Nethinims.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5411:--Nethinims.
a primitive root; to flow forth (literally or figuratively); by implication, to liquify:--drop, gather (together), melt, pour (forth, out).

a primitive root; to give, used with greatest latitude of application (put, make, etc.):--add, apply, appoint, ascribe, assign, X avenge, X be ((healed)), bestow, bring (forth, hither), cast, cause, charge, come, commit, consider, count, + cry, deliver (up), direct, distribute, do, X doubtless, X without fail, fasten, frame, X get, give (forth, over, up), grant, hang (up), X have, X indeed, lay (unto charge, up), (give) leave, lend, let (out), + lie, lift up, make, + O that, occupy, offer, ordain, pay, perform, place, pour, print, X pull , put (forth), recompense, render, requite, restore, send (out), set (forth), shew, shoot forth (up), + sing, + slander, strike, (sub-)mit, suffer, X surely, X take, thrust, trade, turn, utter, + weep, + willingly, + withdraw, + would (to) God, yield.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5414; give:--bestow, give pay.
from 5414; given; Nathan, the name of five Israelites:--Nathan.
from 5414 and 410; given of God; Nethanel, the name of ten Israelites:--Nethaneel.
or Nthanyahuw {neth-an-yaw'-hoo}; from 5414 and 3050; given of Jah; Nethanjah, the name of four Israelites:--Nethaniah.
from 5414 and 4428; given of (the) king; Nethan-Melek, an Israelite:--Nathan-melech.
a primitive root; to tear up:--mar.
for 5422; to tear out:--break.
a primitive root; to tear down:--beat down, break down (out), cast down, destroy, overthrow, pull down, throw down.
a primitive root; to tear off:--break (off), burst, draw (away), lift up, pluck (away, off), pull (out), root out.
from 5423; scurf:--(dry) scall.
a primitive root; to jump, i.e. be violently agitated; causatively, to terrify, shake off, untie:--drive asunder, leap, (let) loose, X make, move, undo.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5425:--shake off.
from 5425; mineral potash (so called from effervescing with acid):--nitre.
a primitive root; to tear away:--destroy, forsake, pluck (out, up, by the roots), pull up, root out (up), X utterly.
from an unused root meaning to define; a seah, or certain measure (as determinative) for grain:--measure.
from 5431; perhaps a military boot (as a protection from mud:--battle.
a primitive root; to be miry; used only as denominative from 5430; to shoe, i.e. (active participle) a soldier shod:--warrior.
for 5429; measurement, i.e. moderation:--measure.
a primitive root; to quaff to satiety, i.e. become tipsy:--drunkard, fill self, Sabean, (wine-)bibber.
of foreign origin; Seba, a son of Cush, and the country settled by him:--Seba.
from 5433; potation, concretely (wine), or abstractly (carousal):--drink, drunken, wine.
patrial from 5434; a Sebaite, or inhabitant of Seba:--Sabean.

a primitive root; to revolve, surround, or border; used in various applications, literally and figuratively (as follows):--bring, cast, fetch, lead, make, walk, X whirl, X round about, be about on every side, apply, avoid, beset (about), besiege, bring again, carry (about), change, cause to come about, X circuit, (fetch a) compass (about, round), drive, environ, X on every side, beset (close, come, compass, go, stand) round about, inclose, remove, return, set, sit down, turn (self) (about, aside, away, back).
from 5437; a (providential) turn (of affairs):--cause.

or (feminine) cbiybah {seb-ee-baw'}; from 5437; (as noun) a circle, neighbour, or environs; but chiefly (as adverb, with or without preposition) around:--(place, round) about, circuit, compass, on every side.
a primitive root; to entwine:--fold together, wrap.
from 5440; a copse:--thicket.
from 5440, a copse:--thick(-et).
(Aramaic) or sabbka: (Aramaic) {sab-bek- aw'}; from a root corresponding to 5440; a lyre:--sackbut.
from 5440; copse-like; Sibbecai, an Israelite:--Sibbecai, Sibbechai.
a primitive root; to carry (literally or figuratively), or (reflexively) be burdensome; specifically, to be gravid:--bear, be a burden, carry, strong to labour.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5445; to erect:--strongly laid.
from 5445; a load (literally or figuratively):--burden, charge.
(only in the form cubbal {soob-bawl'}; from 5445; a load (figuratively):--burden.
from 5445; a porter:--(to bear, bearer of) burden(-s).
from 5447; porterage:--burden.
for 7641; an ear of grain:--Sibboleth.
(Aramaic) a primitive root; to bear in mind, i.e. hope:--think.
dual from a root corresponding to 5452; double hope; Sibrajim, a place in Syria:--Sibraim.
or Cabtah {sab-taw'}; probably of foreign derivation; Sabta or Sabtah, the name of a son of Cush, and the country occupied by his posterity:--Sabta, Sabtah.
probably of foreign derivation; Sabteca, the name of a son of Cush, and the region settled by him:--Sabtecha, Sabtechah.
a primitive root; to prostrate oneself (in homage):--fall down.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5456:--worship.
from 5462; properly, shut up, i.e. the breast (as inclosing the heart); also gold (as generally shut up safely):--caul, gold.
feminine passive participle of an unused root meaning to shut up; wealth (as closely shut up):--jewel, peculiar (treasure), proper good, special.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5461:--governor.
from an unused root meaning to superintend; a prefect of a province:--prince, ruler.
a primitive root; to shut up; figuratively, to surrender:--close up, deliver (up), give over (up), inclose, X pure, repair, shut (in, self, out, up, up together), stop, X straitly.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5462:--shut up.
probably from 5462 in the sense of sweeping away; a pouring rain:--very rainy.
from an unused root meaning to estop; the stocks:--stocks.
from an unused root meaning to envelop; a wrapper, i.e. shirt:--fine linen, sheet.
from an unused root meaning to scorch; burnt (i.e. volcanic or bituminous) district; Sedom, a place near the Dead Sea:-- Sodom.
from an unused root meaning to arrange; order:--order.
from an unused root meaning to be round; roundness:--round.
from the same as 5469; a dungeon (as surrounded by walls):--prison.
of foreign derivation; So, an Egyptian king:--So.
a primitive root; properly, to flinch, i.e. (by implication) to go back, literally (to retreat) or figuratively (to apostatize):--backslider, drive, go back, turn (away, back).
a primitive root (probably rather identical with 5472 through the idea of shrinking from a hedge; compare 7735); to hem in, i.e. bind:--set about.
from 5462; an inclosure, i.e. cage (for an animal):--ward.
from 3245; a session, i.e. company of persons (in close deliberation); by implication, intimacy, consultation, a secret:--assembly, consel, inward, secret (counsel).
from 5475; a confidant; Sodi, an Israelite:--Sodi.
from an unused root meaning to wipe away; sweeping; Suach, an Israelite:--Suah.
from the same as 5477; something swept away, i.e. filth:--torn.
from 7750; roving; Sotai, one of the Nethinim:--Sotai.
a primitive root; properly, to smear over (with oil), i.e. anoint:--anoint (self), X at all.
(Aramaic) or cuwmponyah (Aramaic) {soom-po-neh-yaw'}; or ciyphonya: (Dan. 3:10) (Aramaic) {see-fo-neh-yaw'}; of Greek origin; a bagpipe (with a double pipe):--dulcimer.
(rather to be written Cvenah {sev-ay'-naw}; for Cven {sev-ane'}; i.e to Seven); of Egyptian derivation; Seven, a place in Upper Egypt:--Syene.
or cuc {soos}; from an unused root meaning to skip (properly, for joy); a horse (as leaping); also a swallow (from its rapid flight):--crane, horse((-back, -hoof)). Compare 6571.
feminine of 5483; a mare:--company of horses.
from 5483; horse-like; Susi, an Israelite:--Susi.
a primitive root; to snatch away, i.e. terminate:--consume, have an end, perish, X be utterly.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5486; to come to an end:-- consume, fulfill.
probably of Egyptian origin; a reed, especially the papyrus:--flag, Red (sea), weed. Compare 5489.
for 5488 (by ellipsis of 3220); the Reed (Sea):--Red Sea.
from 5486; a termination:--conclusion, end, hinder participle
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5490:--end.
from 5486; a hurricane:--Red Sea, storm, tempest, whirlwind, Red sea.

or suwr (Hosea 9:12) {soor}; a primitive root; to turn off (literal or figurative):--be(-head), bring, call back, decline, depart, eschew, get (you), go (aside), X grievous, lay away (by), leave undone, be past, pluck away, put (away, down), rebel, remove (to and fro), revolt, X be sour, take (away, off), turn (aside, away, in), withdraw, be without.
probably passive participle of 5493; turned off, i.e. deteriorated:--degenerate.
the same as 5494; Sur, a gate of the temple:--Sur.
perhaps denominative from 7898; properly, to prick, i.e. (figuratively) stimulate; by implication, to seduce:--entice, move, persuade, provoke, remove, set on, stir up, take away.
probably from the same root as 4533; covering, i.e. clothing:--clothes.
a primitive root; to trail along:--draw (out), tear.
from 5498; a rag:--cast clout.
a primitive root; to sweep away:--scrape.
from 5500; refuse (as swept off):--offscouring.
a primitive root; to scrape off:--sweep (away).
a primitive root; to travel round (specifically as a pedlar); intensively, to palpitate:--go about, merchant(-man), occupy with, pant, trade, traffick.
from 5503; profit (from trade):--merchandise.
from 5503; an emporium; abstractly, profit (from trade):--mart, merchandise.
from 5503: traffic:--merchandise.
properly, active participle feminine of 5503; something surrounding the person, i.e. a shield:--buckler.
similar to 5507; probably a (black) tile (or tessara) for laying borders with:--black marble.
or cuwg (Ezek. 22:18) {soog}; from 5472 in the sense of refuse; scoria:--dross.
probably of Persian origin; Sivan, the third Heb. month:--Sivan.
or Ciychon {see-khone'}; from the same as 5477; tempestuous; Sichon, an Amoritish king:--Sihon.
of uncertain derivation; Sin the name of an Egyptian town and (probably) desert adjoining:--Sin.
from an otherwise unknown name of a man; a Sinite, or descendant of one of the sons of Canaan:--Sinite.
of uncertain derivation; Sinai, mountain of Arabia:--Sinai.
plural of an otherwise unknown name; Sinim, a distant Oriental region:--Sinim.
of uncertain derivation; Sisera, the name of a Canaanitish king and of one of the Nethinim:--Sisera.
or Ciyeahai {see-ah-haw'}; from an unused root meaning to converse; congregation; Sia or Siaha, one of the Nethinim:-- Sia, Siaha.

or (feminine) ciyrah {see-raw'}; or cirah (Jeremiah 52:18) {see-raw'}; from a primitive root meaning to boil up; a pot; also a thorn (as springing up rapidly); by implication, a hook:--caldron, fishhook, pan, ((wash-))pot, thorn.
from 5526; properly, a thicket of men, i.e. a crowd:-- multitude.
from 5526; a hut (as of entwined boughs); also a lair:-- covert, den, pavilion, tabernacle.
fem of 5520; a hut or lair:--booth, cottage, covert, pavilion, tabernacle, tent.
feminine of 5519; an (idolatrous) booth:--tabernacle.
or Cukkoth {sook-kohth'}; plural of 5521; booths; Succoth, the name of a place in Egypt and of three in Palestine:-- Succoth.
from 5523 and the (irreg.) plural of 1323; booths of (the) daughters; brothels, i.e. idoalatrous tents for impure purpose:--Succoth-benoth.
patrial from an unknown name (perhaps 5520); a Sukkite, or inhabitant of some place near Egypt (i.e. hut-dwellers):-- Sukkiims.

or sakak (Exod. 33:22) {saw-kak'}; a primitive root; properly, to entwine as a screen; by implication, to fence in, cover over, (figuratively) protect:--cover, defence, defend, hedge in, join together, set, shut up.
from 5526; inclosure; Secacah, a place in Palestine:--Secacah.
for 3688; to be silly:--do (make, play the, turn into) fool(-ish, -ishly, -ishness).
from 5528; silliness; concretely and collectively, dolts:--folly.
from 5528; silly:--fool(-ish), sottish.
or sikluwth (Eccl. 1:17) {sik-looth'}; from 5528; silliness:--folly, foolishness.
a primitive root; to be familiar with; by implication, to minister to, be serviceable to, be customary:--acquaint (self), be advantage, X ever, (be, (un-))profit(-able), treasurer, be wont.
probably a denominative from 7915; properly, to cut, i.e. damage; also to grow (causatively, make) poor:--endanger, impoverish.
a primitive root; to shut up; by implication, to surrender:--stop, give over. See also 5462, 7936.
a primitive root to be silent; by implication, to observe quietly:--take heed.
from 5549; properly, a willow twig (as pendulous), i.e. an osier; but only as woven into a basket:--basket.
a primitive root; to suspend in a balance, i.e. weigh:--compare.
from 5549; an embankment; Silla, a place in Jerusalem:--Silla.
a primitive root; probably to leap (with joy), i.e. exult:--harden self.
from 5539; exultation; Seled, an Israelite:--Seled.
a primitive root; to hang up, i.e. weigh, or (figuratively) contemn:--tread down (under foot), value.
from 5541; suspension (of music), i.e. pause:--Selah.
or Calluw; {sal-loo'}; or Caluw {sal-loo'}; or Callay {sal-lah'-ee}; from 5541; weighed; Sallu or Sallai, the name of two Israelites:--Sallai, Sallu, Salu.
or callown {sal-one'}; from 5541; a prickle (as if pendulous); brier, thorn.
a primitive root; to forgive:--forgive, pardon, spare.
from 5545; placable: ready to forgive.
from 5545; pardon:--forgiveness, pardon.
from an unused root. meaning to walk; walking; Salcah, a place East of the Jordan:--Salcah, Salchah.
a primitive root; to mound up (especially a turnpike); figurative, to exalt; reflexively, to oppose (as by a dam):-- cast up, exalt (self), extol, make plain, raise up.
or cowllah {so-lel-aw'}; active participle feminine of 5549, but used passively; a military mound, i.e. rampart of besiegers:--bank, mount.
from 5549; a stair-case:--ladder.
from 5541; a twig (as pendulous):--basket.
from an unused root meaning to be lofty; a craggy rock, literally or figuratively (a fortress):--(ragged) rock, stone(-ny), strong hold.
the same as 5553; Sela, the rock-city of Idumaea:--rock, Sela(-h).
from 5553 and the plural of 4256 with the article interposed; rock of the divisions; Sela- ham-Machlekoth, a place in Palestine:--Sela-hammalekoth.
apparently from the same as 5553 in the sense of crushing as with a rock, i.e. consuming; a kind of locust (from its destructiveness):--bald locust.
a primitive root; properly, to wrench, i.e. (figuratively) to subvert:--overthrow, pervert.
from 5557; distortion, i.e. (figuratively) viciousness:--perverseness.
(Aramaic) a primitive root; to ascend:--come (up).
from an unused root meaning to strip; flour (as chipped off):--(fine) flour, meal.
from an unused root meaning to smell sweet; an aroma:-- sweet (spice).
of foreign origin; Samgar-Nebo, a Babylonian general:--Samgar-nebo.
of uncertain derivation; a vine blossom; used also adverbially, abloom:--tender grape.

a primitive root; to prop (literally or figuratively); reflexively, to lean upon or take hold of (in a favorable or unfavorable sense):--bear up, establish, (up-)hold, lay, lean, lie hard, put, rest self, set self, stand fast, stay (self), sustain.
from 5564 and 3050; supported of Jah; Semakjah, an Israelite:--Semachiah.
or cemel {say'-mel}; from an unused root meaning to resemble; a likeness:--figure, idol, image.
a primitive root; to designate:--appointed.
a primitive root; to be erect, i.e. bristle as hair:--stand up, tremble.
from 5568; bristling, i.e. shaggy:--rough.
from an unused root meaning to prick; thorny; Senaah, a place in Palestine:--Senaah, Hassenaah (with the article).
of foreign origin; Sanballat, a Persian satrap of Samaria:--Sanballat.
from an unused root meaning to prick; a bramble:--bush.
the same s 5572; thorn; Seneh, a crag in Palestine:--Seneh.
or Cnu.ah {sen-oo-aw'} from the same as 5570; pointed; (used with the article as a proper name) Senuah, the name of two Israelites:--Hasenuah (including the art), Senuah.
of uncertain derivation; (in plural) blindness:--blindness.
of foreign origin; Sancherib, an Assyrian king:--Sennacherib.
from an unused root meaning to be pointed; a twig (as tapering):--bough.
feminine of a form of 5577; a bough; Sansannah, a place in Palestine:--Sansannah.
of uncertain derivation; a fin (collectively):--fins.
from the same as 5483; a moth (from the agility of the fly):--moth.
of uncertain derivation; Sismai, an Israelite:--Sisamai.
a primitive root; to suport (mostly figurative):--comfort, establish, hold up, refresh self, strengthen, be upholden.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5582; to aid:--helping.
a primitive root; to rush:--storm.
from 5586; a fissure (of rocks); also a bough (as subdivided):--(outmost) branch, clift, top.
a primitive root; properly, to divide up; but used only as denominative from 5585, to disbranch (a tree):--top.
or samiph {saw-eef'}; from 5586; divided (in mind), i.e. (abstractly) a sentiment:--opinion.
from 5586; divided (in mind), i.e. (concretely) a skeptic:--thought.
feminine of 5585; a twig:--bough, branch. Compare 5634.

a primitive root; to rush upon; by implication, to toss (transitive or intransitive, literal or figurative):--be (toss with) tempest(-uous), be sore, troubled, come out as a (drive with the, scatter with a) whirlwind.
or (feminine) ctarah {seh-aw-raw'}; from 5590; a hurricane:--storm(-y), tempest, whirlwind.
from 5605, in its original sense of containing; a vestibule (as a limit); also a dish (for holding blood or wine):--bason, bowl, cup, door (post), gate, post, threshold.
the same as 5592; Saph, a Philistine:--Saph. Compare 5598.
a primitive root; properly, to tear the hair and beat the breasts (as Orientals do in grief); generally to lament; by implication, to wail:--lament, mourn(-er), wail.

a primitive root; properly, to scrape (literally, to shave; but usually figuratively) together (i.e. to accumulate or increase) or away (i.e. to scatter, remove, or ruin; intransitively, to perish):--add, augment, consume, destroy, heap, join, perish, put.
or saphach (Isaiah 3:17) {saw-fakh'}; a primitive root; properly, to scrape out, but in certain peculiar senses (of removal or association):--abiding, gather together, cleave, smite with the scab.
from 5596; the mange (as making the hair fall off):--scab.
from 5592; bason-like; Sippai, a Philistine:--Sippai. Compare 5593.
from 5596; something (spontaneously) falling off, i.e. a self-sown crop; figuratively, a freshet:--(such) things as (which) grow (of themselves), which groweth of its own accord (itself).
from 5603; a (sea-going) vessel (as ceiled with a deck):--ship.
from 5608; a gem (perhaps used for scratching other substances), probably the sapphire:--sapphire.
from an unused root meaning to depress; a basin (as deepened out):--bowl, dish.
a primitive root; to hide by covering; specifically, to roof (passive participle as noun, a roof) or wainscot; figuratively, to reserve:--cieled, cover, seated.
from 5603; a wainscot:--cieling.
a primitive root; properly, to snatch away, i.e. terminate; but used only as denominative from 5592 (in the sense of a vestibule), to wait at the threshold:--be a doorkeeper.

or saphaq (1 Kings 20:10; Job 27:23; Isaiah 2:6) {saw-fak'}; a primitive root; to clap the hands (in token of compact, derision, grief, indignation, or punishment); by implication of satisfaction, to be enough; by implication of excess, to vomit:--clap, smite, strike, suffice, wallow.
or sepheq (Job 20:22; 36:18) {seh'-fek}; from 5606; chastisement; also satiety:--stroke, sufficiency.

a primitive root; properly, to score with a mark as a tally or record, i.e. (by implication) to inscribe, and also to enumerate; intensively, to recount, i.e. celebrate:--commune, (ac-)count; declare, number, + penknife, reckon, scribe, shew forth, speak, talk, tell (out), writer.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to 5608; a book:--book, roll.
from 5608; a census:--numbering.
the same as 5610; Sephar, a place in Arabia:--Sephar.
or (feminine) ciphrah (Psa. 56:8 (9)) {sif-raw'}; from 5608; properly, writing (the art or a document); by implication, a book:--bill, book, evidence, X learn(-ed) (-ing), letter, register, scroll.
(Aramaic) from the same as 5609; a scribe (secular or sacred):--scribe.
of foreign derivation; Sepharad, a region of Assyria:--Sepharad.
from 5608; a numeration:--number.
patrial from 5617; a Sepharvite or inhabitant of Sepharvain:--Sepharvite.
(dual)
feminine active participle of 5608; a scribe (properly, female); Sophereth, a temple servant:--Sophereth.
a primitive root; properly, to be weighty; but used only in the sense of lapidation or its contrary (as if a delapidation):--(cast, gather out, throw) stone(-s), X surely.
contracted from 5637; peevish:--heavy, sad.
from an unused root meaning to sting; a thistle:--brier.
(Aramaic) of uncertain derivation; a cloak:--coat.
of foreign derivation; Sargon, an Assyrian king:--Sargon.
from a primitive root meaning to tremble; trembling; Sered, an Israelite:--Sered.
patron from 5624; a Seredite (collectively) or descendants of Sered:--Sardites.
from 5493; departure; Sirah, a cistern so-called:--Sirah. See also 5518.
from 5493; apostasy, crime; figuratively, remission:--X continual, rebellion, revolt((-ed)), turn away, wrong.
a primitive root; to extend (even to excess):--exceeding, hand, spread, stretch self, banish.
from 5628; a redundancy:--remnant.
for 8302; a coat of mail:--brigandine.

or caric {saw-reece'}; from an unused root meaning to castrate; a eunuch; by implication, valet (especially of the female apartments), and thus, a minister of state:--chamberlain, eunuch, officer. Compare 7249.
(Aramaic) of foreign origin; an emir:--president.
from an unused root of uncertain meaning; an axle; figuratively, a peer:--lord, plate.
for 5589; a twig:--bough.
a primitive root; to cremate, i.e. to be (near) of kin (such being privileged to kindle the pyre):--burn.
from 5635; a nettle (as stinging like a burn):--brier.
a primitive root; to turn away, i.e. (morally) be refractory:--X away, backsliding, rebellious, revolter(-ing), slide back, stubborn, withdrew.
from an unused root meaning to hide; winter (as the dark season):--winter.
from 5641; hidden; Sethur, an Israelite:--Sethur.
or satham (Numbers 24:15) {saw-tham'}; a primitive root; to stop up; by implication, to repair; figuratively, to keep secret:--closed up, hidden, secret, shut out (up), stop.
a primitive root; to hide (by covering), literally or figuratively:--be absent, keep close, conceal, hide (self), (keep) secret, X surely.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5641; to conceal; figuratively, to demolish:--destroy, secret thing.

or (feminine) cithrah (Deut. 32:38), {sith-raw'}; from 5641; a cover (in a good or a bad, a literal or a figurative sense):--backbiting, covering, covert, X disguise(-th), hiding place, privily, protection, secret(-ly, place).
from 5643; protective; Sithri, an Israelite,: --Zithri.

(masculine and feminine); from 5743; properly, an envelope, i.e. darkness (or density, 2 Chron. 4:17); specifically, a (scud) cloud; also a copse:--clay, (thick) cloud, X thick, thicket. Compare 5672.
or sob {obe}; from an unused root meaning to cover; properly, equivalent to 5645; but used only as an architectural term, an architrave (as shading the pillars):--thick (beam, plant).

a primitive root; to work (in any sense); by implication, to serve, till, (causatively) enslave, etc.:--X be, keep in bondage, be bondmen, bond-service, compel, do, dress, ear, execute, + husbandman, keep, labour(-ing man, bring to pass, (cause to, make to) serve(-ing, self), (be, become) servant(-s), do (use) service, till(-er), transgress (from margin), (set a) work, be wrought, worshipper,
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5647; to do, make, prepare, keep, etc.:--X cut, do, execute, go on, make, move, work.
(Aramaic) from 5648; a servant:--servant.
from 5647; a servant:--X bondage, bondman, (bond-)servant, (man-)servant.
the same as 5650; Ebed, the name of two Israelites:--Ebed.
from 5647; a deed:--work.
from 5647; work; Abda, the name of two Israelites:--Abda
from the active participle of 5647 and 123; worker of Edom; Obed-Edom, the name of five Israelites: --Obed-edom.
from 5647 and 410; serving God; Abdeel, an Israelite: Abdeel. Compare 5661.
or mabowdah {ab-o-daw'}; from 5647; work of any kind:--act, bondage, + bondservant, effect, labour, ministering(-try), office, service(-ile, -itude), tillage, use, work, X wrought.
passive participle of 5647; something wrought, i.e. (concretely) service:--household, store of servants.
from 5647; servitude; Abdon, the name of a place in Palestine and of four Israelites:--Abdon. Compare 5683.
from 5647; servitude:--bondage.
from 5647; serviceable; Abdi, the name of two Israelites:--Abdi.
from 5650 and 410; servant of God; Abdiel, an Israelite:--Abdiel. Compare 5655.
or mObadyahuw {o-bad-yaw'-hoo}; active participle of 5647 and 3050; serving Jah; Obadjah, the name of thirteen Israelites:--Obadiah.
from 5650 and 4428; servant of a king; Ebed-Melek, a eunuch of Zedekeah:--Ebed-melech.
the same as 5665; Abed-Nego, the Babylonian name of one of Daniel's companions:--Abed-nego.
(Aramaic) of foreign origin; Abed-Nego, the name of Azariah:--Abed-nego.
a primitive root; to be dense:--be (grow) thick(-er).
or rabot {ab-ote'}; from 5670; a pawn:--pledge.
or rabur {aw-boor'}; passive participle of 5674; properly, crossed, i.e. (abstractly) transit; used only adverbially, on account of, in order that:--because of, for (...'s sake), (intent) that, to.
the same as 5668; passed, i.e. kept over; used only of stored grain:--old corn.
a primitive root; to pawn; causatively, to lend (on security); figuratively, to entangle:--borrow, break (ranks), fetch (a pledge), lend, X surely.
from 5670; something pledged, i.e. (collectively) pawned goods:--thick clay (by a false etym.).
or mobiy {ob-ee'}; from 5666; density, i.e. depth or width:--thick(-ness). Compare 5645.
(Aramaic) from 5648; labor or business:--affairs, service, work.

a primitive root; to cross over; used very widely of any transition (literal or figurative; transitive, intransitive, intensive, causative); specifically, to cover (in copulation):--alienate, alter, X at all, beyond, bring (over, through), carry over, (over-)come (on, over), conduct (over), convey over, current, deliver, do away, enter, escape, fail, gender, get over, (make) go (away, beyond, by, forth, his way, in, on, over, through), have away (more), lay, meddle, overrun, make partition, (cause to, give, make to, over) pass(-age, along, away, beyond, by, -enger, on, out, over, through), (cause to, make) + proclaim(-amation), perish, provoke to anger, put away, rage, + raiser of taxes, remove, send over, set apart, + shave, cause to (make) sound, X speedily, X sweet smelling, take (away), (make to) transgress(-or), translate, turn away, (way-)faring man, be wrath.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5676:--beyond, this side.

from 5674; properly, a region across; but used only adverbially (with or without a preposition) on the opposite side (especially of the Jordan; ususally meaning the east):--X against, beyond, by, X from, over, passage, quarter, (other, this) side, straight.
the same as 5676; Eber, the name of two patriarchs and four Israelites:--Eber, Heber.
feminine of 5676; an outburst of passion:--anger, rage, wrath.
from 5674; a crossing-place:--ferry, plain (from the margin).
patronymic from 5677; an Eberite (i.e. Hebrew) or descendant of Eber:--Hebrew(-ess, woman).
the same as 5680; Ibri, an Israelite:--Ibri.
plural of 5676; regions beyond; Abarim, a place in Palestine:--Abarim, passages.
from 5676; transitional; Ebron, a place in Palestine:--Hebron. Perhaps a clerical error for 5658.
feminine of 5683; Ebronah, place in the Desert:--Ebronah.
a primitive root; to dry up:--be rotten.
a primitive root; to interlace, i.e. (figuratively) to pervert:--wrap up.
or rabowth {aw-both'}; from 5686; intwined, i.e. dense:--thick.
or rabowth {ab-oth'}; or (feminine) tabothah {ab- oth-aw'}; the same as 5687; something intwined, i.e. a string, wreath or foliage:--band, cord, rope, thick bough (branch), wreathen (chain).
a primitive root; to breathe after, i.e. to love (sensually):--dote, lover.
from 5689; love (concretely), i.e. amative words:--much love, very lovely.
from 5689; love (abstractly), i.e. amorousness:--inordinate love.
from 5746; an ash-cake (as round):--cake (upon the hearth).
passive part (but with active sense) of an unused root meaning to twitter: probably the swallow:--swallow.
from the same as 5696; something round, i.e. a ring (for the ears):--earring.
from the same as 5696; a (male) calf (as frisking round), especially one nearly grown (i.e. a steer):--bullock, calf.
or magowl {aw-gole'}; from an unused root meaning to revolve, circular:--round.
feminine of 5695; a (female) calf, especially one nearly grown (i.e. a heifer):--calf, cow, heifer.
the same as 5697; Eglah, a wife of David:--Eglah.
from the same as 5696; something revolving, i.e. a wheeled vehicle:--cart, chariot, wagon
from 5695; vituline; Eglon, the name of a place in Palestine and of a Moabitish king:--Eglon.
a primitive root; to be sad:--grieve.
a primitive root; to debar, i.e. from marriage:--stay.

from 5710; properly, a (peremptory) terminus, i.e. (by implication) duration, in the sense of advance or perpetuity (substantially as a noun, either with or without a preposition):--eternity, ever(- lasting, -more), old, perpetually, + world without end.

properly, the same as 5703 (used as a preposition, adverb or conjunction; especially with a preposition); as far (or long, or much) as, whether of space (even unto) or time (during, while, until) or degree (equally with):--against, and, as, at, before, by (that), even (to), for(-asmuch as), (hither-)to, + how long, into, as long (much) as, (so) that, till, toward, until, when, while, (+ as) yet.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5704; X and, at, for, (hither-)to, on till, (un-)to, until, within.
the same as 5703 in the sense of the aim of an attack; booty:--prey.
contracted from 5749 ; concretely, a witness; abstractly, testimony; specifically, a recorder, i.e. prince:--witness.
from an unused root meaning to set a period (compare 5710, 5749); the menstrual flux (as periodical); by implication (in plural) soiling:--filthy.
(Aramaic) or adah (Aramaic) {ad-aw'}; corresponding to 5710:--alter, depart, pass (away), remove, take (away).
a primitive root; to advance, i.e. pass on or continue; causatively, to remove; specifically, to bedeck (i.e. bring an ornament upon):--adorn, deck (self), pass by, take away.
from 5710; ornament; Adah, the name of two women:--Adah.

feminine of 5707 in the original sense of fixture; a stated assemblage (specifically, a concourse, or generally, a family or crowd):--assembly, company, congregation, multitude, people, swarm. Compare 5713.
feminine of 5707 in its techn. sense; testimony:-- testimony, witness. Compare 5712.
or iIddowo {id-do'}; or tIddiy {id-dee'}; from 5710; timely; Iddo (or Iddi), the name of five Israelites:--Iddo. Compare 3035, 3260.
feminine of 5707; testimony:--testimony, witness.
from 5710 in the sense of trappings; finery; generally an outfit; specifically, a headstall:--X excellent, mouth, ornament.
from 5716 and 410; ornament of God; Adiel, the name of three Israelites:--Adiel.
or mAdayahuw {ad-aw-yaw'-hoo}; from 5710 and 3050; Jah has adorned; Adajah, the name of eight Israelites:--Adaiah.
from 5727; voluptuous:--given to pleasures.
the same as 5719; Adin, the name of two Israelites:--Adin.
from 5719; effeminacy; Adina, an Israelite:--Adina.
probably from 5719 in the original sense of slender (i.e. a spear); his spear:--Adino.
dual of a feminine of 5706; double prey; Adithajim, a place in Palestine:--Adithaim.
probably from an unused root of uncertain meaning; Adlai, an Israelite:--Adlai.
probably from the passive participle of the same as 5724; Adullam, a place in Palestine:--Adullam.
patrial from 5725; an Adullamite or native of Adullam:--Adullamite.
a primitive root; to be soft or pleasant; figuratively and reflexively, to live voluptuously:--delight self.
or radennah {ad-en'-naw}; from 5704 and 2004; till now:--yet.
from 5727; pleasure; Eden, a place in Mesopotamia:--Eden.
or (feminine) aednah {ed-naw'}; from 5727; pleasure:--delicate, delight, pleasure. See also 1040.
the same as 5730 (masculine); Eden, the region of Adam's home:--Eden.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to that of 5708; a set time; technically, a year:--time.
from 5727; pleasure; Adna, the name of two Israelites:--Adna.
