from 5727; pleasure; Adnah, the name of two Israelites:--Adnah.
from 5712; festival; Adadah, a place in Palestine:--Adadah.
a primitive root; to be (causatively, have) redundant:--be more, odd number, be (have) over (and above), overplus, remain.
a primitive root; to arrange, as a battle, a vineyard (to hoe); hence, to muster and so to miss (or find wanting):--dig, fail, keep (rank), lack.
from 5737; an arrangement (i.e. drove); Eder, an Israelite:--Ader.
from 5737; an arrangement, i.e. muster (of animals):--drove, flock, herd.
the same as 5739; Eder, the name of an Israelite and of two places in Palestine:--Edar, Eder.
from 5739 and 410; flock of God; Adriel, an Israelite:--Adriel.
from an unused root of uncertain meaning; a lentil:--lentile.
a primitive root; to be dense or dark, i.e. to becloud:--cover with a cloud.
active participle of 5647; serving; Obed, the name of five Israelites:--Obed.
of foreign derivation; Obal, a son of Joktan:--Obal.
a primitive root; properly, to gyrate; but used only as a denominative from 5692, to bake (round cakes on the hearth):--bake.
probably from 5746; round; Og, a king of Bashan:--Og.
or buggab {oog-gawb'}; from 5689 in the original sense of breathing; a reed-instrument of music:--organ.

a primitive root; to duplicate or repeat; by implication, to protest, testify (as by reiteration); intensively, to encompass, restore (as a sort of reduplication):--admonish, charge, earnestly, lift up, protest, call (take) to record, relieve, rob, solemnly, stand upright, testify, give warning, (bear, call to, give, take to) witness.

or rod {ode}; from 5749; properly, iteration or continuance; used only adverbially (with or without preposition), again, repeatedly, still, more:--again, X all life long, at all, besides, but, else, further(-more), henceforth, (any) longer, (any) more(-over), X once, since, (be) still, when, (good, the) while (having being), (as, because, whether, while) yet (within).
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5750:--while.
or mOded {o-dade'}; from 5749; reiteration; Oded, the name of two Israelites:--Oded.
a primitive root; to crook, literally or figuratively (as follows):--do amiss, bow down, make crooked, commit iniquity, pervert, (do) perverse(-ly), trouble, X turn, do wickedly, do wrong.
intensive from 5753 abbreviated; overthrow:--X overturn.
or eAvvae (2 Kings 17:24) {av-vaw'}; for 5754; Ivvah or Avva, a region of Assyria:--Ava, Ivah.
a primitive root; to be strong; causatively, to stregthen, i.e. (figuratively) to save (by flight):--gather (self, self to flee), retire.
patrial from 5755; an Avvite or native of Avvah (only plural):--Avims, Avites.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to 5753; perverseness:--iniquity.
from 5764; a babe:--young child, little one.
from 5765; perverse (morally):--ungodly.
plural of 5757; Avvim (as inhabited by Avvites), a place in Palestine (with the article prefix):--Avim.
or (perhaps Ayowth {ah-yoth'}, as if plural of 5857) cAyuwth {ah-yoth'}; from 5753; ruin; Avvith (or Avvoth), a place in Palestine:--Avith.
a primitive root; to suckle, i.e. give milk:--milch, (ewe great) with young.
from 5763; a babe:--sucking child, infant.
a primitive root; to distort (morally):--deal unjustly, unrighteous.
or lavel {aw'-vel}; and (feminine) lavlah {av-law'}; or owlah {o-law'}; or .olah {o-law'}; from 5765; (moral) evil:--iniquity, perverseness, unjust(-ly), unrighteousness(-ly); wicked(-ness).
intensive from 5765; evil (morally):--unjust, unrighteous, wicked.
or lolal {o-lawl'}; from 5763; a suckling:--babe, (young) child, infant, little one.

or lolam {o-lawm'}; from 5956; properly, concealed, i.e. the vanishing point; generally, time out of mind (past or future), i.e. (practically) eternity; frequentatively, adverbial (especially with prepositional prefix) always:--alway(-s), ancient (time), any more, continuance, eternal, (for, (n-))ever(-lasting, -more, of old), lasting, long (time), (of) old (time), perpetual, at any time, (beginning of the) world (+ without end). Compare 5331, 5703.
denominative from 5869; to watch (with jealosy):--eye.
or oavown (2 Kings 7:9; Psalm 51:5 (7)) {aw-vone'}; from 5753; perversity, i.e. (moral) evil:--fault, iniquity, mischeif, punishment (of iniquity), sin.
from an unused root apparently meaning to dwell together; sexual (cohabitation):--duty of marriage.
from 5753; perversity:--X perverse.

a primitive root; to cover (with wings or obscurity); hence (as denominative from 5775) to fly; also (by implication of dimness) to faint (from the darkness of swooning):--brandish, be (wax) faint, flee away, fly (away), X set, shine forth, weary.
from 5774; a bird (as covered with feathers, or rather as covering with wings), often collectively:--bird, that flieth, flying, fowl.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5775:--fowl.
or mophereth {o-feh'-reth}; feminine participle active of 6080; lead (from its dusty color):--lead.
from 5775; birdlike; Ephai, an Israelite:--Ephai (from margin).
a primitive root; to consult:--take advice ((counsel) together).
apparently from 5779; consultation; Uts, a son of Aram, also a Seirite, and the regions settled by them.:--Uz.
a primitive root; to pack:--be pressed.
a primitive root (rather identical with 5783 through the idea of opening the eyes); to wake (literally or figuratively):--(a- )wake(-n, up), lift up (self), X master, raise (up), stir up (self).
a primitive root; to (be) bare:--be made naked.
(Aramaic) chaff (as the naked husk):--chaff.
from 5783; skin (as naked); by implication, hide, leather:--hide, leather, skin.
a primitive root (rather denominatively from 5785 through the idea of a film over the eyes); to blind:--blind, put out. See also 5895.
intensive from 5786; blind (literally or figuratively):--blind (men, people).
and (feminine) avvereth {av-veh'-reth}; from 5787; blindness:--blind(-ness).
a primitive root; to hasten:--assemble self.
for 5789; to hasten, i.e. succor:--speak in season.
a primitive root; to wrest:--bow self, (make) crooked., falsifying, overthrow, deal perversely, pervert, subvert, turn upside down.
from 5791; oppression:--wrong.
from 5790; succoring; Uthai, the name of two Israelites:--Uthai.
from 5810; strong, vehement, harsh:--fierce, + greedy, mighty, power, roughly, strong.
from 5810; a she-goat (as strong), but masculine in plural (which also is used ellipt. for goat's hair):--(she) goat, kid.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5795:--goat.
or (fully) rowz {oze}; from 5810; strength in various applications (force, security, majesty, praise):--boldness, loud, might, power, strength, strong.
or (Uzzah {ooz-zaw'}; feminine of 5797; strength; Uzza or Uzzah, the name of five Israelites:--Uzza, Uzzah.
from 5795 and 235; goat of departure; the scapegoat:--scapegoat.
a primitive root; to loosen, i.e. relinquish, permit, etc.:--commit self, fail, forsake, fortify, help, leave (destitute, off), refuse, X surely.
from 5800 in the sense of letting go (for a price, i.e. selling); trade, i.e. the place (mart) or the payment (revenue):--fair, ware.
from 5794 and the root of 950; stern depopulator; Azbuk, an Israelite:--Azbuk.
from 5794 and 1409; stern troop; Azgad, an Israelite:--Azgad.
feminine of 5794; strong; Azzah, a place in Palestine:--Azzah, Gaza.
feminine passive participle of 5800; desertion (of inhabitants):--forsaking.
the same as 5805; Azubah, the name of two Israelitesses:--Azubah.
from 5810; forcibleness:--might, strength.
from 5810; forcible; collectively and concretely, an army:--power, strong.
or mAzzur {az-zoor'}; from 5826; helpful; Azzur, the name of three Israelites:--Azur, Azzur.
a primitive root; to be stout (literally or figuratively):--harden, impudent, prevail, strengthen (self), be strong.
from 5810; strong; Azaz, an Israelite:--Azaz.
from 5810 and 3050; Jah has strengthened; Azazjah, the name of three Israelites:--Azaziah.
from 5810; forceful; Uzzi, the name of six Israelites:--Uzzi.
perhaps for 5818; Uzzija, an Israelite:--Uzzia.
from 5756 and 410; strengthened of God; Aziel, an Israelite:--Aziel. Compare 3268.
from 5797 and 410; strength of God; Uzziel, the name of six Israelites:--Uzziel.
patronymically from 5816; an Uzzielite (collectively) or descendants of Uzziel:--Uzzielites.
or Uzziyahuw {ooz-zee-yaw'-hoo}; from 5797 and 3050; strength of Jah; Uzzijah, the name of five Israelites:--Uzziah.
from 5756; strengthfulness; Aziza, an Israelite:--Aziza.
from 5794 and 4194; strong one of death; Azmaveth, the name of three Israelites and of a place in Palestine:--Azmaveth. See also 1041.
from 5794; strong one; Azzan, an Israelite:--Azzan.
probably feminine of 5797; probably the sea-eagle (from its strength):--ospray.
a primitive root; to grub over:--fence about.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to 5823; a signet-ring (as engraved):--signet.
from 5823; tilled; Azekah, a place in Palestine:--Azekah.
a primitive root; to surround, i.e. protect or aid:--help, succour.
from 5826; help; Ezer, the name of two Israelites:--Ezer. Compare 5829.
from 5826; aid:--help.
the same as 5828; Ezer, the name of four Israelites:--Ezer. Compare 5827.
a variation of 5833; Ezra, an Israelite:--Ezra.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5830; Ezra, an Israelite --Ezra.
from 5826 and 410; God has helped; Azarel, the name of five Israelites:--Azarael, Azareel.
or mezrath (Psa. 60:11 (13); 108:12 (13)) {ez-rawth'}; feminine of 5828; aid:--help(-ed, -er).
the same as 5833; Ezrah, an Israelite:--Ezrah.
from 5826 in its original meaning of surrounding; an inclosure; also a border:--court, settle.
from 5828; helpful; Ezri, an Israelite:--Ezri.
from 5828 and 410; help of God; Azriel, the name of three Israelites:--Azriel.
or mAzaryahuw {az-ar-yaw'-hoo}; from 5826 and 3050; Jah has helped; Azarjah, the name of nineteen Israelites:--Azariah.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5838; Azarjah, one of Daniel's companions:--Azariah.
from 5828 and active participle of 6965; help of an enemy; Azrikam, the name of four Israelites:--Azrikam.
patrial from 5804; an Azzathite or inhabitant of Azzah:--Gazathite, Gazite.
from 5860 (contracted) in the sense of swooping, i.e. side-long stroke; a stylus or marking stick:--pen.
(Aramaic) from 3272; prudence:--counsel.
a primitive root; to wrap, i.e. cover, veil, cloth, or roll:--array self, be clad, (put a) cover (-ing, self), fill, put on, X surely, turn aside.
from an unused root meaning apparently to contain; a receptacle (for milk, i.e. pail; figuratively, breast):--breast.
from an unused root meaning to sneeze; sneezing:--sneezing.
of uncertain derivation; a bat:--bat.
a primitive root; to shroud, i.e. clothe (whether transitive or reflex.); hence (from the idea of darkness) to languish:-- cover (over), fail, faint, feebler, hide self, be overwhelmed, swoon.
a primitive root; to encircle (for attack or protection); especially to crown (literally or figuratively):--compass, crown.
from 5849; a crown:--crown.
the same as 5850; Atarah, an Israelitess:--Atarah.
or Ataroth {at-aw-roth'}; plural of 5850; Ataroth, the name (thus simply) of two places in Palestine:--Ataroth.
from the same as 5852 and 146; crowns of Addar; Atroth-Addar, a place in Palestine: --Ataroth-adar(-addar).
from the same as 5852 and 1004 and 3097; crowns of the house of Joab; Atroth-beth-Joab, a place in Palestine:--Ataroth the house of Joab.
from the same as 5852 and a name otherwise unused (being from the same as 8226) meaning hidden; crowns of Shophan; Atroth-Shophan, a place in Palestine:--Atroth, Shophan (as if two places).
from 5753; a ruin (as if overturned):--heap.
or (feminine) uAya( (Neh. 11:31) {ah-yaw'}; or eAyath (Isaiah 10:28) {ah-yawth'}; for 5856; Ai, Aja or Ajath, a place in Palestine:--Ai, Aija, Aijath, Hai.
perhaps from an unused root probably meaning to be bald; bare; Ebal, a mountain of Palestine:--Ebal.
from 5856; ruin; Ijon, a place in Palestine:--Ijon.
a primitive root; to swoop down upon (literally or figuratively):--fly, rail.
from 5860; a hawk or other bird of prey:--bird, fowl, ravenous (bird).
from 5861; hawk-ground; Etam, a place in Palestine:--Etam.
from the plural of 5856 and the plural of the active participle of 5674 with the article interposed; ruins of the passers; Ije-ha-Abarim, a place near Palestine:--Ije-abarim.
plural of 5856; ruins; Ijim, a place in the Desert.:--Iim.
for 5769:--ever.
from 5927; elevated; Ilai, an Israelite:--Ilai.
or mOwlam (Ezra 10:2; Jeremiah 49:36) {o-lawm'}; probably from 5956; hidden, i.e. distant; Elam, a son of Shem and his descendants, with their country; also of six Israelites:--Elam.
of doubtful origin and authenticity; probably meaning strength:--mighty.

probably a primitive word; an eye (literally or figuratively); by analogy, a fountain (as the eye of the landscape):--affliction, outward appearance, + before, + think best, colour, conceit, + be content, countenance, + displease, eye((-brow), (-d), -sight), face, + favour, fountain, furrow (from the margin), X him, + humble, knowledge, look, (+ well), X me, open(-ly), + (not) please, presence, + regard, resemblance, sight, X thee, X them, + think, X us, well, X you(-rselves).
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5869; an eye:--eye.
the same as 5869; fountain; Ajin, the name (thus simply) of two places in Palestine:--Ain.
from 5869 and 1423; fountain of a kid; En-Gedi, a place in Palestine:--En-gedi.
from 5869 and the plural of 1588; fountain of gardens; En-Gannim, a place in Palestine:--En-gannim.
or mEyn Dowr {ane dore}; or Eyn-Dor {ane-dore'}; from 5869 and 1755; fountain of dwelling; En-Dor, a place in Palestine:--En-dor.
from 5869 and the active participle of 7121; fountain of One calling; En-hak-Kore, a place near Palestine:--En-hakhore.
from 5869 and the feminine of a derivative from 2300; fountain of sharpness; En-Chaddah, a place in Palestine:--En-haddah.
from 5869 and the same as 2674; fountain of a village; En-Chatsor, a place in Palestine:--En-hazor.
from 5869 and a derivative of 2729; fountain of trembling; En-Charod, a place in Palestine:--well of Harod.
or mEynam {ay-nawm'}; dual of 5869; double fountain; Enajim or Enam, a place in Palestine:--Enaim, openly (Genesis 38:21).
from 5869 and 4941; fountain of judgment; En-Mishpat, a place near Palestine:--En-mishpat.
from 5869; having eyes; Enan, an Israelite:--Enan. Compare 2704.
5869 and the dual of 5695; fountain of two calves; En-Eglajim, a place in Palestine:--En-eglaim.
from 5869 and the active participle of 7270; fountain of a traveller; En-Rogel, a place near Jerusalem: --En-rogel.

from 5869 and 8121; fountain of the sun; En-Shemesh, a place in Palestine:--En-shemesh.
from 5869 and the plural of 8565; fountain of jackals; En-Tannim, a pool near Jerusalem:--dragon well.
from 5869 and 8598; fountain of an apple-tree; En-Tappuach, a place in Palestine:--En-tappuah.
a primitive root; to languish:--be wearied.
from 5888; languid:--faint, thirsty, weary.
feminine from 5774; obscurity (as if from covering):--darkness.
the same as 5890; Ephah, the name of a son of Midian, and of the region settled by him; also of an Israelite and of an Israelitess:--Ephah.

or (in the plural) par {awr}; or ayar (Judges 10:4) {aw-yar'}; from 5782 a city (a place guarded by waking or a watch) in the widest sense (even of a mere encampment or post):--Ai (from margin), city, court (from margin), town.
the same as 5892; Ir, an Israelite:--Ir.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to 5782; a watcher, i.e. an angel (as guardian):--watcher.
from 5782 in the sense of raising (i.e. bearing a burden); properly, a young ass (as just broken to a load); hence an ass-colt:--(ass) colt, foal, young ass.
from 5782; wakefulness; Ira, the name of three Israelites:--Ira.
from the same as 6166; fugitive; Irad, an antediluvian:--Irad.
from 5892 and 4417 with the article of substance interp.; city of (the) salt; Ir-ham-Melach, a place near Palestine:--the city of salt.
from 5892 and the plural of 8558 with the article interpolated; city of the palmtrees; Ir-hat-Temarim, a place in Palestine:--the city of palmtrees.
from 5892; a citizen; Iru, an Israelite:--Iru.
from 5892; urbane; Iri, an Israelite:--Iri.
from 5892; city-wise; Iram, an Idumaean:--Iram.
or merom {ay-rome'}; from 6191; nudity:--naked(- ness).
from 5892 and 5175; city of a serpent; Ir-Nachash, a place in Palestine:--Ir-nahash.
from 5892 and 8121; city of the sun; Ir-Shemesh, a place in Palestine:--Ir-shemesh.
or mAsh {awsh}; from 5789; the constellation of the Great Bear (perhaps from its migration through the heavens):-- Arcturus.
probably for 5909; Akbor, the name of an Idumaean and of two Israelites:--Achbor.
probably from an unused root in the literal sense of entangling; a spider (as weaving a network):--spider.
probably from the same as 5908 in the secondary sense of attacking; a mouse (as nibbling):--mouse.
apparently from an unused root meaning to hem in; Akko (from its situation on a bay):--Accho.
from 5916; troubled; Akor, the name of a place in Palestine:--Achor.
from an unused root meaning to trouble; troublesome; Akan, an Israelite:--Achan. Compare 5917.
a primitive root; properly, to tie, specifically, with fetters; but used only as denominative from 5914; to put on anklets:--make a tinkling ornament.
from 5913; a fetter; hence, an anklet:--stocks, tinkling ornament.
feminine of 5914; anklet; Aksah, an Israelitess:--Achsah.
a primitive root; properly, to roil water; figuratively, to disturb or affict:--trouble, stir.
from 5916; troublesome; Akar, an Israelite:--Achar. Compare 5912.
from 5916; muddler; Okran, an Israelite:--Ocran.
probably from an unused root meaning to coil; an asp (from lurking coiled up):--adder.
from 5927; properly, the top; specifically, the highest (i.e. God); also (adverb) aloft, to Jehovah:--above, high, most High.

properly, the same as 5920 used as a preposition (in the singular or plural often with prefix, or as conjunction with a particle following); above, over, upon, or against (yet always in this last relation with a downward aspect) in a great variety of applications (as follow):--above, according to(-ly), after, (as) against, among, and, X as, at, because of, beside (the rest of), between, beyond the time, X both and, by (reason of), X had the charge of, concerning for, in (that), (forth, out) of, (from) (off), (up-)on, over, than, through(-out), to, touching, X with.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5921:--about, against, concerning, for, (there-)fore, from, in, X more, of, (there-, up-)on, (in-)to, + why with.
or mowl {ole}; from 5953; a yoke (as imposed on the neck), literally or figuratively:--yoke.
(Aramaic) from 5922; above:--over.
feminine of 5923; burden; Ulla, an Israelite:--Ulla.
from an unused root meaning to stutter; stuttering:--stammerer.

a primitive root; to ascend, intransitively (be high) or actively (mount); used in a great variety of senses, primary and secondary, literal and figurative (as follow):--arise (up), (cause to) ascend up, at once, break (the day) (up), bring (up), (cause to) burn, carry up, cast up, + shew, climb (up), (cause to, make to) come (up), cut off, dawn, depart, exalt, excel, fall, fetch up, get up, (make to) go (away, up); grow (over) increase, lay, leap, levy, lift (self) up, light, (make) up, X mention, mount up, offer, make to pay, + perfect, prefer, put (on), raise, recover, restore, (make to) rise (up), scale, set (up), shoot forth (up), (begin to) spring (up), stir up, take away (up), work.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5930; a holocaust:--burnt offering.
from 5927; a leaf (as coming up on a tree); collectively, foliage:--branch, leaf.

or mowlah {o-law'}; feminine active participle of 5927; a step or (collectively, stairs, as ascending); usually a holocaust (as going up in smoke):--ascent, burnt offering (sacrifice), go up to. See also 5766.
(Aramaic) feminine from a root corresponding to 5927; a pretext (as arising artificially):--occasion.
for 5766; moral perverseness:--iniquity.
or Alyah {al-yaw'}; the same as 5932; Alvah or Aljah, an Idumaean:--Aliah, Alvah.
passive participle of 5956 in the denominative sense of 5958; (only in plural as abstract) adolescence; figuratively, vigor:--youth.
or sAlyan {al-yawn'}; from 5927; lofty; Alvan or Aljan, an Idumaean:--Alian, Alvan.
feminine passive participle of an unused root meaning to suck; the leech:--horse-leech.
a primitive root; to jump for joy, i.e. exult:--be joyful, rejoice, triumph.
from 5937; exultant:--that rejoiceth.
feminine from an unused root meaning to cover; dusk:--dark, twilight.
from 5927; a pestle (as lifted):--pestle.

feminine from 5927; something lofty, i.e. a stair-way; also a second-story room (or even one on the roof); figuratively, the sky:--ascent, (upper) chamber, going up, loft, parlour.
from 5927; an elevation, i.e. (adj.) lofty (compar.); as title, the Supreme:--(Most, on) high(-er, -est), upper(-most).

from 5937; exultant:--joyous, (that) rejoice(-ing)

from 5970; exultation:--rejoicing.
from 5927; a second-story room:--chamber. Compare 5944.

a primitive root; to effect thoroughly; specifically, to glean (also figuratively); by implication (in a bad sense) to overdo, i.e. maltreat, be saucy to, pain, impose (also literal):--abuse, affect, X child, defile, do, glean, mock, practise, thoroughly, work (wonderfully).

a primitive root; to veil from sight, i.e. conceal (literally or figuratively):--X any ways, blind, dissembler, hide (self), secret (thing).

from 5956; hidden; Almon, a place in Palestine See also 5963.

from 5956; a covering; Alemeth, the name of a place in Palestine and of two Israelites:--Alameth, Alemeth.
a primitive root; to leap for joy, i.e. exult, wave joyously:--X peacock, rejoice, solace self.
a prim root; to sip up:--suck up.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6763; a rib:--rib.
a primitive root; to veil or cover; figuratively, to be languid:--faint, overlaid, wrap self.
from 5968; an envelope, i.e. (figuratively) mourning:--fainted.
a primitive root; to jump for joy, i.e. exult:--be joyful, rejoice, triumph.
from 6004; a people (as a congregated unit); specifically, a tribe (as those of Israel); hence (collectively) troops or attendants; figuratively, a flock:--folk, men, nation, people.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5971:--people.

from 6004; adverb or preposition, with (i.e. in conjunction with), in varied applications; specifically, equally with; often with prepositional prefix (and then usually unrepresented in English):--accompanying, against, and, as (X long as), before, beside, by (reason of), for all, from (among, between), in, like, more than, of, (un-)to, with(-al).
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5973:--by, from, like, to(-ward), with.

a primitive root; to stand, in various relations (literal and figurative, intransitive and transitive):--abide (behind), appoint, arise, cease, confirm, continue, dwell, be employed, endure, establish, leave, make, ordain, be (over), place, (be) present (self), raise up, remain, repair, + serve, set (forth, over, -tle, up), (make to, make to be at a, with-)stand (by, fast, firm, still, up), (be at a) stay (up), tarry.

from 5975; a spot (as being fixed):--place, (+ where) stood, upright.

the same as 5980; association; Ummah, a place in Palestine:--Ummah.
or ammud {am-mood'}; from 5975; a column (as standing); also a stand, i.e. platform:--X apiece, pillar.
from 5971; tribal, i.e. inbred; Ammon, a son of Lot; also his posterity and their country:--Ammon, Ammonites.
patronymically from 5983; an Ammonite or (the adjective) Ammonitish:--Ammonite(-s).
feminine of 5984; an Ammonitess:--Ammonite(-ss).
from 6006; burdensome; Amos, an Israelite prophet:--Amos.
from 6009; deep; Amok, an Israelite:--Amok.
from 5971 and 410; people of God; Ammiel, the name of three or four Israelites:--Ammiel.
from 5971 and 1935; people of splendor; Ammihud, the name of three Israelites:--Ammihud.
from 5971 and 2064; people of endowment; Ammizabad, an Israelite:--Ammizabad.
from 5971 and 2353; people of nobility; Ammichur, a Syrian prince:--Ammihud (from the margin).
from 5971 and 5068; people of liberality; Amminadab, the name of four Israelites:--Amminadab.
from 5971 and 5081; my people (is) liberal; Ammi-Nadib, probably an Israelite:--Amminadib.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6012; profound, i.e. unsearchable, deep.
from 6014; a bunch of grain:--handful, sheaf.
from 5971 and 7706; people of (the) Almighty; Ammishaddai, an Israelite:--Ammishaddai.
from a primitive root meaning to associate; companionship; hence (concretely) a comrade or kindred man:--another, fellow, neighbour.
a primitive root; to toil, i.e. work severely and with irksomeness:--(take) labour (in).

from 5998; toil, i.e. wearing effort; hence, worry, wheth. of body or mind:--grievance(-vousness), iniquity, labour, mischief, miserable(-sery), pain(-ful), perverseness, sorrow, toil, travail, trouble, wearisome, wickedness.
the same as 5999; Amal, an Israelite:--Amal.
from 5998; toiling; concretely, a laborer; figuratively, sorrowful:--that laboureth, that is a misery, had taken (labour), wicked, workman.
probably of foreign origin; Amalek, a descendant of Esau; also his posterity and their country:--Amalek.
patronymically from 6002; an Amalekite (or collectively the Amalekites) or descendants of Amalek: --Amalekite(-s).
a primitive root; to associate; by implication, to overshadow (by huddling together):--become dim, hide.
from 5973 and 410 with a pronominal suffix inserted; with us (is) God; Immanuel, a type name of Isaiah's son:--Immanuel.

from 6006 and 3050; Jah has loaded; Amasjah, an Israelite:--Amasiah.
from 5971 and 5703; people of time; Amad, a place in Palestine:--Amad.
a primitive root; to be (causatively, make) deep (literally or figuratively):--(be, have, make, seek) deep(-ly), depth, be profound.
from 6009; a vale (i.e. broad depression):--dale, vale, valley (often used as a part of proper names). See also 1025.
from 6009; depth:--depth.
from 6009; deep (literally or figuratively):--deeper, depth, strange.
from 6009; deep (literally or figuratively):--(X exceeding) deep (thing).
a primitive root; properly, apparently to heap; figuratively, to chastise (as if piling blows); specifically (as denominative from 6016) to gather grain:--bind sheaves, make merchandise of.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6785; wool:--wool.
from 6014; properly, a heap, i.e. a sheaf; also an omer, as a dry measure:--omer, sheaf.
from 6014; a (ruined) heap; Amorah, a place in Palestine:--Gomorrah.
from 6014; heaping; Omri, an Israelite:--Omri.
probably from 5971 and 7311; high people; Amram, the name of two Israelites:--Amram.
from 6019; an Amramite or descendant of Amram:--Amramite.
from 6006; burden; Amasa, the name of two Israelites:--Amasa.
from 6006; burdensome; Amasai, the name of three Israelites:--Amasai.
probably from 6006; burdensome; Amashsay, an Israelite:--Amashai.
from the same as 6025; fruit; Anab, a place in Palestine:--Anab.
from an unused root probably meaning to bear fruit; a grape:--(ripe) grape, wine.
a primitive root; to be soft or pliable, i.e. (figuratively) effeminate or luxurious:--delicate(-ness), (have) delight (self), sport self.
from 6026; luxury:--delight, pleasant.
from 6026; luxurious:--delicate.
a primitive root; to lace fast:--bind, tie.

a primitive root; properly, to eye or (generally) to heed, i.e. pay attention; by implication, to respond; by extens. to begin to speak; specifically to sing, shout, testify, announce:--give account, afflict (by mistake for 6031), (cause to, give) answer, bring low (by mistake for 6031), cry, hear, Leannoth, lift up, say, X scholar, (give a) shout, sing (together by course), speak, testify, utter, (bear) witness. See also 1042, 1043.

a primitive root (possibly rather ident. with 6030 through the idea of looking down or browbeating); to depress literally or figuratively, transitive or intransitive (in various applications, as follows):--abase self, afflict(-ion, self), answer (by mistake for 6030), chasten self, deal hardly with, defile, exercise, force, gentleness, humble (self), hurt, ravish, sing (by mistake for 6030), speak (by mistake for 6030), submit self, weaken, X in any wise.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6030:--answer, speak.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6031:--poor.
probably from 6030; an answer; Anah, the name of two Edomites and one Edomitess:--Anah.
or (by intermixture with 6041) Aanayv {aw-nawv'}; from 6031; depressed (figuratively), in mind (gentle) or circumstances (needy, especially saintly):--humble, lowly, meek, poor. Compare 6041.
passive participle from the same as 6025; borne (as fruit); Anub, an Israelite:--Anub.
feminine of 6035; mildness (royal); also (concretely) oppressed:--gentleness, meekness.
from 6035; condescension, human and subjective (modesty), or divine and objective (clemency):--gentleness, humility, meekness.
from 6031; affliction:--affliction.
from 6031; depression, i.e. misery: --afflicted(-ion), trouble.

from 6031; depressed, in mind or circumstances (practically the same as 6035, although the margin constantly disputes this, making 6035 subjective and 6041 objective):--afflicted, humble, lowly, needy, poor.
from 6031; afflicted; Unni, the name of two Israelites:--Unni.
from 6030; Jah has answered; Anajah, the name of two Israelites:--Anaiah.
for plural of 5869; fountains; Anim, a place in Palestine:--Anim.
from 6031; ado, i.e. (generally) employment or (specifically) an affair:--business, travail.
from the dual of 5869; two fountains; Anem, a place in Palestine: Anem.
as if plural of some Egyptian word; Anamim, a son of Mizraim and his descendants, with their country:--Anamim.
of foreign origin; Anammelek, an Assyrian deity:--Anammelech.

a primitive root; to cover; used only as a denominative from 6051, to cloud over; figuratively, to act covertly, i.e. practise magic:--X bring, enchanter, Meonemin, observe(-r of) times, soothsayer, sorcerer.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6051:--cloud.
from 6049; a cloud (as covering the sky), i.e. the nimbus or thunder-cloud:--cloud(-y).
the same as 6051; cloud; Anan, an Israelite:--Anan.
feminine of 6051; cloudiness:--cloud.
from 6051; cloudy; Anani, an Israelite:--Anani.
from 6049 and 3050; Jah has covered; Ananjah, the name of an Israelite and of a place in Palestine:--Ananiah.
(Aramaic) or deneph (Aramaic) {eh'-nef}; corresponding to 6057:--bough, branch.
from an unused root meaning to cover; a twig (as covering the limbs):--bough, branch.
from the same as 6057; branching:--full of branches.

a primitive root; properly, to choke; used only as denominative from 6060, to collar, i.e. adorn with a necklace; figuratively, to fit out with supplies:--compass about as a chain, furnish, liberally.
from 6059; a necklace (as if strangling):--chain.
the same as 6060; Anak, a Canaanite:--Anak.
patronymically from 6061; an Anakite or descendant of Anak:--Anakim.
probably for 5288; Aner, a Amorite, also a place in Palestine:--Aner.
a primitive root; properly, to urge; by implication, to inflict a penalty, specifically, to fine:--amerce, condemn, punish, X surely.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6066; a mulct:--confiscation.
from 6064; a fine:--punishment, tribute.
from 6030; answer; Anath, an Israelite:--Anath.

or rAnnthowthiy {an-ne-tho-thee'}; patrial from 6068; a Antothite or inhabitant of Anathoth:--of Anathoth, Anethothite, Anetothite, Antothite.
from the same as 6068 and 3050; answers of Jah; Anthothijah, an Israelite:--Antothijah.
from 6072; must or fresh grape-juice (as just trodden out):--juice, new (sweet) wine.
a primitive root; to squeeze out juice; figuratively, to trample:--tread down.
from an unused root meaning to cover; a bough (as covering the tree):--branch.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6073; a twig; bough, i.e. (collectively) foliage:--leaves.
a primitive root; to swell; figuratively, be elated:--be lifted up, presume.
from 6075; a tumor; also a mound, i.e. fortress:--emerod, fort, strong hold, tower.
the same as 6076; Ophel, a ridge in Jerusalem:--Ophel.
from an unused noun (denoting a place in Palestine; from an unused root of uncertain meaning); an Ophnite (collectively) or inhabitants of Ophen:--Ophni.
from 5774; an eyelash (as fluttering); figuratively, morning ray:--dawning, eye-lid.
: a primitive root: meaning either to be gray or perhaps rather to pulverize; used only as denominative from 6083, to be dust:--cast (dust).
probably a variation of 6082; gazelle; Epher, the name of an Arabian and of two Israelites:--Epher.
from 6080; a fawn (from the dusty color):--young roe (hart).
from 6080; dust (as powdered or gray); hence, clay, earth, mud:--ashes, dust, earth, ground, morter, powder, rubbish.
feminine of 6082; female fawn; Ophrah, the name of an Israelite and of two places in Palestine:--Ophrah.
from the same as 6081; fawn-like; Ephron, the name of a Canaanite and of two places in Palestine:--Ephron, Ephrain (from the margin).
from 6095; a tree (from its firmness); hence, wood (plural sticks):--+ carpenter, gallows, helve, + pine, plank, staff, stalk, stick, stock, timber, tree, wood.
a primitive root; properly, to carve, i.e. fabricate or fashion; hence (in a bad sense) to worry, pain or anger:-- displease, grieve, hurt, make, be sorry, vex, worship, wrest.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6087; to afflict:--lamentable.
from 6087; an earthen vessel; usually (painful) toil; also a pang (whether of body or mind): grievous, idol, labor, sorrow.
a variation of 6089; an idol (as fashioned); also pain (bodily or mental):--idol, sorrow, X wicked.
from 6087; an (idolatrous) image:--idol, image.
from 6087; a (hired) workman:--labour.
from 6087; worrisomeness, i.e. labor or pain:--sorrow, toil.
from 6087; a idol; also, a pain or wound:--sorrow, wound.
a primitive root; properly, to fasten (or make firm), i.e. to close (the eyes):--shut.
from 6095; the spine (as giving firmness to the body):--backbone.
feminine of 6086; timber:--trees.
from 3289; advice; by implication, plan; also prudence:--advice, advisement, counsel(l-(or)), purpose.
or matsum {aw-tsoom'}; passive participle of 6105; powerful (specifically, a paw); by implication, numerous:--+ feeble, great, mighty, must, strong.
(shorter) {Etsyon Geber, from 6096 and 1397; backbone-like of a man; Etsjon-Geber, a place on the Red Sea:--Ezion-geber.
a primitive root; to lean idly, i.e. to be indolent or slack:--be slothful.
from 6101; indolent:--slothful, sluggard.
feminine of 6102; (as abstractly) indolence:--slothfulness.
rom 6101; indolence:--idleness.

a primitive root; to bind fast, i.e. close (the eyes); intransitively, to be (causatively, make) powerful or numerous; denominatively (from 6106) to crunch the bones:--break the bones, close, be great, be increased, be (wax) mighty(-ier), be more, shut, be(-come, make) strong(-er).
from 6105; a bone (as strong); by extension, the body; figuratively, the substance, i.e. (as pron.) selfsame:--body, bone, X life, (self-)same, strength, X very.
the same as 6106; bone; Etsem, a place in Palestine:--Azem, Ezem.
from 6105; power; hence, body:--might, strong, substance.
feminine of 6108; powerfulness; by extension, numerousness:--abundance, strength.
feminine of 6099; a bulwark, i.e. (figuratively) argument:--strong.
or iAtsmon {ats-mone'}; from 6107; bone-like; Atsmon, a place near Palestine:--Azmon.
from an unused root meaning to be sharp or strong; a spear:--Eznite (from the margin).

a primitive root; to inclose; by analogy, to hold back; also to maintain, rule, assemble:--X be able, close up, detain, fast, keep (self close, still), prevail, recover, refrain, X reign, restrain, retain, shut (up), slack, stay, stop, withhold (self).
from 6113; restraint:--+ magistrate.
from 6113; closure; also constraint:--X barren, oppression, X prison.
or matsereth {ats-eh'-reth}; from 6113; an assembly, especially on a festival or holiday:--(solemn) assembly (meeting).

a primitive root; properly, to swell out or up; used only as denominative from 6119, to seize by the heel; figuratively, to circumvent (as if tripping up the heels); also to restrain (as if holding by the heel):--take by the heel, stay, supplant, X utterly.

from 6117 in the sense of 6119; a heel, i.e. (figuratively) the last of anything (used adverbially, for ever); also result, i.e. compensation; and so (adverb with preposition or relatively) on account of:--X because, by, end, for, if, reward.

or (feminine) hiqqbah {ik-keb-aw'}; from 6117; a heel (as protuberant); hence, a track; figuratively, the rear (of an army):--heel, (horse-)hoof, last, lier in wait (by mistake for 6120), (foot- )step.
from 6117 in its denominative sense; a lier in wait:--heel (by mistake for 6119).
from 6117; in the original sense, a knoll (as swelling up); in the denominative sense (transitive) fraudulent or (intransitive) tracked:--crooked, deceitful, polluted.
feminine of an unused form from 6117 meaning a trick; trickery:--subtilty.
a primitive root; to tie with thongs:--bind.
from 6123; striped (with bands):--ring straked.
from 5781; constraint:--oppression.
from 6117; insidious; Akkub, the name of five Israelites:--Akkub.
a primitive root; to wrest:--wrong.
from 6127; winding:--by(-way), crooked way.
from 6127; tortuous:--crooked.
from an unused root meaning to twist; tortuous; Akan, an Idummaean:--Akan. Compare 3292.
a primitive root; to pluck up (especially by the roots); specifically, to hamstring; figuratively, to exterminate:--dig down, hough, pluck up, root up.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6131:--pluck up by the roots.
from 6131. figuratively, a transplanted person, i.e. naturalized citizen:--stock.
the same as 6133; Eker, an Israelite:--Eker.
from 6131; sterile (as if extirpated in the generative organs):--(X male or female) barren (woman).
(Aramaic) from 6132; a stock:--stump.
of uncertain derivation; a scorpion; figuratively, a scourge or knotted whip:--scorpion.
from 6131; eradication; Ekron, a place in Palestine:--Ekron.
or mEqroniy {ek-ro-nee'; patrial from 6138; an Ekronite or inhabitant of Ekron:--Ekronite.
a primitive root; to knot or distort; figuratively, to pervert (act or declare perverse):--make crooked, (prove, that is) perverse(-rt).
from 6140; distorted; hence, false:--crooked, froward, perverse.
the same as 6141; perverse; Ikkesh, an Israelite:--Ikkesh.
from 6141; perversity:--X froward.
the same as 5892; a city; Ar, a place in Moab:--Ar.
from 5782; a foe (as watchful for mischief):--enemy.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6145:--enemy.
from 5782; watchful; Er, the name of two Israelites:--Er.

a primitive root; to braid, i.e. intermix; technically, to traffic (as if by barter); also or give to be security (as a kind of exchange):--engage, (inter-)meddle (with), mingle (self), mortgage, occupy, give pledges, be(-come, put in) surety, undertake.
a primitive root (identical with 6148 through the idea of close association); to be agreeable:--be pleasant(-ing), take pleasure in, be sweet.
a primitive root (identical with 6148 through the idea of covering with a texture); to grow dusky at sundown:--be darkened, (toward) evening.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6148; to commingle:--mingle (self), mix.
or mArab {ar-ab'}; from 6150 in the figurative sense of sterility; Arab (i.e. Arabia), a country East of Palestine:--Arabia.
from 6150; dusk:--+ day, even(-ing, tide), night.

or mereb (1 Kings 10:15), (with the article prefix), {eh'-reb}; from 6148; the web (or transverse threads of cloth); also a mixture, (or mongrel race):--Arabia, mingled people, mixed (multitude), woof.
from 6148; a willow (from the use of osiers as wattles):--willow.
from 6149; pleasant:--sweet.
from 6148; a mosquito (from its swarming):--divers sorts of flies, swarm.
or mowreb {o-rabe'}; from 6150; a raven (from its dusky hue):--raven.
or mOwreb {o-rabe'}; the same as 6158; Oreb, the name of a Midianite and of the cliff near the Jordan:--Oreb.

from 6150 (in the sense of sterility); a desert; especially (with the article prefix) the (generally) sterile valley of the Jordan and its continuation to the Red Sea:--Arabah, champaign, desert, evening, heaven, plain, wilderness. See also 1026.
feminine passive participle of 6048 in the sense of a bargain or exchange; something given as security, i.e. (literally) a token (of safety) or (metaphorically) a bondsman:--pledge, surety.
from 6148 (in the sense of exchange); a pawn (given as security):--pledge.
or mArbiy {ar-bee'}; patrial from 6152; an Arabian or inhabitant of Arab (i.e. Arabia):--Arabian.
patrial from 1026; an Arbathite or inhabitant of (Beth-)Arabah:--Arbahite.
a primitive root; to long for:--cry, pant.
from an unused root meaning to sequester itself; fugitive; Arad, the name of a place near Palestine, also of a Canaanite and an Israelite:--Arad.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6171; an onager:--wild ass.
a primitive root; to be (causatively, make) bare; hence, to empty, pour out, demolish:--leave destitute, discover, empty, make naked, pour (out), rase, spread self, uncover.
feminine from 6168; a naked (i.e. level) plot:--paper reed.
or iarugah {ar-oo-gaw'}; feminine passive participle of 6165; something piled up (as if (figuratively) raised by mental aspiration), i.e. a paterre:--bed, furrow.
from the same as 6166; an onager (from his lonesome habits):--wild ass.
from 6168; nudity, literally (especially the pudenda) or figuratively (disgrace, blemish):--nakedness, shame, unclean(-ness).
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6172; nakedness, i.e. (figuratively) impoverishment:--dishonor.
or marom {aw-rome'}; from 6191 (in its original sense); nude, either partially or totally:--naked.
passive participle of 6191; cunning (usually in a bad sense):--crafty, prudent, subtil.
or sarear {ar-awr'}; from 6209 reduplicated; a juniper (from its nudity of situation):--health.
or `Aro`er {ar-o-ayr'}; or `Ar`owr {ar-ore'}; the same as 6176; nudity of situation; Aroer, the name of three places in or near Palestine:--Aroer.
passive participle of 6206; feared, i.e. (concretely) a horrible place or chasm:--cliffs.
from 5782; watchful; Eri, an Israelite:--Eri.
patronymically of 6179; a Erite (collectively) or descendants of Eri:--Erites.
for 6172; nudity:--bare, naked, X quite.
from an unused root meaning to comminute; meal:--dough.
from 6201; the sky (as dropping at the horizon):--heaven.
from 6206; fearful, i.e. powerful or tyrannical:--mighty, oppressor, in great power, strong, terrible, violent.
from 6209; bare, i.e. destitute (of children):--childless.

a primitive root; to set in a row, i.e. arrange, put in order (in a very wide variety of applications):--put (set) (the battle, self) in array, compare, direct, equal, esteem, estimate, expert (in war), furnish, handle, join (battle), ordain, (lay, put, reckon up, set) (in) order, prepare, tax, value.
from 6186; a pile, equipment, estimate:--equal, estimation, (things that are set in) order, price, proportion, X set at, suit, taxation, X valuest.

a primitive root; properly, to strip; but used as denominative from 6189; to expose or remove the prepuce, whether literal (to go naked) or figurative (to refrain from using):--count uncircumcised, foreskin to be uncovered.
rom 6188; properly, exposed, i.e. projecting loose (as to the prepuce); used only technically, uncircumcised (i.e. still having the prepuce uncurtailed):--uncircumcised (person).
feminine of 6189; the prepuce:--foreskin, + uncircumcised.

a primitive root; properly, to be (or make) bare; but used only in the derivative sense (through the idea perhaps of smoothness) to be cunning (usually in a bad sense):--X very, beware, take crafty (counsel), be prudent, deal subtilly.
a primitive root; to pile up:--gather together.
from 6191; a stratagem:--craftiness.
(Jer. 50:26 or (feminine) aremah {ar-ay-maw'}; from 6192; a heap; specifically, a sheaf:--heap (of corn), sheaf.
feminine of 6193; trickery; or (in a good sense) discretion:--guile, prudence, subtilty, wilily, wisdom.
probably from 6191; the plane tree (from its smooth and shed bark):--chestnut tree.
probably from 5782; watchful; Eran, an Israelite:--Eran.
patronymically from 6197; an Eranite or descendant (collectively) of Eran:--Eranites.
from 6209; naked, i.e. (figuratively) poor:--destitute. See also 6176.
patronymically from 6177; an Aroerite or inhabitant of Aroer:--Aroerite.
a primitive root; to droop; hence, to drip:--drop (down).

a primitive root (identical with 6201 through the idea of sloping); properly, to bend downward; but used only as a denominative from 6203, to break the neck; hence (figuratively) to destroy:--that is beheaded, break down, break (cut off, strike off) neck.
from 6202; the nape or back of the neck (as declining); hence, the back generally (whether literal or figurative):-- back ((stiff-)neck((-ed).
feminine of 6203; mane; Orpah, a Moabites:--Orpah.
probably from 6201; gloom (as of a lowering sky):--(gross, thick) dark (cloud, -ness).
a primitive root; to awe or (intransitive) to dread; hence, to harass:--be affrighted (afraid, dread, feared, terrified), break, dread, fear, oppress, prevail, shake terribly.
a primitive root; to gnaw, i.e. (figuratively) eat (by hyberbole); also (participle) a pain:--fleeing, sinew.
patrial from an unused name meaning a tush; an Arkite or inhabitant of Erek:--Arkite.
a primitive root; to bare; figuratively, to demolish:--make bare, break, raise up (perhaps by clerical error for raze), X utterly.
from an unused root meaning perhaps to arch; a couch (properly, with a canopy):--bed(-stead), couch.
from 6244; a moth:--moth. See also 5906.
from an unused root meaning to glisten (or be green); grass (or any tender shoot):--grass, herb.

a primitive root; to do or make, in the broadest sense and widest application (as follows):--accomplish, advance, appoint, apt, be at, become, bear, bestow, bring forth, bruise, be busy, X certainly, have the charge of, commit, deal (with), deck, + displease, do, (ready) dress(-ed), (put in) execute(-ion), exercise, fashion, + feast, (fight-)ing man, + finish, fit, fly, follow, fulfill, furnish, gather, get, go about, govern, grant, great, + hinder, hold ((a feast)), X indeed, + be industrious, + journey, keep, labour, maintain, make, be meet, observe, be occupied, offer, + officer, pare, bring (come) to pass, perform, pracise, prepare, procure, provide, put, requite, X sacrifice, serve, set, shew, X sin, spend, X surely, take, X thoroughly, trim, X very, + vex, be (warr-)ior, work(-man), yield, use.
from 6213 and 410; God has made; Asahel, the name of four Israelites:--Asahel.
apparently a form of the passive participle of 6213 in the original sense of handling; rough (i.e. sensibly felt); Esav, a son of Isaac, including his posterity:--Esau.
from 6231; oppressive (as noun, a tyrant):--oppressor.
or mashuq {aw-shook'}; passive participle of 6231; used in plural masculine as abstractly, tyranny:--oppressed(-ion). (Doubtful.)
or masor {aw-sore'}; from 6235; ten; by abbrev. ten strings, and so a decachord:--(instrument of) ten (strings, -th).
from 6245; shining, i.e. polished:--bright.
for 6219; bright; Ashvath, an Israelite:--Ashvath.
from 6213 and 410; made of God; Asiel, an Israelite:--Asiel.
from 6213 and 3050; Jah has made; Asajah, the name of three or four Israelites:--Asaiah.
from 6238; rich, whether literal or figurative (noble):--rich (man).
from 6235; tenth; by abbreviation, tenth month or (feminine) part:--tenth (part).
a primitive root; to smoke, whether literal or figurative:--be angry (be on a) smoke.
from 6225; smoky:--smoking.
from 6225; smoke, literally or figuratively (vapor, dust, anger):--smoke(-ing).
the same as 6227; Ashan, a place in Palestine:--Ashan.
a primitive root (identical with 6231); to press upon, i.e. quarrel; --strive with.
from 6229; strife:--Esek.
a primitive root (compare 6229); to press upon, i.e. oppress, defraud, violate, overflow:--get deceitfully, deceive, defraud, drink up, (use) oppress((-ion)), -or), do violence (wrong).
from 6231; oppression; Eshek, an Israelite:--Eshek.
from 6231; injury, fraud, (subjectively) distress, (concretely) unjust gain:--cruelly, extortion, oppression, thing (deceitfully gotten).
feminine of 6233; anguish:--oppressed.
masculine of term aasarah {as-aw-raw'}; from 6237; ten (as an accumulation to the extent of the digits):--ten, (fif-, seven-)teen.
(Aramaic) masculine aasrah (Aramaic). {as-raw'}; corresponding to 6235; ten:--ten, + twelve.

a primitive root (ident. with 6238); to accumulate; but used only as denominative from 6235; to tithe, i.e. to take or give a tenth:--X surely, give (take) the tenth, (have, take) tithe(-ing, -s), X truly.
a primitive root; properly, to accumulate; chiefly (specifically) to grow (causatively, make) rich:--be(-come, en-, make, make self, wax) rich, make (1 Kings 22:48 marg). See 6240.
from 6238; wealth:--X far (richer), riches.
for 6235; ten (only in combination), i.e. -teen; also (ordinal) -teenth:--(eigh-, fif-, four-, nine-, seven-, six-, thir-)teen(-th), + eleven(-th), + sixscore thousand, + twelve(-th).
or oissaron {is-saw-rone'}; from 6235; (fractional) a tenth part:--tenth deal.
from 6235; twenty; also (ordinal) twentieth:--(six-)score, twenty(-ieth).
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6242:--twenty.
a primitive root; probably to shrink, i.e. fail:--be consumed.
a primitive root; probably to be sleek, i.e. glossy; hence (through the idea of polishing) to excogitate (as if forming in the mind):--shine, think.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6245; to purpose:--think.
from 6245; a fabric:--bright.
from 6245; cogitation:--thought.
apparently masculine plural construction of 6247 in the sense of an afterthought (used only in connection with 6240 in lieu of 259) eleven or (ordinal) eleventh:--+ eleven(-th).
from 6245; thinking:--thought.
probably from 6238; increase:--flock.
or bAshtaroth {ash-taw-roth'}; plural of 6251; Ashtaroth, the name of a Sidonian deity, and of a place East of the Jordan:--Asharoth, Astaroth. See also 1045, 6253, 6255.
probably for 6251; Ashtoreth, the Phoenician goddess of love (and increase):--Ashtoreth.
patrial from 6252; an Ashterathite or inhabitant of Ashtaroth:--Ashterathite.
from 6252 and the dual of 7161; Ashtaroth of (the) double horns (a symbol of the deity); Ashteroth-Karnaim, a place East of the Jordan:--Ashtoreth Karnaim.

from 5703; time, especially (adverb with preposition) now, when, etc.:--+ after, (al-)ways, X certain, + continually, + evening, long, (due) season, so (long) as, (even-, evening-, noon-)tide, ((meal-)), what) time, when.
a primitive root; to prepare:--make fit, be ready to become.
from 6256; at this time, whether adverb, conjunction or expletive:--henceforth, now, straightway, this time, whereas.
passive participle of 6257; prepared:--ready.
or sattud {at-tood'}; from 6257; prepared, i.e. full grown; spoken only (in plural) of he-goats, or (figuratively) leaders of the people:--chief one, (he) goat, ram.
from 6256; timely:--fit.
for 6261; Attai, the name of three Israelites:--Attai.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6264; prepared:--ready.
from 6257; prepared; by implication, skilful; feminine plural the future; also treasure:--things that shall come, ready, treasures.
from 5790 and 3050; Jah has helped; Athajah, an Israelite:--Athaiah.
from 6275; properly, antique, i.e. venerable or splendid:--durable.
from 6275; removed, i.e. weaned; also antique:--ancient, drawn.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6267; venerable:--ancient.
from an unused root meaning to sojourn; lodging; Athak, a place in Palestine:--Athach.
from an unused root meaning to compress; constringent; Athlai, an Israelite:--Athlai.
or mAthalyahuw {ath-al-yaw'-hoo}; from the same as 6270 and 3050; Jah has constrained; Athaljah, the name of an Israelitess and two Israelites:--Athaliah.
a primitive root; probably to glow, i.e. (figuratively) be desolated:--be darkened.
from an unused root meaning to force; forcible; Othni, an Israelite:--Othni.
from the same as 6273 and 410; force of God; Othniel, an Israelite:--Othniel.
a primitive root; to remove (intransitive or transitive) figuratively, to grow old; specifically, to transcribe:--copy out, leave off, become (wax) old, remove.
from 6275; antique, i.e. valued:--durable.
from 6275 in the sense of license; impudent:--arrogancy, grievous (hard) things, stiff.
from 6256 and 7011; time of a judge; Eth-Katsin, a place in Palestine:--Ittah-kazin (by including directive enclitic).
a primitive root (rather denominative from 6281); to burn incense in worship, i.e. intercede (reciprocally, listen to prayer):--intreat, (make) pray(-er).
a primitive root; to be (causatively, make) abundant:--deceitful, multiply.
from 6280; abundance; Ether, a place in Palestine:--Ether.
from 6280; incense (as increasing to a volume of smoke); hence (from 6279) a worshipper:--suppliant, thick.
from 6280; copiousness:--abundance.
a primitive root; to puff, i.e. blow away:--scatter into corners.
feminine of 6311; properly, mouth in a figurative sense, i.e. direction, region, extremity:--corner, end, quarter, side.

a primitive root; to gleam, i.e. (causatively) embellish; figuratively, to boast; also to explain (i.e. make clear) oneself; denominative from 6288, to shake a tree:--beautify, boast self, go over the boughs, glorify (self), glory, vaunt self.
from 6286; an embellishment, i.e. fancy head-dress:--beauty, bonnet, goodly, ornament, tire.
or pora'h {po-raw'}; or pu'rah {poo-raw'}; from 6286; properly, ornamentation, i.e. (plural) foliage (including the limbs) as bright green:--bough, branch, sprig.
from 6286; properly, illuminated, i.e. a glow; as noun, a flush (of anxiety):--blackness.
from 6286; ornamental; Paran, a desert of Arabia:--Paran.
from an unused root meaning to be torpid, i.e. crude; an unripe fig:--green fig.
or piggul {pig-gool'}; from an unused root meaning to stink; properly, fetid, i.e. (figuratively) unclean (ceremonially):--abominable(-tion, thing).

a primitive root; to impinge, by accident or violence, or (figuratively) by importunity:--come (betwixt), cause to entreat, fall (upon), make intercession, intercessor, intreat, lay, light (upon), meet (together), pray, reach, run.
from 6293; impact (casual):--chance, occurent.
from 6294 and 410; accident of God; Pagiel, an Israelite:--Pagiel.
a primitive root; to relax, i.e. become exhausted:--be faint.
from 6296; a carcase (as limp), whether of man or beast; figuratively, an idolatrous image:--carcase, corpse, dead body.
a primitive root; to come in contact with, whether by accident or violence; figuratively, to concur:--meet (with, together).
a primitive root; to sever, i.e. ransom; gener. to release, preserve:--X at all, deliver, X by any means, ransom, (that are to be, let be) redeem(-ed), rescue, X surely.
from 6299 and 410; God has ransomed; Pedahel, an Israelite:--Pedahel.
from 6299 and 6697; a rock (i.e. God) has ransomed; Pedahtsur, an Israelite:--Pedahzur.
passive participle of 6299. ransomed (and so occurring under 6299); as abstractly (in plural masculine) a ransom:--(that are) to be (that were) redeemed.
from 6299; ransom; Padon, one of the Nethinim. -- Padon.
or pduth {ped-ooth'}; from 6929; distinction; also deliverance:--division, redeem, redemption.
or Pdayahuw {ped-aw-yaw'-hoo}; from 6299 and 3050; Jah has ransomed; Pedajah, the name of six Israelites:--Pedaiah.
or pidyom {pid-yome'}; also pidyown {pid-yone'}; or pidyon {pid-yone'}; from 6299; a ransom; --ransom, that were redeemed, redemption.
from an unused root meaning to extend; a plateau; or Paddan pAram {pad-dan' ar-awm'}; from the same and 758; the table-land of Aram; Paddan or Paddan-Aram, a region of Syria:--Padan, Padan-aram.
a primitive root; to retrieve:--deliver.
from an unused root meaning to be greasy; suet:--fat.

from 6284; the mouth (as the means of blowing), whether literal or figurative (particularly speech); specifically edge, portion or side; adverbially (with preposition) according to:--accord(-ing as, -ing to), after, appointment, assent, collar, command(-ment), X eat, edge, end, entry, + file, hole, X in, mind, mouth, part, portion, X (should) say(-ing), sentence, skirt, sound, speech, X spoken, talk, tenor, X to, + two-edged, wish, word.

or po6 (Job 38:11) {po}; or pow {po}; probably from a primitive inseparable particle "p" (of demonstrative force) and 1931; this place (French ici), i.e. here or hence:--here, hither, the one (other, this, that) side.
or Puvvah {poov-vaw'}; from 6284; a blast; Puah or Puvvah, the name of two Israelites:--Phuvah, Pua, Puah.
a primitive root; to be sluggish:--cease, be feeble, faint, be slacked.
from 6313; intermission:--rest.
a primitive root; to puff, i.e. blow with the breath or air; hence, to fan (as a breeze), to utter, to kindle (a fire), to scoff:--blow (upon), break, puff, bring into a snare, speak, utter.
of foreign origin; Put, a son of Ham, also the name of his descendants or their region, and of a Persian tribe:--Phut, Put.
from an unused root (probably meaning to disparage) and 410; contempt of God; Putiel, an Israelite:--Putiel.
of Egyptian derivation: Potiphar, an Egyptian:--Potiphar.
of Egyptian derivation; Poti-Phera, an Egyptian:--Poti-pherah.
from an unused root meaning to paint; dye (specifically, stibium for the eyes):--fair colours, glistering, paint(-ed) (-ing).
from an unused root meaning to be thick; a bean (as plump):--beans.
of foreign origin; Pul, the name of an Assyrian king and of an Ethiopian tribe:--Pul.
a primitive root meaning to turn, i.e. be perplexed:--be distracted.
patronymically from an unused name meaning a turn; a Punite (collectively) or descendants of an unknown Pun:--Punites.
from 6323; perplexity; Punon, a place in the Desert:--Punon.
from an unused root meaning to glitter; brilliancy; Puah, an Israelitess:--Puah.

a primitive root; to dash in pieces, literally or figuratively (especially to disperse):--break (dash, shake) in (to) pieces, cast (abroad), disperse (selves), drive, retire, scatter (abroad), spread abroad.
a primitive root; to waver:--stumble, move.

a primitive root (identical with 6328 through the idea of dropping out; compare 5312); to issue, i.e. furnish; causatively, to secure; figuratively, to succeed:--afford, draw out, further, get, obtain.
from 6328; a stumbling-block:--grief.
a primitive root; to crush:--break, bring to nought, X utterly take.
also (plural) Puwriym {poo-reem'}; or Puriym {poo-reem'}; from 6331; a lot (as by means of a broken piece):--Pur, Purim.
from 6331; a wine-press (as crushing the grapes):--winepress.
of Persian origin; Poratha, a son of Haman:--Poratha.
a primitive root; to spread; figuratively, act proudly:--grow up, be grown fat, spread selves, be scattered.
patronymically from an unused name meaning a hinge; a Puthite (collectively) or descendants of an unknown Puth:--Puhites (as if from 6312).
from 6338; pure (gold); hence, gold itself (as refined):--fine (pure) gold.
a primitive root; to refine (gold):--best (gold).
a primitive root (identical with 6338); to solidify (as if by refining); also to spring (as if separating the limbs):--leap, be made strong.
a primitive root; to scatter, whether in enmity or bounty:--disperse, scatter (abroad).
from 6351; a (metallic) sheet (as pounded thin); also a spring net (as spread out like a lamina):--gin, (thin) plate, snare.
a primitive root; to be startled (by a sudden alarm); hence, to fear in general:--be afraid, stand in awe, (be in) fear, make to shake.
from 6342; a (sudden) alarm (properly, the object feared, by implication, the feeling):--dread(-ful), fear, (thing) great (fear, -ly feared), terror.
the same as 6343; a testicle (as a cause of shame akin to fear):--stone.
feminine of 6343; alarm (i.e. awe):--fear.
of foreign origin; a prefect (of a city or small district):--captain, deputy, governor.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6346:--captain, governor.
a primitive root; to bubble up or froth (as boiling water), i.e. (figuratively) to be unimportant:--light.
from 6348; ebullition, i.e. froth (figuratively, lust):--unstable.
from 6348; frivolity:--lightness.
a primitive root; to batter out; but used only as denominative from 6341, to spread a net:--be snared.
perhaps from an unused root probably meaning to be black; a coal, whether charred or live:--coals.
(Aramaic) from an unused root probably meaning to fashion; a potter:--potter.
probably from an unused root apparently meaning to dig; a pit, especially for catching animals:--hole, pit, snare.
from 6354 and 4124; pit of Moab; Pachath-Moab, an Israelite:--Pahath-moab.
from the same as 6354; a hole (by mildew in a garment):--fret inward.
of foreign derivation; a gem, probably the topaz:--topaz.
passive participle of 6362; opened, i.e. (as noun) a bud:--open.
from 6362; open, i.e. unoccupied:--free.
intensively from an unused root meaning to pound; a hammer:--hammer.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to that of 6360; a gown (as if hammered out wide):--hose.
a primitive root; to cleave or burst through, i.e. (causatively) to emit, whether literal or figurative (gape):--dismiss, free, let (shoot) out, slip away.
or pitrah {pit-raw'}; from 6362; a fissure, i.e. (concretely) firstling (as opening the matrix):--firstling, openeth, such as open.
of Egyptian origin; Pi-Beseth, a place in Egypt:--Pi-beseth.
from an unused root probably meaning to pierce; (figuratively) misfortune:--destruction, ruin.
or piyah {pee-yaw'}; feminine of 6310; an edge:-- (two-)edge(-d).

from 6310 and the feminine plural of a noun (from the same root as 2356), with the article interpolated; mouth of the gorges; Pi-ha-Chiroth, a place in Egypt: --Pi-hahiroth. (In Numbers 14:19 without Pi-.)
from 6315; a powder (as easily puffed away), i.e. ashes or dust:--ashes.
apparently from 6310 and 3605; mouth of all; Picol, a Philistine:--Phichol.
or pilegesh {pee-leh'-ghesh}; of uncertain derivation; a concubine; also (masculine) a paramour:--concubine, paramour.
probably from an unused root meaning to be plump; obesity:--collops.
apparently from 6310 and a variation of 5175; mouth of a serpent; Pinechas, the name of three Israelites:--Phinehas.
probably the same as 6325; Pinon, an Idumaean:--Pinon.
for 6366; an edge or tooth:--tooth, X two-edged.
from 6329; a tottering:--smite together.
from 6335; dispersive; Pishon, a river of Eden:--Pison.
probably from the same as 6596; expansive; Pithon, an Israelite:--Pithon.
from 6379; a flask (from which a liquid may flow):--box, vial.
a primitive root; to pour:--run out.

from the active participle (of the same form as the first word) feminine of an unused root (meaning to entrap) and plural of 6643; trap of gazelles; Pokereth-Tsebajim, one of the "servants of Solomon":--Pochereth of Zebaim.

a primitive root; properly, perhaps to separate, i.e. distinguish (literally or figuratively); by implication, to be (causatively, make) great, difficult, wonderful:--accomplish, (arise...too, be too) hard, hidden, things too high, (be, do, do a, shew) marvelous(-ly, -els, things, work), miracles, perform, separate, make singular, (be, great, make) wonderful(-ers, -ly, things, works), wondrous (things, works, -ly).
from 6381; a miracle:--marvellous thing, wonder(-ful, -fully).
or paliy1 {paw-lee'}; from 6381; remarkable:--secret, wonderful.
patronymically from 6396; a Palluite (collectively) or descendants of Pallu:--Palluites.
a primitive root; to split (literally or figuratively):--divide.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6385:--divided.
(Aramaic) from 6386; a half:--dividing.
from 6385; a rill (i.e. small channel of water, as in irrigation):--river, stream.
the same as 6388; earthquake; Peleg, a son of Shem:--Peleg.
from 6385; a runlet, i.e. gully:--division, river.
from 6385; a section:--division.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6391:--division.
from an unused root meaning to divide; a cleaver, i.e. iron armature (of a chariot):--torch.
of uncertain derivation; Pildash, a relative of Abraham:--Pildash.
a primitive root; to distinguish (literally or figuratively):--put a difference, show marvellous, separate, set apart, sever, make wonderfully.
from 6395; distinguished; Pallu, an Israelite:--Pallu, Phallu.
patronymically from an unused name (from 6395) meaning separate; a Pelonite or inhabitant of an unknown Palon:-- Pelonite.
a primitive root; to slice, i.e. break open or pierce:--bring forth, cleave, cut, shred, strike through.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6398; to serve or worship:--minister, serve.
from 6398; a slice:--piece.
from 6400; slicing; Pilcha, an Israelite:--Pilcha.
(Aramaic) from 6399; worship:--service.
a primitive root; to slip out, i.e. escape; causatively, to deliver:--calve, carry away safe, deliver, (cause to) escape.
from 6403; escape; Pelet, the name of two Israelites:--Pelet. See also 1046.
from 6403; escape:--deliverance, escape.
from 6403; delivered; Palti, the name of two Israelites:--Palti, Phalti.
patronymically from 6406; a Paltite or descendant of Palti:--Paltite.
for 6407; Piltai, an Israelite:--Piltai.
from the same as 6404 and 410; deliverance of God; Paltiel, the name of two Israelites:--Paltiel, Phaltiel.
or Platyahuw {pel-at-yaw'-hoo}; from 6403 and 3050; Jah has delivered; Pelatjah, the name of four Israelites:--Pelatiah.
or Pla.yah {pel-aw-yaw'}; from 6381 and 3050; Jah has distinguished; Pelajah, the name of three Israelites:--Pelaiah.
or paleyt {paw-late'}; or palet {paw-late'}; from 6403; a refugee:--(that have) escape(-d, -th), fugitive.
or pletah {pel-ay-taw'}; feminine of 6412; deliverance; concretely, an escaped portion:--deliverance, (that is) escape(-d), remnant.
from 6419; a magistrate:--judge.
feminine of 6414; justice:--judgment.
from 6414; judicial:--judge.
feminine of 6416; judicature:--judgment.
from an unused root meaning to be round; a circuit (i.e. district); also a spindle (as whirled); hence, a crutch:--(di-)staff, participle
a primitive root; to judge (officially or mentally); by extension, to intercede, pray:--intreat, judge(-ment), (make) pray(-er, -ing), make supplication.
from 6419; judge; Palal, an Israelite:--Palal.
from 6419 and 3050; Jah has judged; Pelaljah, an Israelite:--Pelaliah.
probably for 6423; a certain one, i.e. so-and-so:--certain.
from 6395; such a one, i.e. a specified peccrson:--such.
a primitive root; properly, to roll flat, i.e. prepare (a road); also to revolve, i.e. weigh (mentally):--make, ponder, weigh.
from 6424; a balance:--scales, weight.
a primitive root; properly, perhaps to rend, i.e. (by implication) to quiver:--tremble.
from 6426; affright:--fearfulness, horror, trembling.
a primitive root; to roll (in dust):--roll (wallow) self.
from 6428; rolling, i.e. migratory; Pelesheth, a region of Syria:--Palestina, Palestine, Philistia, Philistines.
patrial from 6429; a Pelishtite or inhabitant of Pelesheth:--Philistine.
from an unused root meaning to flee; swiftness; Peleth, the name of two Israelites:--Peleth.
from the same form as 6431; a courier (collectively) or official messenger:--Pelethites.
(Aramaic) probably for 6310; the mouth (literally or figuratively):--mouth.
from an unused root meaning to turn; an angle (of a street or wall):--corner.
from 6437; properly, removal; used only (in the construction) adverb as conjunction, lest:--(lest) (peradventure), that...not.
of uncertain derivation; probably pastry:--Pannag.

a primitive root; to turn; by implication, to face, i.e. appear, look, etc.:--appear, at (even-)tide, behold, cast out, come on, X corner, dawning, empty, go away, lie, look, mark, pass away, prepare, regard, (have) respect (to), (re-)turn (aside, away, back, face, self), X right (early).
feminine of 6434; an angle; by implication, a pinnacle; figuratively, a chieftain:--bulwark, chief, corner, stay, tower.
or (more properly,) Pniylel {pen-oo-ale'}; from 6437 and 410; face of God; Penuel or Peniel, a place East of Jordan; also (as Penuel) the name of two Israelites:--Peniel, Penuel.

plural (but always as singular) of an unused noun (paneh {paw-neh'}; from 6437); the face (as the part that turns); used in a great variety of applications (literally and figuratively); also (with prepositional prefix) as a preposition (before, etc.):--+ accept, a-(be- )fore(-time), against, anger, X as (long as), at, + battle, + because (of), + beseech, countenance, edge, + employ, endure, + enquire, face, favour, fear of, for, forefront(-part), form(-er time, -ward), from, front, heaviness, X him(-self), + honourable, + impudent, + in, it, look(-eth) (- s), X me, + meet, X more than, mouth, of, off, (of) old (time), X on, open, + out of, over against, the partial, person, + please, presence, propect, was purposed, by reason of, + regard, right forth, + serve, X shewbread, sight, state, straight, + street, X thee, X them(-selves), through (+ - out), till, time(-s) past, (un-)to(-ward), + upon, upside (+ down), with(- in, + -stand), X ye, X you.
from 6440 with directive enclitic; faceward, i.e. indoors:--(with-)in(-ner part, -ward).
from 6440; interior:--(with-)in(-ner, - ward).
or paniy {paw-nee'}; from the same as 6434; probably a pearl (as round):--ruby.
probably feminine from 6443 contr.; Peninnah, an Israelitess:--Peninnah.
a primitive root; to enervate:--bring up.

from 6461; properly, the palm (of the hand) or sole (of the foot) (compare 6447); by implication (plural) a long and sleeved tunic (perhaps simply a wide one; from the original sense of the root, i.e. of many breadths):--(divers) colours.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to 6461; the palm (of the hand, as being spread out):--participle
a primitive root; to cut up, i.e. (figuratively) contemplate:--consider.
from 6448; a cleft; Pisgah, a mt. East of Jordan:--Pisgah.
from 6446 and the plural of 1818; palm (i.e. dell) of bloodshed; Pas-Dammim, a place in Palestine:--Pas-dammim. Compare 658.
from 6461; expansion, i.e. abundance:--handful.
a primitive root; to hop, i.e. (figuratively) skip over (or spare); by implication, to hesitate; also (literally) to limp, to dance:--halt, become lame, leap, pass over.
from 6452; a pretermission, i.e. exemption; used only techically of the Jewish Passover (the festival or the victim):--passover (offering).
from 6452; limping; Paseach, the name of two Israelites:--Paseah, Phaseah.
from 6452; lame:--lame.
from 6458; an idol:--carved (graven) image, quarry.
from an unused root meaning to divide; divider; Pasak, an Israelite:--Pasach.
a primitive root; to carve, whether wood or stone:--grave, hew.
from 6458; an idol:--carved (graven) image.
(Aramaic) or pcanteriyn {pes-an-tay-reen'}; a transliteration of the Gr. psalterion; a lyre:--psaltery.
a primitive root; probably to disperse, i.e. (intransitive) disappear:--cease.
perhaps from 6461; dispersion; Pispah, an Israelite:--Pispah.
a primitive root; to scream:--cry.
or Pamiy {paw-ee'}; from 6463; screaming; Pau or Pai, a place in Edom:--Pai, Pau.
from 6473; a gap; Peor, a mountain East of Jordan; also (for 1187) a deity worshipped there:--Peor. See also 1047.
a primitive root; to do or make (systematically and habitually), especially to practise:--commit, (evil-) do(-er), make(-r), ordain, work(-er).
from 6466; an act or work (concretely):--act, deed, do, getting, maker, work.
feminine passive participle of 6466; (abstractly) work:--labour, reward, wages, work.
from 6468; laborious; Peullethai, an Israelite:--Peulthai.
a primitive root; to tap, i.e. beat regularly; hence (generally) to impel or agitate:--move, trouble.

or (feminine) pa;amah {pah-am-aw'}; from 6470; a stroke, literally or figuratively (in various applications, as follow):--anvil, corner, foot(-step), going, (hundred-)fold, X now, (this) + once, order, rank, step, + thrice, ((often-)), second, this, two) time(-s), twice, wheel.
from 6471; a bell (as struck):--bell.
a primitive root; to yawn, i.e. open wide (literally or figuratively):--gape, open (wide).
from 6473; yawning; Paarai, an Israelite:--Paarai.
a primitive root; to rend, i.e. open (especially the mouth):--deliver, gape, open, rid, utter.
a primitive root; to break out (in joyful sound):--break (forth, forth into joy), make a loud noise.
from 6484; bluntness:--+ file.
a primitive root; to peel:--pill.
from 6478; a peeling:--strake.
a primitive root; to rend (by earthquake):--break.
a primitive root; to split, i.e. wound:--wound.
from 6481; a wound:--wound(-ing).
from an unused root meaning to dissever; dispersive; Pitstsets, a priest:--Apses (including the article).
a primitive root; to peck at, i.e. (figuratively) stun or dull:--press, urge, stubbornness.

a primitive root; to visit (with friendly or hostile intent); by analogy, to oversee, muster, charge, care for, miss, deposit, etc.:--appoint, X at all, avenge, bestow, (appoint to have the, give a) charge, commit, count, deliver to keep, be empty, enjoin, go see, hurt, do judgment, lack, lay up, look, make, X by any means, miss, number, officer, (make) overseer, have (the) oversight, punish, reckon, (call to) remember(-brance), set (over), sum, X surely, visit, want.

feminine passive participle of 6485; visitation (in many senses, chiefly official):--account, (that have the) charge, custody, that which...laid up, numbers, office(-r), ordering, oversight, + prison, reckoning, visitation.
from 6485; a deposit:--that which was delivered (to keep), store.
from 6496; supervision:--ward.
from 6485; punishment; Pekod, a symbolic name for Bab.:--Pekod.
or piqqud {pik-kood'}; from 6485; properly, appointed, i.e. a mandate (of God; plural only, collectively, for the Law):--commandment, precept, statute.
a primitive root; to open (the senses, especially the eyes); figuratively, to be observant:--open.
from 6491; watch; Pekach, an Israelite king:--Pekah.
from 6491; clear-sighted; figuratively, intelligent:--seeing, wise.
from 6491 and 3050; Jah has observed; Pekachjah, an Israelite king:--Pekahiah.
from 6491 redoubled; opening (of a dungeon), i.e. jail-delivery (figuratively, salvation for sin):--opening of the prison.
from 6485; a superintendent (civil, military or religious):--which had the charge, governor, office, overseer, (that) was set.
from an unused root meaning to burst; only used as an architectural term of an ornament similar to 6498, a semi-globe:--knop.
from the same as 6497; the wild cucumber (from splitting open to shed its seeds):--gourd.
or par {pawr}; from 6565; a bullock (apparently as breaking forth in wild strength, or perhaps as dividing the hoof):--(+ young) bull(-ock), calf, ox.
a primitive root; to bear fruit:--be fruitful.
or pereh (Jeremiah 2:24) {peh'-reh}; from 6500 in the secondary sense of running wild; the onager:--wild (ass).
from 6501; wildly; Piram, a Canaanite:--Piram.
or Parvar {par-vawr'}; of foreign origin; Parbar or Parvar, a quarter of Jerusalem:--Parbar, suburb.
a primitive root; to break through, i.e. spread or separate (oneself):--disperse, divide, be out of joint, part, scatter (abroad), separate (self), sever self, stretch, sunder.
from 6504; a mule (perhaps from his lonely habits):--mule.
feminine of 6505; a she-mule:--mule.
feminine passive participle of 6504; something separated, i.e. a kernel:--seed.
of foreign origin; a park:--forest, orchard.
a primitive root; to bear fruit (literally or figuratively):--bear, bring forth (fruit), (be, cause to be, make) fruitful, grow, increase.
feminine of 6499; a heifer:--cow, heifer, kine.
the same as 6510; Parah, a place in Palestine:--Parah.
from 6331; a hole (as broken, i.e. dug):--+ mole. Compare 2661.
for 6288; foliage; Purah, an Israelite:--Phurah.
or Priyda {per-ee-daw'}; from 6504; dispersion; Peruda or Perida, one of "Solomon's servants":--Perida, Peruda.
passive participle of 6524; blossomed; Paruach, an Israelite:--Paruah.
of foreign origin; Parvajim, an Oriental region:--Parvaim.
passive participle of 6565 in the sense of spreading out (compare 6524); a skillet (as flat or deep):--pan, pot.
from an unused root meaning to separate, i.e. decide; a chieftain:--village.
from the same as 6518; an open country:--(unwalled) town (without walls), unwalled village.
from the same as 6518; magistracy, i.e. leadership (also concretely, chieftains):--village.
or prowziy {per-o-zee'}; from 6519; a rustic:--village.
for 6521; inhabitant of the open country; a Perizzite, one of the Canaanitish tribes:--Perizzite.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 1270; iron:--iron.

a primitive root; to break forth as a bud, i.e. bloom; generally, to spread; specifically, to fly (as extending the wings); figuratively, to flourish:--X abroad, X abundantly, blossom, break forth (out), bud, flourish, make fly, grow, spread, spring (up).
from 6524; a calyx (natural or artificial); generally, bloom:--blossom, bud, flower.
from 6524; progeny, i.e. a brood:--youth.
a primitive root; to scatter words, i.e. prate (or hum):--chant.
from 6527; a stray or single berry:--grape.
from 6509; fruit (literally or figuratively):--bough, ((first-)) fruit((-ful)), reward.
from 6555; violent, i.e. a tyrant:--destroyer, ravenous, robber.
from an unused root meaning to break apart; fracture, i.e. severity:--cruelty, rigour.
feminine active participle of the same as 6531; a separatrix, i.e. (the sacred) screen:--vail.
a primitive root; to tear:--rend.
of Persian origin; Parmashta, a son of Haman:--Parmasta.
of uncertain derivation; Parnak, an Israelite:--Parnach.
a primitive root; to break in pieces, i.e. (usually without violence) to split, distribute:--deal, divide, have hoofs, part, tear.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6536; to split up:--divide, (U-)pharsin.
from 6536; a claw; also a kind of eagle:--claw, ossifrage.
of foreign origin; Paras (i.e. Persia), an Eastern country, including its inhabitants:--Persia, Persians.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6539:--Persia, Persians.
feminine of 6538; a claw or split hoof:--claw, (cloven-)footed, hoof.
patrial from 6539; a Parsite (i.e. Persian), or inhabitant of Peres:--Persian.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6542:--Persian.
a primitive root; to loosen; by implication, to expose, dismiss; figuratively, absolve, begin:--avenge, avoid, bare, go back, let, (make) naked, set at nought, perish, refuse, uncover.
from 6544; the hair (as dishevelled):--locks.
feminine of 6545 (in the sense of beginning); leadership (plural concretely, leaders):--+ avenging, revenge.
of Egyptian derivation; Paroh, a general title of Egyptian kings:--Pharaoh.
of Egyptian derivation; Paroh- Chophra, an Egyptian king:--Pharaoh-hophra.
or Parpoh Nkow {par-o' nek-o'}; of Egyptian derivation; Paroh-Nekoh (or -Neko), an Egyptian king: --Pharaoh-necho, Pharaoh-nechoh.
probably from 6544 and 6211; a flea (as the isolated insect):--flea.
the same as 6550; Parosh, the name of our Israelite:--Parosh, Pharosh.
from 6546; chieftaincy; Pirathon, a place in Palestine:--Pirathon.
or Pirathoniy {pir-aw-tho-nee'}; patrial from 6552; a Pirathonite or inhabitant of Pirathon:--Pirathonite.
probably from 6565 in the sense of rushing; rapid; Parpar, a river of Syria:--Pharpar.

a primitive root; to break out (in many applications, direct and indirect, literal and figurative):--X abroad, (make a) breach, break (away, down, -er, forth, in, up), burst out, come (spread) abroad, compel, disperse, grow, increase, open, press, scatter, urge.
from 6555; a break (literally or figuratively):--breach, breaking forth (in), X forth, gap.
the same as 6556; Perets, the name of two Israelites:--Perez, Pharez.
patronymically from 6557; a Partsite (collectively) or descendants of Perets:--Pharzites.
plural of 6556; breaks; Peratsim, a mountain in Palestine:--Perazim.
from 6556 and 5798; break of Uzza; Perets-Uzza, a place in Palestine:--Perez-uzza.
a primitive root; to break off or crunch; figuratively, to deliver:--break (off), deliver, redeem, rend (in pieces), tear in pieces.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6561; to discontinue:--break off.
from 6561; rapine; also a fork (in roads):--crossway, robbery.
from 6561; soup (as full of crumbed meat):--broth. See also 4832.

a primitive root; to break up (usually figuratively, i.e. to violate, frustrate:--X any ways, break (asunder), cast off, cause to cease, X clean, defeat, disannul, disappoint, dissolve, divide, make of none effect, fail, frustrate, bring (come) to nought, X utterly, make void.
