a primitive root; to break apart, disperse, etc.:--break, chop in pieces, lay open, scatter, spread (abroad, forth, selves, out), stretch (forth, out).
a primitive root; to separate, literally (to disperse) or figuratively (to specify); also (by implication) to wound:-- scatter, declare, distinctly, shew, sting.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6567; to specify:--distinctly.
from 6567; excrement (as eliminated):--dung.
the same as 6569; Peresh, an Israelite:--Peresh.
from 6567; a steed (as stretched out to a vehicle, not single nor for mounting (compare 5483)); also (by implication) a driver (in a chariot), i.e. (collectively) cavalry:--horseman.
or pathshegen {path-sheh'-gen}; of foreign origin; a transcript:--copy.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6572:--copy.
perhaps by compounding 6567 and 6504 (in the sense of straddling) (compare 6576); the crotch (or anus):--dirt.
from 6567; exposition:--declaration, sum.
a root apparently formed by compounding 6567 and that of 6518 (compare 6574); to expand:--spread.
of Persian origin; Parshandatha, a son of Haman:--Parshandatha.
from an unused root meaning to break forth; rushing; Perath (i.e. Euphrates), a river of the East:--Euphrates.
of Persian origin; a grandee:--(most) noble, prince.
probably from an unused root meaning to disintegrate; stupidity (as a result of grossness or of degeneracy):--extremity.
a primitive root; to spread:--spread.
a primitive root; to tear in pieces:--pull in pieces.
probably from 6582; liberation; Pashchur, the name of four Israelites:--Pashur.

a primitive root; to spread out (i.e. deploy in hostile array); by analogy, to strip (i.e. unclothe, plunder, flay, etc.):--fall upon, flay, invade, make an invasion, pull off, put off, make a road, run upon, rush, set, spoil, spread selves (abroad), strip (off, self).
a primitive root; to stride (from spreading the legs), i.e. rush upon:--go.
a primitive root (identical with 6585 through the idea of expansion); to break away (from just authority), i.e. trespass, apostatize, quarrel:--offend, rebel, revolt, transgress(-ion, -or).
from 6585; a stride:--step.
from 6586; a revolt (national, moral or religious):--rebellion, sin, transgression, trespass.
a primitive root; to dispart (the feet or lips), i.e. become licentious:--open (wide).
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6622; to interpret:--make (interpretations), interpreting.
(Aramaic) from 6590; an interpretation:--interpretation.
corresponding to 6591:--interpretation.
from the same as 6580 as in the sense of comminuting; linen (i.e. the thread, as carded):--flax, linen.
feminine of 6593; flax; by implication, a wick:--flax, tow.
from 6626; a bit:--meat, morsel, piece.
or pothah (Ezek. 13:19) {po-thaw'}; from an unused root meaning to open; a hole, i.e. hinge or the female pudenda:--hinge, secret participle
or pith.om {pith-ome'}; from 6621; instantly:--straightway, sudden(-ly).
of Persian origin; a dainty:--portion (provision) of meat.
of Persian origin; a (judicial) sentence:--decree, sentence.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6599; a word, answer, letter or decree:--answer, letter, matter, word.

a primitive root; to open, i.e. be (causatively, make) roomy; usually figuratively (in a mental or moral sense) to be (causatively, make) simple or (in a sinister way) delude:--allure, deceive, enlarge, entice, flatter, persuade, silly (one).
from 6601 and 410; enlarged of God; Pethuel, an Israelite:--Pethuel.
or pittuach {pit-too'-akh; passive participle of 6605; sculpture (in low or high relief or even intaglio):--carved (work) (are, en-)grave(-ing, -n).
of foreign origin; Pethor, a place in Mesopotamia:--Pethor.

a primitive root; to open wide (literally or figuratively); specifically, to loosen, begin, plough, carve:--appear, break forth, draw (out), let go free, (en-)grave(-n), loose (self), (be, be set) open(-ing), put off, ungird, unstop, have vent.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6605; to open:--open.
from 6605; an opening (literally), i.e. door (gate) or entrance way:--door, entering (in), entrance (-ry), gate, opening, place.
from 6605; opening (figuratively) i.e. disclosure:--entrance.
from 6605; something opened, i.e. a drawn sword:--drawn sword.
from 6605; opening (the act):--open(-ing).
from 6605 and 3050; Jah has opened; Pethachjah, the name of four Israelites:--Pethakiah.
or pethiy {peh'-thee}; or pthaeiy {peth-aw-ee'}; from 6601; silly (i.e. seducible):--foolish, simple(-icity, one).
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to 6601; open, i.e. (as noun) width:--breadth.
of uncertain derivation; probably a figured mantle for holidays:--stomacher.
from 6612; silliness (i.e. seducibility):--simple.
from 6617; twine:--bound, bracelet, lace, line, ribband, thread, wire.
a primitive root; to twine, i.e. (literally) to struggle or (figuratively) be (morally) tortuous:--(shew self) froward, shew self unsavoury, wrestle.
from 6617; tortuous (i.e. crafty):--crooked.
of Egyptian derivation; Pithom, a place in Egypt:--Pithom.
from an unused root meaning to twist; an asp (from its contortions):--adder.
from an unused root meaning to open (the eyes); a wink, i.e. moment (compare 6597) (used only (with or without preposition) adverbially, quickly or unexpectedly):--at an instant, suddenly, X very.
a primitive root; to open up, i.e. (figuratively) interpret (a dream):--interpret(-ation, -er).
or pithron {pith-rone'}; from 6622; interpretation (of a dream):--interpretation.
of Egyptian derivation; Pathros, a part of Egypt:--Pathros.
patrial from 6624; a Pathrusite, or inhabitant of Pathros:--Pathrusim.
a primitive root; to open, i.e. break:--participle
from 3318; issue, i.e. (human) excrement:--that (which) cometh from (out).
from an unused root meaning to be slender; the lotus tree:--shady tree.

or tsaown (Psalm 144:13) {tseh-one'}; from an unused root meaning to migrate; a collective name for a flock (of sheep or goats); also figuratively (of men):--(small) cattle, flock (+ -s), lamb (+ -s), sheep((-cote, -fold, -shearer, -herds)).
from the same as 6629 used denominatively; sheep pasture; Zaanan, a place in Palestine:--Zaanan.
from 3318; issue, i.e. produce, children:--that which cometh forth (out), offspring.
from an unused root meaning to establish; a palanquin or canopy (as a fixture); also a species of lizard (probably as clinging fast):--covered, litter, tortoise.
a primitive root; to mass (an army or servants):--assemble, fight, perform, muster, wait upon, war.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6623 in the figurative sense of summoning one's wishes; to please:--will, would.

or (feminine) tsbadah {tseb-aw-aw'}; from 6633; a mass of persons (or figuratively, things), especially reg. organized for war (an army); by implication, a campaign, literally or figuratively (specifically, hardship, worship):--appointed time, (+) army, (+) battle, company, host, service, soldiers, waiting upon, war(-fare).
or (more correctly) Tsbiyiym {tseb-ee-yeem'}; or Tsbiyim {tseb-ee-yeem'}; plural of 6643; gazelles; Tseboim or Tsebijim, a place in Palestine:--Zeboiim, Zeboim.
feminine active participle of the same as 6632; the canopier (with the article); Tsobebah, an Israelitess:--Zobebah.
a primitive root; to amass, i.e. grow turgid; specifically, to array an army against:--fight swell.
from 6638; turgid:--swell.
(Aramaic) from 6634; properly, will; concretely, an affair (as a matter of determination):--purpose.
passive participle of the same as 6648; dyed (in stripes), i.e. the hyena:--speckled.
a primitive root; to grasp, i.e. hand out:--reach.
from 6638 in the sense of prominence; splendor (as conspicuous); also a gazelle (as beautiful):--beautiful(-ty), glorious (-ry), goodly, pleasant, roe(-buck).
for 6645; Tsibja, an Israelite:--Zibia.
for 6646; Tsibjah, an Israelitess:--Zibiah.
feminine of 6643; a female gazelle:--roe.
(Aramaic) a root corresponding to that of 6648; to dip:--wet.
from an unused root meaning to dip (into coloring fluid); a dye:--divers, colours.
from the same as 6648; variegated; Tsibon, an Idumaean:--Zibeon.
plural of 6641; hyenas; Tseboim, a place in Palestine:--Zeboim.
a primitive root; to aggregate:--gather (together), heap (up), lay up.
from 6551; a pile:--heap.
from an unused root apparently meaning to grip; a lock of stalks:--handful.
contr. from an unused root meaning to sidle off; a side; figuratively, an adversary:--(be-)side.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6654; used adverbially (with preposition) at or upon the side of:--against, concerning.
(Aramaic) from an unused root corresponding to 6658 in the sense of intentness; a (sinister) design:--true.
from the same as 6654; a siding; Tsedad, a place near Palestine:--Zedad.
a primitive root; to chase; by implication, to desolate:--destroy, hunt, lie in wait.
from 6663; just; Tsadok, the name of eight or nine Israelites:--Zadok.
from 6658; design (compare 6656):--lying in wait.
plural of 6654; sides; Tsiddim (with the article), a place in Palestine:--Ziddim.
from 6663; just:--just, lawful, righteous (man).
a primitive root; to be (causatively, make) right (in a moral or forensic sense):--cleanse, clear self, (be, do) just(-ice, -ify, -ify self), (be turn to) righteous(-ness).
from 6663; the right (natural, moral or legal); also (abstractly) equity or (figuratively) prosperity:--X even, (X that which is altogether) just(-ice), ((un-))right(-eous) (cause, -ly, - ness).
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6666; beneficence:-- righteousness.
from 6663; rightness (abstractly), subjectively (rectitude), objectively (justice), morally (virtue) or figuratively (prosperity):--justice, moderately, right(-eous) (act, -ly, -ness).
or Tsidqiyahuw {tsid-kee-yaw'-hoo}; from 6664 and 3050; right of Jah; Tsidkijah, the name of six Israelites:--Zedekiah, Zidkijah.
a primitive root; to glitter, i.e. be golden in color:--X fine.
from 6668; golden in color:--yellow.
a prim root; to gleam, i.e. (figuratively) be cheerful; by transf. to sound clear (of various animal or human expressions):--bellow, cry aloud (out), lift up, neigh, rejoice, make to shine, shout.
a primitive root; to glisten; used only as denominative from 3323, to press out oil:--make oil.
from 6671; a light (i.e. window): dual double light, i.e. noon:--midday, noon(-day, -tide), window.
or tsav {tsawv}; from 6680; an injunction:--commandment, precept.
or tsov {tso}; from an unused root meaning to issue; soiled (as if excrementitious):--filthy.
or tsovah {tso-aw'}: feminine of 6674; excrement; generally, dirt; figuratively, pollution:--dung, filth(-iness). Marg. for 2716.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6677:--neck.

or tsavvar (Nehemiah 3:5) {tsav-vawr'}; or tsavvaron (Song of Solomon 4:9) {tsav-vaw-rone'}; or (feminine) tsavva.rah (Micah 2:3) {tsav-vaw-raw'}; intensively from 6696 in the sense of binding; the back of the neck (as that on which burdens are bound):--neck.
or Tsowbah {tso-baw'}; or Tsobah {tso-baw'}; from an unused root meaning to station; a station; Zoba or Zobah, a region of Syria:--Zoba, Zobah.
a primitive root; to lie alongside (i.e. in wait); by implication, to catch an animal (figuratively, men); (denominative from 6718) to victual (for a journey):--chase, hunt, sore, take (provision).
a primitive root; (intensively) to constitute, enjoin:--appoint, (for-)bid, (give a) charge, (give a, give in, send with) command(-er, -ment), send a messenger, put, (set) in order.
a primitive root; to screech (exultingly):--shout.
from 6681; a screech (of anguish): --cry(-ing).
from an unused root meaning to sink: an abyss (of the sea):--deep.
a primitive root; to cover over (the mouth), i.e. to fast:--X at all, fast.
or tsom {tsome}; from from 6684; a fast: --fast(-ing).
from 6819; small; Tsuar, an Israelite:--Zuar.
a primitive root; to overflow:--(make to over-)flow, swim.
from 6687; comb of honey (from dripping):--honeycomb.
or Tsowphay {tso-fah'-ee}; or Tsiyph {tseef}; from 6688; honey-comb; Tsuph or Tsophai or Tsiph, the name of an Israelite and of a place in Palestine:--Zophai, Zuph.
from an unused root meaning to expand, breadth; Tsophach, an Israelite:--Zophah.
from 6852; departing; Tsophar, a friend of Job:--Zophar.
a primitive root; to twinkle, i.e. glance; by analogy, to blossom (figuratively, flourish):--bloom, blossom, flourish, shew self.
a primitive root; to compress, i.e. (figuratively) oppress, distress:--constrain, distress, lie sore, (op-)press(-or), straiten.
a primitive root (identical with 6693 through the idea of narrowness (of orifice)); to pour out, i.e. (figuratively) smelt, utter:--be molten, pour.
or (feminine) tsuwqah {tsoo-kaw'}; from 6693; a strait, i.e. (figuratively) distress:--anguish, X troublous.

a primitive root; to cramp, i.e. confine (in many applications, literally and figuratively, formative or hostile):--adversary, assault, beset, besiege, bind (up), cast, distress, fashion, fortify, inclose, lay siege, put up in bags.

or tsur {tsoor}; from 6696; properly, a cliff (or sharp rock, as compressed); generally, a rock or boulder; figuratively, a refuge; also an edge (as precipitous):--edge, X (mighty) God (one), rock, X sharp, stone, X strength, X strong. See also 1049.
the same as 6697; rock; Tsur, the name of a Midianite and of an Israelite:--Zur.
feminine of 6697; a rock (Job 28:10); also a form (as if pressed out):--form, rock.
from 6697 and 410; rock of God; Tsuriel, an Israelite:--Zuriel.
from 6697 and 7706; rock of (the) Almighty; Tsurishaddai, an Israelite:--Zurishaddai.
a primitive root; to blaze:--burn.
from 6705; dazzling, i.e. sunny, bright, (figuratively) evident:--clear, dry, plainly, white.
from an unused root meaning to glow; parched:--dried up.
a primitive root; to glare, i.e. be dazzling white:--be whiter.
from 6705; glaring, i.e. exposed to the bright sun:--higher place, top.
feminine of 6706; a parched region, i.e. the desert:--dry land.
from 6706; bare spot, i.e. in the glaring sun:--higher place.
from an unused root meaning to putrefy; stench:--ill savour.
from 6705; a dry place, i.e. desert:--drought.
a primitive root; to laugh outright (in merriment or scorn); by implication, to sport:--laugh, mock, play, make sport.
from 6711; laughter (in pleasure or derision):--laugh(-ed to scorn).
from an unused root meaning to dazzle; sheen, i.e. whiteness:--white.
from the same as 6713; whiteness; Tsochar, the name of a Hittite and of an Israelite:--Zohar. Compare 3328.
from the same as 6713; white:--white.
from 6680; a ship (as a fixture):--ship.
from the same as 6678; station; Tsiba, an Israelite:--Ziba.

from a form of 6679 and meaning the same; the chase; also game (thus taken); (generally) lunch (especially for a journey):--X catcheth, food, X hunter, (that which he took in) hunting, venison, victuals.
from the same as 6718; a huntsman:--hunter.
or tsedah {tsay-daw'}; feminine of 6718; food:--meat, provision, venison, victuals.
or Tsiydon {tsee-done'}; from 6679 in the sense of catching fish; fishery; Tsidon, the name of a son of Canaan, and of a place in Palestine:--Sidon, Zidon.
patrial from 6721; a Tsidonian or inhabitant of Tsidon:--Sidonian, of Sidon, Zidonian.
from an unused root meaning to parch; aridity; concretely, a desert:--barren, drought, dry (land, place), solitary place, wilderness.
from the same as 6723; a desert:--dry place.
from the same as 6723 in the sense of conspicuousness (compare 5329); a monumental or guiding pillar:--sign, title, waymark.
the same (regularly) as 6725; Tsijon (as a permanent capital), a mountain of Jerusalem:--Zion.
or Tsicha( {tsee-khaw'}; as if feminine of 6704; drought; Tsicha, the name of two Nethinim:--Ziha.
from the same as 6723; a desert-dweller, i.e. nomad or wild beast:--wild beast of the desert, that dwell in (inhabiting) the wilderness.
from an unused root meaning to confine; the pillory:--stocks.
from 6819; small; Tsior, a place in Palestine:--Zior.
or tsits {tseets}; from 6692; properly, glistening, i.e. a burnished plate; also a flower (as bright-colored); a wing (as gleaming in the air):--blossom, flower, plate, wing.
the same as 6731; bloom; Tsits, a place in Palestine:--Ziz.
feminine of 6731; a flower:--flower.
feminine of 6731; a floral or wing-like projection, i.e. a forelock of hair, a tassel:--fringe, lock.

from 6696; a hinge (as pressed in turning); also a throe (as a phys. or mental pressure); also a herald or errand-doer (as constrained by the principal):--ambassador, hinge, messenger, pain, pang, sorrow. Compare 6736.
the same as 6735; a form (of beauty; as if pressed out, i.e. carved); hence, an (idolatrous) image:--beauty, idol.
a denominative from 6735 in the sense of ambassador; to make an errand, i.e. betake oneself:--make as if...had been ambassador.
from 6751; shade, whether literal or figurative:--defence, shade(-ow).
(Aramaic) probably corresponding to 6760 in the sense of bowing; pray:--pray.
a primitive root; to roast:--roast.
feminine of 6738; Tsillah, an antediluvian woman:--Zillah.
from 6749 in the sense of rolling; a (round or flattened) cake:--cake.

or tsaleach {tsaw-lay'-akh}; a primitive root; to push forward, in various senses (literal or figurative, transitive or intransitive):--break out, come (mightily), go over, be good, be meet, be profitable, (cause to, effect, make to, send) prosper(-ity, -ous, - ously).
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6743; to advance (transitive or intransitive):--promote, prosper.
from 6743; something protracted or flattened out, i.e. a platter:--pan.
from 6743; something prolonged or tall, i.e. a vial or salt-cellar:--cruse.
from 6743; something advanced or deep, i.e. a bowl; figuratively, the bosom:--bosom, dish.
passive participle of 6740; roasted:--roast.
a primitive root; properly, to tumble down, i.e. settle by a waving motion:--sink. Compare 6750, 6751.
a primitive root (identical with 6749 through the idea of vibration); to tinkle, i.e. rattle together (as the ears in reddening with shame, or the teeth in chattering with fear):--quiver, tingle.
a primitive root (identical with 6749 through the idea of hovering over (compare 6754)); to shade, as twilight or an opaque object:--begin to be dark, shadowing.
from 6751; shade:--shadow.
from 6752 and the active participle of 6437; shade-facing; Tselelponi, an Israelitess:--Hazelelponi (including the article).
from an unused root meaning to shade; a phantom, i.e. (figuratively) illusion, resemblance; hence, a representative figure, especially an idol:--image, vain shew.
(Aramaic) or tslem (Aramaic) {tsel-em'}; corresponding to 6754; an idolatrous figure:--form, image.
from 6754; shady; Tsalmon, the name of a place in Palestine and of an Israelite:--Zalmon.
from 6738 and 4194; shade of death, i.e. the grave (figuratively, calamity):--shadow of death.
feminine of 6757; shadiness; Tsalmonah, a place in the Desert:--Zalmonah.
from 6738 and 4513; shade has been denied; Tsalmunna, a Midianite:--Zalmunna.
a primitive root: probably to curve; used only as denominative from 6763, to limp (as if one-sided):--halt.
from 6760; a limping or full (figuratively):--adversity, halt(-ing).
the same as 6761; Tsela, a place in Palestine:--Zelah.

or (feminine) tsalTah {tsal-aw'}; from 6760; a rib (as curved), literally (of the body) or figuratively (of a door, i.e. leaf); hence, a side, literally (of a person) or figuratively (of an object or the sky, i.e. quarter); architecturally, a (especially floor or ceiling) timber or plank (single or collective, i.e. a flooring):--beam, board, chamber, corner, leaf, plank, rib, side (chamber).
from an unused root of unknown meaning; Tsalaph, an Israelite:--Zalaph.
from the same as 6764 and 259; Tselophchad, an Israelite:--Zelophehad.
from 6738 and 6703; clear shade; Tseltsach, a place in Palestine:--Zelzah.
from 6750 reduplicated; a clatter, i.e. (abstractly) whirring (of wings); (concretely) a cricket; also a harpoon (as rattling), a cymbal (as clanging):--cymbal, locust, shadowing, spear.
from an unused root meaning to split; fissure; Tselek, an Israelite:--Zelek.
from the feminine of 6738; shady; Tsillethai, the name of two Israelites:--Zilthai.
a primitive root; to thirst (literally or figuratively):--(be a-, suffer) thirst(-y).
from 6770; thirsty (literally or figuratively):--(that) thirst(-eth, -y).
from 6770; thirst (literally or figuratively):--thirst(-y).
feminine of 6772; thirst (figuratively, of libidinousnes):--thirst.
from 6771; a thirsty place, i.e. desert:--drought, dry ground, thirsty land.
a primitive root; to link, i.e. gird; figuratively, to serve, (mentally) contrive:--fasten, frame, join (self).
a yoke or team (i.e. pair); hence, an acre (i.e. day's task for a yoke of cattle to plough):--acre, couple, X together, two (donkeys), yoke (of oxen).
from an unused root meaning to fasten on; a veil:--locks.
from 6784; a cake of dried grapes:--bunch (cluster) of raisins.

a primitive root; to sprout (transitive or intransitive, literal or figurative):--bear, bring forth, (cause to, make to) bud (forth), (cause to, make to) grow (again, up), (cause to) spring (forth, up).
from 6779; a sprout (usually concrete), literal or figurative:--branch, bud, that which (where) grew (upon), spring(-ing).
or tsamid {tsaw-meed'}; from 6775; a bracelet or arm-clasp; generally, a lid:--bracelet, covering.
from the same as 6777; a noose (as fastening); figuratively, destruction:--robber.
or tsmithuth {tsem-ee-thooth'}; from 6789; excision, i.e. destruction; used only (adverbially) with prepositional prefix to extinction, i.e. perpetually:--ever.
a primitive root; to dry up:--dry.
from an unused root probably meaning to be shaggy; wool:--wool(-len).
patrial from an unused name of a place in Palestine; a Tsemarite or branch of the Canaanites:--Zemarite.
dual of 6785; double fleece; Tsemarajim, a place in Palestine:--Zemaraim.
from the same as 6785; fleeciness, i.e. foliage:--highest branch, top.
a primitive root; to extirpate (literally or figuratively):--consume, cut off, destroy, vanish.
from an unused root meaning to prick; a crag; Tsin, a part of the Desert:--Zin.
from an unused root meaning to be prickly; a thorn; hence, a cactus-hedge:--thorn.
or tsoneh {tso-neh'}; for 6629; a flock:--sheep.
feminine of 6791; a hook (as pointed); also a (large) shield (as if guarding by prickliness); also cold (as piercing):-- buckler, cold, hook, shield, target.
from an unused root perhaps meaning to be hollow; a culvert:--gutter, water-spout.
a primitive root; to alight; (transitive) to cause to descend, i.e. drive down:--fasten, light (from off).
or tsanin {tsaw-neen'}; from the same as 6791; a thorn:--thorn.
or tsanowph {tsaw-nofe'}; or (feminine) tsaniyphah {tsaw-nee-faw'}; from 6801; a head-dress (i.e. piece of cloth wrapped around):--diadem, hood, mitre.
a primitive root; to blast or shrink:--withered.
probably for 6630; Tsenan, a place near Palestine:--Zenan.
a primitive root; to humiliate:--humbly, lowly.
a primitive root; to wrap, i.e. roll or dress:--be attired, X surely, violently turn.
from 6801; a ball:--X toss.
from the same as 6791; a vase (probably a vial tapering at the top):--pot.
probably from the same as 6794; a tube:--pipe.
a primitive root; to pace, i.e. step regularly; (upward) to mount; (along) to march; (down and causatively) to hurl:-- bring, go, march (through), run over.
from 6804; a pace or regular step:--pace, step.
feminine of 6806; a march; (concretely) an (ornamental) ankle-chain:--going, ornament of the legs.

a primitive root; to tip over (for the purpose of spilling or pouring out), i.e. (figuratively) depopulate; by implication, to imprison or conquer; (reflexive) to lie down (for coitus):--captive exile, travelling, (cause to) wander(-er).
from an unused root meaning to wrap over; a veil:--vail.
or tsanowr {tsaw-ore'}; from 6819; little; (in number) few; (in age) young, (in value) ignoble:--least, little (one), small (one), + young(-er, -est).
the same as 6810; Tsair, a place in Idumaea:--Zair.
feminine of 6810; smallness (of age), i.e. juvenility:--youth.
a primitive root; to load up (beasts), i.e. to migrate:--be taken down.
of Egyptian derivation; Tsoan, a place in Egypt:--Zoan.
or (dual) Tsaeanayim {tsah-an-ah'-yim}; plural from 6813; removals; Tsaanannim or Tsaanajim, a place in Palestine:--Zaannannim, Zaanaim.
from an unused root meaning to bestrew with carvings; sculpture:--image (work).
a primitive root; to shriek; (by implication) to proclaim (an assembly):--X at all, call together, cry (out), gather (selves) (together).
from 6817; a shriek:--cry(-ing).
a primitive root; to be small, i.e. (figuratively) ignoble:--be brought low, little one, be small.
from 6819; little; Tsoar, a place East of the Jordan:--Zoar.
a primitive root; to adhere:--cleave.
a primitive root; properly, to lean forward, i.e. to peer into the distance; by implication, to observe, await:-- behold, espy, look up (well), wait for, (keep the) watch(-man).
a primitive root (probably identical with 6822 through the idea of expansion in outlook, transferring to action); to sheet over (especially with metal):--cover, overlay.
from 6823; an inundation (as covering):--X swimmest.
or Tsphiy {tsef-ee'}; from 6822; observant; Tsepho or Tsephi, an Idumaean:--Zephi, Zepho.
from 6823; encasement (with metal):--covering, overlaying.
probably for 6837; Tsephon, an Israelite:--Zephon.
or tsaphon {tsaw-fone'}; from 6845; properly, hidden, i.e. dark; used only of the north as a quarter (gloomy and unknown):--north(-ern, side, -ward, wind).
the same as 6828; boreal; Tsaphon, a place in Palestine:--Zaphon.
from 6828; northern:--northern.
patronymically from 6827; a Tsephonite, or (collectively) descendants of Tsephon:--Zephonites.
from the same as 6848; excrement (as protruded):--dung.
or tsippor {tsip-pore'}; from 6852; a little bird (as hopping):--bird, fowl, sparrow.
the same as 6833; Tsippor, a Moabite:--Zippor.
from an unused root meaning to expand; a saucer (as flat):--cruse.
from 6822; watchfulness:--watching.
from 6822; watch-tower; Tsiphjon, an Israelite:--Ziphion. Compare 6827.
from the same as 6835; a flat thin cake:--wafer.
plural of active participle of 6822; watchers; Tsophim, a place East of the Jordan:--Zophim.
from 6845; a treasure (as hidden):--hid.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6842; a he-goat:--he (goat).
from 6852; a male goat (as prancing):--(he) goat.
feminine formed like 6842; a crown (as encircling the head); also a turn of affairs (i.e. mishap):--diadem, morning.
from 6822; a sentry:--watchtower.

a primitive root; to hide (by covering over); by implication, to hoard or reserve; figuratively to deny; specifically (favorably) to protect, (unfavorably) to lurk:--esteem, hide(-den one, self), lay up, lurk (be set) privily, (keep) secret(-ly, place).
or Tsphanyahuw {tsef-an-yaw'-hoo}; from 6845 and 3050; Jah has secreted; Tsephanjah, the name of four Israelites:--Zephaniah.
of Egyptian derivation; Tsophnath-Paneach, Joseph's Egyptian name:--Zaphnath-paaneah.
from an unused root meaning to extrude; a viper (as thrusting out the tongue, i.e. hissing):--adder, cockatrice.
feminine from the same as 6848; an outcast thing:--issue.
a primitive root; to coo or chirp (as a bird):--chatter, peep, whisper.
from 6687; a willow (as growing in overflowed places):--willow tree.
a primitive root; to skip about, i.e. return:--depart early.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6833; a bird. -- bird.
from 6852 and a word elsewhere unused meaning a swamp; a marsh-leaper, i.e. frog:--frog.
feminine of 6833; bird; Tsipporah, Moses' wife:--Zipporah.
from 6852 (in the denominative sense (from 6833) of scratching); properly, a claw, i.e. (human) nail; also the point of a style (or pen, tipped with adamant):--nail, point.
from 6822; watch-tower; Tsephath, a place in Palestine:--Zephath.
from an unused root meaning to encircle; a capital of a column:--chapiter.
the same as 6857; Tsephathah, a place in Palestine:--Zephathah.
or Tsiyqlag (1 Chronicles 12:1,20) {tsee-kel-ag'}; of uncertain derivation: Tsiklag or Tsikelag, a place in Palestine:--Ziklag.
from an unused root meaning to wind; a sack (as tied at the mouth):--husk.

or tsar {tsawr}; from 6887; narrow; (as a noun) a tight place (usually figuratively, i.e. trouble); also a pebble (as in 6864); (transitive) an opponent (as crowding):--adversary, afflicted(-tion), anguish, close, distress, enemy, flint, foe, narrow, small, sorrow, strait, tribulation, trouble.
from 6887; rock; Tser, a place in Palestine:--Zer.
from 6696; a stone (as if pressed hard or to a point); (by implication, of use) a knife:--flint, sharp stone.
or Tsowr {tsore}; the same as 6864; a rock; Tsor, a place in Palestine:--Tyre, Tyrus.
a primitive root; to burn:--burn.
from 6686; conflagration (of fire or disease):--burning, inflammation.
or Tsredathah {tser-ay-daw'-thaw}; apparently from an unused root meaning to pierce; puncture; Tseredah, a place in Palestine:--Zereda, Zeredathah.
feminine of 6862; tightness (i.e. figuratively, trouble); transitively, a female rival:--adversary, adversity, affliction, anguish, distress, tribulation, trouble.
feminine passive participle from the same as 6875; wounded; Tserujah, an Israelitess:--Zeruiah.
feminine passive participle of 6879; leprous; Tseruah, an Israelitess:--Zeruah.
or (shorter) tsror {tser-ore'}; from 6887; a parcel (as packed up); also a kernel or particle (as if a package):--bag, X bendeth, bundle, least grain, small stone.
a primitive root; to be clear (in tone, i.e. shrill), i.e. to whoop:--cry, roar.
the same as 6875; Tseri, an Israelite:--Zeri. Compare 3340.
or tsoriy {tsor-ee'}; from an unused root meaning to crack (as by pressure), hence, to leak; distillation, i.e. balsam:--balm.
patrial from 6865; a Tsorite or inhabitant of Tsor (i.e. Syrian):--(man) of Tyre.
from 6873 in the sense of clearness of vision; a citadel:--high place, hold.
from an unused root meaning to need; need:--need.
a primitive root; to scourge, i.e. (intransitive and figurative) to be stricken with leprosy:--leper, leprous.
from 6879; a wasp (as stinging):--hornet.
apparently another form for 6880; Tsorah, a place in Palestine:--Zareah, Zorah, Zoreah.
or Tsortathiy {tsor-aw-thee'}; patrial from 6881; a Tsorite or Tsorathite, i.e. inhabitants of Tsorah:--Zorites, Zareathites, Zorathites.
from 6879; leprosy:--leprosy.
a primitive root; to fuse (metal), i.e. refine (literally or figuratively):--cast, (re-)fine(-er), founder, goldsmith, melt, pure, purge away, try.
from 6884; refiner; Tsorephi (with the article), an Israelite:--goldsmith's.
from 6884; refinement; Tsarephath, a place in Palestine:--Zarephath.

a primitive root; to cramp, literally or figuratively, transitive or intransitive (as follows):--adversary, (be in) afflict(-ion), beseige, bind (up), (be in, bring) distress, enemy, narrower, oppress, pangs, shut up, be in a strait (trouble), vex.
apparently by erroneous transcription for 6868; Tsererah for Tseredah:--Zererath.
perhaps from 6671; splendor; Tsereth, an Israelite:--Zereth.
from the same as 6889 and 7837 with the article interposed; splendor of the dawn; Tsereth-hash-Shachar, a place in Palestine:--Zareth-shahar.
perhaps for 6868; Tsarethan, a place in Palestine:--Zarthan.
or qiys {kee}; from 6958; vomit:--vomit.
from 6958; probably the pelican (from vomiting):--cormorant.
from 6895; a hollow, i.e. vessel used as a (dry) measure:--cab.
a primitive root; to scoop out, i.e. (figuratively) to malign or execrate (i.e. stab with words):--X at all, curse.
from 6895; the paunch (as a cavity) or first stomach of ruminants:--maw.
from 6895; the abdomen (as a cavity):--belly.
from 6895; a pavilion (as a domed cavity):--tent.
from 6908; a throng:--company.
or qburah {keb-oo-raw'}; feminine passive participle of 6912; sepulture; (concretely) a sepulchre:--burial, burying place, grave, sepulchre.
a primitive root; to admit, i.e. take (literally or figuratively):--choose, (take) hold, receive, (under-)take.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6901; to acquire:--receive, take.

(Aramaic) or qobel (Aramaic) {kob-ale'}; (corresponding to 6905; (adverbially) in front of; usually (with other particles) on account of, so as, since, hence:--+ according to, + as, + because, before, + for this cause, + forasmuch as, + by this means, over against, by reason of, + that, + therefore, + though, + wherefore.
from 6901 in the sense of confronting (as standing opposite in order to receive); a battering-ram:--war.
from 6901 in the sense of opposite (see 6904); the presence, i.e. (adverbially) in front of:--before.
a primitive root; to cover, i.e. (figuratively) defraud:--rob, spoil.
from 6906; a goblet (as deep like a cover):--dregs.
a primitive root; to grasp, i.e. collect:--assemble (selves), gather (bring) (together, selves together, up), heap, resort, X surely, take up.
from 6908 and 410; God has gathered; Kabtseel, a place in Palestine:--Kabzeel. Compare 3343.
feminine passive participle of 6908; a hoard:--X gather.
dual from 6908; a double heap; Kibtsajim, a place in Palestine:--Kibzaim.
a primitive root; to inter:--X in any wise, bury(-ier).
or (feminine) qibrah {kib-raw'}; from 6912; a sepulchre:--burying place, grave, sepulchre.
from the feminine plural of 6913 and 8378 with the article interposed; graves of the longing; Kibroth-hat-Taavh, a place in the Desert:--Kibroth-hattaavah.
a primitive root; to shrivel up, i.e. contract or bend the body (or neck) in deference:--bow (down) (the) head, stoop.
from 6915; cassia bark (as in shrivelled rolls):--cassia.
passive participle of 6923; a pristine hero:--ancient.
or qadosh {kaw-doshe'}; from 6942; sacred (ceremonially or morally); (as noun) God (by eminence), an angel, a saint, a sanctuary:--holy (One), saint.
a primitive root to inflame:--burn, kindle.
from 6919; inflammation, i.e. febrile disease:--burning ague, fever.
or qadim {kaw-deem'}; from 6923; the fore or front part; hence (by orientation) the East (often adverbially, eastward, for brevity the east wind):--east(-ward, wind).
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6918. --holy (One), saint.
a primitive root; to project (one self), i.e. precede; hence, to anticipate, hasten, meet (usually for help):--come (go, (flee)) before, + disappoint, meet, prevent.

or qedmah {kayd'-maw}; from 6923; the front, of place (absolutely, the fore part, relatively the East) or time (antiquity); often used adverbially (before, anciently, eastward):--aforetime, ancient (time), before, east (end, part, side, -ward), eternal, X ever(-lasting), forward, old, past. Compare 6926.
(Aramaic) or qdam (Aramaic) (Daniel 7:l3) {ked-awm'}; corresponding to 6924; before:--before, X from, X I (thought), X me, + of, X it pleased, presence.
feminine of 6924; the forward part (or relatively) East (often adverbially, on the east or in front):--east(-ward).
from 6923; priority (in time); also used adverbially (before):--afore, antiquity, former (old) estate.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6927; former time:-- afore(-time), ago.
from 6923; precedence; Kedemah, a son of Ishmael:--Kedemah.
from 6923; eastern:--east.
or qadmoniy {kad-mo-nee'}; from 6930; (of time) anterior or (of place) oriental:--ancient, they that went before, east, (thing of) old.
from 6923; beginnings; Kedemoth, a place in eastern Palestine:--Kedemoth.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to 6923; first:--first.
from 6924 and 410; presence of God; Kadmiel, the name of three Israelites:--Kadmiel.
the same as 6931; ancient, i.e. aboriginal; Kadmonite (collectively), the name of a tribe in Palestine:-- Kadmonites.
from 6915; the crown of the head (as the part most bowed):--crown (of the head), pate, scalp, top of the head.
a primitive root; to be ashy, i.e. dark-colored; by implication, to mourn (in sackcloth or sordid garments):--be black(-ish), be (make) dark(-en), X heavily, (cause to) mourn.
from 6937; dusky (of the skin or the tent); Kedar, a son of Ishmael; also (collectively) Bedouin (as his descendants or representatives):--Kedar.
from 6937; dusky place; Kidron, a brook near Jerusalem:--Kidron.
from 6937; duskiness:--blackness.
adverb from 6937; blackish ones (i.e. in sackcloth); used adverbially, in mourning weeds:--mournfully.

a primitive root; to be (causatively, make, pronounce or observe as) clean (ceremonially or morally):--appoint, bid, consecrate, dedicate, defile, hallow, (be, keep) holy(-er, place), keep, prepare, proclaim, purify, sanctify(-ied one, self), X wholly.
from 6942; a sanctum; Kedesh, the name of four places in Palestine:--Kedesh.
from 6942; a sacred place or thing; rarely abstract, sanctity:--consecrated (thing), dedicated (thing), hallowed (thing), holiness, (X most) holy (X day, portion, thing), saint, sanctuary.
from 6942; a (quasi) sacred person, i.e. (technically) a (male) devotee (by prostitution) to licentious idolatry:-- sodomite, unclean.
the same as 6945; sanctuary; Kadesh, a place in the Desert:--Kadesh. Compare 6947.

from the same as 6946 and an otherwise unused word (apparently compounded of a correspondent to 1251 and a derivative of 5128) meaning desert of a fugitive; Kadesh of (the) Wilderness of Wandering; Kadesh-Barnea, a place in the Desert:--Kadesh-barnea.
feminine of 6945; a female devotee (i.e. prostitute):--harlot, whore.
a primitive root; to be dull:--be set on edge, be blunt.
a primitive root; to convoke:--assemble (selves) (together), gather (selves) (together).
from 6950; assemblage (usually concretely):--assembly, company, congregation, multitude.
from 6950; an assemblage:--assembly, congregation.
feminine of active participle from 6950; a (female) assembler (i.e. lecturer): abstractly, preaching (used as a "nom de plume", Koheleth):--preacher.
from 6950; convocation; Kehelathah, a place in the Desert:--Kehelathah.
from an unused root meaning to ally oneself; allied; Kehath, an Israelite:--Kohath.
patronymically from 6955; a Kohathite (collectively) or descendants of Kehath:--Kohathites.
or qav {kawv}; from 6960 (compare 6961); a cord (as connecting), especially for measuring; figuratively, a rule; also a rim, a musical string or accord:--line. Compare 6978.
or qayah (Jer. 25:27) {kaw-yaw'}; a primitive root; to vomit:--spue (out), vomit (out, up, up again).
a form collateral to 3553; a helmet:--helmet.
a primitive root; to bind together (perhaps by twisting), i.e. collect; (figuratively) to expect:--gather (together), look, patiently, tarry, wait (for, on, upon).
from 6960; a (measuring) cord (as if for binding):--line.
a primitive root; properly, to cut off, i.e. (figuratively) detest:--begrieved, loathe self.

or qol {kole}; from an unused root meaning to call aloud; a voice or sound:--+ aloud, bleating, crackling, cry (+ out), fame, lightness, lowing, noise, + hold peace, (pro-)claim, proclamation, + sing, sound, + spark, thunder(-ing), voice, + yell.
from 6963 and 3050; voice of Jah; Kolajah, the name of two Israelites:--Kolaiah.

a primitive root; to rise (in various applications, literal, figurative, intensive and causative):--abide, accomplish, X be clearer, confirm, continue, decree, X be dim, endure, X enemy, enjoin, get up, make good, help, hold, (help to) lift up (again), make, X but newly, ordain, perform, pitch, raise (up), rear (up), remain, (a-)rise (up) (again, against), rouse up, set (up), (e-)stablish, (make to) stand (up), stir up, strengthen, succeed, (as-, make) sure(-ly), (be) up(-hold, - rising).
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6965:--appoint, establish, make, raise up self, (a-)rise (up), (make to) stand, set (up).
from 6965; height:--X along, height, high, stature, tall.
from 6965; elevation, i.e. (adverbially) erectly (figuratively): upright.
a primitive root; to strike a musical note, i.e. chant or wail (at a funeral):--lament, mourning woman.
probably from 6972 in the original sense of cutting off; curtailment; Koa, a region of Bab.:--Koa.
or qoph {kofe}; probably of foreign origin; a monkey:--ape.
a primitive root; to clip off; used only as denominative from 7019; to spend the harvest season:--summer.

a primitive root (identical with 6972 through the idea of severing oneself from (compare 6962)); to be (causatively, make) disgusted or anxious:--abhor, be distressed, be grieved, loathe, vex, be weary.
a primitive root (identical with 6972 through the idea of abruptness in starting up from sleep (compare 3364)); to awake (literally or figuratively):--arise, (be) (a-)wake, watch.
or qots {kotse}; from 6972 (in the sense of pricking); a thorn:--thorn.
the same as 6975; Kots, the name of two Israelites:--Koz, Hakkoz (including the article).
feminine passive participle of 6972 in its original sense; a forelock (as shorn):--lock.
from 6957 (in the sense of a fastening); stalwart:--X meted out.
a primitive root; to trench; by implication, to throw forth; also (denominative from 7023) to wall up, whether literal (to build a wall) or figurative (to estop):--break down, cast out, destroy, dig.
from 6979; (only plural) trenches, i.e. a web (as if so formed):--web.
or Qore7 (1 Chronicles 26:1) {ko-ray'}; active participle of 7121; crier; Kore, the name of two Israelites:--Kore.
or qorah {ko-raw'}; from 6979; a rafter (forming trenches as it were); by implication, a roof:--beam, roof.
a primitive root; to bend; used only as denominative for 3369, to set a trap:--lay a snare.
from the passive participle of 6983 and 3050; entrapped of Jah; Kushajah, an Israelite:--Kushaiah.
from 6990 in the sense of abbreviation; a little, i.e. (adverbially) merely:--very.
from an unused root meaning to cut off; ruin:--destroying, destruction.
from the same as 6986; extermination:--destruction.
from 6999; perfume:--incense.
feminine passive participle of 6999; perfumed; Keturah, a wife of Abraham:--Keturah.
a primitive root; to clip off, i.e. (figuratively) destroy:--be cut off.
a primitive root; properly, to cut off, i.e. (figuratively) put to death:--kill, slay.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6991; to kill:--slay.
from 6991; a violent death:--slaughter.
a primitive root (rather denominative from 6996); to diminish, i.e. be (causatively, make) diminutive or (figuratively) of no account:--be a (make) small (thing), be not worthy.
from 6994; a pettiness, i.e. the little finger:--little finger.

or qaton {kaw-tone'}; from 6962; abbreviated, i.e. diminutive, literally (in quantity, size or number) or figuratively (in age or importance):--least, less(-er), little (one), small(-est, one, quantity, thing), young(-er, -est).
the same as 6996; small; Katan, an Israelite:--Hakkatan (including the article).
a primitive root; to strip off:--crop off, cut down (up), pluck.

a primitive root (identical with 7000 through the idea of fumigation in a close place and perhaps thus driving out the occupants); to smoke, i.e. turn into fragrance by fire (especially as an act of worship):--burn (incense, sacrifice) (upon), (altar for) incense, kindle, offer (incense, a sacrifice).
a primitive root; to inclose:--join.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to 7000; a knot (as tied up), i.e. (figuratively) a riddle; also a vertebra (as if a knot):--doubt, joint.
from 6999; perfume:--incense.
from 6999; fumigative; Kitron, a place in Palestine:--Kitron.
from 6999; a fumigation:--(sweet) incense, perfume.
from 6996; littleness; Kattath, a place in Palestine:--Kattath.
a primitive root; to vomit:--spue.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7019; harvest:--summer.
or qiytor {kee-tore'}; from 6999; a fume, i.e. cloud:--smoke, vapour.
from 6965; an opponent (as rising against one), i.e. (collectively) enemies:--substance.
(Aramaic) from 6966; an edict (as arising in law):--decree, statute.
(Aramaic) from 6966; permanent (as rising firmly):--stedfast, sure.
from 6965; an arising:--rising up.
from 6969 in the original sense of fixity; a lance (as striking fast):--spear.
the same as 7013 (with a play upon the affinity to 7069); Kajin, the name of the first child, also of a place in Palestine, and of an Oriental tribe:--Cain, Kenite(-s).
from 6969; a dirge (as accompanied by beating the breasts or on instruments):--lamentation.
the same as 7015; Kinah, a place in Palestine:--Kinah.
or Qiyniy (1 Chron. 2:55) {kee-nee'}; patronymic from 7014; a Kenite or member of the tribe of Kajin:--Kenite.
from the same as 7064; fixed; Kenan, an antediluvian:--Cainan, Kenan.
from 6972; harvest (as the crop), whether the product (grain or fruit) or the (dry) season:--summer (fruit, house).
from 6972; terminal:--out- (utter-)most.
perhaps from 7006; the gourd (as nauseous):--gourd.
from 7036; intense disgrace:--shameful spewing.
or qir (Isa. 22:5) {keer}; or (feminine) qiyrah {kee-raw'}; from 6979; a wall (as built in a trench):--+ mason, side, town, X very, wall.
the same as 7023; fortress; Kir, a place in Assyrian; also one in Moab:--Kir. Compare 7025.

or (feminine of the latter word) Qiyr Chareseth {keer khar-eh'-seth}; from 7023 and 2789; fortress of earthenware; Kir-Cheres or Kir-Chareseth, a place in Moab:--Kir-haraseth, Kir-hareseth, Kir-haresh, Kir-heres.
or Qeroc {kay-roce'}; from the same as 7166; ankled; Keros, one of the Nethinim:--Keros.
from 6983; a bow; Kish, the name of five Israelites:--Kish.
from 6983; winding; Kishon, a river of Palestine:--Kishon, Kison.
from 6983; bowed; Kishi, an Israelite:--Kishi.
(Aramaic) of Greek origin; a lyre:--harp.
contracted from 7043; light; (by implication) rapid (also adverbial):--light, swift(-ly).
(Aramaic) corresponding to 6963:--sound, voice.
a primitive root (rather identical with 7034 through the idea of shrinkage by heat); to toast, i.e. scorch partially or slowly:--dried, loathsome, parch, roast.
a primitive root; to be light (as implied in rapid motion), but figuratively, only (be (causatively, hold) in contempt):--base, contemn, despise, lightly esteem, set light, seem vile.
for 6950; to assemble:--gather together.
from 7034; disgrace; (by implication) the pudenda:-- confusion, dishonour, ignominy, reproach, shame.
apparently but a form for 6747; a kettle:--caldron.
a primitive root; to maim:--lacking in his parts.
or qaliyi {kaw-lee'}; from 7033; roasted ears of grain:--parched corn.
from 7043; frivolous; Kallai, an Israelite:--Kallai.
from 7034; insignificance; Kelajah, an Israelite:--Kelaiah.
from 7038; maiming; Kelita, the name of three Israelites:--Kelita.

a primitive root; to be (causatively, make) light, literally (swift, small, sharp, etc.) or figuratively (easy, trifling, vile, etc.):--abate, make bright, bring into contempt, (ac-)curse, despise, (be) ease(-y, -ier), (be a, make, make somewhat, move, seem a, set) light(-en, -er, -ly, -ly afflict, -ly esteem, thing), X slight(-ly), be swift(-er), (be, be more, make, re-)vile, whet.
from 7043; brightened (as if sharpened):--burnished, polished.
from 7043; vilification:--(ac-)curse(-d, - ing).
a primitive root; to disparage, i.e. ridicule:--mock, scoff, scorn.
from 7046; a laughing-stock:--derision.
intensive from 7046; ridicule:--mocking.
a primitive root: to sling: also to carve (as if a circular motion, or into light forms):--carve, sling (out).
from 7049; a sling; also a (door) screen (as if slung across), or the valve (of the door) itself:--hanging, leaf, sling.
intensive from 7049; a slinger:--slinger.
from 7043; insubstantial:--light.
from an unused root meaning to prick; a prong, i.e. hay-fork:--fork.
feminine of active participle of 6965; something that rises, i.e. a stalk of grain:--(standing) corn, grown up, stalk.
from 6965 and 410; raised of God; Kemuel, the name of a relative of Abraham, and of two Israelites:--Kemuel.
from 6965; an elevation; Kamon, a place East of the Jordan:--Camon.
or qiymowsh {kee-moshe'}; from an unused root meaning to sting; a prickly plant:--nettle. Compare 7063.
from an unused root probably meaning to grind; flour:--flour, meal.
a primitive root; to pluck, i.e. destroy:--cut down, fill with wrinkles.
a primitive root; to wither:--hew down, wither.
a primitive root; to grasp with the hand:--take an handful.
from 7061; a grasp, i.e. handful:--handful.
from the same as 7057; a prickly plant:--thorn.
contracted from 7077; a nest (as fixed), sometimes including the nestlings; figuratively, a chamber or dwelling:--nest, room.
a primitive root; to be (causatively, make) zealous, i.e. (in a bad sense) jealous or envious:--(be) envy(-ious), be (move to, provoke to) jealous(-y), X very, (be) zeal(-ous).
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7069; to purchase:--buy.
from 7065; jealous:--jealous. Compare 7072.
from 7065; jealousy or envy:--envy(-ied), jealousy, X sake, zeal.

a primitive root; to erect, i.e. create; by extension, to procure, especially by purchase (causatively, sell); by implication to own:--attain, buy(-er), teach to keep cattle, get, provoke to jealousy, possess(-or), purchase, recover, redeem, X surely, X verily.

from 7069; a reed (as erect); by resemblance a rod (especially for measuring), shaft, tube, stem, the radius (of the arm), beam (of a steelyard):--balance, bone, branch, calamus, cane, reed, X spearman, stalk.
feminine of 7070; reediness; Kanah, the name of a stream and of a place in Palestine:--Kanah.
for 7067; jealous or angry:--jealous.
probably from an unused root meaning to hunt; hunter; Kenaz, the name of an Edomite and of two Israelites:--Kenaz.
patronymic from 7073, a Kenizzite or descendant of Kenaz:--Kenezite, Kenizzites.
from 7069; creation, i.e. (concretely) creatures; also acquisition, purchase, wealth:--getting, goods, X with money, riches, substance.
from an unused root (meaning to erect); cinnamon bark (as in upright rolls):--cinnamon.
a primitive root; to erect; but used only as denominative from 7064; to nestle, i.e. build or occupy as a nest:-- make...nest.
from an unused root probably meaning to wrench; perversion:--end.
from 7069; possession; Kenath, a place East of the Jordan:--Kenath.
a primitive root; properly, to distribute, i.e. determine by lot or magical scroll; by implication, to divine:--divine(-r, -ation), prudent, soothsayer, use (divination).
from 7080; a lot: also divination (including its fee), oracle:--(reward of) divination, divine sentence, witchcraft.
a primitive root; to lop off:--cut off.
from the same as 3563 (or as 7185); properly, a cup, i.e. an ink-stand:--inkhorn.
perhaps from 7049 in the sense of inclosing; citadel; Keilah, a place in Palestine:--Keilah.
from the same as 6970; an incision or gash:--+ mark.
probably from 7167; a bowl (as cut out hollow):--charger, dish.
a primitive root; to shrink, i.e. thicken (as unracked wine, curdled milk, clouded sky, frozen water):--congeal, curdle, dark, settle.
a primitive root; to contract, i.e. roll together:--cut off.
from 7088; shrinking, i.e., terror:--destruction.
or qippod {kip-pode'}; from 7088; a species of bird, perhaps the bittern (from its contracted form):--bittern.
from an unused root meaning to contract, i.e. spring forward; an arrow-snake (as darting on its prey):--great owl.
a primitive root; to draw together, i.e. close; by implication, to leap (by contracting the limbs); specifically, to die (from gathering up the feet):--shut (up), skip, stop, take out of the way.
contracted from 7112; an extremity; adverbially (with prepositional prefix) after:--+ after, (utmost) border, end, (in-)finite, X process.
a primitive root; to clip, or (generally) chop:--cut down, shorn.
from 7094; shape (as if cut out); base (as if there cut off):--bottom, size.
a primitive root; to cut off; (figuratively) to destroy; (partially) to scrape off:--cut off, cut short, scrape (off).

or (negative only) qetseh {kay'-tseh}; from 7096; an extremity (used in a great variety of applications and idioms; compare 7093):--X after, border, brim, brink, edge, end, (in-)finite, frontier, outmost coast, quarter, shore, (out-)side, X some, ut(-ter-)most (part).
feminine of 7097; a termination (used like 7097):--coast, corner, (selv-)edge, lowest, (uttermost) participle
and (feminine) qitsvah {kits-vaw'}; from 7096; a limit (used like 7097, but with less variety):--end, edge, uttermost participle
from an unused root apparently meaning to incise; fennelflower (from its pungency):--fitches.
from 7096 in the sense of determining; a magistrate (as deciding) or other leader:--captain, guide, prince, ruler. Compare 6278.
from 7106; cassia (as peeled; plural the bark):--cassia.
the same as 7102; Ketsiah, a daughter of Job:--Kezia.
from 7112; abrupt; Keziz, a valley in Palestine:--Keziz.
from 7114; severed, i.e. harvest (as reaped), the crop, the time, the reaper, or figuratively; also a limb (of a tree, or simply foliage):--bough, branch, harvest (man).
a primitive root; to strip off, i.e. (partially) scrape; by implication, to segregate (as an angle):--cause to scrape, corner.
a primitive root; to crack off, i.e. (figuratively) burst out in rage:--(be) anger(-ry), displease, fret self, (provoke to) wrath (come), be wroth.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7107; to become enraged:--be furious.
(Aramaic) from 7108; rage:--wrath.
from 7107; a splinter (as chipped off); figuratively, rage or strife:--foam, indignation, X sore, wrath.
from 7107; a fragment:--bark(-ed).
a primitive root; to chop off (literally or figuratively):--cut (asunder, in pieces, in sunder, off), X utmost.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7112:--cut off.

a primitive root; to dock off, i.e. curtail (transitive or intransitive, literal or figurative); especially to harvest (grass or grain):--X at all, cut down, much discouraged, grieve, harvestman, lothe, mourn, reap(-er), (be, wax) short(-en, -er), straiten, trouble, vex.
from 7114; shortness (of spirit), i.e. impatience:--anguish.
from 7114; short (whether in size, number, life, strength or temper):--few, hasty, small, soon.
from 7096; a termination (literally or figuratively); also (by implication) a portion; adverbially (with prepositional prefix) after:--end, part, X some.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7117:--end, partly.
contracted from an unused root meaning to chill; cool; figuratively, quiet:--cold, excellent (from the margin).
from the same as 7119; cold:--cold.

a primitive root (rather identical with 7122 through the idea of accosting a person met); to call out to (i.e. properly, address by name, but used in a wide variety of applications):--bewray (self), that are bidden, call (for, forth, self, upon), cry (unto), (be) famous, guest, invite, mention, (give) name, preach, (make) proclaim(- ation), pronounce, publish, read, renowned, say.
a primitive root: to encounter, whether accidentally or in a hostile manner:--befall, (by) chance, (cause to) come (upon), fall out, happen, meet.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7121:--call, cry, read.
properly, active participle of 7121; a caller, i.e. partridge (from its cry):--partridge. See also 6981.
from 7122; an encountering, accidental, friendly or hostile (also adverbially, opposite):--X against (he come), help, meet, seek, X to, X in the way.

a primitive root; to approach (causatively, bring near) for whatever purpose:--(cause to) approach, (cause to) bring (forth, near), (cause to) come (near, nigh), (cause to) draw near (nigh), go (near), be at hand, join, be near, offer, present, produce, make ready, stand, take.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7126:--approach, come (near, nigh), draw near.
from 7126; hostile encounter:--battle, war.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7128:--war.

from 7126; properly, the nearest part, i.e. the center, whether literal, figurative or adverbial (especially with preposition):--X among, X before, bowels, X unto charge, + eat (up), X heart, X him, X in, inward (X -ly, part, -s, thought), midst, + out of, purtenance, X therein, X through, X within self.
from 7126; near:--approach, come (near, nigh), draw near.
from 7126; approach:--approaching, draw near.
or qurban {koor-bawn'}; from 7126; something brought near the altar, i.e. a sacrificial present:--oblation, that is offered, offering.
perhaps from 6923 in the sense of striking upon; an axe:--ax.
feminine of 7119; coolness:--cold.

a primitive root; to light upon (chiefly by accident); causatively, to bring about; specifically, to impose timbers (for roof or floor):--appoint, lay (make) beams, befall, bring, come (to pass unto), floor, (hap) was, happen (unto), meet, send good speed.
from 7136; an (unfortunate) occurrence, i.e. some accidental (ceremonial) disqualification:--uncleanness that chanceth.

or qarob {kaw-robe'}; from 7126; near (in place, kindred or time):--allied, approach, at hand, + any of kin, kinsfold(-sman), (that is) near (of kin), neighbour, (that is) next, (them that come) nigh (at hand), more ready, short(-ly).
a primitive root; to depilate:--make (self) bald.
or qorach {ko'-rakh}; from 7139; ice (as if bald, i.e. smooth); hence, hail; by resemblance, rock crystal:--crystal, frost, ice.
from 7139; ice; Korach, the name of two Edomites and three Israelites:--Korah.
from 7139; bald (on the back of the head):--bald (head).
from 7139; bald; Kareach, an Israelite:--Careah, Kareah.
or qorcha; (Ezek. 27:31) {kor-khaw'}; from 7139; baldness:--bald(-ness), X utterly.
patronymic from 7141; a Korchite (collectively) or descendants of Korach:--Korahite, Korathite, sons of Kore, Korhite.
from 7139; a bald spot (on the back of the head); figuratively, a threadbare spot (on the back side of the cloth):--bald head, bare within.
from 7136; hostile encounter:--contrary.
from 7121; called, i.e. select:--famous, renowned.
(Aramaic) or qiryah (Aramaic) {keer-yaw'}; corresponding to 7151:--city.
from 7121; a proclamation:--preaching.
from 7136 in the sense of flooring, i.e. building; a city:--city.
plural of 7151; buildings; Kerioth, the name of two places in Palestine:--Kerioth, Kirioth.

or (with the article interposed) Qiryath ha- Arbaw (Neh. 11:25) {keer-yath' haw-ar-bah'}; from 7151 and 704 or 702; city of Arba, or city of the four (giants); Kirjath-Arba or Kirjath-ha-Arba, a place in Palestine:--Kirjath-arba.
from 7151 and 1168; city of Baal; Kirjath-Baal, a place in Palestine:--Kirjath-baal.
from 7151 and the feminine plural of 2351; city of streets; Kirjath-Chutsoth, a place in Moab:--Kirjath-huzoth.
dual of 7151; double city; Kirjathaim, the name of two placed in Palestine:--Kiriathaim, Kirjathaim.

or (Jer. 26:20) with the article interposed; or (Josh. 18:28) simply the former part of the word; or Qiryath tAriym {keer-yath' aw-reem'}; from 7151 and the plural of 3293 or 5892; city of forests, or city of towns; Kirjath-Jearim or Kirjath-Arim, a place in Palestine:--Kirjath, Kirjath-jearim, Kirjath-arim.

or Qiryath Cepher {keer-yath' say-fer}; from 7151 and a simpler feminine from the same as 5577, or (for the latter name) 5612; city of branches, or of a book; Kirjath-Sannah or Kirjath-Sepher, a place in Palestine:--Kirjath-sannah, Kirjath-sepher.
a primitive root; to cover:--cover.
a primitive root; to push or gore; used only as denominative from 7161, to shoot out horns; figuratively, rays:--have horns, shine.

from 7160; a horn (as projecting); by implication, a flask, cornet; by resembl. an elephant's tooth (i.e. ivory), a corner (of the altar), a peak (of a mountain), a ray (of light); figuratively, power:--X hill, horn.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7161; a horn (literally or for sound):--horn, cornet.
from 7161 and 6320; horn of cosmetic; Keren-hap-Puk, one of Job's daughters:--Keren-happuch.
a primitive root; properly, to protrude; used only as denominative from 7165 (for alliteration with 7167), to hunch, i.e. be hump-backed:--stoop.
from 7164; a knob or belaying-pin (from its swelling form):--tache.
from 7164; an ankle (as a protuberance or joint):--foot.
a primitive root; to rend, literally or figuratively (revile, paint the eyes, as if enlarging them):--cut out, rend, X surely, tear.
from 7167; a rag:--piece, rag.

a primitive root; to pinch, i.e. (partially) to bite the lips, blink the eyes (as a gesture of malice), or (fully) to squeeze off (a piece of clay in order to mould a vessel from it):--form, move, wink.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7171 in the sense of a bit (to "eat the morsels of" any one, i.e. chew him up (figuratively) by slander):--+ accuse.
from 7169; extirpation (as if by constriction):--destruction.
from 7167; floor (as if a pavement of pieces or tesseroe), of a building or the sea:--bottom, (X one side of the) floor.
the same as 7172; ground-floor; Karka (with the article prefix), a place in Palestine:--Karkaa.
from 6979; foundation; Karkor, a place East of the Jordan:--Karkor.
from an unused root meaning to split off; a slab or plank; by implication, a deck of a ship:--bench, board.
from 7136 in the sense of building; a city:--city.
from 7176; city; Kartah, a place in Palestine:--Kartah.
from 7176; city-plot; Kartan, a place in Palestine:--Kartan.
from 7197; straw (as dry):--stubble.
from an unused root (meaning to be hard); a cucumber (from the difficulty of digestion):--cucumber.
a primitive root; to prick up the ears, i.e. hearken:--attend, (cause to) hear(-ken), give heed, incline, mark (well), regard.
from 7181; a hearkening:--X diligently, hearing, much heed, that regarded.
or qashshub {kash-shoob'}; from 7181; hearkening:--attent(-ive).
or qasvah {kas-vaw'}; from an unused root meaning to be round; a jug (from its shape):--cover, cup.

a primitive root; properly, to be dense, i.e. tough or severe (in various applications):--be cruel, be fiercer, make grievous, be ((ask a), be in, have, seem, would) hard(-en, (labour), -ly, thing), be sore, (be, make) stiff(-en, (-necked)).

from 7185; severe (in various applications):--churlish, cruel, grievous, hard((-hearted), thing), heavy, + impudent, obstinate, prevailed, rough(-ly), sore, sorrowful, stiff((necked)), stubborn, + in trouble.
(Aramaic) or qshot (Aramaic) {kesh-ote'}; corresponding to 7189; fidelity:--truth.
a primitive root; to be (causatively, make) unfeeling:--harden.
or qosht {kosht}; from an unused root meaning to balance; equity (as evenly weighed), i.e. reality:--truth.
from 7185; obstinacy:--stubbornness.
from 7190; hard ground; Kishjon, a place in Palestine:--Kishion, Keshon.
from an unused root (probably meaning to weigh out); an ingot (as definitely estimated and stamped for a coin):--piece of money (silver).
by reduplication from an unused root meaning to shale off as bark; a scale (of a fish); hence a coat of mail (as composed of or covered with jointed plates of metal):--mail, scale.
a primitive root: to tie, physically (gird, confine, compact) or mentally (in love, league):--bind (up), (make a) conspire(-acy, -ator), join together, knit, stronger, work (treason).
from 7194; an (unlawful) alliance:--confederacy, conspiracy, treason.
from 7194; an (ornamental) girdle (for women):--attire, headband.
a primitive root; to become sapless through drought; used only as denominative from 7179; to forage for straw, stubble or wood; figuratively, to assemble:--gather (selves) (together).
from 7185 in the original sense (of 6983) of bending: a bow, for shooting (hence, figuratively, strength) or the iris:--X arch(-er), + arrow, bow((-man, -shot)).
intensive (as denominative) from 7198; a bowman:--X archer.

a primitive root; to see, literally or figuratively (in numerous applications, direct and implied, transitive, intransitive and causative):--advise self, appear, approve, behold, X certainly, consider, discern, (make to) enjoy, have experience, gaze, take heed, X indeed, X joyfully, lo, look (on, one another, one on another, one upon another, out, up, upon), mark, meet, X be near, perceive, present, provide, regard, (have) respect, (fore-, cause to, let) see(-r, -m, one another), shew (self), X sight of others, (e-)spy, stare, X surely, X think, view, visions.
from 7200; a bird of prey (probably the vulture, from its sharp sight):--glede. Compare 1676.
from 7200; seeing, i.e. experiencing:--see.
active participle of 7200; a seer (as often rendered); but also (abstractly) a vision:--vision.
for 7203; prophet; Roeh, an Israelite:--Haroeh (including the article).
from the imperative of 7200 and 1121; see ye a son; Reuben, a son of Jacob:--Reuben.
patronymic from 7205; a Reubenite or descendant of Reuben:--children of Reuben, Reubenites.
from 7200; sight, i.e. satisfaction:--behold.
feminine passive participle of 7213; raised; Reumah, a Syrian woman:--Reumah.
from 7200; a mirror (as seen):--looking glass.
from 7200; sight, whether abstractly (vision) or concretely (a spectacle):--gazingstock, look to, (that) see(-th).
from 7200 and 3050; Jah has seen; Reajah, the name of three Israelites:--Reaia, Reaiah.
from 7200; sight:--beholding.
a primitive root; to rise:--be lifted up.
or rieym {reh-ame'}; or reym {rame}; or rem {rame}; from 7213; a wild bull (from its conspicuousness):--unicorn.
from 7213; something high in value, i.e. perhaps coral:--coral.
or Ramoth {raw-moth'}; plural of 7215; heights; Ramoth, the name of two places in Palestine:--Ramoth.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7218; the head; figuratively, the sum:--chief, head, sum.

from an unused root apparently meaning to shake; the head (as most easily shaken), whether literal or figurative (in many applications, of place, time, rank, itc.):--band, beginning, captain, chapiter, chief(-est place, man, things), company, end, X every (man), excellent, first, forefront, ((be-))head, height, (on) high(-est part, (priest)), X lead, X poor, principal, ruler, sum, top.
or rowsh (Deut. 32:32) {roshe}; apparently the same as 7218; a poisonous plant, probably the poppy (from its conspicuous head); generally poison (even of serpents):--gall, hemlock, poison, venom.
probably the same as 7218; Rosh, the name of an Israelite and of a foreign nation:--Rosh.
from the same as 7218; a beginning:--beginning.
feminine of 7218; the head:--head(-stone).

or riishon {ree-shone'}; from 7221; first, in place, time or rank (as adjective or noun):--ancestor, (that were) before(-time), beginning, eldest, first, fore(-father) (-most), former (thing), of old time, past.
from 7223; first:--first.
from the same as 7218; the first, in place, time, order or rank (specifically, a firstfruit):--beginning, chief(-est), first(-fruits, part, time), principal thing.
from 7218; a pillow (being for the head):--bolster.

by contracted from 7231; abundant (in quantity, size, age, number, rank, quality):--(in) abound(-undance, -ant, -antly), captain, elder, enough, exceedingly, full, great(-ly, man, one), increase, long (enough, (time)), (do, have) many(-ifold, things, a time), ((ship-))master, mighty, more, (too, very) much, multiply(-tude), officer, often(-times), plenteous, populous, prince, process (of time), suffice(-lent).
by contraction from 7232; an archer (or perhaps the same as 7227):--archer.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7227:--captain, chief, great, lord, master, stout.

from 7231; abundance (in any respect):--abundance(- antly), all, X common (sort), excellent, great(-ly, -ness, number), huge, be increased, long, many, more in number, most, much, multitude, plenty(-ifully), X very (age).

a primitive root; properly, to cast together (compare 7241), i.e. increase, especially in number; also (as denominative from 7233) to multiply by the myriad:--increase, be many(-ifold), be more, multiply, ten thousands.
a primitive root (rather identical with 7231 through the idea of projection); to shoot an arrow:--shoot.
from 7231; abundance (in number), i.e. (specifically) a myriad (whether definite or indefinite):--many, million, X multiply, ten thousand.
a primitive root; to spread:--deck.

a primitive root; to increase (in whatever respect):--(bring in) abundance (X -antly), + archer (by mistake for 7232), be in authority, bring up, X continue, enlarge, excel, exceeding(-ly), be full of, (be, make) great(-er, -ly, X -ness), grow up, heap, increase, be long, (be, give, have, make, use) many (a time), (any, be, give, give the, have) more (in number), (ask, be, be so, gather, over, take, yield) much (greater, more), (make to) multiply, nourish, plenty(-eous), X process (of time), sore, store, thoroughly, very.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7235:--make a great man, grow.
feminine of 7227; great; Rabbah, the name of two places in Palestine, East and West:--Rabbah, Rabbath.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to 7235; increase (of dignity):--greatness, majesty.
from 7231; or ribbow {rib-bo'} from 7231; a myriad, i.e. indefinitely, large number:--great things, ten ((eight)-een, (for)-ty, + sixscore, + threescore, X twenty, (twen)-ty) thousand.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7239:--X ten thousand times ten thousand.
from 7231; a rain (as an accumulation of drops):--shower.
from 7234; a collar (as spread around the neck):--chain.
or rbiiy {reb-ee-ee'}; from 7251; fourth; also (fractionally) a fourth:--foursquare, fourth (part).
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7243 -- fourth.
from 7231; multitude; Rabbith, a place in Palestine:--Rabbith.
a primitive root; to soak (bread in oil):--baken, (that which is) fried.
from an unused root meaning to be fruitful; fertile; Riblah, a place in Syria:--Riblah.
from 7227 and a foreign word for a Magian; chief Magian; Rab-Mag, a Bab. official:--Rab-mag.
from 7227 and a foreign word for a eunuch; chief chamberlain; Rab-Saris, a Babylonian official:--Rab-saris.
a primitive root; to squat or lie out flat, i.e. (specifically) in copulation:--let gender, lie down.

a primitive root (rather identical with 7250 through the idea of sprawling "at all fours" (or possibly the reverse is the order of deriv.); compare 702); properly, to be four (sided); used only as denominative of 7253; to be quadrate:--(four-)square(-d).
from 7250; prostration (for sleep):--lying down.
from 7251; a fourth (part or side):--fourth part, side, square.
the same as 7253; Reba, a Midianite:--Reba.
from 7251; a quarter:--fourth participle
from 7251; a descendant of the fourth generation, i.e. great great grandchild:--fourth.

a primitive root; to crouch (on all four legs folded, like a recumbent animal); be implication, to recline, repose, brood, lurk, imbed:--crouch (down), fall down, make a fold, lay, (cause to, make to) lie (down), make to rest, sit.
from 7257; a couch or place of repose:--where each lay, lie down in, resting place.
from an unused root probably meaning to clog by tying up the fetlock; fettering (by beauty); Ribkah, the wife of Isaac:-- Rebekah.
(Aramaic) from 7229; huge (in size); domineering (in character):--(very) great (things).
(Aramaic) from 7260; a magnate:--lord, prince.
from 7227 and 8248; chief butler; Rabshakeh, a Bab. official:--Rabshakeh.
from an unused root meaning to pile together; a lump of clay:--clod.
a primitive root; to quiver (with any violent emotion, especially anger or fear):--be afraid, stand in awe, disquiet, fall out, fret, move, provoke, quake, rage, shake, tremble, trouble, be wroth.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7264:--provoke unto wrath.
(Aramaic) from 7265; violent anger:--rage.
from 7264; commotion, restlessness (of a horse), crash (of thunder), disquiet, anger:--fear, noise, rage, trouble(-ing), wrath.
intensive from 7264; timid:--trembling.
feminine of 7267; trepidation:--trembling.

a primitive root; to walk along; but only in specifically, applications, to reconnoiter, to be a tale-bearer (i.e. slander); also (as denominative from 7272) to lead about:--backbite, search, slander, (e-)spy (out), teach to go, view.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7272:--foot.

from 7270; a foot (as used in walking); by implication, a step; by euphem. the pudenda:--X be able to endure, X according as, X after, X coming, X follow, ((broken-))foot((-ed, -stool)), X great toe, X haunt, X journey, leg, + piss, + possession, time.
from 7272; a footman (soldier):--(on) foot(- man).
plural of active participle of 7270; fullers (as tramping the cloth in washing); Rogelim, a place East of the Jordan:-- Rogelim.
a primitive root (compare 7263, 7321, 7551); to cast together (stones), i.e. to lapidate:--X certainly, stone.
from 7275; stoneheap; Regem, an Israelite:--Regem.
feminine of the same as 7276; a pile (of stones), i.e. (figuratively) a throng:--council.
from 7276 and 4428; king's heap; Regem-Melek, an Israelite:--Regem-melech.
a primitive root; to grumble, i.e. rebel:--murmur.

a primitive root; properly, to toss violently and suddenly (the sea with waves, the skin with boils); figuratively (in a favorable manner) to settle, i.e. quiet; specifically, to wink (from the motion of the eye-lids):--break, divide, find ease, be a moment, (cause, give, make to) rest, make suddenly.
from 7280. a wink (of the eyes), i.e. a very short space of time:--instant, moment, space, suddenly.
from 7280; restful, i.e. peaceable:--that are quiet.
a primitive root; to be tumultuous:--rage.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7283; to gather tumultuously:--assemble (together).
or (feminine) rigshah {rig-shaw'}; from 7283; a tumultuous crowd:--company, insurrection.
a primitive root; to tread in pieces, i.e. (figuratively) to conquer, or (specifically) to overlay:--spend, spread, subdue.
a primitive root; to tread down, i.e. subjugate; specifically, to crumble off:--(come to, make to) have dominion, prevail against, reign, (bear, make to) rule,(-r, over), take.
intensive from 7287; domineering; Raddai, an Israelite:--Raddai.
from 7286 in the sense of spreading; a veil (as expanded):--vail, veil.
a primitive root; to stun, i.e. stupefy (with sleep or death):--(be fast a-, be in a deep, cast into a dead, that) sleep(-er, -eth).
a primitive root; to run after (usually with hostile intent; figuratively (of time) gone by):--chase, put to flight, follow (after, on), hunt, (be under) persecute(-ion, -or), pursue(-r).
a primitive root; to urge severely, i.e. (figuratively) importune, embolden, capture, act insolently:--overcome, behave self proudly, make sure, strengthen.
from 7292, bluster(-er):--proud, strength.
the same as 7293; Rahab (i.e. boaster), an epithet of Egypt:--Rahab.
from 7292; insolent:--proud.
from 7292; pride:--strength.
a primitive root; to fear:--be afraid.
from an unused root apparently meaning to hollow out; a channel or watering-box; by resemblance a ringlet of hair (as forming parallel lines):--gallery, gutter, trough.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to 7200; aspect:--form.
a primitive root; to tramp about, i.e. ramble (free or disconsolate):--have the dominion, be lord, mourn, rule.
a primitive root; to slake the thirst (occasionally of other appetites):--bathe, make drunk, (take the) fill, satiate, (abundantly) satisfy, soak, water (abundantly).
from 7301; sated (with drink):--drunkenness, watered.
from an unused root probably meaning to cry out; outcry; Rohagah, an Israelite:--Rohgah.
a primitive root (identical with 7306); properly, to breathe freely, i.e. revive; by implication, to have ample room:--be refreshed, large.
from 7304; room, literally (an interval) or figuratively (deliverance):--enlargement, space.
a primitive root; properly, to blow, i.e. breathe; only (literally) to smell or (by implication, perceive (figuratively, to anticipate, enjoy):--accept, smell, X touch, make of quick understanding.

from 7306; wind; by resemblance breath, i.e. a sensible (or even violent) exhalation; figuratively, life, anger, unsubstantiality; by extension, a region of the sky; by resemblance spirit, but only of a rational being (including its expression and functions):--air, anger, blast, breath, X cool, courage, mind, X quarter, X side, spirit((-ual)), tempest, X vain, ((whirl-))wind(-y).
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7307:--mind, spirit, wind.
feminine of 7305; relief:--breathing, respite.
from 7301; satisfaction:--runneth over, wealthy.

a primitive root; to be high actively, to rise or raise (in various applications, literally or figuratively):--bring up, exalt (self), extol, give, go up, haughty, heave (up), (be, lift up on, make on, set up on, too) high(-er, one), hold up, levy, lift(-er) up, (be) lofty, (X a-)loud, mount up, offer (up), + presumptuously, (be) promote(-ion), proud, set up, tall(-er), take (away, off, up), breed worms.
or rum {room}; from 7311; (literally) elevation or (figuratively) elation:--haughtiness, height, X high.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7311; (figuratively only):-- extol, lift up (self), set up.
(Aramaic) from 7313; (literally) altitude:--height.
from 7311; elevation, i.e. (adverbially) aloft:--on high.
from 7311; height; Rumah, a place in Palestine:--Rumah.
feminine of 7315; elation, i.e. (adverbially) proudly:--haughtily.
from 7426; exaltation, i.e. (figuratively and specifically) praise:--be extolled.
feminine active participle of 7426; exaltation, i.e. praise:--high.
(or Romam from 7311 and 5828; I have raised up a help; Romamti-Ezer, an Israelite:--Romamti- ezer.

a primitive root; to mar (especially by breaking); figuratively, to split the ears (with sound), i.e. shout (for alarm or joy):--blow an alarm, cry (alarm, aloud, out), destroy, make a joyful noise, smart, shout (for joy), sound an alarm, triumph.
a primitive root; properly, to triturate (in a mortar), i.e. (figuratively) to agitate (by concussion):--tremble.
a primitive root; to run (for whatever reason, especially to rush):--break down, divide speedily, footman, guard, bring hastily, (make) run (away, through), post.
a primitive root; to pour out (literally or figuratively), i.e. empty:--X arm, cast out, draw (out), (make) empty, pour forth (out).
a primitive root; to slaver (with spittle), i.e. (by analogy) to emit a fluid (ulcerous or natural):--run.
a primitive root; to be destitute:--lack, needy, (make self) poor (man).
probably for 7468; friend; Ruth, a Moabitess:--Ruth.
(Aramaic) from an unused root probably meaning to attenuate, i.e. (figuratively) hide; a mystery:--secret.
a primitive root; to emaciate, i.e. make (become) thin (literally or figuratively):--famish, wax lean.
from 7329; thin:--lean.
from 7336; prince; Rezon, a Syrian:--Rezon.
from 7329; thinness:--leanness, X scant.
from 7336; a dignitary:--prince.
from 7329; thinness:--leanness.
a primitive root; to twinkle the eye (in mockery): wink.
a primitive root; probably to be heavy, i.e. (figuratively) honorable:--prince, ruler.
a primitive root; to broaden (intransitive or transitive, literal or figurative):--be an en-(make) large(-ing), make room, make (open) wide.
from 7337; a width:--breadth, broad place.
or rchowb {rekh-obe'}; from 7337; a width, i.e. (concretely) avenue or area:--broad place (way), street. See also 1050.
or Rchowb {rekh-obe'}; the same as 7339; Rechob, the name of a place in Syria, also of a Syrian and an Israelite:--Rehob.
from 7337; width (literally or figuratively):--breadth, broad, largeness, thickness, wideness.
from 7337; roomy, in any (or every) direction, literally or figuratively:--broad, large, at liberty, proud, wide.
the same as 7342; proud; Rachab, a Canaanitess:--Rahab.
or Rchoboth {rekh-o-both'}; plural of 7339; streets; Rechoboth, a place in Assyria and one in Palestine:-- Rehoboth.
or Rchabyahuw {rek-ab-yaw'-hoo}; from 7337 and 3050; Jah has enlarged; Rechabjah, an Israelite:--Rehabiah.
from 7337 and 5971; a people has enlarged; Rechabam, an Israelite king:--Rehoboam.
from an unused root meaning to pulverize; a mill-stone:--mill (stone).
a form of 7349; Rechum, the name of a Persian and of three Israelites:--Rehum.
from 7355; compassionate:--full of compassion, merciful.

or rachoq {raw-khoke'}; from 7368; remote, literally or figuratively, of place or time; specifically, precious; often used adverbially (with preposition):--(a-)far (abroad, off), long ago, of old, space, great while to come.
from the same as 7298; a panel (as resembling a trough):--rafter.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7350:--far.
from an unused root meaning to journey; a ewe (the females being the predominant element of a flock) (as a good traveller):--ewe, sheep.
the same as 7353; Rachel, a wife of Jacob:--Rachel.

a primitive root; to fondle; by implication, to love, especially to compassionate:--have compassion (on, upon), love, (find, have, obtain, shew) mercy(-iful, on, upon), (have) pity, Ruhamah, X surely.
from 7355; compassion (in the plural); by extension, the womb (as cherishing the fetus); by implication, a maiden:-- bowels, compassion, damsel, tender love, (great, tender) mercy, pity, womb.
the same as 7356; pity; Racham, an Israelite:--Raham.
