from 7355; the womb (compare 7356):--matrix, womb.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7356; (plural) pity:--mercy.
or (feminine) rachamah {raw-khaw-maw'}; from 7355; a kind of vulture (supposed to be tender towards its young):--gier- eagle.
feminine of 7356; a maiden:--damsel.
from 7355; compassionate:--pitiful.
a primitive root; to brood; by implication, to be relaxed:--flutter, move, shake.
a primitive root; to lave (the whole or a part of a thing):--bathe (self), wash (self).
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7364 (probably through the accessory idea of ministering as a servant at the bath); to attend upon:--trust.
from 7364; a bath:--wash(-pot).
feminine of 7366; a bathing place:--washing.

a primitive root; to widen (in any direction), i.e. (intransitively) recede or (transitively) remove (literally or figuratively, of place or relation):--(a-, be, cast, drive, get, go, keep (self), put, remove, be too, (wander), withdraw) far (away, off), loose, X refrain, very, (be) a good way (off).
from 7368; remote:--that are far.
a primitive root; to gush:--indite.
from 7306; a winnowing-fork (as blowing the chaff away):--shovel.
a primitive root; to be moist:--be wet.
from 7372; moist (with sap):--green.
from an unused root meaning to tremble; terror:--fear.
a root compounded from 7373 and 2954; to be rejuvenated:--be fresh.
a primitive root; to dash down:--dash (in pieces).
from 7301; irrigation, i.e. a shower:--watering.

or ruwb {roob}; a primitive root; properly, to toss, i.e. grapple; mostly figuratively, to wrangle, i.e. hold a controversy; (by implication) to defend:--adversary, chide, complain, contend, debate, X ever, X lay wait, plead, rebuke, strive, X thoroughly.
or rib {reeb}; from 7378; a contest (personal or legal):--+ adversary, cause, chiding, contend(-tion), controversy, multitude (from the margin), pleading, strife, strive(-ing), suit.
from 7378; contentious; Ribai, an Israelite:--Ribai.
from 7306; odor (as if blown):--savour, scent, smell.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7381:--smell.
or riphah {ree-faw'}; from 7322; (only plural), grits (as pounded):--ground corn, wheat.
or (probably by orthographical error) Diyphath {dee-fath'}; of foreign origin; Riphath, a grandson of Japheth and his descendants:--Riphath.
from 7324; emptiness; figuratively, a worthless thing; adverbially, in vain:--empty, to no purpose, (in) vain (thing), vanity.
or (shorter) req {rake}; from 7324; empty; figuratively, worthless:--emptied(-ty), vain (fellow, man).
from 7386; emptily; figuratively (objective) ineffectually, (subjective) undeservedly:--without cause, empty, in vain, void.
from 7325; saliva; by resemblance, broth:--spittle, white (of an egg).
or resh {raysh}; or riysh {reesh}; from 7326; poverty:--poverty.
from 7401; tender (literally or figuratively); by implication, weak:--faint((-hearted), soft, tender ((-hearted), one), weak.
from 7401; softness (figuratively):--tenderness.

a primitive root; to ride (on an animal or in a vehicle); causatively, to place upon (for riding or generally), to despatch:--bring (on (horse-)back), carry, get (oneself) up, on (horse-)back, put, (cause to, make to) ride (in a chariot, on, -r), set.
from 7392; a vehicle; by implication, a team; by extension, cavalry; by analogy a rider, i.e. the upper millstone:--chariot, (upper) millstone, multitude (from the margin), wagon.
from 7392; rider; Rekab, the name of two Arabs and of two Israelites:--Rechab.
from 7392; a charioteer:--chariot man, driver of a chariot, horseman.
feminine of 7393; a chariot (collectively):--chariots.
probably feminine from 7401; softness; Rekah, a place in Palestine:--Rechah.
from passive participle of 7392; a vehicle (as ridden on):--chariot.
or rkush {rek-oosh'}; from passive participle of 7408; property (as gathered):--good, riches, substance.
from 7402 a scandal-monger (as travelling about):--slander, carry tales, talebearer.
a primitive root; to soften (intransitively or transitively), used figuratively:--(be) faint((-hearted)), mollify, (be, make) soft(-er), be tender.
a primitive root; to travel for trading:--(spice) merchant.
from 7402; merchant; Rakal, a place in Palestine:--Rachal.
feminine passive participle of 7402; trade (as peddled):--merchandise, traffic.
a primitive root; to tie:--bind.
from 7405; a mountain ridge (as of tied summits):--rough place.
from 7405; a snare (as of tied meshes):--pride.
a primitive root; to lay up, i.e. collect:--gather, get.
from 7408; a relay of animals on a post-route (as stored up for that purpose); by implication, a courser:--dromedary, mule, swift beast.
active participle of 7311; high; Ram, the name of an Arabian and of an Israelite:--Ram. See also 1027.
a primitive root; to hurl; specifically, to shoot; figuratively, to delude or betray (as if causing to fall):--beguile, betray, (bow-)man, carry, deceive, throw.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7411; to throw, set, (figuratively) assess:--cast (down), impose.
feminine active participle of 7311; a height (as a seat of idolatry):--high place.
the same as 7413; Ramah, the name of four places in Palestine:--Ramah.
from 7426 in the sense of breading (compare 7311); a maggot (as rapidly bred), literally or figuratively:--worm.
or rimmon {rim-mone'}; from 7426; a pomegranate, the tree (from its upright growth) or the fruit (also an artificial ornament):--pomegranate.

or (shorter) Rimmon {rim-mone'}; or Rimmownow (1 Chronicles 6:62 (77)) {rim-mo-no'}; the same as 7416; Rimmon, the name of a Syrian deity, also of five places in Palestine:--Remmon, Rimmon. The addition "-methoar" (Josh. 19:13) is ham-mthonar {ham-meth-o-awr'}; passive participle of 8388 with the article; the (one) marked off, i.e. which pertains; mistaken for part of the name.

or Ramath Negeb {raw'-math neh'-gheb}; from the plural or construct form of 7413 and 5045; heights (or height) of the South; Ramoth-Negeb or Ramath-Negeb, a place in Palestine:--south Ramoth, Ramath of the south.
from 7311; a heap (of carcases):--height.
from an unused root meaning to hurl; a lance (as thrown); especially the iron point:--buckler, javelin, lancet, spear.
for 761; a Ramite, i.e. Aramaean:--Syrian.
from 7311 and 3050; Jah has raised; Ramjah, an Israelite:--Ramiah.
from 7411; remissness, treachery:--deceit(- ful, -fully), false, guile, idle, slack, slothful.
of foreign origin; a brood mare:--dromedary.
from an unused root and 3050 (perhaps meaning to deck); Jah has bedecked; Remaljah, an Israelite:--Remaliah.
a primitive root; to rise (literally or figuratively):--exalt, get (oneself) up, lift up (self), mount up.
from the active participle of 7426; exaltation:--lifting up of self.
from 7416 and 6556; pomegranate of the breach; Rimmon-Perets, a place in the Desert:--Rimmon-parez.
a primitive root; to tread upon (as a potter, in walking or abusively):--oppressor, stamp upon, trample (under feet), tread (down, upon).
a primitive root; properly, to glide swiftly, i.e. to crawl or move with short steps; by analogy to swarm:--creep, move.
from 7430; a reptile or any other rapidly moving animal:--that creepeth, creeping (moving) thing.
from 7411; height; Remeth, a place in Palestine:--Remeth.

or Ramoth Giliad (2 Chronicles 22:5) {raw-moth' gil-awd'}; from the plural of 7413 and 1568; heights of Gilad; Ramoth-Gilad, a place East of the Jordan:--Ramoth-gilead, Ramoth in Gilead. See also 7216.
from 7413 and 4707 with the article interpolated; height of the watch-tower; Ramath-ham- Mitspeh, a place in Palestine:--Ramath-mizpeh.
patronymic of 7414; a Ramathite or inhabitant of Ramah:--Ramathite.
from the dual of 7413 and the plural of the active participle of 6822; double height of watchers; Ramathajim-Tsophim, a place in Palestine:--Ramathaimzophim.
from 7413 and 3895; height of a jaw-bone; Ramath-Lechi, a place in Palestine:--Ramath-lehi.
from 7442; a shout (of deliverance):--song.
a primitive root; to whiz:--rattle.
from 7442; properly, a creaking (or shrill sound), i.e. shout (of joy or grief):--cry, gladness, joy, proclamation, rejoicing, shouting, sing(-ing), triumph.
the same as 7440; Rinnah, an Israelite:--Rinnah.

a primitive root; properly, to creak (or emit a stridulous sound), i.e. to shout (usually for joy):--aloud for joy, cry out, be joyful (greatly, make to) rejoice, (cause to) shout (for joy), (cause to) sing (aloud, for joy, out), triumph.
from 7442; an ostrich (from its wail):--X goodly.
intensive from 7442; shouting (for joy):--singing.
from 7442; a shout (for joy):--joyful (voice), singing, triumphing.
from 7450; a ruin (as dripping to pieces); Rissah, a place in the Desert:--Rissah.
from 7450; properly, dripping to pieces, i.e. a ruin; also a dew-drop:--breach, drop.
from an unused root meaning to curb; a halter (as restraining); by implication, the jaw:--bridle.
the same as 7448; Resen, a place in Assyrian:--Resen.
a primitive root; to comminute; used only as denominative from 7447, to moisten (with drops):--temper.

from 7489; bad or (as noun) evil (natural or moral):-- adversity, affliction, bad, calamity, + displease(-ure), distress, evil((- favouredness), man, thing), + exceedingly, X great, grief(-vous), harm, heavy, hurt(-ful), ill (favoured), + mark, mischief(-vous), misery, naught(-ty), noisome, + not please, sad(-ly), sore, sorrow, trouble, vex, wicked(-ly, -ness, one), worse(-st), wretchedness, wrong. (Incl. feminine raaah; as adjective or noun.).
from 7321; a crash (of thunder), noise (of war), shout (of joy):--X aloud, noise, shouted.
or reya2 {ray'-ah}; from 7462; an associate (more or less close):--brother, companion, fellow, friend, husband, lover, neighbour, X (an-)other.
from 7462; a thought (as association of ideas):--thought.
from 7489; badness (as marring), physically or morally:--X be so bad, badness, (X be so) evil, naughtiness, sadness, sorrow, wickedness.
a primitive root; to hunger:--(suffer to) famish, (be, have, suffer, suffer to) hunger(-ry).
from 7456; hungry (more or less intensely):--hunger bitten, hungry.
from 7456; hunger (more or less extensive):--dearth, famine, + famished, hunger.
from 7456; famine:--famine.
a primitive root: to shudder (more or less violently):--tremble.
or (feminine) radah {reh-aw-daw'}; from 7460; a shudder:--trembling.

a primitive root; to tend a flock; i.e. pasture it; intransitively, to graze (literally or figuratively); generally to rule; by extension, to associate with (as a friend):--X break, companion, keep company with, devour, eat up, evil entreat, feed, use as a friend, make friendship with, herdman, keep (sheep)(-er), pastor, + shearing house, shepherd, wander, waste.
from 7462; a (male) companion:--friend.
feminine of 7453; a female associate:--companion, fellow.
for 7455; breakage:--broken, utterly.
for 7471 in the sense of 7453; friend; Reu, a postdiluvian patriarch:--Reu.
from the same as 7466 and 410; friend of God; Reuel, the name of Moses' father-in-law, also of an Edomite and an Israelite:--Raguel, Reuel.
from 7462 in the sense of 7453; a female associate; generally an additional one:--+ another, mate, neighbour.
probably from 7462; a feeding upon, i.e. grasping after:--vexation.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7469; desire:--pleasure, will.
from 7462; pasture:--pasture.
from 7453; social; Rei, an Israelite:--Rei.
from active participle of 7462; pastoral; as noun, a shepherd:--shipherd.
feminine of 7453; a female associate:--fellow, love.
from 7462 in the sense of 7469; desire:--vexation.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7475; a grasp. i.e. (figuratively) mental conception:--cogitation, thought.
a primitive root; to reel, i.e. (figuratively) to brandish:--terribly shake.
from 7477; a reeling (from intoxication):--trembling.
feminine of 7478; a long veil (as fluttering):--muffler.
from 7477 and 3050; made to tremble (i.e. fearful) of Jah; Reelajah, an Israelite:--Reeliah.
a primitive root; to tumble, i.e. be violently agitated; specifically, to crash (of thunder); figuratively, to irritate (with anger):--make to fret, roar, thunder, trouble.
from 7481; a peal of thunder:--thunder.
feminine of 7482; the mane of a horse (as quivering in the wind):--thunder.
the same as 7483; Ramah, the name of a grandson of Ham, and of a place (perhaps founded by him):--Raamah.
from 7481 and 3050; Jah has shaken; Raamjah, an Israelite:--Raamiah.
or Raamcec {rah-am-sace'}; of Egyptian origin; Rameses or Raamses, a place in Egypt:--Raamses, Rameses.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7488; green, i.e. (figuratively) prosperous; --flourishing.
from an unused root meaning to be green; verdant; by analogy, new; figuratively, prosperous:--green, flourishing.

a primitive root; properly, to spoil (literally, by breaking to pieces); figuratively, to make (or be) good for nothing, i.e. bad (physically, socially or morally):--afflict, associate selves (by mistake for 7462), break (down, in pieces), + displease, (be, bring, do) evil (doer, entreat, man), show self friendly (by mistake for 7462), do harm, (do) hurt, (behave self, deal) ill, X indeed, do mischief, punish, still, vex, (do) wicked (doer, -ly), be (deal, do) worse.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7489:--break, bruise.
a primitive root; to drip:--distil, drop (down).
a primitive root; to break in pieces; figuratively, harass:--dash in pieces, vex.

a primitive root; to undulate (as the earth, the sky, etc.; also a field of grain), partic. through fear; specifically, to spring (as a locust):--make afraid, (re-)move, quake, (make to) shake, (make to) tremble.
from 7493; vibration, bounding, uproar:--commotion, confused noise, earthquake, fierceness, quaking, rattling, rushing, shaking.
or raphah {raw-faw'}; a primitive root; properly, to mend (by stitching), i.e. (figuratively) to cure:--cure, (cause to) heal, physician, repair, X thoroughly, make whole. See 7503.
from 7495 in the sense of 7503; properly, lax, i.e. (figuratively) a ghost (as dead; in plural only):--dead, deceased.
or raphah {raw-faw'}; from 7495 in the sense of invigorating; a giant:--giant, Rapha, Rephaim(-s). See also 1051.
or Raphah {raw-faw'}; probably the same as 7497; giant; Rapha or Raphah, the name of two Israelites:--Rapha.
feminine passive participle of 7495; a medicament:--heal(-ed), medicine.
from 7495; a cure:--health.
from 7495 and 410; God has cured; Rephael, an Israelite:--Rephael.
a primitive root; to spread (a bed); by implication, to refresh:--comfort, make (a bed), spread.

a primitive root; to slacken (in many applications, literal or figurative):--abate, cease, consume, draw (toward evening), fail, (be) faint, be (wax) feeble, forsake, idle, leave, let alone (go, down), (be) slack, stay, be still, be slothful, (be) weak(-en). See 7495.
from 7503; slack (in body or mind):--weak. raphah, Raphah. See 7497, 7498. riphah. See 7383.
passive participle of 7495; cured; Raphu, an Israelite:--Raphu.
from an unused root apparently meaning to sustain; support; Rephach, an Israelite:--Rephah.
from 7502; a railing (as spread along):--bottom.
plural of the masculine of the same as 7507; ballusters; Rephidim, a place in the Desert:--Rephidim.
from 7495 and 3050; Jah has cured; Rephajah, the name of five Israelites:--Rephaiah.
from 7503; slackness:--feebleness.
a primitive root; to trample, i.e. prostrate:--humble self, submit self.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7511:--stamp.
from 7511; a raft (as flat on the water):--flote.
a primitive root; to recline:--lean.
a primitive root; to trample, i.e. roil water:--foul, trouble.
from 7515; mud (as roiled):--mire.
probably from 7503; a stall for cattle (from their resting there):--stall.
contracted from 7533; a fragment:--piece.
a primitive root; to run; also to delight in:--accept, run.
a primitive root; probably to look askant, i.e. (figuratively) be jealous:--leap.

a primitive root; to be pleased with; specifically, to satisfy a debt:--(be) accept(-able), accomplish, set affection, approve, consent with, delight (self), enjoy, (be, have a) favour(-able), like, observe, pardon, (be, have, take) please(-ure), reconcile self.
or ratson {raw-tsone'}; from 7521; delight (especially as shown):--(be) acceptable(-ance, -ed), delight, desire, favour, (good) pleasure, (own, self, voluntary) will, as...(what) would.
a primitive root; properly, to dash in pieces, i.e. kill (a human being), especially to murder:--put to death, kill, (man-)slay(-er), murder(-er).
from 7523; a crushing; specifically, a murder-cry:--slaughter, sword.
from 7521; delight; Ritsjah, an Israelite:--Rezia.
probably for 7522; Retsin, the name of a Syrian and of an Israelite:--Rezin.
a primitive root; to pierce:--bore.
a denominative from 7529; to tessellate, i.e. embroider (as if with bright stones):--pave.
for 7565; a red-hot stone (for baking):--coal.
the same as 7529; Retseph, a place in Assyrian:--Rezeph.
feminine of 7529; a hot stone; also a tessellated pavement:--live coal, pavement.
the same as 7531; Ritspah, an Israelitess:--Rizpah.
a primitive root; to crack in pieces, literally or figuratively:--break, bruise, crush, discourage, oppress, struggle together.
from 7556 in its original sense; emaciated (as if flattened out):--lean((-fleshed)), thin.

the same as 7534 as a noun; properly, leanness, i.e. (figuratively) limitation; only adverbial, merely, or conjunctional, although:--but, even, except, howbeit howsoever, at the least, nevertheless, nothing but, notwithstanding, only, save, so (that), surely, yet (so), in any wise.
from 7556; spittle:--spit(-ting, -tle).
a primitive root; to decay (as by worm-eating):--rot.
from 7537; decay (by caries):--rottenness (thing).
from 7538; decay (by caries):--rotten.
a primitive root; properly, to stamp, i.e. to spring about (wildly or for joy):--dance, jump, leap, skip.
feminine of 7534; properly, thinness, i.e. the side of the head:--temple.
from 7534; thinness; Rakkon, a place in Palestine:--Rakkon.
a primitive root; to perfume:--apothecary, compound, make (ointment), prepare, spice.
from 7543; properly, perfumery, i.e. (by implication) spicery (for flavor):--spiced.
from 7542; an aromatic:--confection, ointment.
from 7543; a male perfumer:--apothecary.
from 7543; a scented substance:--perfume.
feminine of 7547; a female perfumer:--confectioner.
from 7554; properly, an expanse, i.e. the firmament or (apparently) visible arch of the sky:--firmament.
from, 7556 in its original sense; a thin cake; -- cake, wafer.
a primitive root; to variegate color, i.e. embroider; by implication, to fabricate:--embroiderer, needlework, curiously work.
from 7551; versi-color; Rekem, the name of a place in Palestine, also of a Midianite and an Israelite:--Rekem.
from 7551; variegation of color; specifically, embroidery:--broidered (work), divers colours, (raiment of) needlework (on both sides).

a primitive root; to pound the earth (as a sign of passion); by analogy to expand (by hammering); by implication, to overlay (with thin sheets of metal):--beat, make broad, spread abroad (forth, over, out, into plates), stamp, stretch.
from 7554; beaten out, i.e. a (metallic) plate:--broad.
a primitive root; to spit:--spit.
from 7556 in its original sense of diffusing; a beach (as expanded shingle); Rakkath, a place in Palestine:--Rakkath.
from an unused root meaning to have leave; a permit:--grant.
a primitive root; to record:--note.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7559:--sign, write.
a primitive root; to be (causatively, do or declare) wrong; by implication, to disturb, violate:--condemn, make trouble, vex, be (commit, deal, depart, do) wicked(-ly, -ness).
from 7561; a wrong (especially moral):--iniquity, wicked(-ness).
from 7561; morally wrong; concretely, an (actively) bad person:--+ condemned, guilty, ungodly, wicked (man), that did wrong.
feminine of 7562; wrong (especially moral):--fault, wickedly(-ness).
from 8313; a live coal; by analogy lightning; figuratively, an arrow, (as flashing through the air); specifically, fever:--arrow, (burning) coal, burning heat, + spark, hot thunderbolt.
the same as 7565; Resheph, an Israelite:--Resheph.
a primitive root; to demolish:--impoverish.
from 3423; a net (as catching animals):--net(- work).
from 7576; a chain:--chain.
a primitive root; to boil:--boil.
from 7570; a boiling:--X (boil) well.
from 7576; a chain:--chain.
a primitive root; to yoke up (to the pole of a vehicle):--bind.
or rothem {ro'-them}; from 7573; the Spanish broom (from its pole-like stems):--juniper (tree).
feminine of 7574; Rithmah, a place in the Desert:--Rithmah.
a primitive root; to fasten:--bind.
feminine passive participle of 7576; something fastened, i.e. a chain:--chain.
for 7374; terror:--trembling.
a primitive root; to bale up water:--(woman to) draw(-er, water).
a primitive root; to rumble or moan:--X mightily, roar.
from 7580; a rumbling or moan:--roaring.
a primitive root; to rush; by implication, to desolate:--be desolate, (make a) rush(-ing), (lay) waste.
a primitive root (identical with 7582 through the idea of whirling to giddiness); to stun, i.e. (intransitively) be astonished:--wonder.
from 7582; a tempest (as rushing):--desolation.
or shol {sheh-ole'}; from 7592; Hades or the world of the dead (as if a subterranean retreat), including its accessories and inmates:--grave, hell, pit.
passive participle of 7592; asked; Shaul, the name of an Edomite and two Israelites:--Saul, Shaul.
patronymic from 7856; a Shaulite or descendant of Shaul:--Shaulites.
from 7582; uproar (as of rushing); by implication, destruction:--X horrible, noise, pomp, rushing, tumult (X -uous).
from an unused root meaning to push aside; contempt:--despite(-ful).
for active part of 7750 (compare 7589); one contemning:--that (which) despise(-d).
from 7582; desolation:--destruction.

or shael {shaw-ale'}; a primitive root; to inquire; by implication, to request; by extension, to demand:--ask (counsel, on), beg, borrow, lay to charge, consult, demand, desire, X earnestly, enquire, + greet, obtain leave, lend, pray, request, require, + salute, X straitly, X surely, wish.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7592:--ask, demand, require.
from 7592; request; Sheal, an Israelite:--Sheal.
(Aramaic) from 7593; properly, a question (at law), i.e. judicial decision or mandate:--demand.
or shelah (1 Samuel 1:17) {shay-law'}; from 7592; a petition; by implication, a loan:--loan, petition, request.
or Shaltiy(el {shal-tee-ale'}; from 7592 and 410; I have asked God; Shealtiel, an Israelite:--Shalthiel, Shealtiel.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7597:--Shealtiel.
a primitive root; to loll, i.e. be peaceful:--be at ease, be quiet, rest. See also 1052.
from 7599; secure; in a bad sense, haughty:--that is at ease, quiet, tumult. Compare 7946.
a primitive root; to plunder:--spoil.
a primitive root; to inhale eagerly; figuratively, to cover; by implication, to be angry; also to hasten:--desire (earnestly), devour, haste, pant, snuff up, swallow up.
from 7604; barm or yeast-cake (as swelling by fermentation):--leaven.
a primitive root; properly, to swell up, i.e. be (causatively, make) redundant:--leave, (be) left, let, remain, remnant, reserve, the rest.
from 7604; a remainder:--X other, remnant, residue, rest.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7605:--X whatsoever more, residue, rest.
from 7604; flesh (as swelling out), as living or for food; generally food of any kind; figuratively, kindred by blood:-- body, flesh, food, (near) kin(-sman, -swoman), near (nigh) (of kin).
feminine of 7607; female kindred by blood:--near kinswomen.
the same as 7608; Sheerah, an Israelitess:--Sherah.
from 7605 and 7725; a remnant will return; Shear-Jashub, the symbolic name of one of Isaiah's sons:--Shear-jashub.
from 7604; a remainder or residual (surviving, final) portion:--that had escaped, be left, posterity, remain(-der), remnant, residue, rest.
from 7582; devastation:--desolation.
from 5375; an elevation or leprous scab; figuratively, elation or cheerfulness; exaltation in rank or character:-- be accepted, dignity, excellency, highness, raise up self, rising.
of foreign origin; Sheba, the name of three early progenitors of tribes and of an Ethiopian district:--Sheba, Sabeans.
patronymic from 7614; a Shebaite or descendant of Sheba:--Sabean.
from an unused root meaning to break up; a fragment, i.e. ruin:--broken in pieces.
a primitive root; to transport into captivity:--(bring away, carry, carry away, lead, lead away, take) captive(-s), drive (take) away.

from an unused root (probably identical with that of 7617 through the idea of subdivision into flashes or streamers (compare 7632) meaning to flame; a gem (from its sparkle), probably the agate:--agate.
or Shuwbanel {shoo-baw-ale'}; from 7617 (abbrev.) or 7725 and 410; captive (or returned) of God; Shebuel or Shubael, the name of two Israelites:--Shebuel, Shubael.
or shabuan {shaw-boo'-ah}; also (feminine) shbu.ah {sheb-oo-aw'}; properly, passive participle of 7650 as a denominative of 7651; literal, sevened, i.e. a week (specifically, of years):--seven, week.
feminine passive participle of 7650; properly, something sworn, i.e. an oath:--curse, oath, X sworn.
or shbiyth {sheb-eeth'}; from 7617; exile, concretely, prisoners; figuratively, a former state of prosperity:-- captive(-ity).
a primitive root; properly, to address in a loud tone, i.e. (specifically) loud; figuratively, to pacify (as if by words):--commend, glory, keep in, praise, still, triumph.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7623; to adulate, i.e. adore:--praise.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7626; a clan:--tribe.

from an unused root probably meaning to branch off; a scion, i.e. (literally) a stick (for punishing, writing, fighting, ruling, walking, etc.) or (figuratively) a clan:--X correction, dart, rod, sceptre, staff, tribe.
of foreign origin; Shebat, a Jewish month:--Sebat.
from 7618; exiled; captured; as noun, exile (abstractly or concretely and collectively); by extension, booty:--captive(-ity), prisoners, X take away, that was taken.
from 7617; captor; Shobi, an Ammonite:--Shobi.
for 7629; Shobai, an Israelite:--Shobai.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7632:--flame.
from the same as 7616; flame (as split into tongues):--spark.
feminine of 7628; exile (abstractly or concretely and collectively):--captives(-ity).
feminine of the same as 7629; captivation; Shobjah, an Israelite:--Shachia (from the margin).
from the same as 7640; a track or passage-way (as if flowing along):--path.
from an unused root meaning to interweave; a netting for the hair:--caul.
or shbi iy {sheb-ee-ee'}; ordinal from 7657; seventh:--seventh (time).
from an unused root meaning to intwine; a netting (ornament to the capital of a column):--net.
feminine of 7638; a net-work, i.e (in hunting) a snare, (in architecture) a ballustrade; also a reticulated ornament to a pillar:--checker, lattice, network, snare, wreath(-enwork).
from an unused root meaning to flow; a lady's train (as trailing after her):--leg.

or (feminine) shibboleth {shib-bo'-leth}; from the same as 7640; a stream (as flowing); also an ear of grain (as growing out); by analogy, a branch:--branch, channel, ear (of corn), ((water-))flood, Shibboleth. Compare 5451.
from the same as 7640; a snail (as if floating in its own slime):--snail.
or (feminine) Sibmah {sib-maw'}; probably from 1313; spice; Sebam or Sibmah, a place in Moab:--Shebam, Shibmah, Sibmah.
: or Shebnah {sheb-naw'}; from an unused root meaning to grow; growth; Shebna or Shebnah, an Israelite:--Shebna, Shebnah.
or Shbanyahuw {sheb-an-yaw'-hoo}; from the same as 7644 and 3050; Jah has grown (i.e. prospered); Shebanjah, the name of three or four Israelites:--Shebaniah.

or sabeay {saw-bay'-ah}; a primitive root; to sate, i.e. fill to satisfaction (literally or figuratively):--have enough, fill (full, self, with), be (to the) full (of), have plenty of, be satiate, satisfy (with), suffice, be weary of.
from 7646; copiousness:--abundance, plenteous(- ness, -ly).
from 7646; satisfaction (of food or (figuratively) joy):--fill, full(-ness), satisfying, be satisfied.
from 7646; satiated (in a pleasant or disagreeable sense):--full (of), satisfied (with).

a primitive root; propr. to be complete, but used only as a denominative from 7651; to seven oneself, i.e. swear (as if by repeating a declaration seven times):--adjure, charge (by an oath, with an oath), feed to the full (by mistake for 7646), take an oath, X straitly, (cause to, make to) swear.

or (masculine) shibrah {shib-aw'}; from 7650; a primitive cardinal number; seven (as the sacred full one); also (adverbially) seven times; by implication, a week; by extension, an indefinite number:--(+ by) seven(-fold),-s, (-teen, -teenth), -th, times). Compare 7658.
the same as 7651; seven; Sheba, the name of a place in Palestine, and of two Israelites:--Sheba.
feminine of 7647; satiety:--fulness.
feminine of 7648; satiety:--(to have) enough, X till...be full, (un-)satiable, satisfy, X sufficiently.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7651:--seven (times).
masculine of 7651; seven(-th); Shebah, a well in Palestine:--Shebah.
multiple of 7651; seventy:--seventy, threescore and ten (+ -teen).
prol. for the masculine of 7651; seven:--seven.
dual (adverbially) of 7651; seven- times:--seven(-fold, times).
a primitive root; to interweave (colored) threads in squares; by implication (of reticulation) to inchase gems in gold:--embroider, set.
from 7660; entanglement, i.e. (figuratively) perplexity:--anguish.
(Aramaic) corresponding to the root of 7733; to quit, i.e. allow to remain:--leave, let alone.
erroneously shabar (Nehemiah 2:13, 15) {shaw-bar'}; a primitive root; to scrutinize; by implication (of watching) to expect (with hope and patience):--hope, tarry, view, wait.
from 7663; expectation:--hope.

a primitive root; to burst (literally or figuratively):--break (down, off, in pieces, up), broken((-hearted)), bring to the birth, crush, destroy, hurt, quench, X quite, tear, view (by mistake for 7663).
denominative from 7668; to deal in grain:--buy, sell.

or sheber {shay'-ber}; from 7665; a fracture, figuratively, ruin; specifically, a solution (of a dream):--affliction, breach, breaking, broken(-footed, -handed), bruise, crashing, destruction, hurt, interpretation, vexation.
the same as 7667; grain (as if broken into kernels):--corn, victuals.
the same as 7667; Sheber, an Israelite:--Sheber.
from 7665; rupture, i.e. a pang; figuratively, ruin:--breaking, destruction.
plural of 7667; ruins; Shebarim, a place in Palestine:--Shebarim.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7660; to entangle, i.e. perplex:--be astonished.

a primitive root; to repose, i.e. desist from exertion; used in many implied relations (causative, figurative or specific):--(cause to, let, make to) cease, celebrate, cause (make) to fail, keep (sabbath), suffer to be lacking, leave, put away (down), (make to) rest, rid, still, take away.
from 7673; rest, interruption, cessation:--cease, sit still, loss of time.
infinitive of 3427; properly, session; but used also concretely, an abode or locality:--place, seat. Compare 3429.
intensive from 7673; intermission, i.e (specifically) the Sabbath:--(+ every) sabbath.
from 7676; a sabbatism or special holiday:--rest, sabbath.
from 7676; restful; Shabbethai, the name of three Israelites:--Shabbethai.
: a primitive root; to grow, i.e. (causatively) to enlarge, (figuratively) laud:--increase, magnify.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7679; to increase:--grow, be multiplied.
probably from 7686; erring; Shage, an Israelite:--Shage.

a primitive root; to be (causatively, make) lofty, especially inaccessible; by implication, safe, strong; used literally and figuratively --defend, exalt, be excellent, (be, set on) high, lofty, be safe, set up (on high), be too strong.
a primitive root; to stray, i.e. (figuratively) sin (with more or less apology):--X also for that, deceived, err, go astray, sin ignorantly.
from 7683; a mistake or inadvertent transgression:--error, ignorance, at unawares; unwittingly.
a primitive root; to enlarge (especially upward, also figuratively):--grow (up), increase.

a primitive root; to stray (causatively, mislead), usually (figuratively) to mistake, especially (morally) to transgress; by extension (through the idea of intoxication) to reel, (figuratively) be enraptured:--(cause to) go astray, deceive, err, be ravished, sin through ignorance, (let, make to) wander.
from 7682; aloft; Segub, the name of two Israelites:--Segub.
a primitive root; to peep, i.e. glance sharply at:--look (narrowly).
from 7679; (superlatively) mighty:--excellent, great.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7689; large (in size, quantity or number, also adverbial):--exceeding, great(-ly); many, much, sore, very.
from 7686; a moral mistake:--error.
or shiggayonah {shig-gaw-yo-naw'}; from 7686; properly, aberration, i.e. (technically) a dithyramb or rambling poem:--Shiggaion, Shigionoth.
a primitive root; to copulate with:--lie with, ravish.
from 7693; a queen (from cohabitation):--queen.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7694; a (legitimate) queen:--wife.
a primitive root; to rave through insanity:--(be, play the) mad (man).
from 7696; craziness:--furiously, madness.
from an unused root probably meaning to eject; the fetus (as finally expelled):--that cometh of, increase.
or shod {shode}; probably from 7736 (in its original sense) contracted; the breast of a woman or animal (as bulging):--breast, pap, teat.
from 7736; a doemon (as malignant):--devil.
or showd (Job 5:21) {shode}; from 7736; violence, ravage:--desolation, destruction, oppression, robbery, spoil(-ed, -er, - ing), wasting.
a primitive root; to abrade, i.e. harrow a field:--break clods, harrow.
a primitive root; properly, to be burly, i.e. (figuratively) powerful (passively, impregnable); by implication, to ravage:--dead, destroy(-er), oppress, robber, spoil(-er), X utterly, (lay) waste.
or saday {saw-dah'-ee}; from an unused root meaning to spread out; a field (as flat):--country, field, ground, land, soil, X wild.
from 7703; a wife (as mistress of the house):--X all sorts, musical instrument.
from 7703; the Almighty:--Almighty.
from the same as 7704 and 217; spreader of light; Shedejur, an Israelite:--Shedeur.
plural from the same as 7704; flats; Siddim, a valley in Palestine:--Siddim.
apparently from 7704; a cultivated field; -- blasted, field.
a primitive root; to scorch:--blast.
or shiddaphown {shid-daw-fone'}; from 7710; blight:--blasted(-ing).
(Aramaic) a primitive root; to endeavor:--labour.
from an unused root meaning to regulate; a row, i.e. rank (of soldiers), story (of rooms):--board, range.
probably of foreign origin; Shadrak, the Bab. name of one of Daniel's companions:--Shadrach.
(Aramaic) the same as 7714:--Shadrach.
or sey {say}; probably from 7582 through the idea of pushing out to graze; a member of a flock, i.e. a sheep or goat:--(lesser, small) cattle, ewe, goat, lamb, sheep. Compare 2089.
from an unused root meaning to testify; a witness:--record.
from an unused root probably mean to blanch; a gem, probably the beryl (from its pale green color):--onyx.
the same as 7718; Shoham, an Israelite:--Shoham.
from the same as 5469; a round pendant for the neck:--ornament, round tire like the moon.
from an unused root (akin to 5375 and 7722) meaning to rise; a rising:--arise.
or (feminine) showtah {sho-aw'}; or shoah {sho-aw'}; from an unused root meaning to rush over; a tempest; by implication, devastation:--desolate(-ion), destroy, destruction, storm, wasteness.

or shav {shav}; from the same as 7722 in the sense of desolating; evil (as destructive), literally (ruin) or morally (especially guile); figuratively idolatry (as false, subjective), uselessness (as deceptive, objective; also adverbially, in vain):--false(-ly), lie, lying, vain, vanity.
from the same as 7723; false; Sheva, an Israelite:--Sheva.

a primitive root; to turn back (hence, away) transitively or intransitively, literally or figuratively (not necessarily with the idea of return to the starting point); generally to retreat; often adverbial, again:--((break, build, circumcise, dig, do anything, do evil, feed, lay down, lie down, lodge, make, rejoice, send, take, weep)) X again, (cause to) answer (+ again), X in any case (wise), X at all, averse, bring (again, back, home again), call (to mind), carry again (back), cease, X certainly, come again (back), X consider, + continually, convert, deliver (again), + deny, draw back, fetch home again, X fro, get (oneself) (back) again, X give (again), go again (back, home), (go) out, hinder, let, (see) more, X needs, be past, X pay, pervert, pull in again, put (again, up again), recall, recompense, recover, refresh, relieve, render (again), requite, rescue, restore, retrieve, (cause to, make to) return, reverse, reward, + say nay, send back, set again, slide back, still, X surely, take back (off), (cause to, make to) turn (again, self again, away, back, back again, backward, from, off), withdraw.
from 7725; apostate, i.e. idolatrous:--backsliding, frowardly, turn away (from margin).
the same as 7726; rebellious; Shobab, the name of two Israelites:--Shobab.
from 7725; apostate, i.e. heathenish or (actually) heathen:--backsliding.
from 7725; a return:--returning.
for 5441; a thicket, i.e. interlaced branches:--thick boughs.
perhaps for 7730; Shobak, a Syrian:--Shobach.
from the same as 7640; overflowing; Shobal, the name of an Edomite and two Israelites:--Shobal.
active participle from a primitive root meaning to leave (compare 7662); forsaking; Shobek, an Israelite:--Shobek.
a primitive root; to retreat:--turn back.
a primitive root; to hedge in:--make to grow.
a primitive root; properly, to swell up, i.e. figuratively (by implication of insolence) to devastate:--waste.

a primitive root; properly, to level, i.e. equalize; figuratively, to resemble; by implication, to adjust (i.e. counterbalance, be suitable, compose, place, yield, etc.):--avail, behave, bring forth, compare, countervail, (be, make) equal, lay, be (make, a- )like, make plain, profit, reckon.
a primitive root; to destroy:--X substance (from the margin).
(Aramaic): corresponding to 7737; to resemble:--make like.
from 7737; plain; Shaveh, a place in Palestine:--Shaveh.
from the same as 7740 and the dual of 7151; plain of a double city; Shaveh-Kirjathajim, a place East of the Jordan:--Shaveh Kiriathaim.
a primitive root; to muse pensively:--meditate.
a primitive root; to sink, literally or figuratively:--bow down, incline, humble.
from 7743; dell; Shuach, a son of Abraham:--Shuah.
from 7743; a chasm:--ditch, pit.
the same as 7745; Shuchah, an Israelite:--Shuah.
patronymic from 7744; a Shuchite or descendant of Shuach:--Shuhite.
from 7743; humbly; Shucham, an Israelite:--Shuham.
patronymic from 7748; a Shuchamite (collectively):--Shuhamites.
or (by permutation) cuwt {soot}; a primitive root; to detrude, i.e. (intransitively and figuratively) become derelict (wrongly practise; namely, idolatry):--turn aside to.

a primitive root; properly, to push forth; (but used only figuratively) to lash, i.e. (the sea with oars) to row; by implication, to travel:--go (about, through, to and fro), mariner, rower, run to and fro.
from 7751; a lash (literally or figuratively):--scourge, whip.
a primitive root; to entwine, i.e. shut in (for formation, protection or restraint):--fence, (make an) hedge (up).
or (feminine) sowkah {so-kaw'}; from 7753; a branch (as interleaved):--bough.
or Sokoh {so-ko'}; or Sowkow {so-ko'}; from 7753; Sokoh or Soko, the name of two places in Palestine:--Shocho, Shochoh, Sochoh, Soco, Socoh.
probably patronymic from a name corresponding to 7754 (feminine); a Sukathite or descendant of an unknown Israelite named Sukah:--Suchathite.
from an unused root meaning to hang down; a skirt; by implication, a bottom edge:--hem, skirt, train.
or sheylal (Micah 1:8) {shay-lawl'}; from 7997; nude (especially bare-foot); by implication, captive:--spoiled, stripped.
from 7999; peaceful (with the article always prefixed, making it a pet name); the Shulammith, an epithet of Solomon's queen:--Shulamite.

or siym {seem}; a primitive root; to put (used in a great variety of applications, literal, figurative, inferentially, and elliptically):--X any wise, appoint, bring, call (a name), care, cast in, change, charge, commit, consider, convey, determine, + disguise, dispose, do, get, give, heap up, hold, impute, lay (down, up), leave, look, make (out), mark, + name, X on, ordain, order, + paint, place, preserve, purpose, put (on), + regard, rehearse, reward, (cause to) set (on, up), shew, + stedfastly, take, X tell, + tread down, ((over-))turn, X wholly, work.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7760:--+ command, give, lay, make, + name, + regard, set.
from an unused root meaning to exhale; garlic (from its rank odor):--garlic.
or Shomer {sho-mare'}; active participle of 8104; keeper; Shomer, the name of two Israelites:--Shomer.
from an unused root meaning to rest; quiet; Shuni, an Israelite:--Shuni.
patronymic from 7764; a Shunite (collectively) or descendants of Shuni:--Shunites.
probably from the same as 7764; quietly; Shunem, a place in Pal:--Shunem.
patrial from 7766; a Shunammitess, or female inhabitant of Shunem:--Shunamite.
a primitive root; properly, to be free; but used only causatively and reflexively, to halloo (for help, i.e. freedom from some trouble):--cry (aloud, out), shout.
from 7768; a halloo:--cry, riches.
the same as 7769; Shua, a Canaanite:--Shua, Shuah.
from 7768 in the original sense of freedom; a noble, i.e. liberal, opulent; also (as noun in the derived sense) a halloo:--bountiful, crying, rich.
the same as 7771; rich; Shoa, an Oriental people:--Shoa.
from 7768; a halloo:--cry.
from 7768; wealth; Shua, an Israelitess:--Shua.
feminine of 7773; a hallooing:--crying.
or shunal {shoo-awl'}; from the same as 8168; a jackal (as a burrower):--fox.
the same as 7776; Shual, the name of an Israelite and of a place in Palestine:--Shual.
or shomer {sho-are'}: active participle of 8176 (as denominative from 8179); a janitor:--doorkeeper, porter.
a primitive root; properly, to gape, i.e. snap at; figuratively, to overwhelm:--break, bruise, cover.
from 8210; poured; Shophak, a Syrian:--Shophach.
patronymic from 8197; a Shuphamite (collectively) or descendants of Shephupham:--Shuphamite.
or shophar {sho-far'}; from 8231 in the original sense of incising; a cornet (as giving a clear sound) or curved horn:--cornet, trumpet.
a primitive root; to run after or over, i.e. overflow:--overflow, water.
from 7783; a street (as run over):--street.
from 7783; the (lower) leg (as a runner):--hip, leg, shoulder, thigh.
a primitive root; properly, to vanquish; by implication, to rule (causatively, crown):--make princes, have power, reign. See 5493.
a primitive root (identical with 7786 through the idea of reducing to pieces; compare 4883); to saw:--cut.
a primitive root; properly, to turn, i.e. travel about (as a harlot or a merchant):--go, singular See also 7891.

a primitive root (identical with 7788 through the idea of going round for inspection); to spy out, i.e. (generally) survey, (for evil) lurk for, (for good) care for:--behold, lay wait, look, observe, perceive, regard, see.
from 7889; a foe (as lying in wait):--enemy.
from 7788; a wall (as going about):--wall.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7791:--wall.
the same as 7791; Shur, a region of the Desert:--Shur.
from 7788; a bullock (as a traveller):--bull(-ock), cow, ox, wall (by mistake for 7791).
from 7786 in the primitive sense of 5493; properly, a ring, i.e. (by analogy) a row (adverbially):--principal.
the same as 8321; a vine; Sorek, a valley in Palestine:--Sorek.
or siys {sece}; a primitive root; to be bright, i.e. cheerful:--be glad, X greatly, joy, make mirth, rejoice.
from 7797; joyful; Shavsha, an Israelite:--Shavsha.

or showshan {sho-shawn'}; or shoshan {sho- shawn'}; and (feminine) showshannah {sho-shan-naw'}; from 7797; a lily (from its whiteness), as a flower of arch. ornament; also a (straight) trumpet (from the tubular shape): lily, Shoshannim.
the same as 7799; Shushan, a place in Persia:--Shushan.
(Aramaic) of foreign origin; a Shushankite (collectively) or inhabitants of some unknown place in Assyrian:--Susanchites.

or (plural of former) Showshanniym aEduwth {sho-shan-neem' ay-dooth'}; from 7799 and 5715; lily (or trumpet) of assemblage; Shushan-Eduth or Shoshannim-Eduth, the title of a popular song:--Shoshannim-Eduth, Shushan-eduth.
probably from 7582 and the same as 8520; crash of breakage; Shuthelach, the name of two Israelites:--Shuthelah.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 5800; to leave, i.e. (causatively) free:--deliver.
a primitive root; to tan (by sun-burning); figuratively (as if by a piercing ray) to scan:--look up, see.
a primitive root; to twist (a thread of straw):--twine.
from 7817; sunk, i.e. downcast:--+ humble.
for 7879; communion, i.e. (reflexively) meditation:--thought.
a primitive root; to donate, i.e. bribe:--hire, give a reward.
from 7809; a donation (venal or redemptive):--bribe(-ry), gift, present, reward.
a primitive root; to swim; causatively, to inundate:--(make to) swim.

a primitive root; to depress, i.e. prostrate (especially reflexive, in homage to royalty or God):--bow (self) down, crouch, fall down (flat), humbly beseech, do (make) obeisance, do reverence, make to stoop, worship.
from 7811; a pond (for swimming):--to swim in.
or schoq {sekh-oke'}; from 7832; laughter (in merriment or defiance):--derision, laughter(-ed to scorn, -ing), mocked, sport.
from 7835; dinginess, i.e. perhaps soot:--coal.
from 7812; pit:--pit.
a primitive root; to sink or depress (reflexive or causative):--bend, bow (down), bring (cast) down, couch, humble self, be (bring) low, stoop.
a primitive root; to tread out, i.e. squeeze (grapes):--press.
a primitive root; to slaughter (in sacrifice or massacre):--kill, offer, shoot out, slay, slaughter.
a primitive root (identical with 7819 through the idea of striking); to hammer out:--beat.
from 7819; slaughter:--killing.
from an unused root probably meaning to burn; inflammation, i.e. an ulcer; --boil, botch.
or cachiysh {saw-kheesh'}; from an unused root apparently meaning to sprout; after-growth:--(that) which springeth of the same.
from the same as 7828; a board (as chipped thin):--cieled with.
from 7812; a pit-fall (literally or figuratively):--destruction, pit.
from an unused root probably meaning to roar; a lion (from his characteristic roar):--(fierce) lion.
apparently from the same as 7826 through some obscure idea, perhaps that of peeling off by concussion of sound; a scale or shell, i.e. the aromatic mussel.:--onycha.
from an unused root meaning to peel, i.e. emaciate; the gull (as thin):--cuckoo.
from the same as 7828; emaciation:--consumption.
from an unused root apparently meaning to strut; haughtiness (as evinced by the attitude):--X lion, pride.
from the same as 7830; proudly; Shachatsom, a place in Palestine:--Shahazimah (from the margin).
a primitive root; to laugh (in pleasure or detraction); by implication, to play:--deride, have in derision, laugh, make merry, mock(-er), play, rejoice, (laugh to) scorn, be in (make) sport.
a primitive root; to comminate (by trituration or attrition):--beat, wear.
from 7833; a powder (as beaten small): by analogy, a thin vapor; by extension, the firmament:--cloud, small dust, heaven, sky.
a primitive root (identical with 7836 through the idea of the duskiness of early dawn); to be dim or dark (in color):--be black.

a primitive root; properly, to dawn, i.e. (figuratively) be (up) early at any task (with the implication of earnestness); by extension, to search for (with painstaking):--(do something) betimes, enquire early, rise (seek) betimes, seek diligently) early, in the morning).
from 7836; dawn (literal, figurative or adverbial):--day(-spring), early, light, morning, whence riseth.
or shachowr {shaw-khore'}; from 7835; properly, dusky, but also (absol.) jetty:--black.
from 7836; a dawning, i.e. (figuratively) juvenescence:--youth.
from 7835; swarthy:--black.
from 7836 and 3050; Jah has sought; Shecharjah, an Israelite:--Shehariah.
dual of 7837; double dawn; Shacharajim, an Israelite:--Shaharaim.

a primitive root; to decay, i.e. (causatively) ruin (literally or figuratively):--batter, cast off, corrupt(-er, thing), destroy(-er, -uction), lose, mar, perish, spill, spoiler, X utterly, waste(-r).
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7843:--corrupt, fault.
from 7743; a pit (especially as a trap); figuratively, destruction:--corruption, destruction, ditch, grave, pit.
or cet {sayt}; from 7750; a departure from right, i.e. sin:--revolter, that turn aside.
a primitive root; to deviate from duty:--decline, go aside, turn.
feminine of a derivative (only in the plural shittiym {shit-teem'}; meaning the sticks of wood) from the same as 7850; the acacia (from its scourging thorns):--shittah, shittim. See also 1029.
a primitive root; to expand:--all abroad, enlarge, spread, stretch out.
active participle of an otherwise unused root meaning (properly, to pierce; but only as a denominative from 7752) to flog; a goad:--scourge.
the same as the plural of 7848; acacia trees; Shittim, a place East of the Jordan:--Shittim.
a primitive root; properly, to lurk for, i.e. persecute:--hate, oppose self against.
a primitive root; to attack, (figuratively) accuse:--(be an) adversary, resist.
from 7853; an opponent; especially (with the article prefixed) Satan, the arch-enemy of good:--adversary, Satan, withstand.
from 7853; opposition (by letter):--accusation.
the same as 7855; Sitnah, the name of a well in Pal:--Sitnah.
a primitive root; to gush; by implication, to inundate, cleanse; by analogy, to gallop, conquer:--drown, (over-)flow(- whelm, rinse, run, rush, (throughly) wash (away).
or sheteph {shay'-tef}; from 7857; a deluge (literally or figuratively):--flood, outrageous, overflowing.
(Aramaic) of uncertain derivation; a side:--side.
active participle of an otherwise unused root probably meaning to write; properly, a scribe, i.e. (by analogy or implication) an official superintendent or magistrate:--officer, overseer, ruler.
from the same as 7860; magisterial; Shitrai, an Israelite:--Shitrai.
probably from 7737; a gift (as available):--present.
from the same as 7721 by permutation; elevation:-- excellency.
for 7724; Sheja, an Israelite:--Sheva (from the margin).
from 7863; peak; Sion, the summit of Mt. Hermon:--Sion.
from the same as 7722; ruin; Shijon, a place in Palestine --Shihon.
a primitive root; properly, to become aged, i.e. (by implication) to grow gray:--(be) grayheaded.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7867:--elder.
from 7867; old age:--age.
by permutation from 7725; a return (of property):--captivity.
from 3427; residence:--while...lay.
feminine of 7869; old age:--(be) gray (grey hoar,-y) hairs (head,-ed), old age.
from 7734; a withdrawal (into a private place):--pursuing.
a primitive root probably meaning to boil up (compare 7736); used only as denominative from 7875; to plaster:--plaister.
from 7874; lime (as boiling when slacked):--lime, plaister.
a primitive root; to keep in memory:--be unmindful. (Render Deuteronomy 32:18, "A Rock bore thee, thou must recollect; and (yet) thou hast forgotten," etc.)
of unknown derivation; Shiza, an Is.:--Shiza.
a primitive root; to ponder, i.e. (by implication) converse (with oneself, and hence, aloud) or (transitively) utter:-- commune, complain, declare, meditate, muse, pray, speak, talk (with).
from 7878; a contemplation; by implication, an utterance:--babbling, communication, complaint, meditation, prayer, talk.
from 7878; a shoot (as if uttered or put forth), i.e. (generally) shrubbery:--bush, plant, shrub.
feminine of 7879; reflection; be extension, devotion:--meditation, prayer.
for 7745; a pit-fall:--pit.
or Shichowr {shee-khore'}; or Shichor {shee-khore'}; probably from 7835; dark, i.e. turbid; Shichor, a stream of Egypt:--Shihor, Sihor.
from the same as 7883 and 3835; darkish whiteness; Shichor-Libnath, a stream of Palestine:--Shihor-libnath.
from 7751; an oar; also (compare 7752) a scourge (figuratively):--oar, scourge.
from 7951; tranquil; Shiloh, an epithet of the Messiah:--Shiloh.
or Shiloh {shee-lo'}; or Shiylow {shee-lo'}; or Shilow {shee-lo'}; from the same as 7886; Shiloh, a place in Palestine:--Shiloh.
or Shiyloniy {shee-lo-nee'}; or Shiloniy {shee-lo-nee'}; from 7887; a Shilonite or inhabitant of Shiloh:--Shilonite.
apparently for 3452; desert; Shimon, an Israelite:--Shimon.
from an unused root meaning to urinate; urine:--piss.

or (the original form) shuwr (1 Sam. 18:6) {shoor}; a primitive root (identical with 7788 through the idea of strolling minstrelsy); to sing:--behold (by mistake for 7789), sing(-er, -ing man, - ing woman).
or feminine shiyrah {shee-raw'}; from 7891; a song; abstractly, singing:--musical(-ick), X sing(-er, -ing), song.
from an unused root meaning to bleach, i.e. whiten; white, i.e. marble. See 8336.
from the same as 7893; whiteness; Shisha, an Israelite:--Shisha.
or Shuwshaq {shoo-shak'}; of Egyptian derivation; Shishak, an Egyptian king:--Shishak.
a primitive root; to place (in a very wide application):--apply, appoint, array, bring, consider, lay (up), let alone, X look, make, mark, put (on), + regard, set, shew, be stayed, X take.
from 7896; a dress (as put on):--attire.
from 7896; scrub or trash, i.e. wild growth of weeds or briers (as if put on the field):--thorns.
from 5526 in the sense of 7753; a brier (as of a hedge):--prick.
from 5526 in the sense of 7753; a booth (as interlaced):--tabernacle.

a primitive root; to lie down (for rest, sexual connection, decease or any other purpose):--X at all, cast down, ((lover-))lay (self) (down), (make to) lie (down, down to sleep, still with), lodge, ravish, take rest, sleep, stay.
from 7901; a lying down (of dew, or for the sexual act):--X carnally, copulation, X lay, seed.
from 7901; a (sexual) lying with:--X lie.
a primitive root; to roam (through lust):--in the morning (by mistake for 7925).
feminine of 7900 in the sense of 7899; a dart (as pointed like a thorn):--barbed iron.
from an unused root apparently meaning to surmount; an observatory (with the article); Seku, a place in Palestine:--Sechu.
from the same as 7906; observant, i.e. (concretely) the mind:--heart.
infinitive of 7921; bereavement:--loss of children, spoiling.
or shakkul {shak-kool'}; from 7921; bereaved:--barren, bereaved (robbed) of children (whelps).
or shikkor {shik-kore'}; from 7937; intoxicated, as a state or a habit:--drunk(-ard, -en, -en man).
or shakeach {shaw-kay'-akh}; a primitive root; to mislay, i.e. to be oblivious of, from want of memory or attention:--X at all, (cause to) forget.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7911 through the idea of disclosure of a covered or forgotten thing; to discover (literally or figuratively):--find.
from 7911; oblivious:--forget.
feminine from the same as 7906; a conspicuous object:--picture.
intensive perhaps from the same as 7906 in the sense of 7753; a knife (as pointed or edged):--knife.
from 7936; a man at wages by the day or year:--hired (man, servant), hireling.
feminine of 7916; a hiring:--that is hired.
a primitive root; to weave (i.e. lay) a trap; figuratively, (through the idea of secreting) to allay (passions; physically, abate a flood):--appease, assuage, make to cease, pacify, set.

a primitive root; to be (causatively, make or act) circumspect and hence, intelligent:--consider, expert, instruct, prosper, (deal) prudent(-ly), (give) skill(-ful), have good success, teach, (have, make to) understand(-ing), wisdom, (be, behave self, consider, make) wise(- ly), guide wittingly.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7919:--consider.

a primitive root; properly, to miscarry, i.e. suffer abortion; by analogy, to bereave (literally or figuratively):--bereave (of children), barren, cast calf (fruit, young), be (make) childless, deprive, destroy, X expect, lose children, miscarry, rob of children, spoil.
or sekel {say'-kel}; from 7919; intelligence; by implication, success:--discretion, knowledge, policy, prudence, sense, understanding, wisdom, wise.
plural from 7921; childlessness (by continued bereavements):--to have after loss of others.
(Aramaic) from 7920; intelligence:--understanding.

a primitive root; properly, to incline (the shoulder to a burden); but used only as denominative from 7926; literally, to load up (on the back of man or beast), i.e. to start early in the morning:--(arise, be up, get (oneself) up, rise up) early (betimes), morning.
from 7925; the neck (between the shoulders) as the place of burdens; figuratively, the spur of a hill:--back, X consent, portion, shoulder.
the same as 7926; ridge; Shekem, a place in Palestine:--Shechem.
for 7926; Shekem, the name of a Hivite and two Israelites:--Shechem.
feminine of 7926; the shoulder-bone:--shoulder blade.
patronymic from 7928; a Shikmite (collectively), or descendants of Shekem:--Shichemites.

a primitive root (apparently akin (by transmission) to 7901 through the idea of lodging; compare 5531, 7925); to reside or permanently stay (literally or figuratively):--abide, continue, (cause to, make to) dwell(-er), have habitation, inhabit, lay, place, (cause to) remain, rest, set (up).
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7931:--cause to dwell, have habitation.
from 7931; a residence:--habitation.
from 7931; a resident; by extension, a fellow-citizen:--inhabitant, neighbour, nigh.
or (prol.) Shkanyahuw {shek-an-yaw'-hoo}; from 7931 and 3050; Jah has dwelt; Shekanjah, the name of nine Israelites:--Shecaniah, Shechaniah.

or (by permutation) cakar (Ezra 4:5) {saw-kar'}; a primitive root (apparently akin (by prosthesis) to 3739 through the idea of temporary purchase; compare 7937); to hire:--earn wages, hire (out self), reward, X surely.

a primitive root; to become tipsy; in a qualified sense, to satiate with a stimulating drink or (figuratively) influence:--(be filled with) drink (abundantly), (be, make) drunk(-en), be merry. (Superlative of 8248.)
from 7936; wages:--reward, sluices.
from 7936; payment of contract; concretely, salary, fare, maintenance; by implication, compensation, benefit:--hire, price, reward(-ed), wages, worth.
the same as 7939; recompense; Sakar, the name of two Israelites:--Sacar.
from 7937; an intoxicant, i.e. intensely alcoholic liquor:--strong drink, + drunkard, strong wine.
for 7943; drunkenness, Shikkeron, a place in Palestine:--Shicron.
from 7937; intoxication:--(be) drunken(-ness).
from 7952 abbrev.; a fault:--error.
for the rel. 834; used with prepositional prefix, and often followed by some pronominal affix; on account of, whatsoever, whichsoever:--cause, sake.
for 7600; tranquil:--being at ease.
a primitive root; to space off; intensive (evenly) to make equidistant:--equally distant, set in order.
from 7947; a spacer or raised interval, i.e. the stile in a frame or panel:--ledge.
a primitive root; properly, meaning to be white; used only as denominative from 7950; to be snow-white (with the linen clothing of the slain):--be as snow.
from 7949; snow (probably from its whiteness):--snow(-y).
or shalav (Job 3:26) {shaw-lav'}; a primitive root; to be tranquil, i.e. secure or successful:--be happy, prosper, be in safety.
a primitive root (probably identical with 7953 through the idea of educing); to mislead:--deceive, be negligent.
a primitive root (rather cognate (by contraction) to the base of 5394, 7997 and their congeners through the idea of extracting); to draw out or off, i.e. remove (the soul by death):--take away.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7951; to be secure:--at rest.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to 7952; a wrong:--thing amiss.
the same as 7596 (shortened); request; Shelah, the name of a postdiluvian patriarch and of an Israelite:--Shelah.
from the same as 3851 with sibilant prefix; a flare of fire:--(flaming) flame.
or slayv {sel-awv'}; by orthographical variation from 7951 through the idea of sluggishness; the quail collectively (as slow in flight from its weight):--quails.
from 7951; security:--prosperity.
(Aramaic) or shaluwth (Aramaic) {shaw-looth'}; from the same as 7955; a fault:--error, X fail, thing amiss.
or shaleyv {shaw-lave'}; feminine shlevah {shel-ay-vaw'}; from 7951; tranquil; (in a bad sense) careless; abstractly, security:--(being) at ease, peaceable, (in) prosper(-ity), quiet(-ness), wealthy.
from 7951; security (genuine or false):--abundance, peace(-ably), prosperity, quietness.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7962; safety:--tranquillity. See also 7961.
or shilluach {shil-loo'-akh}; from 7971; (only in plural) a dismissal, i.e. (of a wife) divorce (especially the document); also (of a daughter) dower:--presents, have sent back.

or shalom {shaw-lome'}; from 7999; safe, i.e. (figuratively) well, happy, friendly; also (abstractly) welfare, i.e. health, prosperity, peace:--X do, familiar, X fare, favour, + friend, X great, (good) health, (X perfect, such as be at) peace(-able, -ably), prosper(-ity, -ous), rest, safe(-ty), salute, welfare, (X all is, be) well, X wholly.
or shillum {shil-loom'}; from 7999; a requital, i.e. (secure) retribution, (venal) a fee:--recompense, reward.
or (shorter) Shallum {shal-loom'}; the same as 7966; Shallum, the name of fourteen Israelites:--Shallum.
probably for 7967; Shallun, an Israelite:--Shallum.

or shalosh {shaw-loshe'}; masculine shlowshah {shel-o-shaw'}; or shloshah {shel-o-shaw'}; a primitive number; three; occasionally (ordinal) third, or (multipl.) thrice:--+ fork, + often(-times), third, thir(-teen, -teenth), three, + thrice. Compare 7991.
or shloshiym {shel-o-sheem'}; multiple of 7969; thirty; or (ordinal) thirtieth:--thirty, thirtieth. Compare 7991.

a primitive root; to send away, for, or out (in a great variety of applications):--X any wise, appoint, bring (on the way), cast (away, out), conduct, X earnestly, forsake, give (up), grow long, lay, leave, let depart (down, go, loose), push away, put (away, forth, in, out), reach forth, send (away, forth, out), set, shoot (forth, out), sow, spread, stretch forth (out).
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7971:--put, send.
from 7971; a missile of attack, i.e. spear; also (figuratively) a shoot of growth; i.e. branch:--dart, plant, X put off, sword, weapon.
the same as 7973; Shelach, a postdiluvian patriarch:--Salah, Shelah. Compare 7975.
or (in imitation of 7974) Shelach (Neh. 3:15) {sheh'-lakh}; from 7971; rill; Shiloach, a fountain of Jerusalem:-- Shiloah, Siloah.
feminine of 7964; a shoot:--branch.
from 7973; missive, i.e. armed; Shilchi, an Israelite:--Shilhi.
plural of 7973; javelins or sprouts; Shilchim, a place in Palestine:--Shilhim.
from 7971; a table (as spread out); by implication, a meal:--table.
a primitive root; to dominate, i.e. govern; by implication, to permit:--(bear, have) rule, have dominion, give (have) power.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7980:--have the mastery, have power, bear rule, be (make) ruler.
from 7980; probably a shield (as controlling, i.e. protecting the person):--shield.
(Aramaic) from 7980; a potentate; --power.
(Aramaic) or shilton {shil-tone'}; corresponding to 7983:--ruler.
(Aramaic) from 7981; empire (abstractly or concretely):--dominion.
feminine from 7980; a vixen:--imperious.
from 7951; privacy:--+ quietly.
feminine from 7953; a fetus or babe (as extruded in birth):--young one.
from 7980; potent; concretely, a prince or warrior:--governor, mighty, that hath power, ruler.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7989; mighty; abstractly, permission; concretely, a premier:--captain, be lawful, rule(- r).

or shalowsh ( 1 Chron. 11:11; 12:18) {shaw- loshe'}; or shalosh (2 Sam. 23:13) {shaw-loshe'}; from 7969; a triple, i.e. (as a musical instrument) a triangle (or perhaps rather three-stringed lute); also (as an indefinite, great quantity) a three-fold measure (perhaps a treble ephah); also (as an officer) a general of the third rank (upward, i.e. the highest):--captain, instrument of musick, (great) lord, (great) measure, prince, three (from the margin).
ordinal from 7969; third; feminine a third (part); by extension, a third (day, year or time); specifically, a third-story cell):--third (part, rank, time), three (years old).
a primitive root; to throw out, down or away (literally or figuratively):--adventure, cast (away, down, forth, off, out), hurl, pluck, throw.
from 7993; bird of prey, usually thought to be the pelican (from casting itself into the sea):--cormorant.
from 7993; a felling (of trees):--when cast.
the same as 7995; Shalleketh, a gate in Jerusalem:--Shalleketh.
a primitive root; to drop or strip; by implication, to plunder:--let fall, make self a prey, X of purpose, (make a, (take)) spoil.
from 7997; booty:--prey, spoil.

a primitive root; to be safe (in mind, body or estate); figuratively, to be (causatively, make) completed; by implication, to be friendly; by extension, to reciprocate (in various applications):--make amends, (make an) end, finish, full, give again, make good, (re-)pay (again), (make) (to) (be at) peace(-able), that is perfect, perform, (make) prosper(-ous), recompense, render, requite, make restitution, restore, reward, X surely.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7999; to complete, to restore:--deliver, finish.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7965; prosperity:--peace.
from 7999; properly, requital, i.e. a (voluntary) sacrifice in thanks:--peace offering.
from 7999; complete (literally or figuratively); especially friendly:--full, just, made ready, peaceable, perfect(-ed), quiet, Shalem (by mistake for a name), whole.
the same as 8003; peaceful; Shalem, an early name of Jerusalem:--Salem.
from 7999; requital:--recompense.
the same as 8005; Shillem, an Israelite:--Shillem.
probably for 8008; clothing; Salma, the name of two Israelites:--Salma.
transp. for 8071; a dress:--clothes, garment, raiment.
the same as 8008; clothing; Salmah, an Israelite:--Salmon. Compare 8012.
from 7965; peaceful; Shelomah, David's successor:--Solomon.
feminine of 7966; retribution:--recompense.
from 8008; investiture; Salmon, an Israelite:--Salmon. Compare 8009.
feminine plural of 7965; pacifications; Shelomoth, the name of two Israelites:--Shelomith (from the margin), Shelomoth. Compare 8019.
from 8008; clothed; Salmai, an Israelite:--Shalmai.
from 7965; peaceable; Shelomi, an Israelite:--Shelomi.
patronymically from 8006; a Shilemite (collectively) or descendants of Shillem:--Shillemites.
from 7965 and 410; peace of God; Shelumiel, an Israelite:--Shelumiel.
or Shelemyahuw {shel-em-yaw'-hoo}; from 8002 and 3050; thank-offering of Jah; Shelemjah, the name of nine Israelites:--Shelemiah.
or Shlowmiyth (Ezra 8:10) {shel-o- meeth'}; from 7965; peaceableness; Shelomith, the name of five Israelites and three Israelitesses:--Shelomith.
of foreign derivation; Shalman, a king apparently of Assyria:--Shalman. Compare 8022.
from 7999; a bribe:--reward.
of foreign derivation; Shalmaneser, an Assyrian king:--Shalmaneser. Comp 8020.
the same as 7888; Shiloni, an Israelite:--Shiloni.
from 7956; a Shelanite (collectively), or descendants of Shelah:--Shelanites.
a primitive root; to pull out, up or off:--draw (off), grow up, pluck off.
from 8025; extract; Sheleph, a son of Jokthan:--Sheleph.

a primitive root perhaps originally to intensify, i.e. treble; but apparently used only as denominative from 7969, to be (causatively, make) triplicate (by restoration, in portions, strands, days or years):--do the third time, (divide into, stay) three (days, - fold, parts, years old).
from 8027; triplet; Shelesh, an Israelite:--Shelesh.
from 8027; a descendant of the third degree, i.e. great grandchild:--third (generation).
feminine from the same as 8028; triplication; Shilshah, an Israelite:--Shilshah.
feminine from 8027; trebled land; Shalishah, a place in Palestine:--Shalisha.

or shilshom {shil-shome'}; from the same as 8028; trebly, i.e. (in time) day before yesterday:--+ before (that time, - time), excellent things (from the margin), + heretofore, three days, + time past.
a primitive particle (rather from the relative pronoun, 834); there (transferring to time) then; often thither, or thence:--in it, + thence, there (-in, + of, + out), + thither, + whither.

a primitive word (perhaps rather from 7760 through the idea of definite and conspicuous position; compare 8064); an appellation, as a mark or memorial of individuality; by implication honor, authority, character:--+ base, (in-)fame(-ous), named(-d), renown, report.
the same as 8034; name; Shem, a son of Noah (often includ. his posterity):--Sem, Shem.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 8034:--name.
from 8074; desolation; Shamma, an Israelite:--Shamma.
apparently from 8034 and 83; name of pinion, i.e. illustrious; Shemeber, a king of Zeboim:--Shemeber.
perhaps for 8093; Shimah, an Israelite:--Shimah. Compare 8043.

or smosl {sem-ole'}; a primitive word (rather perhaps from the same as 8071 (by insertion of the aleph) through the idea of wrapping up); properly, dark (as enveloped), i.e. the north; hence (by orientation), the left hand:--left (hand, side).
a primitive root (denominative from 8040); to use the left hand or pass in that direction):--(go, turn) (on the, to the) left.
from 8040; situated on the left side:--left.
for 8039 (compare 38); Shimam, an Israelite:--Shimeam.
of uncertain derivation; Shamgar, an Israelite judge:--Shamgar.
a primitive root; to desolate:--destory(- uction), bring to nought, overthrow, perish, pluck down, X utterly.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 8045:--consume.
from 8074; ruin; by implication, consternation:--astonishment, desolate(-ion), waste, wonderful thing.
the same as 8047; Shammah, the name of an Edomite and four Israelites:--Shammah.
for 8048; desolation; Shamhuth, an Israelite:--Shamhuth.
from the passive participle of 8085 and 410; heard of God; Shemuel, the name of three Israelites:--Samuel, Shemuel.
from 8074; renowned; Shammua, the name of four Israelites:--Shammua, Shammuah.
feminine passive participle of 8074; something heard, i.e. an announcement:--bruit, doctrine, fame, mentioned, news, report, rumor, tidings.
passive participle of 8103; observed; Shamur, an Israelite:--Shamir (from the margin).
plural of 8047; ruins; Shammoth, an Israelite:--Shamoth.

a primitive root; probably to brighten up, i.e. (figuratively) be (causatively, make) blithe or gleesome:--cheer up, be (make) glad, (have, make) joy(-ful), be (make) merry, (cause to, make to) rejoice, X very.
from 8055; blithe or gleeful:--(be) glad, joyful, (making) merry((-hearted), -ily), rejoice(-ing).
from 8056; blithesomeness or glee, (religious or festival):--X exceeding(-ly), gladness, joy(-fulness), mirth, pleasure, rejoice(-ing).
a primitive root; to fling down; incipiently to jostle; figuratively, to let alone, desist, remit:--discontinue, overthrow, release, let rest, shake, stumble, throw down.
from 8058; remission (of debt) or suspension of labor):--release.
from 8073; destructive; Shammai, the name of three Israelites:--Shammai.
apparently from 8034 and 3045; name of knowing; Shemida, an Israelite:--Shemida, Shemidah.
patronymically from 8061; a Shemidaite (collectively) or descendants of Shemida:--Shemidaites.
from 5564; a run (as sustaining the Oriental sitter):--mantle.

dual of an unused singular shameh {shaw-meh'}; from an unused root meaning to be lofty; the sky (as aloft; the dual perhaps alluding to the visible arch in which the clouds move, as well as to the higher ether where the celestial bodies revolve):--air, X astrologer, heaven(-s).
(Aramaic) corresponding to 8064:--heaven.
from 8083; eight:--eight.
feminine of 8066; probably an eight-stringed lyre:--Sheminith.
from 8104 in the original sense of pricking; a thorn; also (from its keenness for scratching) a gem, probably the diamond:--adamant (stone), brier, diamond.
the same as 8068; Shamir, the name of two places in Palestine:--Shamir. Compare 8053.
or Shmariymowth {shem-aw-ree- moth'}; probably from 8034 and plural of 7413; name of heights; Shemiramoth, the name of two Israelites:--Shemiramoth.

perhaps by permutation for the feminine of 5566 (through the idea of a cover assuming the shape of the object beneath); a dress, especially a mantle:--apparel, cloth(-es, -ing), garment, raiment. Compare 8008.
probably for the same as 8071; Samlah, an Edomite:--Samlah.
for 8014; Shamlai, one of the Nethinim:--Shalmai (from the margin).

a primitive root; to stun (or intransitively, grow numb), i.e. devastate or (figuratively) stupefy (both usually in a passive sense):--make amazed, be astonied, (be an) astonish(-ment), (be, bring into, unto, lay, lie, make) desolate(-ion, places), be destitute, destroy (self), (lay, lie, make) waste, wonder.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 8074:--be astonied.
from 8074; ruined:--desolate.
or shimamah {shee-mam-aw'}; feminine of 8076; devastation; figuratively, astonishment:--(laid, X most) desolate(- ion), waste.
from 8074; stupefaction:--astonishment.
probably from 8074 (in the sense of poisoning); a lizard (from the superstition of its noxiousness):--spider.
a primitive root; to shine, i.e. (by analogy) be (causatively, make) oily or gross:--become (make, wax) fat.
from 8080; grease, especially liquid (as from the olive, often perfumed); figuratively, richness:--anointing, X fat (things), X fruitful, oil((-ed)), ointment, olive, + pine.
from 8080; greasy, i.e. gross; figuratively, rich:--fat, lusty, plenteous.

or shmowneh {shem-o-neh'}; feminine shmonah {shem-o-naw'}; or shmownah {shem-o-naw'}; apparently from 8082 through the idea of plumpness; a cardinal number, eight (as if a surplus above the "perfect" seven); also (as ordinal) eighth:--eight((-een, -eenth)), eighth.
