or sason {saw-sone'}; from 7797; cheerfulness; specifically, welcome:--gladness, joy, mirth, rejoicing.
perhaps from 8336; whitish; Shashai, an Israelite:--Shashai.
probably for 8343; Sheshai, a Canaanite:--Sheshai.
from 8337; sixth, ord. or (feminine) fractional:--sixth (part).
multiple of 8337; sixty:--sixty, three score.
of foreign derivation; Sheshak, a symbol. name of Babylon:--Sheshach.
perhaps for 7799; lily; Sheshan, an Israelite:--Sheshan.
probably from the base of 7785; pedestrian; Shashak, an Israelite:--Shashak.
perhaps from the base of 8324 in the sense of that of 8320; red ochre (from its piercing color):--vermillion.
(Numbers from 7582; tumult:--Sheth.
from 7896; put, i.e. substituted; Sheth, third son of Adam:--Seth, Sheth.
(Aramaic) or shith (Aramaic) {sheeth}; corresponding to 8337:--six(-th).
a primitive root; to imbibe (literally or figuratively):--X assuredly, banquet, X certainly, drink(-er, -ing), drunk (X -ard), surely. (Prop. intensive of 8248.)
(Aramaic) corresponding to 8354:--drink.
from 7896; a basis, i.e. (figuratively) political or moral support:--foundation, purpose.
from 7896; the seat (of the person):--buttock.
from 8354; intoxicaion:--drunkenness.
from 7896; a fixture, i.e. the warp in weaving:--warp.
feminine of 8358; potation:--drinking.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 8346 (compare 8353); sixty:--threescore.
a primitive root; to transplant:--plant.
from 8362; a sprig (as if transplanted), i.e. sucker:--plant.
patronymically from 7803; a Shuthalchite (collectively) or descendants of Shuthelach:--Shuthalhites.
a primitive root; to unveil (figuratively):--be open.
a primitive root; (causatively) to make water, i.e. urinate:--piss.
a primitive root; to subside:--be calm, cease, be quiet.
a primitive root; to break out (as an eruption):--have in (one's) secret parts.
of foreign derivation; Shethar, a Persian satrap:--Shethar.
of foreign derivation; Shethar-Bozenai, a Persian officer:--Shethar-boznai.
a primitive root; to place, i.e. array; reflex. to lie:--be laid, set.
and (feminine) ta ah (Ezek. 40:12) {taw-aw'}; from (the base of) 8376; a room (as circumscribed):--(little) chamber.
a primitive root; to desire:--long.
a primitive root (probably identical with 8373 through the idea of puffing disdainfully at; compare 340); to loathe (morally):--abhor.
from 8374 (compare 15); desire:--longing.
a primitive root; to mark off, i.e. (intensively) designate:--point out.
and towt (the original form) {toh}; from 8376; a species of antelope (probably from the white stripe on the cheek):--wild bull (ox).
from 183 (abbreviated); a longing; by implication, a delight (subjectively, satisfaction, objectively, a charm):--dainty, desire, X exceedingly, X greedily, lust(ing), pleasant. See also 6914.
from 8376; a limit, i.e. full extent:--utmost bound.
or taom {taw-ome'}; from 8382; a twin (in plural only), literally or figuratively:--twins.
from 422; an imprecation:--curse.
a primitive root; to be complete; but used only as denominative from 8380, to be (causatively, make) twinned, i.e. (figuratively) duplicate or (arch.) jointed:--coupled (together), bear twins.
from 205; naughtiness, i.e. toil:--lie.
or (in the singular, feminine) t:enah {teh-ay- naw'}; perhaps of foreign derivation; the fig (tree or fruit):--fig (tree).
or tonanah {to-an-aw'}; from 579; an opportunity or (subjectively) purpose:--occasion.
from 578; lamentation:--heaviness, mourning.
from 8385 and 7887; approach of Shiloh; Taanath-Shiloh, a place in Palestine:--Taanath-shiloh.
a primitive root; to delineate; reflex. to extend:--be drawn, mark out, (Rimmon-)methoar (by union with 7417).
from 8388; outline, i.e. figure or appearance:--+ beautiful, X comely, countenance, + fair, X favoured, form, X goodly, X resemble, visage.
perhaps from 772; Taarea, an Israelite:--Tarea. See 8475.
from 833; a species of cedar (from its erectness):--box (tree).
perhaps of foreign derivation; a box:--ark.
from 935; income, i.e. produce (literally or figuratively):--fruit, gain, increase, revenue.
and (feminine) tbuwnah {teb-oo-naw'}; or towbunah {to-boo-naw'}; from 995; intelligence; by implication, an argument; by extension, caprice:--discretion, reason, skilfulness, understanding, wisdom.
from 947; a treading down, i.e. ruin:--destruction.
from a root corresponding to 8406; broken region; Tabor, a mountain in Palestine, also a city adjacent:--Tabor.
apparently from 1101; mixture, i.e. unnatural bestiality:--confusion.
from 2986; the earth (as moist and therefore inhabited); by extension, the globe; by implication, its inhabitants; specifically, a partic. land, as Babylonia, Palestine:--habitable part, world.
from 1086; consumption:--destruction.
from 1101 in the original sense of flowing: a cataract (in the eye):--blemish.
probably from 1129; properly, material, i.e. (specifically) refuse haum or stalks of grain (as chopped in threshing and used for fodder):--chaff, straw, stubble.
from 8401; strawy; Tibni, an Israelite:--Tibni.
from 1129; structure; by implication, a model, resemblance:--figure, form, likeness, pattern, similitude.
from 1197; burning; Taberah, a place in the Desert:--Taberah.
from the same as 948; whiteness; Tebets, a place in Palestine:--Thebez.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7665; to be fragile (figuratively):--broken.

or Tiglath Plecer {tig- lath pel-eh-ser}; or Tilgath Pilnlecer {til-gath' pil-neh-eh'-ser} or Tilgath Pilnecer {til-gath' pil-neh'-ser}; of foreign derivation; Tiglath- Pileser or Tilgath-pilneser, an Assyr. king:--Tiglath-pileser, Tilgath- pilneser.
from 1580; a bestowment:--benefit.
from 1624; strife, i.e. infliction:--blow.
apparently from 1725; enduring; a species of hard-wood or lasting tree (perhaps oak):--pine (tree).
(Aramaic) from 1753 in the original sense of enduring; permanence, i.e. (adverb) constantly:--continually.
or Tammor (1 Kings 9:18) {tam-more'}; apparently from 8558; palm-city; Tadmor, a place near Palestine:--Tadmor.
perhaps from 1763; fearfulness; Tidal, a Canaanite:--Tidal.

from an unused root meaning to lie waste; a desolation (of surface), i.e. desert; figuratively, a worthless thing; adverbially, in vain:--confusion, empty place, without form, nothing, (thing of) nought, vain, vanity, waste, wilderness.
or thom {teh-home'}; (usually feminine) from 1949; an abyss (as a surging mass of water), especially the deep (the main sea or the subterranean water-supply):--deep (place), depth.
from 1984; laudation; specifically (concretely) a hymn:--praise.
feminine of an unused noun (apparently from 1984) meaning bluster; braggadocio, i.e. (by implication) fatuity:--folly.
from 1980; a procession:--X went.
from 2015; a perversity or fraud:--(very) froward(-ness, thing), perverse thing.
from 8427; a mark; by implication, a signature:--desire, mark.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7725, to come back; specifically (transitive and ellip.) to reply:--answer, restore, return (an answer).
or Tubal {too-bal'}; probably of foreign derivation; Tubal, a postdiluvian patriarch and his posterity:--Tubal.
apparently from 2986 (compare 2981) and 7014; offspring of Cain; Tubal-Kajin, an antidiluvian patriarch:--Tubal-cain.
from 3013; depression (of spirits); concretely a grief:--heaviness, sorrow.
or Togarmah {to-gar-maw'}; probably of foreign derivation; Togarmah, a son of Gomer and his posterity:--Togarmah.

from 3034; properly, an extension of the hand, i.e. (by implication) avowal, or (usually) adoration; specifically, a choir of worshippers:--confession, (sacrifice of) praise, thanks(-giving, offering).
a primitive root; to mark out, i.e. (primitive) scratch or (definite) imprint:--scrabble, set (a mark).
a primitive root (or perhaps ident. with 8427 through a similar idea from scraping to pieces); to grieve:--limit (by confusion with 8427).
(Aramaic) corresponding to 8539 or perhaps to 7582 through the idea of sweeping to ruin (compare 8428); to amaze, i.e. (reflex. by implication) take alarm:--be astonied.
from an unused root meaning to depress; humble; Toach, an Israelite:--Toah.
from 3176; expectation:--hope.

from an unused root meaning to sever; a bisection, i.e. (by implication) the centre:--among(-st), X between, half, X (there- ,where-), in(-to), middle, mid(-night), midst (among), X out (of), X through, X with(-in).

and towkachath {to-kakh'-ath}; from 3198; chastisement; figuratively (by words) correction, refutation, proof (even in defence):--argument, X chastened, correction, reasoning, rebuke, reproof, X be (often) reproved.
from 3205; posterity; Tolad, a place in Palestine:--Tolad. Compare 513.
or toldah {to-led-aw'}; from 3205; (plural only) descent, i.e. family; (figuratively) history:--birth, generations.
from 8524; suspension; Tulon, an Israelite:--Tilon (from the margin).
from 3213; causing to howl, i.e. an oppressor:--that wasted.

and (feminine) towleoah {to-lay-aw'}; or towla ath {to-lah'-ath}; or tolaiath {to-lah'-ath}; from 3216; a maggot (as voracious); specifically (often with ellipsis of 8144) the crimson-grub, but used only (in this connection) of the color from it, and cloths dyed therewith:--crimson, scarlet, worm.
the same as 8438; worm; Tola, the name of two Israelites:--Tola.
patronymically from 8439; a Tolaite (collectively) or descendants of Tola:--Tolaites.

or tonebah {to-ay-baw'}; feminine active participle of 8581; properly, something disgusting (morally), i.e. (as noun) an abhorrence; especially idolatry or (concretely) an idol:-- abominable (custom, thing), abomination.
feminine active participle of 8582; mistake, i.e. (morally) impiety, or (political) injury:--error, hinder.
from 3286; (only in plural collective) weariness, i.e. (by implication) toil (treasure so obtained) or speed:--plenty, strength.

or totsaah {to-tsaw-aw'}; from 3318; (only in plural collective) exit, i.e. (geographical) boundary, or (figuratively) deliverance, (actively) source:--border(-s), going(-s) forth (out), issues, outgoings.
from the same as 3349; obedience; Tokahath, an Israelite:--Tikvath (by correction for 8616).
a primitive root; to meander (causatively, guide) about, especially for trade or reconnoitring:--chap(-man), sent to descry, be excellent, merchant(-man), search (out), seek, (e-)spy (out).
or tor {tore}; from 8446; a succession, i.e. a string or (abstractly) order:--border, row, turn.
probably the same as 8447; a manner (as a sort of turn):--estate.
or tor {tore}; probably the same as 8447; a ring-dove, often (figuratively) as a term of endearment:--(turtle) dove.
(Aramaic) corresponding (by permutation) to 7794; a bull:--bullock, ox.
or torah {to-raw'}; from 3384; a precept or statute, especially the Decalogue or Pentateuch:--law.
probably feminine of 8448; a custom:--manner.

or toshab (1 Kings 17:1) {to-shawb'}; from 3427; a dweller (but not outlandish (5237)); especially (as distinguished from a native citizen (active participle of 3427) and a temporary inmate (1616) or mere lodger (3885)) resident alien:--foreigner, inhabitant, sojourner, stranger.

or tushiyah { too-shee-yaw'}; from an unused root probably meaning to substantiate; support or (by implication) ability, i.e. (direct) help, (in purpose) an undertaking, (intellectual) understanding:--enterprise, that which (thing as it) is, substance, (sound) wisdom, working.
from an unused root meaning to smite; a club:--darts.
a primitive root; to lop off:--cut down.
or taznuth {taz-nooth'}; from 2181; harlotry, i.e. (figuratively) idolatry:--fornication, whoredom.

or tachbuwlah {takh-boo-law'}; from 2254 as denominative from 2256; (only in plural) properly, steerage (as a management of ropes), i.e. (figuratively) guidance or (by implication) a plan:--good advice, (wise) counsels.
from an unused root meaning to depress; abasement; Tochu, an Israelite:--Tohu.
(Aramaic) or tchoth (Aramaic) {tekh-oth'}; corresponding to 8478; beneath:--under.
probably for 2453; sagacious; Tachkemoni, an Israelite:--Tachmonite.
from 2490 in the sense of opening; a commencement; rel. original (adverb, -ly):--begin(-ning), first (time).
or tachalui {takh-al-oo'}; from 2456; a malady:--disease, X grievous, (that are) sick(-ness).
from 2554; a species of unclean bird (from its violence), perhaps an owl:--night hawk.
probably from 2583; station; Tachan, the name of two Israelites:--Tahan.
from 2583; (only plural collectively) an encampment:--camp.
from 2603; graciousness; causatively, entreaty:--favour, grace, supplication.
the same as 8467; Techinnah, an Israelite:--Tehinnah.
or (feminine) tachanuwnah {takh-an-oo-naw'}; from 2603; earnest prayer:--intreaty, supplication.
patronymically from 8465; a Tachanite (collectively) or descendants of Tachan:--Tahanites.

or Tchaphnchec (Ezek. 30:18) {tekh- af-nekh-ace'}; or Tachpnec (Jeremiah 2:16) {takh-pen-ace'}; of Egyptian derivation; Tachpanches, Techaphneches or Tachpenes, a place in Egypt:--Tahapanes, Tahpanhes, Tehaphnehes.
of Egyptian derivation; Tachpenes, an Egyptian woman:--Tahpenes.
from 2734 in the original sense of 2352 or 2353; a linen corslet (as white or hollow):--habergeon.
a facitious root from 2734 through the idea of the heat of jealousy; to vie with a rival:--close, contend.
for 8390; Tachrea, an Israelite:--Tahrea.
probably of foreign derivation; a (clean) animal with fur, probably a species of antelope:--badger.
the same as 8476; Tachash, a relative of Abraham:--Thahash.

from the same as 8430; the bottom (as depressed); only adverbially, below (often with prepositional prefix underneath), in lieu of, etc.:--as, beneath, X flat, in(-stead), (same) place (where...is), room, for...sake, stead of, under, X unto, X when...was mine, whereas, (where-)fore, with.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 8478:--under.
the same as 8478; Tachath, the name of a place in the Desert, also of three Israelites:--Tahath.
or tachton {takh-tone'}; from 8478; bottommost:--lower(-est), nether(-most).
from 8478; lowermost; as noun (feminine plural) the depths (figuratively, a pit, the womb):--low (parts, -er, -er parts, - est), nether (part).
apparently from the plural masculine of 8482 or 8478 and 2320; lower (ones) monthly; Tachtim-Chodshi, a place in Palestine:--Tahtim-hodshi.
or tiykon {tee-kone'}; from 8432; central:--middle(-most), midst.
or Temao {tay-maw'}; probably of foreign derivation; Tema, a son of Ishmael, and the region settled by him:--Tema.
or teman {tay-mawn'}; denominative from 3225; the south (as being on the right hand of a person facing the east):--south (side, -ward, wind).
or Teman {tay-mawn'}; the same as 8486; Teman, the name of two Edomites, and of the region and descendant of one of them:--south, Teman.
probably for 8489; Temeni, an Israelite:--Temeni.
patronymically from 8487; a Temanite or descendant of Teman:--Temani, Temanite.
or timarah {tee-maw-raw'}; from the same as 8558; a column, i.e. cloud:--pillar.
patrial or patronymically from an unused noun of uncertain meaning; a Titsite or descendant or inhabitant of an unknown Tits:--Tizite.
or tiyrosh {tee-roshe'}; from 3423 in the sense of expulsion; must or fresh grape-juice (as just squeezed out); by implication (rarely) fermented wine:--(new, sweet) wine.
probably from 3372; fearful, Tirja, an Israelite:--Tiria.
probably of foreign derivation; Tiras, a son of Japheth:--Tiras.
from an unused root meaning to butt; a buck or he-goat (as given to butting):--he goat.
or towk (Psa. 72:14) {toke}; from the same base as 8432 (in the sense of cutting to pieces); oppression:--deceit, fraud.
a primitive root; to strew, i.e. encamp:--sit down.
feminine passive participle of 8505; adjustment, i.e. structure; by implication, equipage:--fashion, store.
from 3559; or probably ident. with 8498; something arranged or fixed, i.e. a place:--seat.
or tuwkkiy {took-kee'}; probably of foreign derivation; some imported creature, probably a peacock:--peacock.
from an unused root meaning to dissever, i.e. crush:--deceitful.
from 3615; completeness:--perfection.
from 3615; completion; by implication, an extremity:--end, perfect(-ion).
probably for 7827; the cerulean mussel, i.e. the color (violet) obtained therefrom or stuff dyed therewith:--blue.

a primitive root; to balance, i.e. measure out (by weight or dimension); figuratively, arrange, equalize, through the idea of levelling (ment. estimate, test):--bear up, direct, be ((un-))equal, mete, ponder, tell, weigh.
from 8505; a fixed quantity:--measure, tale.
the same as 8506; Token, a place in Palestine:--Tochen.
from 8506; admeasurement, i.e. consummation:--pattern, sum.
apparently from an unused root meaning to encompass; a wrapper or robe:--garment.
by contraction from 8524; a mound:--heap, X strength.
a primitive root; to suspend; figuratively (through hesitation) to be uncertain; by implication (of mental dependence) to habituate:--be bent, hang (in doubt).
from 8510 and 24; mound of green growth; Tel-Abib, a place in Chaldaea:--Tel-abib.
from 3811; distress:--travail, travel, trouble.
from 3851; desiccation:--great drought.
or Tlassar {tel-as-sar'}; of foreign derivation; Telassar, a region of Assyria:--Telassar.
from 3847; a garment:--clothing.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 7950; snow:--snow.
a primitive root; to suspend (especially to gibbet):--hang (up).
or tlunnah {tel-oon-naw'}; from 3885 in the sense of obstinacy; a grumbling:--murmuring.
probably from an unused root meaning to dissever; breach; Telach, an Israelite:--Telah.
from 8510 and the feminine of 2798; mound of workmanship; Tel-Charsha, a place in Babylonia:--Tel-haresha, Tel-harsa.
probably from 8518; a quiver (as slung):--quiver.
(Aramaic) or taltiy (Aramaic) {tal-tee'}; ordinal from 8532; third:--third.
a primitive root; to pile up, i.e. elevate:--eminent. Compare 2048.
from an unused root meaning to accumulate; a bank or terrace:--furrow, ridge.
from 8525; ridged; Talmai, the name of a Canaanite and a Syrian:--Talmai.
from 3925; a pupil:--scholar.
from 8510 and 4417; mound of salt; Tel-Melach, a place in Babylonia:--Tel-melah.
a denominative from 8438; to crimson, i.e. dye that color:--X scarlet.
feminine from an unused root meaning to tower; something tall, i.e. (plural collective) slenderness:--armoury.
(Aramaic) from 8532; a tertiary rank:--third.
(Aramaic) masculine tlathah (Aramaic) {tel-aw-thaw'}; or tlatha (Aramaic) {tel-aw-thaw'}; corresponding to 7969; three or third:--third, three.
(Aramaic) mult. of 8532; ten times three:--thirty.
by reduplication, from 8524 through the idea of vibration; a trailing bough (as pendulous):--bushy.
from 8552; complete; usually (morally) pious; specifically, gentle, dear:--coupled together, perfect, plain, undefiled, upright.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 8033; there:--X thence, there, X where.
from 8552; completeness; figuratively, prosperity; usually (morally) innocence:--full, integrity, perfect(-ion), simplicity, upright(-ly, -ness), at a venture. See 8550.
feminine of 8537; innocence:--integrity.
a primitive root; to be in consternation:--be amazed, be astonished, marvel(-lously), wonder.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to 8539; a miracle:--wonder.
from 8539; consternation:--astonishment.
of uncertain derivation; Tammuz, a Phoenician deity:--Tammuz.

or tmol {tem-ole'}; probably for 865; properly, ago, i.e. a (short or long) time since; especially yesterday, or (with 8032) day before yesterday:--+ before (-time), + these (three) days, + heretofore, + time past, yesterday.

or tmunah {tem-oo-naw'}; from 4327; something portioned (i.e. fashioned) out, as a shape, i.e. (indefinitely) phantom, or (specifically) embodiment, or (figuratively) manifestation (of favor):--image, likeness, similitude.
from 4171; barter, compensation:--(ex-)change(-ing), recompense, restitution.
from 4191; execution (as a doom):--death, die.
of uncertain derivation; Temach, one of the Nethinim:--Tamah, Thamah.

from an unused root meaning to stretch; properly, continuance (as indefinite extension); but used only (attributively as adjective) constant (or adverbially, constantly); ellipt. the regular (daily) sacrifice:--alway(-s), continual (employment, -ly), daily, ((n-))ever(-more), perpetual.

from 8552; entire (literally, figuratively or morally); also (as noun) integrity, truth:--without blemish, complete, full, perfect, sincerely (-ity), sound, without spot, undefiled, upright(-ly), whole.
plural of 8537; perfections, i.e. (techn.) one of the epithets of the objects in the high-priest's breastplate as an emblem of complete Truth:--Thummim.
a primitive root; to sustain; by implication, to obtain, keep fast; figuratively, to help, follow close:--(take, up-)hold (up), maintain, retain, stay (up).

a primitive root; to complete, in a good or a bad sense, literal, or figurative, transitive or intransitive (as follows):--accomplish, cease, be clean (pass-)ed, consume, have done, (come to an, have an, make an) end, fail, come to the full, be all gone, X be all here, be (make) perfect, be spent, sum, be (shew self) upright, be wasted, whole.
from 4487; a portion assigned; Timnah, the name of two places in Palestine:--Timnah, Timnath, Thimnathah.
patrial from 8553; a Timnite or inhabitant of Timnah:--Timnite.
from 4513; restraint; Timna, the name of two Edomites:--Timna, Timnah.
or Timnath Cerach {tim-nath seh'-rakh}; from 8553 and 2775; portion of (the) sun; Timnath-Cheres, a place in Palestine:--Timnath-heres, Timnath-serah.
from 4529; liquefaction, i.e. disappearance:--melt.
from an unused root meaning to be erect; a palm tree:--palm (tree).
the same as 8558; Tamar, the name of three women and a place:--Tamar.
from the same root as 8558; a palm trunk:--palm tree.
(plural o or (feminine) timmorah (singular and plural) {tim-mo-raw'}; from the same root as 8558; (arch.) a palm-like pilaster (i.e. umbellate):--palm tree.
or tamruq {tam-rook'}; or tamriyq {tam-reek'}; from 4838; properly, a scouring, i.e. soap or perfumery for the bath; figuratively, a detergent:--X cleanse, (thing for) purification(-fying).
from 4843; bitterness (plural as collective):--X most bitter(-ly).
from the same root as 8558; an erection, i.e. pillar (probably for a guide-board):--high heap.

from an unused root probably meaning to elongate; a monster (as preternaturally formed), i.e. a sea-serpent (or other huge marine animal); also a jackal (or other hideous land animal):--dragon, whale. Compare 8577.
a primitive root; to present (a mercenary inducement), i.e. bargain with (a harlot):--hire.
a primitive root (identical with 8566 through the idea of attributing honor); to ascribe (praise), i.e. celebrate, commemorate:--lament, rehearse.
probably feminine of 8565; a female jackal:--dragon.
from 5106; alienation; by implication, enmity:--breach of promise, occasion.
from 5107; produce:--fruit, increase.
perhaps from the same as 594 through the idea of protraction; a pinnacle, i.e. extremity:--tip.
from 5123; drowsiness, i.e. sleep:--slumber(-ing).
from 5130; a brandishing (in threat); by implication, tumult; specifically, the official undulation of sacrificial offerings:--offering, shaking, wave (offering).
from 5216; a fire-pot:--furnace, oven.
or tanchum {tan-khoom'}; and (feminine) tanchuwmah {tan-khoo-maw'}; from 5162; compassion, solace:--comfort, consolation.
for 8575 (feminine); Tanchumeth, an Israelite:--Tanhumeth.
or tanniym (Ezek. 29:3) {tan-neem'}; intensive from the same as 8565; a marine or land monster, i.e. sea-serpent or jackal:--dragon, sea-monster, serpent, whale.
(Aramaic) corresponding to 8147; second:--second.
(Aramaic) from 8578; a second time:--again.

from 5395; properly, a hard breather, i.e. the name of two unclean creatures, a lizard and a bird (both perhaps from changing color through their irascibility), probably the tree-toad and the water-hen:--mole, swan.
a primitive root; to loathe, i.e. (morally) detest:--(make to be) abhor(-red), (be, commit more, do) abominable(-y), X utterly.

a primitive root; to vacillate, i.e. reel or stray (literally or figuratively); also causative of both:--(cause to) go astray, deceive, dissemble, (cause to, make to) err, pant, seduce, (make to) stagger, (cause to) wander, be out of the way.
or Tomiy {to'-ee}; from 8582; error, Tou or Toi, a Syrian king:--Toi, Tou.
from 5749; attestation, i.e. a precept, usage:--testimony.
from 5927; a channel (into which water is raised for irrigation); also a bandage or plaster (as placed upon a wound):--conduit, cured, healing, little river, trench, watercourse.
from 5953; caprice (as a fit coming on), i.e. vexation; concretely a tyrant:--babe, delusion.
from 5956; a secret:--thing that is hid, secret.
or taanug {tah-an-oog'}; and (feminine) taeanugah {tah-ah-oog-aw'}; from 6026; luxury:--delicate, delight, pleasant.
from 6031; affliction (of self), i.e. fasting:--heaviness.
or Tanak {tah-nawk'}; of uncertain derivation; Taanak or Tanak, a place in Palestine:--Taanach, Tanach.
a primitive root; to cheat; by analogy, to maltreat:--deceive, misuse.
from 6105; might (plural collective):--power.
from 6168; a knife or razor (as making bare): also a scabbard (as being bare, i.e. empty):--(pen-)knife, razor, scabbard, shave, sheath.
from 6148; suretyship, i.e. (concretely) a pledge:--+ hostage.
from 8591; a fraud:--error.
from 8608 contracted; a tambourine:--tabret, timbrel.
